INSERT INTO `tournaments` VALUES (2850,'NISEI World Championship 2020','2020.10.09.','10:30 PDT','United States','CA','','California','','','ChIJPV4oX_65j4ARVW8IJ6IJUYs',294,17,'!!!THIS EVENT IS ONLINE NOT IN CALIFORNIA!!! Buy tickets here: [here](https://www.eventbrite.com/e/2020-nisei-world-championship-online-tickets-120756286303)\r\n\r\n![Worlds](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/34F7BMBRphnwreXxTZsGbE41-PNrutyp_a8_IG8udnkU7N3-zv5i9GAOSZkW2XIsktJ-9PAlOZN-TiybOtRIwxjlap41VqAnLYCoc1rFdQF8RFtx3qP9cJPSKjOr_9_nDL-DiGxz)\r\n\r\nThe World Championship will be occurring entirely online over 9, 10, and 11 October 2020. As with the Continental Championships, play will occur via jinteki.net and communication via the [Project NISEI Discord server](https://discord.gg/mDdBdMb). The schedule is below:\r\n\r\n**Day 1A: Friday 9 October 2020**\r\nThis is the ideal day for players in North and South America.\r\nCheck in - 10:30am PDT (UTC -7) (1:30am Saturday AWST)\r\nPlayer Meeting - 11:20am\r\nRound 1- 11:30am\r\n\r\n**Day 1B: Saturday 10 October 2020**\r\nThis day’s schedule is better suited for those in Europe and Africa.\r\nCheck In - 10:30am CEST (UTC +2) (4:30pm AWST)\r\nPlayer Meeting - 11:20am\r\nRound 1 - 11:30am\r\n\r\nWe have arranged the time zones for all three days to best suit the majority of attendees. We recognize that these times will not be ideal for everyone, but we encourage players to prepare for playing in these time zones just as they would for an in-person event. Check-in times for both Day 1A and Day 1B are also noted in AWST to help those in Asia-Pacific decide which day better suits their schedule.\r\n\r\nEach day of Swiss will be up to seven 65-minute rounds, with a 45-minute break between rounds 4 and 5. We expect each Swiss to take about 9 hours, so plan accordingly. Just like previous virtual events, you will need to check-in via the Project NISEI Discord server before the event begins, and remember to check this periodically as we will use it for all official communication over the weekend.\r\n\r\nTickets are on sale now and may be purchased at the link above. You will also need to fill out the registration form which will include your decklist. Be aware that once you submit a decklist it cannot be changed, so please be careful. You may also indicate your preference for Day 1A or Day 1B (or both). We will do our best to honour everyone’s preference while still maintaining balance in the number of players each day. If you have no preference, we will assign you to whichever day has fewer players.\r\n\r\nThe registration form can be found [here](https://forms.gle/XdiBJfSvENaT6cdM7), but it does not open until 18 September to give players time to adjust to the new Standard banlist. If you are able to purchase your ticket and complete your registration before 6 October, please do so, as last-minute registrations put a strain on our admin team and may lead to confusion. Don’t worry - we’ll send you a reminder email on or around the 18th containing the link.\r\n\r\n**Day 2: Sunday 11 October 2020**\r\nCheck in - 11:00am UTC\r\nTiebreaker round - 12pm UTC\r\nCut starts 12:50pm UTC\r\n\r\nThe final day is the culmination of the event with a single tiebreaker round (if required) followed by a cut to top 16. We estimate any players with 11 or more wins during Day 1 will qualify for Day 2 and those with 10 wins may qualify for a Tiebreaker round to make the cut. An announcement at the end of Day 1B will clarify who has qualified and those players will also be notified individually. \r\n\r\nAt the conclusion of the double elimination rounds, NISEI will host a short Prize Ceremony with the top players on the official stream. There’s a secret prize for Top 4, and we will announce exactly what they have won at this time!\r\n\r\n**Side Events**\r\nAlso running all day Sunday are side events - Standard, Core Experience, Eternal, and Draft. These events have no scheduled start and end times and will be run on a first-come, first-serve basis. Side events will not be covered on the official stream - but we encourage streamers who want to cover these events to reach out to us at projectnisei@gmail.com! Entrance for these events are included in your main event ticket, and there is no limit to how many you can join. Sign up sheets and further information will be posted in the Project NISEI Discord on Sunday, with them firing periodically when enough people show interest.\r\n\r\n\r\n**Afterparties/Socializing**\r\nMost people agree that the best part of large Netrunner events is the socializing - going out to the restaurant or the bar with your friends, or even hanging out back at the hotel. Don’t worry - not all is lost in 2020! Every day at the conclusion of the main event, NISEI and others will be hosting virtual afterparties! Some of these will include fun activities like Jackbox party games and Netrunner trivia via Kahoot. There will be plenty of separate rooms to join based on your preferences. If you are interested in hosting your own virtual happy hour or afterparty or helping with an official one, please reach out to us at projectnisei@gmail.com! At the end of each day we’ll provide a list of events that you can join to “see” your friends, or make new ones!',1,1,0,28653,1,'ur',5,'2020-09-13 22:10:01','2025-11-02 12:07:27',NULL,4,36.778261,-119.417932,NULL,0,0,'',1,1,'2020.10.11.',1276,'2020-10-11 18:32:00',0,'America/Los_Angeles',70,'','10:30 PDT',17,0),(3113,'NISEI Worlds Side Event - Cube Draft','2021.11.21.','11:00','','','','','','','',8,NULL,'A Cube Draft side event for Worlds 2021, at 11:00am CET (meaning 10:00am UTC) on Sunday morning.\r\n\r\nThere will be 3 rounds with no top cut; prizes will be provided by Nisei.\r\nIf (and only if) you have a ticket for Worlds, you can subscribe to the tournament by sending me a DM on Discord. There will also be a dedicated channel on the Nisei Event Hub, under the \"2021 side events\" tab.\r\n\r\nSince this is a draft tournament, it\'s capped at 8 participants. If you didn\'t make it in time, organize your own cube draft -- just ask lostgeek!\r\n\r\nTo draft your deck, you will need to make an account on https://meteor.stimhack.com/\r\n\r\nWe will be playing with these pools:\r\n\r\nhttps://meteor.stimhack.com/decks/6DuJ4K8csKFHp4rRq\r\nhttps://meteor.stimhack.com/decks/uZNDpucqA6Z2tesJq\r\n\r\n Runner Starting Cards:\r\n- 1x The Catalyst: Convention Breaker\r\n- 1x Armitage Codebusting\r\n\r\nCorp Starting Cards:\r\n\r\n- 1x The Syndicate: Profit over Principle\r\n- 3x Priority Requisition\r\n- 1x Eden Fragment\r\n- 1x Hades Fragment\r\n- 1x Utopia Fragment\r\n- 1x Jackson Howard',1,0,0,4142,1,'sg',1,'2021-11-20 21:20:27','2025-12-18 14:52:40',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,5,NULL,4142,'2021-11-21 20:28:25',0,NULL,NULL,'','',21,1),(3282,'Warsaw A:NR League - Autumn 2022 edition',NULL,'18:00','Poland','','https://chat.whatsapp.com/L9hTefmB8ZsDjsQiSr2jSb','Warszawa','Cybermachina Warszawa','Nowy świat 54/56 Wejście od strony ul Gałczyńskiego!, 00-369 Warszawa, Poland','ChIJ7UVAibjNHkcRN-QmJm3cZiU',NULL,NULL,'> A new administration means we have to start greasing the wheels all over again. Let\'s get to work.\r\n\r\n\r\n## Zapraszamy wszystkich chętnych na reaktywowaną Warszawską Ligę Netrunnera! \r\n\r\nExploratory Romp oraz letni sezon ligowy zakończyły się oszałamiającym sukcesem, Warszawska Liga Netrunner została faktycznie, ostatecznie i nieodwołalnie reaktywowana. Po kilku dobrych latach nieobecności wracamy w nowej odsłonie i w nowym miejscu. Obecność nie jest obowiązkowa, ale nieobecność będzie źle widziana.\r\n\r\nZapraszamy więc na następny sezon, który rozegramy jesienią 2022! \r\n\r\n![Image](https://www.belloflostsouls.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/android-netrunner-banner-copyright-ffg-07.jpg)\r\n\r\nWracamy do starego, sprawdzonego formatu - 10 cotygodniowych spotkań w formacie Standard wyłoni Królową bądź Króla warszawskich runnerów, który to tytuł zapewnia:\r\n* koronę (jednorazowa, z bibuły)\r\n* owację na stojąco\r\n* uścisk dłoni współgraczy (dostępny na życzenie)\r\n* zwycięski drink w barze (darmowy)\r\n* matczyną dumę (jak wytłumaczycie jej, co to jest Netrunner)\r\n* nagrody (z naszych kuferków na strychu)\r\n\r\nSpotykamy się pierwszy raz 4 października o 18:00 w Cybermachinie na Nowym Świecie 54/56 (wejście od ul. Gałczyńskiego), i aż do 29 listopada włącznie co tydzień gramy 3 rundy swiss taliami legalnymi w formacie Standard. Po 10 spotkaniach odrzucamy 2 najsłabsze wyniki każdego z graczy, a pozostałe sumujemy i na tej podstawie dokonamy koronacji.\r\n\r\nJeśli nie interesuje Cię tytuł królewski i granie konkursowe, ale chcesz wpaść zagrać z nami w Netrunnera (lub nauczyć się grać w Netrunnera) - serdecznie zapraszamy! \r\n\r\nNie możemy się doczekać, żeby zobaczyć Was na żywo!\r\n\r\n\r\n## We cordially invite you to participate in the reactivated Warsaw Netrunner League!\r\n\r\nExploratory Romp, as well as a summer league season were both a tremendous success, the Warsaw Netrunner League has been definitively and irrevocably reactivated. After a few years of absence we are back in a new home. Attendance is not mandatory, but the absence will be frowned upon.\r\n\r\nFollowing up on that success, we would like to invite any and all to participate in the next season - Autumn 2022. \r\n\r\nWe are reviving an old, tried forumula - 10 weekly meetings of Standard-format games will determine the Queen or King of Warsaw netrunners, which entitles to:\r\n* a crown (one-time use, tissue paper)\r\n* standing ovation\r\n* other players\' handshake (available upon request)\r\n* drink of your choice (free of charge)\r\n* mother\'s pride (once you explain her what \"Netrunner\" is)\r\n* prizes (let\'s call them... \"vintage\")\r\n\r\nStarting on October4th we meet weekly in Cybermachina (Nowy Świat 54/56, entrance from Gałczyński street) and are playing 3 rounds of swiss using Standard-format legal decks. On November 29th (after 10 meetings) we will discard 2 worst results per player, and total the rest - person having the most points after that will ascend the royal throne. \r\n\r\nWe cannot wait to see you in person!\r\n\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nJeśli masz jakieś pytania, zapraszamy na [naszą grupę](https://chat.whatsapp.com/L9hTefmB8ZsDjsQiSr2jSb) WhatsApp.\r\nIn case of any questions, feel free to ask them on our [WhatsApp channel](https://chat.whatsapp.com/L9hTefmB8ZsDjsQiSr2jSb).\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nWięcej informacji nt. formatu Standard znajdziecie [tutaj](https://nisei.net/players/supported-formats/#standard), ale mile widziani będą zarówno starzy wyjadacze pamiętający czasy pierwszego Core Set\'u, jak i zupełnie nowi gracze - jeśli masz ochotę wpaść i pograć, a nie wiesz co to \"Standard\", zupełnie się nie przejmuj!\r\n\r\nMore information on the Standard format can be found [here](https://nisei.net/players/supported-formats/#standard), but we will happily accommodate players of any experience level - whether you remember the first Core Set, or are completely new to Netrunner world and have no idea what \"Standard\" is, we don\'t care!',0,0,0,25023,1,'unknown',8,'2022-06-06 07:42:12','2026-01-10 23:49:05','2026-01-10 23:49:05',0,52.235090,21.018839,2,0,0,'https://www.facebook.com/groups/android.netrunner.warszawa/events',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'Europe/Warsaw',NULL,'prizes are going to be a surprise for everyone, organizers included','18:00',23,0),(3466,'Netrunner Rediscovery',NULL,'18:00','United States','TX','','Houston','','1318 Telephone Rd, Houston, TX 77023, USA','ChIJu3MVSYq-QIYReu7tpqM6b0w',NULL,NULL,'Rediscover Netrunner and laugh along the way\r\nWill be at Coral Sword 6pm\r\nAddress: 1318 Telephone Rd #3, Houston, TX 77023',0,0,0,33904,1,'unknown',8,'2022-10-06 19:50:00','2025-12-13 12:02:06','2025-12-13 12:02:06',0,29.730731,-95.327477,2,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'America/Chicago',NULL,'Friendship','',23,0),(3832,'Esslinger CO 09/2023','2023.09.02.','11:00','Germany','','pascal.ziniel@gmail.com','Esslingen am Neckar','WürfelZwerg','Landolinsgasse 10, 73728 Esslingen am Neckar, Germany','ChIJRw5PQDLBmUcR93djfBJ-feY',17,4,'Liebe Runner,\r\n\r\nich freue mich zu verkünden, dass der Würfelzwerg erneut seine Türen für ein famoses Netrunnertunier öffnen wird.  \r\n  \r\nKartenlegalität wird inklusive Liberation sein. Ich hoffe bis dahin sind für jeden die Karten angekommen, ansonsten sind Proxys natürlich nach NSG-Richtlinie legal.  \r\nDecklisten bitte gerne einfach digital per Mail zusenden.\r\n  \r\nAufgrund der Räumlichkeiten sind wir leider auf 24 Personen beschränkt. Eine Anmeldung über die genannte EMail Adresse bei mir ist daher Pflicht.  \r\nBitte denkt daher auch daran euch Abzumelden, solltet ihr nach eurer Anmeldung doch nicht kommen können.  \r\nDie Anmeldegebühr beträngt je nach Teilnehmeranzahl 10-15€.\r\n\r\nDear Runner,\r\n\r\nI am pleased to announce that the Würfelzwerg will again open its doors for an exciting Netrunner tournament.\r\n\r\nCard legality will be up to Liberation. If card prints have not arrived, proxies will be legal as per NSG standard. \r\nFeel free to send your decklist via mail.\r\n\r\nDue to location restricitons we are limited to 24 persons. Therefor please give notice via mail to ensure your spot.  \r\nAdditionally I would like to ask to inform me, if you might be no longer able to come by to free the spot.\r\n\r\nAdresse/Addresse:\r\nWürfelZwerg\r\nLandolinsgasse 10\r\n73728 Esslingen\r\n\r\nParkmöglichkeiten im Parkhaus NeckarForum Esslingen oder Küferstraße Altstadt.  \r\nVom Bahnhof benötigt man ca. 10-15min zum Laden. Ab Stuttgart via S1 oder RE.  \r\n  \r\nParking is avialable at the parking deck NeckarForum or at the Küferstreet.  \r\nAlternatively the train station is just a 10-15min walk away. Coming from Stuttgart either take the S1 or an RE.  \r\n  \r\nAngedachter Zeitplan/ Timing:  \r\n10:30-11:00 letzter Aufbau/Anmeldung  \r\n11:00-12:05 Swiss 1  \r\n12:20-13:25 Swiss 2  \r\n13:25-14:00 Mittag  \r\n14:00-14:05 Swiss 3  \r\n14:20-15:25 Swiss 4  \r\n\r\nBei 16+ Spieler folgt noch der Top4-Cut\r\n  \r\nBei Fragen & Anmerkungen - gerne melden.  \r\nIf there are any questions, feel free to get in contact.  \r\n\r\nBest regards,\r\nPascal - Virulentz',1,1,0,13592,1,'tai',11,'2023-07-10 15:28:59','2026-01-30 10:51:34',NULL,4,48.742059,9.310677,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,13592,'2023-09-03 12:28:12',0,'Europe/Berlin',95,'Various cards of former Store/CO/GNKs','10:30',25,0),(3855,'Stuttgart Meetup [Weekly]',NULL,'17:00','Germany','','Virulentz @Discord or WA group','Stuttgart','Forum 3 Café','Gymnasiumstraße 21, 70173 Stuttgart, Germany','ChIJnUGF2knbmUcR8Iilryqua7g',NULL,NULL,'Who are we?\r\nWe are a small group of international and local Netrunner enthusiasts meeting weekly for fun Netrunner evening.\r\nPlease say \'Hi\' inn he sub-channel of the Netrunmer Germany Discord. There we can also get you into our WA group.\r\n\r\nWhere and when?\r\nWe meet on Tuesdays at the Forum3 from 5p.m. to around 9.30p.m.\r\nAlthough we are there most weeks, I would recommend checking via the Discord - just in case.\r\n\r\n\r\nAt the venue you can get drinks and smaller meals. There are also other people meeting up for different board games.\r\n\r\nWhat do we play?\r\nMostly we play Standard but occasionally also Startup format. Be prepared to face some jank ;)\r\nLearning decks are normally available as well - so feel free to just come by.\r\n\r\nIf there are any remarks or questions, just get in contact.\r\n\r\nkeep running,\r\nPascal - Virulentz',0,0,0,13592,1,'unknown',8,'2023-08-05 08:10:12','2025-11-03 16:32:41',NULL,0,48.776540,9.173700,2,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'Europe/Berlin',NULL,'','16:30',99999,0),(3950,'23-10 Accelerated Meta Test','2023.10.29.','11:00','','','','','','','',40,3,'![2023-3 AMT](https://alwaysberunning.net/photo/2677.png)\r\nNetrunners - NSG will be hosting monthly events for all of \'23!\r\n\r\nThis is another Accelerated Meta Test, and is open to anyone who wants to play. These will be Circuit Openers, but the only prizing will be an Invite to the Circuit Breaker Invitational in January of \'24 for the top finisher (or top 2 if we exceed 20 entrants).\r\n\r\nThis event is starting on October 29th 11:00 EDT (15:00 UTC).\r\n\r\nThe event will be run through the [NSG Online Event Hub Discord](https://discord.gg/EMB3cHVgmw). Registration will start the day before, and close at 10:45 EDT. We anticipate this being four rounds with a top 3 cut. The Player Meeting will start at 10:50 EDT, and the event will start at 11:00 EDT.\r\n\r\nThe event will be run on Jinteki.net. Decklists will not need to be submitted beforehand.',1,0,0,33530,1,'tai',11,'2023-10-20 11:32:25','2026-01-30 10:51:23',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,33530,'2023-10-30 00:05:19',0,NULL,NULL,'','10:00',26,1),(3952,'New Years Showdown 🌍 🌎 H2 CO','2024.01.06.','08:00','','','maninthem00n - on discord','','','','',64,8,'**Start Time: 8am Seattle (PST) and 16:00 UTC** - I\'m hoping this will be as convened as possible for as many people as possible (sorry APAC). [Check your timezone here.](https://www.worldtimebuddy.com/?pl=1&lid=5809844,100&h=5809844&date=1/6/2024%7C5&hf=1)\r\n\r\n**[Watch the Stream here](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=G8khc3wE4Xw)**\r\n\r\n[__Buy your ticket here 15$* USD__](https://checkout.eventcreate.com/netrunnermaninthemoon/select-buy)\r\nTicket sales deadline is 30mins before the start of the player meeting. Please try and have decklists submitted before then as well, but DL deadline is the player meeting. \r\n\r\nThis will be an H2 CO kit with additional prizes and basic USPS world wide shipping included. Please put it on your calendars and join for a wonderful day of netrunner. CBI invites will be valid for the 2025 CBI. \r\n\r\nWe will be playing 8 rounds of single sided swiss in standard format. With a cut to top 4 if we have16-32 players, if we get 33+ we will do a cut to top 8. This will be a lot of netrunner, but from my experience this is the best way to run a medium - large event. \r\n\r\nI hope competitors will take this as an opportunity to practice for the CBI and/or play creative decks they would like to showcase on the international stage. 😃\r\n\r\nGames will be played on Jinteki.net, I will be coordinating the event through the Null Signal online events hub Discord server. You can join the server [here](https://discord.gg/ymmy6fJnEZ) we will be using the #online-store-championship channel for announcements. \r\n\r\nThe event will be streamed, if you have interest or availability to help stream the event please reach out to me on discord!\r\n\r\n*My main goal in running this tournament online is to increase the accessibility of competitive netrunner. I have made an effort to keep the ticket price affordable, but I want to make sure cost isn\'t a [barrier](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/31077) for anyone who would like to join. If you are hesitant to play because of the cost reach out to me on discord @maninthem00n I have a sliding scale ticket option available. ❤️',1,1,0,37550,1,'tai',11,'2023-10-20 19:42:54','2026-01-30 10:51:14',NULL,5,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,37550,'2024-01-10 00:02:00',0,NULL,99,'The tournament will use a boosted 2023 H2 CO kit along with a large collection of extra prizes. \r\n\r\nThe H2 bonus Oaktowns will be given to the first 5 players to register who have never played in an online tournament before. If you\'ve been thinking about trying competitive netrunner, but haven\'t yet taken the plunge this is a great opportunity ❤️ **Update:** The Oaktowns are all taken, I will include a non-Oaktown extra surprise participation prize for any first time tournament players!\r\n\r\nI got a collection of older NSG prizes donated to me. I will be using them as participation prizes! Everyone will get 3x Scrubber and their choice of either: 3x House of Knives or 3x Embezzle. If you already have those older alt arts you can opt for two random play sets I\'ll select from my prize support collection.\r\n\r\n2019 Regionals Scrubber\r\n2019 Store Champ Embezzle (limited to the first 27 player who want them)\r\n2020 Store Champ House of Knives (limited to the first 32 player who want them)\r\n\r\nJakuza acrylic IDs:\r\nholographic Rielle \"Kit\" Peddler (This is a 1x in the world exclusive!)\r\nLat: Ethical Freelancer\r\nJinteki: Restoring Humanity\r\n\r\n1st - 2nd 2025 CBI invite with\r\n1st - 3rd Choice of Jakuza IDs based on placement.\r\n1st - 4th Banner playmat\r\n1st - 8th Moshing alt art\r\n1st - 16th Magnet alt art\r\nEveryone participation alt art choice\r\n\r\nEvent capacity is not limited, but I have set a temporary ticket limit to make sure I don\'t run out of the participation prizes that are limited.\r\n\r\n![2019 Regionals Scrubber](https://imgur.com/iICEr9w.png) ![2019 Store Champ Embezzle](https://imgur.com/25qShTU.png) ![2020 Store Champ House of Knifes](https://imgur.com/jECw2HY.png) ![Jakuza IDs](https://imgur.com/v4G3Ad6.png)','08:00',26,1),(4003,'CO2-23 Frankfurt - 24.2.2024','2024.02.24.','11:00','Germany','','tradonnetrunner@hotmail.com','Frankfurt am Main','','','ChIJocYM6H0IvUcRDNeSPjY3oJo',6,0,'second CO für season 2023 - save the date.\r\n\r\n**Bitte meldet euch an - das hilft uns enorm bei der Planung und andere Leute sehen, dass auch jemand kommt und sind dadurch vielleicht motivierter.** \r\n\r\n**Ort:** siehe Karte am Rand: Kalbacher Stadtpfad 8; 60437 Frankfurt\r\n**Zeit:** Registrierung ab 10.00uhr - Start Runde 1 ab 11.00uhr (gebt gern direkt Bescheid wenn ihr zeitlich knapp seid - wir sind flexibel!)\r\n**Kosten:** 10€ pro Person (Geld wird benutzt für Kosten CO-Preiskit, Spende an die Location, zus. Preise)\r\n\r\n**gespieltes Format:** Standard, aktueller Kartenpool (aktuell bis TAI) + aktuelle MWL (aktuell 23.09) -  bitte Deckliste ausgedruckt / lesbar geschrieben mitbringen oder per Mail an tradonnetrunner@hotmail.com\r\nRundenanzahl usw. nach Anzahl der Spieler - voraussichtlich 3-4 Runden\r\n\r\nWer mag darf mir gern ne Mail schicken, dann kann ich ihn/sie/es/euch per Mail über Änderungen informieren. Ist aber komplett optional. Guckt gern auch im Netrunner-Deutschland-Discord vorbei :)\r\nIch krieg außerdem theoretisch n paar (ca. 2-5, je nachdem) Leute bei mir unter für en Übernachtung - gebt mir bei Interesse gern kurz Bescheid (solange der Platz reicht).\r\n\r\n**Falls Fragen sind: schickt mir eine Mail**\r\n\r\n*If someone needs english information or has questions - pls mail me and I will happily translate or answer everything you\'d like to know :)*\r\n\r\nPat, aka Tradon\r\n- keep runnin\'',1,1,0,23078,1,'tai',11,'2023-11-25 17:58:13','2026-01-30 10:51:03',NULL,4,50.186677,8.636492,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,23078,'2024-02-25 17:09:36',0,'Europe/Berlin',99,'','10:00',26,0),(4049,'OKORINA 6','2024.02.03.','19:00','','','testrunning on discord','','','','',10,3,'# OKORINA 6\r\n\r\n ![Image](https://ibb.co/GvcywrSj)\r\n\r\n_“You aren’t the Only Kind Of Runner In New Angeles.”_\r\n\r\n – Kati Jones\r\n\r\nWhat if Ms. Jones was wrong? In the Only Kind Of Runner In New Angeles (OKORINA) format, we imagine what Netrunner would be like if you could take on a new Netrunner friend as your identity.\r\n\r\nWelcome to the 6th edition of this wonderful format. The format was invented by @sanjay. This tournament is organized by me with blessing and input by @sanjay.\r\n\r\n## Format Details\r\n\r\nInstead of choosing a standard identity, you pick a non-neutral, unique connection resource, and start the game with that as your identity after triggering any “when installed” abilities as if you had installed it.\r\n\r\nOn the corp side, instead of picking a standard identity, you pick a non-neutral agenda, and start the game with that as your identity after triggering any “when scored” abilities as if you had scored it.\r\n\r\nEach legal resource and agenda has received a minimum decksize and a maximum influence size (as well as starting link and subtypes).\r\n\r\nThe full list of legal IDs is [here](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1Avf9W-3c_QABj-DUpfwVzt9UvXWapzzlTdwzYTPU8OM/edit?usp=sharing) and here is the [FAQ](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1mYg_Ih8_XutL71ltpkJkAxcpUVmCvvf77aZlNuDt4t0/edit?usp=sharing).\r\n\r\nHightlight patch notes for the 6th edition (now fully SBT approved*):\r\n- AR-Enhanced Security now take their enhanced security seriously and don\'t allow cards from rivaling corporation anymore\r\n- Fixed a bug that Weyland would kindly stop exploiting the rain forest after doing so once\r\n- Fixed a bug that \"Baklan\" forgot who he was after doing what he does\r\n- Daeg now can correctly access the MU of his ship\r\n- The Class Acts Decksize is now without compare\r\n- Chaos Theory finished her PhD and changed her legal name to \"Nuka Vrolyck\"\r\n- Avgustina\'s MU now correctly reflect the server depicted in her art\r\n\r\n*thanks for lostgeek and tugtetgut helping with the balance.\r\n\r\n## Tournament Details\r\n\r\nUPDATE: 2h later to not overlapp with AMT.\r\n\r\nThe Tournament will be held online via the NSG [Event Hub Discord](https://discord.gg/FffGCWEF). There is a role and channel for OKORINA. Get the role (from #roles) to receive pings at the checkin and tournament.\r\n\r\nTournament will start 19:00 UTC and we will play SSS for probably 6-8 Rounds depending on Number of Players, followed by a top 3 single elimination cut.\r\n\r\nYou can pre-register [here](https://forms.gle/b6RzkNagHPwSows66). Be in the Discord 18:45 UTC and be registered so that we can start on time.\r\n\r\n## Prizes\r\n\r\nThis is a community event for fun. However Winner has the traditional prize of designing a new ID for the OKORINA (from eg neutral cards). Also Fame and Glory. \r\n\r\nAlso also the winner will receive a ~one off~ only of a kind playmat (see above for the art).',1,0,0,15130,1,'tai',6,'2023-12-21 20:04:46','2025-11-23 15:18:25',NULL,5,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,6,NULL,15130,'2024-02-04 09:31:23',0,NULL,NULL,'','18:30',26,1),(4084,'Casual Netrunner Night!',NULL,'18:00','United States','CA','drewcuth1@gmail.com','San Francisco','Southern Pacific Brewing','620 Treat Ave, San Francisco, CA 94110, USA','ChIJn5G9Fzp-j4ARRs66QTw4XAY',NULL,NULL,'Come out and join San Francisco Netrunners on Thursday nights at Southern Pacific!  All players welcome regardless of experience level.  We typically play standard format, but are happy to dip into other formats if requested.\r\n\r\n[Join us on discord!](https://discord.gg/UzM7ED8NGd)\r\nWe usually post a roll call each week, so check there if you want to see who else is attending. \r\n\r\nNew to the game? No problem! We love teaching our favorite game to newcomers and have starter decks on hand every week in case anyone new drops by. \r\n\r\nNotes on the venue:\r\n* Southern Pacific is a restaurant and bar, feel free to get food and drinks while you\'re here but it\'s not required\r\n* We meet upstairs in the mezzanine.\r\n\r\nThis event is up to date as of 2026.\r\n\r\nFor more info on Netrunner around the Bay, including Learn to Play events, casual GNKs, and tournaments, check out [sansan.cards](https://sansan.cards/).',0,0,0,42980,1,'unknown',8,'2024-01-29 06:00:07','2026-01-29 18:52:35',NULL,0,37.760076,-122.414224,4,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'America/Los_Angeles',NULL,'Each week everyone who attends can take home a card from our fabulous supply of alt art cards, including official cards from FFG, NSG, and community artist alt arts!\r\n\r\n![Alts](https://i.imgur.com/ZHaiCcy.jpeg)','',26,0),(4153,'Online 🌍 🌎 - Summer Showdown 🌞 🦋','2024.05.18.','07:30','','','maninthem00n - on discord','','','','',72,8,'## ➡️ [**Stream Here!!**](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dkGzYmBXSGo)  🥳 🌞 🦋 🏆\r\n\r\n----\r\nI hope this tournament will help people prepare for the upcoming continentals season and/or play creative decks they would like to showcase on the international stage. 😃 I expect this will be another epic netrunner tournament bringing together new and old players of all levels for a wonderful day of connecting with friends and hacking servers 🥳\r\n\r\n**The event will be using the \"OLD\" Ban list 24.03!** There was a banlist update this morning. Though these changes are exciting and I\'m sure there are a lot of players itching to test out this new meta, I don\'t think it is reasonable or responsible for me to adjust the banlist the day before this event.\r\n\r\nGame time Information can be found in the [Netrunner events hub discord channel #online-store-championship](https://discord.com/channels/372121348300079106/731253452675743744/1240881035185623072).\r\n\r\n➡️ **Check my timezone** [Player meeting at 14:00 UTC , 10:00am Eastern USA, 7:00 am PDT \r\nRound 1 starts 30 minutes later](https://www.worldtimebuddy.com/?qm=1&lid=8,100,5809844,5&h=8&date=2024-5-18&sln=7-17&hf=1)\r\n\r\n➡️ [**Buy Your Ticket Here!**](https://checkout.eventcreate.com/online-summer-showdown-2024/select-buy) If you\'ve never played in an online tournament before you get a playset of the Alt-art Drafters by Scott Uminga (while my supplies last) 🤩 \r\n\r\n![Prizes for summer showdown](https://imgur.com/VCbZG14.png)\r\n\r\n**Optional fundraiser for netrunner travel:** There is an option to donate to a travel fund at checkout donations are being split 50% towards my worlds travel and 50% going to the **Fly to EMEA Fund.** Atien has contributed some EMEA exclusive prizes that will be raffled off during each round! Every round you play you will be entered into a drawing for EMEA prizes below. All players will be entered into the raffle (donation not required). 👀 🥳\r\n\r\n![Prizes for EMEA raffle](https://imgur.com/Z2Mz640.png)\r\n\r\nWe will be playing 8 rounds of single sided swiss in the standard format with a cut to top 4 if we have 16-47 players, and a top 8 cut with 48+ players. This will be a lot of netrunner, from my experience this is the best way to run a medium - large scale event. \r\n\r\nGames will be played on Jinteki.net. I will be coordinating the event through the Null Signal online events hub Discord server. You can join the server [here.](https://discord.gg/ymmy6fJnEZ) We will be using the [#online-store-championship channel](https://discord.com/channels/372121348300079106/731253452675743744) for announcements. \r\n\r\nI plan to have event streamed, if you have interest in commentating or helping stream please reach out to me on discord!\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\n**Affordability** My main goal in running this tournament online is to increase the accessibility of competitive netrunner. I have made an effort to keep the ticket price affordable, but I want to make sure cost isn\'t a [barrier](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/31077) for anyone who would like to join. If you are hesitant to play because of the cost you\'re welcome to use the discount code _NETRUNNER4EVERYONE_   for 100% off the ticket price ❤️ \r\n\r\n**UPDATE:** Almost all of the free tickets I budgeted for have been claimed. I added another option for 50% off with the code _HALFOFF._ I\'m hoping to make sure anyone who wants to play can participate. As of right now either code should work. \r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\n**AI disclaimer:** I \"created/designed\" the used art for the Hagen using generative AI tools. It is my goal as a TO to run the best possible events in order support our wonderful community. Art is a huge part of the community and I am actively seeking out more artist like Lenny and PiCat I can collaborate with for future projects. I personally feel very conflicted about generative AI. If you are an artist, an artist supporter, or anyone curious to read more about my thoughts, [please check out this google doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1hAdWMoiM7F3KAy8oB-EGKxvNagylnirgjkduJ_vFvT4/edit) ❤️🙃',1,1,0,37550,1,'rwr',11,'2024-03-12 06:22:37','2026-01-30 10:50:35',NULL,5,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,37550,'2024-05-19 02:01:02',0,NULL,104,'**Optional fundraiser for netrunner travel:** There is an option to donate to a travel fund at checkout donations are being split 50% towards my worlds travel and 50% going to the **Fly to EMEA Fund.** Atien has contributed some EMEA exclusive prizes that will be raffled off during each round! Every round you play you will be entered into a drawing for EMEA prizes below. All players will be entered into the raffle (donation not required).\r\n\r\nThe tournament will use be using 1-3 2024 H1 CO kits along with a large collection of extra prizes. \r\n\r\nThe bonus H1 Drafters by Scott Uminga will be **given to players who have never played in an online tournament before** (while supplies last). If you\'ve been thinking about trying competitive netrunner, but haven\'t yet taken the plunge this is a great opportunity ❤️\r\n\r\nI have a collection of options available as participation prizes. Everyone gets to pick two of their choice. \r\n\r\n**Participation alt art choices**\r\nMaw alt-art NSG 2024 Q1 GNK \r\nMavirus alt-art [by PiCat314](https://www.instagram.com/picat_314/)\r\nSpin Doctor alt-art [by Lenny](https://lenney.xyz/)\r\nHagen alt-art Designed by ManintheMoon\r\n\r\n**Jakuza acrylic IDs:**\r\n**Lat:** Ethical Freelancer\r\n**Sportsmetal:** Go Big or Go Home\r\nNyusha **\"Sable\"** Sintashta: Symphonic Prodigy\r\n**1st** Choice of Jakuza IDs based on placement.\r\n**2nd** Choice of Jakuza IDs based on placement.\r\n**3rd** Choice of Jakuza IDs based on placement.\r\n\r\n**Official CO Kit Prizes***\r\n1st - 2nd 2025 CBI invite\r\n1st - 6th Cat’s Cradle playmat (illustrated by Bruno Balixa)\r\n1st - 12th  Prepaid VoicePAD (illustrated by Elizaveta Sokolova)\r\n1st - 24th Tatu-Bola (illustrated by Cat Shen)\r\n\r\n*I\'m going to be using 1/2/3 regular H1 CO kits for prizing if we have 8-24 / 25-49 / 50+ participants. So the official CO prizing will scale with tournament size. 50+ players met ✅\r\n*Prizes potentially subject to change. \r\n\r\n\r\n![Prizes for EMEA raffle](https://imgur.com/Z2Mz640.png)\r\n![Participation Prizes for summer showdown](https://imgur.com/tPUW6vi.png)\r\n![Jakuza IDs](https://imgur.com/jzYway2.png)\r\n![Prizes for summer showdown](https://imgur.com/VCbZG14.png)','07:00',29,1),(4181,'Online Liga Netrunner Deutschland Discord','2024.04.07.','12:00','','','@TorpedoTyrus on Discord! Oder über den Channel im Discord: https://discord.gg/UrKxTGZ','','','','',18,0,'Liebe Community,\r\n\r\nwir starten die zweite Runde der Online-Liga des Discord-Servers Netrunner Deutschland! Jeder Spieler ist willkommen, vor allem auch Anfänger, Wiedereinsteiger oder Jinteki-Neulinge. Es sei hier noch einmal erwähnt, dass es sich um eine Online-Liga handelt, gespielt wird auf Jinteki.com und die Organisation läuft über https://discord.com/channels/321600585159671809/1198606741546475520! \r\n\r\nFolgende Regeln gelten:\r\n\r\n-Keine festen Decklisten\r\nGespielt wird jeweils 1 Runde Corp und Runner, Standard, mit aktueller Banlist\r\n\r\n-Das Pairing wird am Sonntag bekannt gegeben, privat verabredet und dann innerhalb einer Woche gespielt und im Discord gemeldet\r\n\r\n-Wir werden je nach Anzahl der Spieler ~6-8 Wochen spielen!\r\n\r\nAuch Einsteiger in das Standard-Format sind willkommen! Es wird auch einen kleinen Preissupport geben, der von einigen SpielerInnen selbst zu Verfügung gestellt wurde!\r\n\r\nFreue mich auf euch! \r\n\r\nLiebe Grüße, Tyrus',1,0,0,31154,1,'rwr',12,'2024-03-25 16:15:00','2026-01-30 10:50:49',NULL,3,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,23078,'2024-06-20 15:11:38',0,NULL,NULL,'','12:00',29,1),(4199,'Offenburg July CO','2024.06.15.','11:30','Germany','','netrunner@of15-15.de','Offenburg','MARKTerLEBEN im einMACHGLAS Offenburg GmbH','Am Marktpl. 19, 77652 Offenburg, Germany','ChIJB3Q63DDTlkcRlSnf68xvbHQ',7,0,'## EDIT: We start 30 minutes later \r\n\r\n#### Herzlich Willkommen zum zweiten Circuit Opener in Offenburg!\r\nWir werden wieder im Unverpacktladen einMACHGLAS spielen, etwa 10 Minuten vom Bahnhof entfernt. Das Turnier wird im Standard-Format und mit single sided swiss stattfinden, vermutlich werden wir 6 Swiss-Runden spielen. Decklisten sind Pflicht, über Anmeldung hier auf ABR freue ich mich.\r\n\r\ngeplanter Zeitplan:\r\n11:00 - 11:30 Registrierung und Aufbau\r\n11:30 - 14:15 Swiss 1 - 3\r\n14:15 - 15:00 Mittagspause.\r\n15:00 - 17:45 Swiss 4 - 6\r\n\r\n10€ Teilnahmegebür für das CO Kit und die location. Alles übrige geht ebenfalls ans Einmachglas.\r\n\r\nBei Fragen gerne per Mail oder Discord melden\r\nBis Juni\r\nOF15-15\r\n\r\n--------\r\n\r\n#### Welcome to the second Circuit Opener in Offenburg!\r\n\r\nWe\'ll be playing at the zero-waste shop einMACHGLAS, about 10 minutes from the train station. The tournament will be standard format and single sided swiss, we will probably play 6 rounds. Decklists are mandatory and it would be awesome if everyone indicates interest here on ABR. \r\n\r\nplanned Timing:\r\n11:00 - 11:30 registration and setup\r\n11:30 - 14:15 Swiss 1 - 3\r\n14:15 - 15:00 meal break\r\n15:00 - 17:45 Swiss 4 - 6\r\n\r\nDepending on attendance, we\'ll do a top3 cut\r\n\r\n10€ Entry fee for the price kit and for the location. Everything earned will be donated to the einMACHGLAS. \r\n\r\nIf you have any questions, please write via mail or on discord.\r\nSee you in June\r\nOF15-15',1,1,1,34833,1,'rwr',11,'2024-03-31 04:27:31','2026-02-25 16:08:46',NULL,5,48.470319,7.941664,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,34833,'2024-06-16 10:05:43',0,'Europe/Berlin',104,'','11:00',30,0),(4227,'Standard AMT - May 19th (EMEA)','2024.05.19.','09:00 UTC','','','Kror','','','','',17,4,'![Accelerated Meta Test](https://alwaysberunning.net/photo/2677.png)\r\nNetrunners - NSG will continue hosting online events every month for all of \'24!\r\n\r\nThis is an Accelerated Meta Test in the **Standard** Format using **Single-Sided Swiss**, and is open to anyone who wants to play. Prizing for this event will be an Invite to the Circuit Breaker Invitational in January of \'25 for the top finisher (or top 2 if we exceed 20 entrants).\r\n\r\n**Netrunners from all levels of play are welcome and encouraged to participate in AMTs**\r\n\r\nThis event is starting on [May 19th, 09:00 UTC](https://everytimezone.com/s/4467142b). With registration closing and player meeting beginning *15 minutes beforehand*. \r\n\r\nThe event will be run through the [NSG Online Event Hub Discord](https://discord.gg/s9tWsq3sQP). Registration will open on [Aesopstables](http://www.aesopstables.net) at least an hour before event start. We anticipate this event being six rounds with a top 4 cut. \r\n\r\nThe event will be run on Jinteki.net.',1,0,0,33530,1,'rwr',11,'2024-04-14 01:23:43','2026-01-30 10:50:21',NULL,5,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,33530,'2024-05-19 13:20:09',0,NULL,NULL,'','08:00 UTC',29,1),(4327,'Russian National Championship 2024','2024.08.10.','12:00','Russia','','amarumacies@gmail.com','Sankt-Peterburg','Pair of Dice','Bronnitskaya Ulitsa, 26, Sankt-Peterburg, Russia, 190013','ChIJG0JqhasxlkYR8_qknN2PA1E',18,4,'Про дату, время и место проведения:\r\n\r\n10 августа, суббота, клуб Pair of Dice (бывш. SpellMarket) \r\n11:30 начало регистрации\r\n12:00 паринги и начало турнира \r\n\r\nПро регламент:\r\nФормат Standard, актуальный на момент турнира банлист. (текущий 24.05)\r\n\r\nИграем 6 раундов Single Sided Swiss, (односторонняя швейцарка: \r\nв первом раунде оппоненты определяются случайно, далее по балансу сторон, если в первом раунде играл раннером и победил, во втором будешь играть корпорацией с тем, кто победил за корпорацию)\r\n\r\n40 минут на раунд. (если нас будет 16 и более, будет топ 4 кат в формате дабл элиминейшн), между раундами перерыв 5 минут. \r\nОбед после 3 раундов. Продолжительность обеда 35-40 минут. \r\n\r\nДеклисты обязательны, для регистрации необходимо скинуть мне в личные сообщения ссылку на нрдб или напечатать на листочке и принести с собой. \r\n\r\nПро призы:\r\n\r\nТоп 1 получает инвайт на онлайн-турнир с клевыми призами CBI (Circuit Breaker Invitational), бесплатный билет на Worlds и титул \"2024 Russian National Champion\".\r\nТоп 4 получат ковры Asmund Pudlat \r\nТоп 6 получат промо Stargate \r\nТоп 8 получат металлические кубики нац\'24\r\nТоп 16 получат промо Joy Ride \r\nТоп 40 получат промо Wall to Wall\r\n\r\nПро взнос на турнир:\r\n\r\nВзнос будет 700 рублей в клуб (200 обычное посещение + 500 турнир).',1,1,0,39503,1,'rwr',4,'2024-06-10 11:58:46','2025-12-26 10:48:54',NULL,5,59.913677,30.323665,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,39503,'2024-08-13 05:51:45',0,'Europe/Moscow',107,'Участники получат комплект промо фойл Buzzsaw by DB','11:30',30,0),(4337,'Running in the dwarf cave - the Esslinger CO','2024.09.07.','11:00','Germany','','Discord -  Virulentz // pascal.ziniel /at/ gmail.com','Esslingen am Neckar','WürfelZwerg','Landolinsgasse 10, 73728 Esslingen am Neckar, Germany','ChIJRw5PQDLBmUcR93djfBJ-feY',4,0,'Liebe Runner,\r\n\r\nich freue mich zu verkünden, dass der [WürfelZwerg](http://www.wuerfelzwerg.de/) am 7.September 2024 erneut seine Türen für ein famoses Netrunnertunier öffnen wird.\r\n\r\n\r\nAufgrund der Räumlichkeiten sind wir leider **auf 24 Personen beschränkt**. Eine **Anmeldung** über die **genannte EMail Adresse** bei mir ist daher Pflicht.\r\nBitte denkt daher auch daran, euch Abzumelden, solltet ihr nach eurer Anmeldung doch nicht kommen können.\r\n\r\nDie Anreise erfolgt via Zug über den Esslinger Bahnhof (RE oder S1 von Stuttgart) und einem 10min Fußmarsch in die Altstadt. Mit dem Auto am besten über die A8 oder A81/B10 von Norden kommend. Parken kann man im Parkhaus Neckarforum.\r\n\r\nAdresse:\r\n> WürfelZwerg\r\n> Landolinsgasse 10\r\n> 73728 Esslingen\r\n\r\nDie Anmeldegebühr beträgt je nach Teilnehmeranzahl 10-15€. Geld über die Kosten des Preis-Kits hinaus gehen an die Location.\r\nDecklisten werden sehr gern auch via Mail entgegen genommen.\r\n\r\nAngedachter Zeitplan:\r\n> 10:30 - 11:00 letzter Aufbau/Anmeldung\r\n> 11:00 - 11:45 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 1\r\n> 11:50 - 12:35 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 2\r\n> 12:40 - 13:25 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 3\r\n> 13:25 - 14:15 Mittag\r\n> 14:15 - 15:00 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 4\r\n> 15:05 - 15:50 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 5\r\n> 15:55 - 16:40 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 6\r\n\r\nSpezialpreise: [Spoiler](https://www.facebook.com/photo/?fbid=6969251436419470&set=pcb.6969251639752783)\r\n\r\nBei Fragen & Anmerkungen - gerne melden.\r\n(Discord)[https://discord.com/channels/321600585159671809/1214253784658870312]\r\n\r\nPascal - Virulentz\r\n\r\n___\r\nDear Runners,\r\n\r\nI am pleased to announce that the [WürfelZwerg](http://www.wuerfelzwerg.de/) will open its doors for an exciting Netrunner tournament again at the 7th September 2024.\r\n\r\nDue to location restricitons we are **limited to 24 persons**. Therefor it is mandatory to give **notice via mail to claim your spot**.\r\nAdditionally I would like you to inform me, if you will be no longer able to come to free the spot.\r\n\r\n\r\nArrival via train is possible with the RE or the S1 to Esslingen Station and a short 10min walk through the city. Arrival by car can be done via the A8 or A81/B10 from the north. Parkin is possible at the NeckarForum parking garage.\r\n\r\nAddress:\r\n WürfelZwerg\r\n Landolinsgasse 10\r\n 73728 Esslingen\r\n\r\nFeel free to send your decklist via mail.\r\nEntry fee will be dependent on participation 10-15€. Money beyond the price kit costs will go to the location.\r\n\r\nSchedule:\r\n> 10:30 - 11:00 letzter Aufbau/Anmeldung\r\n> 11:00 - 11:45 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 1\r\n> 11:50 - 12:35 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 2\r\n> 12:40 - 13:25 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 3\r\n> 13:25 - 14:15 Lunch\r\n> 14:15 - 15:00 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 4\r\n> 15:05 - 15:50 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 5\r\n> 15:55 - 16:40 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 6\r\n\r\nSpecial prices: [Spoiler](https://www.facebook.com/photo/?fbid=6969251436419470&set=pcb.6969251639752783)\r\n\r\nIf there are any questions, feel free to get in contact.\r\n(Discord)[https://discord.com/channels/321600585159671809/1214253784658870312]\r\n\r\nPascal - Virulentz',1,1,0,13592,1,'rwr',11,'2024-06-18 16:23:57','2026-01-30 10:50:15',NULL,5,48.742059,9.310677,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,13592,'2024-09-07 12:59:30',0,'Europe/Berlin',104,'Mark-DICE\r\nTop 1 - !!! [Farbe/Coloured](https://www.facebook.com/photo?fbid=6969251443086136&set=pcb.6969251639752783) !!!\r\nTop2-4 [S&W/B&W](https://www.facebook.com/photo/?fbid=6969251436419470&set=pcb.6969251639752783)\r\nby Annudice/ Bookkeeper \r\n\r\n\r\nPossibly a GNK2 and remaining cards of older tournaments.','10:30',30,0),(4397,'Ulm Startup 2024','2024.09.29.','10:30','Germany','','grakhirt /at/ gmx.de','Ulm','','','ChIJ8fGtlBdkmUcRudyu4dzuvzg',5,0,'Nachdem es 2023 zu meinem Bedauern nicht geklappt hat.\r\n\r\nUlm hat 2024 wieder ein Zweitagesevent. Samstag CO Standard und Sonntag Startup .\r\n\r\nTeilnahmegebühr für einen Tag 15 Euro (in Abhängigkeit von den Anmeldungen); für zwei Tage 25.\r\n\r\nAdresse: Gemeindehaus Rupert-Mayer; Neunkirchenweg 63; 89077 Ulm\r\n\r\nStartup am 29.09.2024, kein offizielles CO, da das Kit nach den neuen OP Vorgaben zu alt ist',1,0,0,14354,1,'rwr',1,'2024-08-11 07:43:09','2026-01-30 10:49:47',NULL,5,48.386559,9.961991,NULL,0,0,'',0,11,NULL,14354,'2024-09-29 09:34:42',0,'Europe/Berlin',95,'Neben den Kits gibt es viele Sonderpreise:\r\nPlaymats (alte FFG und NSG Raritäten): Interference 2013, Deep Red 2014, Freelancer 2014, Tri-Maf 2015, Day Job 2015, Android World Book, Silhouette 2015, Leela 2016, Kit 2015, Smoke 2018, Find the Truth 2017, Project Vitruvius 2013, Run Amok 2017, Wotan 2014, The Artist 2019, Tyr 2020, Rezeki 2019, Colossus 2020, Noise 2019, Always have a Backup Plan 2019 und mehr\r\nPromokarten (FFG, NSG inkl. Foil)\r\nNSG Würfel\r\nund und und\r\nWas sich so bei mir in den letzten 9 Jahren so alles angesammelt hat.','10:00',30,0),(4423,'Standard AMT - September 22nd (EMEA)','2024.09.22.','09:00 UTC','','','op@nullsignal.games','','','','',21,4,'![Accelerated Meta Test](https://alwaysberunning.net/photo/2677.png)\r\nNetrunners - NSG will continue hosting online events every month for all of \'24!\r\n\r\nThis is an Accelerated Meta Test in the **Standard** Format using **Single-Sided Swiss**, and is open to anyone who wants to play. Prizing for this event will be an Invite to the Circuit Breaker Invitational in January of \'25 for the top finisher (or top 2 if we exceed 20 entrants).\r\n\r\n**Netrunners from all levels of play are welcome and encouraged to participate in AMTs**\r\n\r\nThis event is starting on [September 22nd, 09:00 UTC](https://everytimezone.com/s/87df43f6). With registration closing and player meeting beginning *15 minutes beforehand*. \r\n\r\nThe event will be run through the [NSG Online Event Hub Discord](https://discord.gg/qUEHWSDPWa). Registration will open on [Aesopstables](http://www.aesopstables.net) at least an hour before event start. We anticipate this event being six rounds with a top 4 cut. \r\n\r\nThe event will be run on Jinteki.net.',1,0,0,33530,1,'rwr',11,'2024-08-21 07:24:54','2026-01-30 10:50:06',NULL,5,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,33530,'2024-09-22 12:58:59',0,NULL,NULL,'','08:00 UTC',30,1),(4610,'Germany\'s Next Top Hoshiko - 2025','2025.02.22.','10:00','','','tradonnetrunner@hotmail.com','','','','',14,4,'![Image](https://alwaysberunning.net/photo/3383.jpeg)\r\n> ## **Offen für jeden, nicht nur Deutsche - *open for everyone, not just german players***\r\n\r\n## **Special: Jede/-r muss als Runner-ID Hoshiko spielen - die beste Hoshiko gewinnt eine Keiko-Plushie!!! :D**\r\n\r\n## ***Special: Everyone has to play Hoshiko as Runner-ID - the best Hoshiko wins a Keiko-Plushie!!! :D***\r\n\r\nWann: 22.02.2025\r\nWo: online - Orga über den [Netrunner-Deutschland-Discord:](https://discord.gg/UrKxTGZ)\r\n\r\nErstens: [Alle Informationen + Anmeldung](https://forms.gle/N4hSCJDrA2fZoChY8) \r\nDanach: [Registrierung auf cobr.ai](https://tinyurl.com/2djcmdkz)\r\nKosten: 10€/Person\r\n\r\n------------------------\r\n\r\n*When: 22nd of February 2025\r\nWhere: online - organisation via the [Netrunner Germany Discord](https://discord.gg/UrKxTGZ)*\r\n\r\nFirst: *[All information + Sign In](https://forms.gle/N4hSCJDrA2fZoChY8)\r\nAfter that: [registration via cobr.ai](https://tinyurl.com/2djcmdkz)\r\nCosts: 10€/person*',1,1,0,23078,1,'rwr',6,'2024-12-22 00:14:15','2026-01-30 10:49:37',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,23078,'2025-02-22 16:03:25',0,NULL,NULL,'Es wird haufenweise Preise geben - siehe folgende Fotos\r\nDazu kommen noch weitere Alt-Arts, Spielmatten usw. die verlost bzw. random verteilt werden.\r\n\r\nEs ist ok, sich anzumelden wenn jemand nur die Teilnehmerpreise haben möchte ohne mitzuspielen.\r\n\r\nKeiko-Plushies: (sponsored by NSG)\r\nPlatz 1: Die beste Hoshiko bekommt ein Keiko-Plushie!!!\r\nVerlosung: Zudem wird eine weitere Keiko-Plushie pro 10 Teilnehmer unter allen Teilnehmern verlost!\r\n\r\n+++ Playmats, Alt-Arts, Fan-Arts, etc. - siehe Fotos + Anmeleformular + Discord\r\n\r\n--------------\r\n\r\nThere will be heaps of prizes - see the following photos\r\nThere will also be other Alt-Arts, play mats etc. which will be raffled or randomly distributed.\r\n\r\nIt is ok to sign up if someone just wants to have the participation prizes without playing.\r\n\r\nKeiko-Plushies: (sponsored by NSG)\r\n1st place: The best Hoshiko gets a Keiko-Plushie!!!\r\nRaffle: In addition, one additional Keiko-Plushie per 10 participants will be raffled among all participants!\r\n\r\n+++ Playmats, Alt-Arts, Fan-Arts, etc. - see Pictures + Sign-in-form + Discord','09:30',33,1),(4653,'Original 1996 Netrunner','2026.02.01.','13:00','Germany','','weinschwaermer@web.de','Koblenz','Restaurant OM','Bechelstraße 23, 56073 Koblenz, Germany','ChIJtaZ6M01jvkcRdRJLQSNCLng',NULL,NULL,'On Sunday, February 1st, we will play a three round tournament with Original 1996 Netrunner cards (the old Richard Garfield game printed by Wizards of the Coast / R. Talsorian games).\r\n\r\nWe will start at 12 o\'clock in Restaurant OM.\r\nThe tournament is for free, but you are encouraged to eat something in the restaurant (because especially for us, it stays open during hours when it is normally closed).\r\n\r\nSeven players signed up so far: Two rather new players, three veterans from the Netherlands and two Veterans from Germany.\r\nYou don\'t need to bring your own cards, I have a draft cube.\r\nBut please sign up by e-mail, so I can bring enough cards.\r\n\r\nAnd if you want to play an online test game with the old cards, just send me an e-mail.\r\nJinteki.net does not have the 1996 cards, but it is possible through Magic Workstation 0.94.',0,0,0,19089,1,'elev',8,'2025-01-12 22:23:52','2025-12-16 21:11:51',NULL,0,50.361477,7.581464,NULL,0,0,'',0,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'Europe/Berlin',NULL,'','12:00',99999,0),(4662,'Gadigal District Championship 2025','2025.03.30.','09:30','Australia','','iamtom','Ultimo','Behold Games','17, 99 Jones Street Corner of Macarthur and Jones, Ultimo NSW 2007, Australia','ChIJJ4JSosevEmsR8ScyjS_OfQo',19,4,'# Join us for the 2025 Gadigal District Championship, held at Behold Games in Ultimo on Sunday 30th March!  \r\n\r\n[Please Buy Your Ticket Here](https://www.eventbrite.com.au/e/gadigal-district-championship-2025-netrunner-tournament-tickets-1147838228039?utm-campaign=social&utm-content=attendeeshare&utm-medium=discovery&utm-term=listing&utm-source=cp&aff=ebdsshcopyurl)\r\n\r\n## Format\r\nThere will be 6 rounds of Single Sided Swiss, followed by a cut to Top 4 Single Elimination. We will be playing in the Standard format on the active banlist as of the day of the tournament.\r\n\r\n## Timing\r\nDoors will open for Registration at 9am, with Round 1 beginning at 9:30am. I know this is an early start, but we have a lot of Netrunner to play and we only have the space until 6pm at the latest, so will be aiming to have everything happening as per schedule. Please let iamtom know on discord if you are running late. There will be a lunch break around Midday, and an afternoon break at the end of Swiss. \r\n\r\n## Price\r\nEntry for this event is $20, please ensure you [buy tickets on Eventbrite.](https://www.eventbrite.com.au/e/gadigal-district-championship-2025-netrunner-tournament-tickets-1147838228039?utm-campaign=social&utm-content=attendeeshare&utm-medium=discovery&utm-term=listing&utm-source=cp&aff=ebdsshcopyurl) Due to timing and space restrictions, there are only 24 tickets available, so please purchase yours early to avoid missing out. If purchasing a ticket at this price is not feasible due to personal circumstances, feel free to reach out to iamtom on discord (if you feel comfortable doing so).\r\n\r\n## Player Expectations\r\nThis is a competitive-level event, and as such has stricter expectations on competitors. The main things to note are:\r\n* Proxies are legal (at all levels of play), but please ensure that your proxies are legible (handwritten proxies are not allowed).\r\n* Printed decklists are mandatory (ordered by Type and then Alphabetical). There will be printed templates available to handwrite your decklist if needed.\r\n* Alt Arts must adhere to Appendix III of the NSG Organised Play Policy. If you are unsure if your alt arts adhere, please check with the TO prior to the tournament (and bring the original card as a back up).\r\nFor more information on Player Expectations see https://nullsignal.games/organizers/organized-play-policies/\r\n\r\n## Venue Information\r\nBehold Games is home to Sydney Netrunner’s fortnightly Wednesday sessions. The store is very LGBTQIA+ friendly and has a wide range of Boardgames, RPGs, Card Games, Dice and other gaming accessories on offer, as well as great selection of snacks!  The store is at C17/99 Jones Street Ultimo, for more information on how to get there (including parking), please visit https://beholdgames.com.au/pages/how-to-find-us).\r\n\r\n## Prizing\r\nSee below for the 2025 Districts Prize Kit.',1,1,1,14284,1,'rwr',16,'2025-01-16 05:52:27','2025-11-02 22:47:51',NULL,4,-33.880006,151.197556,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,14284,'2025-03-30 04:22:20',0,'Australia/Sydney',120,'','09:00',33,0),(4779,'Birmingham Startup CTK 1.0 Release-Elevator ver.','2025.04.26.','11:30','United Kingdom','','chowlapyin123@gmail.com','Birmingham','Geek Retreat Birmingham','18b Hall St, Birmingham B18 6BS, UK','ChIJi0fhgY-8cEgRtDlnJG25R-U',11,0,'Edit on 05/04: Minor timings change -> Registration now open from 11:00 instead\r\nIn celebration of Elevation release, we will be the first tournament to make use of the set - Code Name: Elevator. So rack your brains and bring your hope and dreams. *Or whatever broken card you think NSG should not have made and prove it to the world.*\r\n\r\n**When?**: 26th April, Saturday\r\n**Where?**: Geek Retreat Birmingham, Hall Street, Birmingham, B18 6BS\r\n**Who?**: the person reading this, hopefully\r\n**Entry**: £4\r\n**Registration**: 11:00\r\n**Round 1 starts at**: 11:30\r\n**Format**: Startup **With Elevation, No System Update**, Startup Balance Update 25.04 applies, Six rounds of Single Sided Swiss\r\nThere are a maximum of 16 spaces for this tournament.  \r\nPlease click \"going\" so I can keep an eye on numbers.\r\n\r\n**(I can sort out printing! Let me know what cards you need before *4pm Friday*  and I can print any cards you need. *DO NOT ask me to print out the entire Elevation set*)**\r\n\r\n![Elevation](https://nullsignal.games/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Elevation-Concept-1-2048x1152.jpg)\r\n\r\nJust like last time, we\'ve got a fun and beginner-friendly tournament coming your way, if your way is Birmingham (or an adjacent region). We’re gonna be playing six rounds of Single Sided Swiss to determine who is the best Startup player in all of [insert relevant region here depending on turnout], but more importantly to have a lovely time with the latest set release. \r\n\r\nIt’s going to be very casual, so should be an ideal space for those of you who’ve played a few games and are looking for a friendly space for your first tournament.\r\n\r\nHere are the details you need to know!\r\n\r\n# Location\r\nWe will be at Geek Retreat Birmingham (18b Hall St, Birmingham B18 6BS), which Google Maps says is a twenty minute walk from Birmingham New Street station or a short walk from St Pauls tram station. While it’s free to hire tables at the venue (the entry cost is solely to pay for prizes), they do not allow outside food and drink.\r\n\r\nWhen you get there, go downstairs (that\'s where the tables are).\r\n\r\n# Timings and Format\r\nThe event is on Satuday 26th April with registration open at 11:00 and round 1 starting at 11:30. There will be a lunch break after round 2, there will be 6 rounds in total with each round lasting 40 mins. \r\n\r\nPrize handouts at the shop.\r\n\r\nIf we get significantly fewer signups than expected, I may change the format - this will be communicated clearly on the day.\r\n\r\n**The tournament is in the Startup format, which means that cards from System Gateway, Elevation, The Automata Initiative and Rebellion Without Rehearsal will be legal.**\r\n\r\nPlease note that we will be using the most recent startup ban list that applies after elevation\'s release ([Startup Balance Update 25.04](https://nullsignal.games/blog/startup-balance-update-25-04/))\r\n\r\n***!!!!! System Update 2021 WILL NOT BE LEGAL !!!!!***\r\n\r\n# Prizes\r\nCards are all given out as playset of 3\'s.\r\n\r\n*Top 2*: Trick Shot (illustrated by Ed Mattinian) playmat\r\n*Top 4*: Fermenter (illustrated by Toby Woodman)\r\n*Top 8*: Angelique Garza Correa (illustrated by Olie Boldador) \r\n\r\n# New Players\r\nIf you’re new and nervous about coming to your first tournament, feel free to contact me if you’d like to talk about picking decks, what to expect from the tournament, printing proxies or anything else about Netrunner. I may be a bit slow to reply but I will get back to you when I can!\r\nThe Midlands City Grid Discord server (ask for an invite) will also be able to help you!\r\n\r\n# tl;dr\r\nThis is a casual tournament, sign up if you want a place (limit 16 players), £4 entry fee payable on the day.',1,0,0,39354,1,'elev',11,'2025-03-06 14:04:29','2025-11-03 11:36:55',NULL,4,52.487972,-1.908756,NULL,0,0,'',0,11,NULL,39354,'2025-04-26 14:25:15',0,'Europe/London',119,'','11:00',0,0),(4829,'EMEA Continentals 2025 @Cologne [Sponsored by NSG]','2025.08.01.','10:00','Germany','','netrunner@of15-15.de','Köln','Bürgerhaus Stollwerck','Dreikönigenstraße 23, 50678 Köln, Germany','ChIJlTHzKEokv0cR8ozHh3bKHuQ',110,16,'# [Discord](https://discord.gg/SfuuASdhmm) \r\n\r\n- we\'re full but DM me to get put onto the waiting list, we also might have free spots on the day\r\n- banlist is 25.08, ABR doesn\'t support this yet\r\n- you will receive a mail with registration infos soon-ish\r\n\r\n![Continentals banner](https://imgur.com/u1rpQm2.png)\r\n# EMEA Continentals @Cologne\r\n\r\nStandard format, lots of SSS rounds (probably 10) on Saturday and a double elimination Top16 cut on Sunday. This is a competitive-level tournament, but all players are welcome\r\n\r\n## Announced side events\r\n- [Team tournament](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/4964/emea25-team-tournament)\r\n- [Startup side event](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/4965/emea25-casual-startup-tournament)\r\n- [Eternal side event](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/4966/emea25-eternal-tournament)\r\n\r\n## Shipments to Cologne\r\nThere will be 4 Shipments to Cologne in different formats, fundraising events to help everyone get to Cologne! 🚢 See the tournament links below for more info :)\r\n\r\n[Startup Shipment](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/4877)\r\n[1st Standard Shipment](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/4875)\r\n[Eternal Shipment](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/4878)\r\n[2nd Standard Shipment](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/4876)\r\n\r\nWe already have some cool prices spoiled on the respective ABR pages by ElessarEllie  and TorpedoTyrus, so check them out and register 🥳\r\n\r\nIf you\'d like to volunteer for anything, this is greatly appreciated! Please fill out the ticket form as well. \r\n\r\n👋Looking forward to August 🙌 🎉',1,1,0,34833,1,'elev',9,'2025-03-29 21:21:00','2026-01-30 10:49:17',NULL,4,50.925279,6.964487,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,'2025.08.03.',34833,'2025-08-04 09:04:45',0,'Europe/Berlin',125,'Signup: The Price by *Brindlemold*\r\n![the price](https://i.imgur.com/gNzHrdO.png)\r\n\r\nNSG official prize kit:\r\n![NSG official prize kit](https://nullsignal.games/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/2025_continentals_-_card_fan1.png)\r\n\r\nmore prizes tba','09:30',0,0),(4856,'[Online] 🌎 🌍 2026 New Year\'s Showdown! 🏆 🎉','2026.01.03.','','','','maninthem00n - on discord or mitm.netrunner@gmail.com','','','','',167,16,'![Showdown2026](https://imgur.com/Y4Ysuj2.png)\r\n## [➡️ **Buy Tickets Here!**](https://netrunnercards.net/products/new-years-showdown-ticket-2026) \r\n\r\n➡️ **Check my timezone**  [Player meeting at 16:00 UTC , 11:00am Eastern USA, 8:00 am PDT\r\nRound 1 starts 30 minutes later](https://www.worldtimebuddy.com/?qm=1&lid=8,100,5&h=8&date=2026-1-3&sln=8-17.5&hf=1)\r\n\r\nShowdowns are fairly casual events and I make a special effort to make them approachable and inviting for newer players. This is a great place to start **if you\'ve never played in an online or any tournament before.** There is even a bonus prize if this is your first online Showdown! The online Showdowns are a great way to make connections with netrunner players all around the globe! 😃 I expect this will be another epic netrunner tournament bringing together new and old players of all skill levels for a wonderful day of connecting with friends and hacking servers 🥳\r\n\r\nGames will be played on Jinteki.net. I will be coordinating the event through the Null Signal online events hub Discord server. You can [join the server here.](https://discord.gg/WtE3nbwnBu) \r\n\r\n**How long will the event be?** This is going to be a large event and I expect to run 10 rounds of single sided swiss plus a meal break on day one. This should take between 9-10 hours. You\'re definitely not required to play the whole event to get prizes. I\'m sure some people will end up dropping part way through. We will cut to top 16 on day two; this will be a standard double elim cut with the same start time as day one. \r\n\r\nThe Showdown events have gotten big enough that I’m looking for additional help on the operations side. If you’re interested in **volunteering, please fill out [this google from.](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1LgHCWOA1mVzpq-2Oh4CHNo2VSKqJJZQnF39nT5ZUP_g/)**\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\n**What happens if I buy a ticket and can\'t make it?** You have two choices. First, I can refund your ticket. The earlier you can register the better it is for me and I don\'t want that to cost you if your plans change. The second option is to keep your ticket and I will ship you the participation prizes and any early registration bonuses. Playing is required to receive the *first Showdown tournament bonus*. \r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\n**Affordability** My main goal for running the Showdown tournaments is to increase access to competitive netrunner and help connect our global community. I make an effort to keep the base ticket price affordable, but I want to make sure the cost isn\'t a barrier for anyone who would like to play and receive prizes. If you are hesitant to play because of the cost you have a couple of options.  \r\n\r\nFirst of all, **anyone can play completely free without a ticket** (tickets are only required to receive physical prizes). If you would like to play without receiving prizes, all you need to do is [register on Cobra](https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/tournaments/4381) and show up in the Discord events hub at the start of the event. Without a ticket you can still win any non-physical prizes and [Beans.](https://netrunner-beanstalk.net/)\r\n\r\nIf you want to play and receive prizes but paying for a ticket would prevent you, use the discount code **NETRUNNER4EVERYONE** for 100% off the base ticket price. This discount code does not have unlimited uses. **Please use one if it would help**, but only if you plan to participate in the event. If the free tickets happen to run out you can check again later as quite a few players donate to support additional free tickets. ❤️\r\n\r\nAlternatively, if paying the whole ticket price would be a burden, you\'re welcome to take $6 off with the code **18$TICKET**. I really want to avoid the ticket price being a financial barrier, and I\'m hoping to make sure anyone who wants to play can participate. ❤️\r\n\r\nThese discounts are available thanks in large part to my Patrons on Patreon! If you’re interested in supporting my events, check out my [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/maninthemoon). (There are extra goodies!)\r\n\r\nThanks so much to my patrons who help make this event possible: **Rongydoge, stefdh, Wenjong, Stwyde, Tradon, OdsyWrenn, Wynaut, Radiant, liadahlia, dotv, ksodiya, Seabeast, New Puldrix, Ish, Battle_fennec, CyberShark, Human_Kirby, jelo and Baxder**',1,1,0,37550,1,'elev',11,'2025-04-12 04:41:51','2026-01-30 12:03:28',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,'2026.01.04.',37550,'2026-01-04 22:54:24',0,NULL,NULL,'**Players who have never played in an Online Showdown event before** will get a playset of their choice:\r\n**Spin Doctor by [Lenny.xyz](https://lenney.xyz/)!** \r\n**[Tucana](https://netrunnercards.net/products/48x-tucana-by-helabellaart) by HelabellaArt!**\r\nIf you\'ve been thinking about trying online competitive netrunner but haven\'t yet taken the plunge this is a great opportunity. ❤️\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\nAs is tradition with the Showdowns, most of the best prizes are just for showing up! Everyone gets to pick two Participation Prize playsets of their choice from the list below:\r\n\r\n#### **Participation Prize choices**\r\n**The Class Act** by [V4lvi_](https://imgur.com/rG87NU8)\r\n**Rising Tide** by ManintheMoon\r\n**Regolith Mining License** by [Kira L. Nguyen](https://www.artstation.com/kiralng)\r\n**Carpe Diem** full art by NSG GNK\r\n**Offworld Office** full art by NSG GNK\r\n\r\n\r\n#### **Past Participation Prizes (only available for first 48 hours)**\r\n[**Semak-Samun** by ManintheMoon](https://netrunnercards.net/products/semak-samun-playset)\r\n**Unity** by [Aleksandra Simonović](https://aleksandraink.com/)\r\n**Telework Contract** by [Kira L. Nguyen](https://www.artstation.com/kiralng)\r\n**[Arruaceiras Crew](https://netrunnercards.net/products/arruaceiras-crew-playset)** by [Lenney.xyz](https://lenney.xyz/)\r\n**[Strike Fund](https://netrunnercards.net/products/strike-fund-playset)** by [Matheus Calza](https://www.artstation.com/matheuscalza)\r\n[**Bladderwort**](https://netrunnercards.net/products/bladderwort-playset) by ManintheMoon\r\n**[Finality](https://netrunnercards.net/products/finality-by-cat-shen)** by [Cat Shen](https://www.makeplayingcards.com/sell/kysra)\r\n**End of the Line** by [Brindelmold](https://brindelmoldart.wordpress.com/)\r\n\r\n\r\n#### **Add-On New Year’s Showdown 2026 Souvenir Prize** \r\n**[Laser-cut iridescent acrylic Sable Dragon ID!](https://imgur.com/YFyDpK8)** Illustration by Aleksandra Simonović. This iridescent variant is exclusive to the New Year’s Showdown 2026. Fancy, shiny things are fun and it’s nice to have something extra special to remember the event!\r\n\r\n#### **Placement Prizes**\r\n\r\n**Early Registration** (first 48 hours only) - [Arissana by V4lvi_](https://imgur.com/LZzuWiI)\r\n\r\n**2 wins (6+ points) or played all rounds of Swiss**\r\n1x [Showdown Exclusive variant of Hannah “Wheels” Pilintra by V4lvi_](https://imgur.com/V3kN9cm)\r\nThis 2-wins prize will be repeated at all Showdowns in 2026. Because of the way I ship the prizes I can only afford to include a single card in the new 2 wins slot. I spent a long time trying to figure out a good option and Hannah is both useful if you have only a single copy, but still fun to collect a full playset. A slightly less epic version of this card will also eventually be for sale on my site, but this version will be exclusive to Showdowns in 2026. \r\n\r\n**3 wins (9+ points) or played all rounds of Swiss**\r\n[Stained Glass Sable by Aleksandra Simonović](https://imgur.com/JtM8wAs)\r\n\r\n**4 wins (12+ points)** \r\n[Hostile Architecture, by Jandon Banyu](https://imgur.com/4tCOHGo)\r\n\r\n**5 wins (15+ points)**\r\nThe New Year’s Showdown Key - redeemable at one of the next two Showdowns\r\n\r\n**6 wins (18+ points)**\r\n**Foil** [Semak-Samun](https://netrunnercards.net/products/semak-samun-playset) by ManintheMoon\r\n\r\n**7 wins (21+ points)**\r\n[Set of 6 Acrylic Botulus Tokens](https://imgur.com/J7vXSSN) by ManintheMoon\r\n\r\n**16th - 8th**\r\nAcrylic Leo laser engraved, produced by ManintheMoon.\r\n\r\n**Top 16**\r\nUnique Jnet Cardbacks\r\n\r\n**Top 8**\r\nGold Mirror Acrylic Leo laser engraved with placement, produced by ManintheMoon.\r\n\r\n**Top 4**\r\nInvitation to the [Ultimate Showdown 2026](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5231/ultimate-showdown-2026)\r\n\r\n**Top 2**\r\nSlate Leo laser engraved with placement, produced by ManintheMoon.\r\n\r\n**First place**\r\nOne of a kind 2026 Showdown Champion dog tag by Atien\r\n\r\n**Top 5%** \r\nCBI invite handed down if needed (top cut only). \r\n\r\nAll prizes potentially subject to change. (This has often meant adding more stuff).\r\n\r\n![New Year’s Showdown Prizes](https://imgur.com/iWFjDmX.png)','',33,1),(4857,'[Online] 🌎 🌍 2025 Worlds Showdown! 🏆 🎉','2025.09.27.','','','','maninthem00n - on discord or mitm.netrunner@gmail.com','','','','',190,16,'## How do I join the player meeting? \r\nThe player meeting will be held on discord, you can [join the server here](https://discord.gg/eCcDFNp4AS). Look for the voice lobby with 200 players in it. \r\n\r\n![Showdown2025](https://imgur.com/OnxqjdD.png)\r\n## [➡️ **Buy Tickets Here!**](https://www.netrunnercards.net/products/worlds-showdown-2025-ticket) \r\n\r\n➡️ **Check my timezone**  [Player meeting at 15:00 UTC , 11:00am Eastern USA, 8:00 am PDT \r\nRound 1 starts 30 minutes later](https://www.worldtimebuddy.com/?qm=1&lid=8,100,5&h=8&date=2025-9-27&sln=8-18&hf=1)\r\n\r\nShowdowns are fairly casual events and I make a special effort to make them approachable and inviting for newer players. This is a great place to start **if you\'ve never played in an online or any tournament before.** There is even a bonus prize if you have never played in an online Showdown before! The online Showdowns are a great way to make connections with netrunner players all around the globe! 😃 I expect this will be another epic netrunner tournament bringing together new and old players of all skill levels for a wonderful day of connecting with friends and hacking servers 🥳\r\n\r\nGames will be played on Jinteki.net. I will be coordinating the event through the Null Signal online events hub Discord server. You can [join the server here.](https://discord.gg/ymmy6fJnEZ) \r\n\r\n**Note:** We will be using the [25.10 World’s Banlist](https://nullsignal.games/blog/standard-ban-list-25-10/) for this event released on September 17th.\r\n\r\n**How long will the event be?** This is going to be a large event and I expect to run 8-9 rounds of single sided swiss plus a meal break on day one. This should take between 7-10 hours. You\'re definitely not required to play the whole event to get prizes. I\'m sure some people will end up dropping part way through. I plan to run a cut to top 16 on day two, this will be a standard double elim cut with the same start time as day one. \r\n\r\nThe Showdown events have gotten big enough that I’m looking for additional help on the operations side. If you’re interested in **volunteering, please fill out [this google from.](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfrydvNUfGNbgk_bOAKRapcKWG05e4HRvON5i-EAw1vkfxe2g/viewform?usp=sharing&ouid=116193247199921358659)**\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\n**What happens if I buy a ticket and can\'t make it?** You have two choices. First, I can refund your ticket. The earlier you can register the better it is for me and I don\'t want that to cost you if your plans change. The second option is to keep your ticket and I will ship you the participation prizes and any early registration bonuses. Playing is required to receive the *first Showdown tournament bonus*. \r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\n**Affordability** My main goal for running the Showdown tournaments is to increase access to competitive netrunner and help connect our global community. I make an effort to keep the base ticket price affordable, but I want to make sure the cost isn\'t a barrier for anyone who would like to play and receive prizes. If you are hesitant to play because of the cost you have a couple of options.  \r\n\r\nFirst of all, **anyone can play completely free without a ticket** (tickets are only required to receive physical prizes). If you would like to play without receiving prizes, all you need to do is [register on Cobra](https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/tournaments/4128) and show up in the Discord events hub at the start of the event. Without a ticket you can still win a CBI invite and [Beans.](https://netrunner-beanstalk.net/?season=3&formatCode=standard)\r\n\r\nIf you want to play and receive prizes but paying for a ticket would prevent you, use the discount code **NETRUNNER4EVERYONE** for 100% off the base ticket price. This discount code does not have unlimited uses. **Please use one if it would help**, but only if you plan to fully participate in the event. If the free tickets happen to run out you can check again later as quite a few players donate to support additional free tickets. ❤️\r\n\r\nAlternatively, if paying the whole ticket price would be a burden, you\'re welcome to take $6 off with the code **18$TICKET**. I really want to avoid the ticket price being a financial barrier, and I\'m hoping to make sure anyone who wants to play can participate. ❤️\r\n\r\nThese discounts are available thanks in large part to my Patrons on Patreon! If you’re interested in supporting my events, check out my [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/maninthemoon) (There are extra goodies!)\r\n\r\nThanks so much to my patrons who help make this event possible: **liadahlia, dotv, ksodiya, Seabeast, New Puldrix, Ish, Battle_fennec, CyberShark, Human_Kirby, jelo and Baxder.**',1,1,0,37550,1,'elev',11,'2025-04-12 04:42:01','2026-01-04 05:38:21',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,'2025.09.28.',37550,'2025-09-28 19:17:12',0,NULL,108,'**Players who have never played in an Online Showdown event before** will get a playset of their choice:\r\n**Spin Doctor by [Lenny.xyz](https://lenney.xyz/)!** \r\n**[Tucana](https://netrunnercards.net/products/48x-tucana-by-helabellaart) by HelabellaArt!**\r\n**Carpe Diem [NSG full-art](https://nullsignal.games/blog/2024-q4-2025-q1-game-night-kits-are-now-available/)!** \r\nIf you\'ve been thinking about trying online competitive netrunner but haven\'t yet taken the plunge this is a great opportunity. ❤️\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\nAs is tradition with the Showdowns, most of the best prizes are just for showing up! Everyone gets to pick two Participation Prize playsets of their choice from the list below:\r\n\r\n#### **Participation Prize choices**\r\n**Unity** by [Alexsandria Simonović](https://aleksandraink.com/)\r\n**Semak-samun** by Hermann von Königsbrunn and Abraham McBride\r\n**Telework Contract** (Art in final stages) by [Kira L. Nguyen](https://www.artstation.com/kiralng)\r\n**Ablative Barrier** full art by NSG GNK\r\n**Audrey v2** full art by NSG GNK\r\n**Behold!** full art by NSG GNK\r\n\r\n#### **Past Participation Prizes (only available for first 48 hours)** - Ended\r\n**[Strike Fund](https://netrunnercards.net/products/strike-fund-playset)** by [Matheus Calza](https://www.artstation.com/matheuscalza)\r\n**[Arruaceiras Crew](https://netrunnercards.net/products/arruaceiras-crew-playset)** by [Lenney.xyz](https://lenney.xyz/)\r\n**[Finality](https://netrunnercards.net/products/finality-by-cat-shen)** by [Cat Shen](https://www.makeplayingcards.com/sell/kysra)\r\n**[Revolver](https://netrunnercards.net/products/revolver-by-prenic)** by PreNic\r\n**[Sure Gamble](https://netrunnercards.net/products/sure-gamble-psk)** by Cassius Marcellus Coolidge and PSK\r\n**[Spin Doctor](https://netrunnercards.net/products/spin-doctor-by-lenny-xyz)** by [Lenney.xyz](https://lenney.xyz/)\r\n**[Mavirus](https://netrunnercards.net/products/mavirus-by-picat)** by [PiCat](https://www.instagram.com/picat_314/)\r\n\r\n\r\n#### **Add-On World’s Showdown 2025 Souvenir Prizes** \r\n**[Laser-cut iridescent acrylic AU Co. ID and/or Ob Superheavy Logistics ID!](https://imgur.com/1Diic5U)** Illustrations by Aleksandria Simonović. This iridescent variant is exclusive to the World’s Showdown 2025. I like fancy shiny things and thought you might too. \r\n\r\n#### **Placement Prizes**\r\n\r\n**Early Registration** (first 48 hours only) - Ended\r\n[Phoenix by ElessarEllie](https://imgur.com/bvxAkql)\r\n\r\n**3 wins (9+ points) or played all rounds of Swiss**\r\n[MuslihaT by Valentina de la Rosa](https://imgur.com/8mgMt8y)\r\n\r\n**4 wins (12+ points)** \r\nRestoring Humanity, by Jandon Banyu\r\n\r\n**5 wins (15+ points)**\r\n**Foil** [Bladderwort](https://netrunnercards.net/products/bladderwort-playset) by Martin J. Heade and Abraham McBride\r\n\r\n**6 wins (18+ points)**\r\n[Stained Glass Epiphany and Precision Design](https://imgur.com/j4pxnLf) by [Alexsandria Simonović](https://aleksandraink.com/)\r\n\r\n**7 wins (21+ points)**\r\n[Stained Glass Ob and AU Co.](https://imgur.com/j4pxnLf) by [Alexsandria Simonović](https://aleksandraink.com/)\r\n\r\n**Top 25**\r\nCollectors’ Edition Metal Physarum Entangler Token\r\n\r\n**5th - 16th**\r\nAluminum Haas-Bioroid: Precision Design laser engraved, produced by ManintheMoon.\r\n\r\n**Top 8**\r\nUnique [Jnet Cardbacks](https://imgur.com/a/HXLD067)\r\n\r\n**Top 6**\r\nInvitation to the [Ultimate Showdown](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/4936/invitational-2025-ultimate-showdown-)\r\n\r\n**Top 4**\r\nSlate Haas-Bioroid: Precision Design laser engraved with placement, produced by ManintheMoon\r\n\r\n**First place**\r\nOne of a kind 2025 Showdown Champion dog tag by Atien\r\n\r\n**Top 5%** \r\nCBI invite handed down if needed (top cut only). \r\n\r\n**Top 8**\r\nH2 2024 Casual Tournament Kit prizes.\r\n(This is to qualify the event for CBI Invites and Beans!)\r\n\r\nAll prizes potentially subject to change. (this has often meant adding more stuff).\r\n\r\n![World’s Showdown Registration Prizes](https://imgur.com/Zx91wH3.png)\r\n![World’s Showdown Placement Prizes](https://imgur.com/sxiBIDz.png)','',0,1),(4859,'Online Elevation Swiss League','2025.05.16.','','','','julia.larrea.montoya@protonmail.com','','','','',85,8,'# **WELCOME TO THE ONLINE ELEVATION SWISS LEAGUE**  🌄 \r\nThe Online Elevation Swiss League is a **free entry** tournament starting  and running for between 5 and 7 weeks based on attendance, plus 3 more weeks of a top 8 cut. **There will be prizes**, even if you don\'t pay anything. You can sign up here: \r\n**https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/tournaments/3903**\r\n\r\n## **Scheduling** 📆 \r\nEvery Friday I will post the pairings for that week and you will have 7 days to schedule and play a **Double Sided Match** with your opponent. If you cannot play your match, both players may ask for an extension. Otherwise, we will award a 0-0 Tie. If you make an effort to reach out and your opponent does not show up, you may be awarded a 6-0 win.\r\n\r\n## **Play your games**  \r\nEvery week you will play one game of runner and one game of corp. **You can change your decks every week**. If during a game you have any rules question or issue, you can hop over to GLC and ping for a @glc Judge. If there\'s no GLC judge online, you can ping for a @Judge! here.  \r\n**Play your games in the Tournament tab**. After each round, whoever won the last match should go and post both games\' replays on that weeks\' replay thread. \r\n\r\n## **Prizes** \r\nWe will be distributing ManInTheMoon\'s cards, PennysHaver cards, Run Together Pack 1 and 2 cards, prize wall style, based on attendance. Top Cut players will get a Jinteki.net cardback (TBD) and Top 2 players will get a Jnet Donator account.\r\nThe tournament will be organized on the Null Signal Games discord server. \r\n\r\nMore Information to come as the date approaches.',1,0,0,36566,1,'elev',12,'2025-04-12 19:21:25','2026-01-30 10:45:35',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,36566,'2025-07-26 09:01:35',0,NULL,123,'Prize wall for: \r\n- GNK Q2 and Q3\r\n- Run Together 2025 \r\n- Pennys Haver 2025\r\n- Various Other Alt Arts\r\nFirst and Second place will get a Premium Jinteki.net Account.','',35,1),(4862,'NYC Megacity - NO SLEEP TILL BROOKLAN','2025.07.19.','13:30','United States','NY','','Brooklyn','BrookLAN','339 Troutman St, Brooklyn, NY 11237, USA','ChIJoQzszopdwokRgf4do3_gAH0',31,8,'![image](https://i.imgur.com/fQsjdlu.png)\r\n\r\nOne of the final competitive stops in the US before [Continentals in the great white north](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/4858/2025-americas-continental-championship-montral). Come out for your chance to win a bye to continentals, get some sick prizes, and play the best damn card game out there! Main Event starts Saturday, Side Event of Hand and Brain on Sunday.\r\n\r\n## Registration begins Saturday at 12:30 PM, round 1 starts at 1:30 PM.\r\n## Sunday rounds start at 12:30 PM\r\n\r\nEntry Fee: $45 for the Main Event (please contact .cado on discord if you need any financial assistance)\r\n\r\n# DECKLISTS MANDATORY: Please Pre-register with your decklists on [Aesop\'s Tables](https://www.aesopstables.net/7353) if able. We will also have the ability for you to register your decklist on site as well, if you want to print out your deck list you can use this layout: [Decklist Sheet](https://access.nullsignal.games/OPdownloads/Decklist-Sheet-2022.pdf)\r\n\r\nMain Event: 8 Rounds of Single Sided Swiss with a cut to Top 8. (Number of Swiss Rounds subject to change dependent on attendance).\r\n\r\nSide Event: In [Hand and Brain](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1pmeouxYb84YB869k1Tp_FC9KfAZyLmvt9bsbaEqoUhE/edit?tab=t.0#heading=h.do7eifdcfehc), two players join forces to become one! Teams of 2 compete against each other using one Standard legal deck per team, with one player choosing the action (the Brain says “install”) while the other player chooses everything else (the hand then chooses what card to install and installs it.)\r\n\r\nDAY 1: Main Event: Rounds 1 - 7 of Single Sided Swiss. Dinner Break after Round 5. \r\nDAY 2: Main Event: Round 8 of Single Sided Swiss, Top 8 Double Elimination. Lunch Break Between Swiss and Top 8\r\n	Side Event: Hand and Brain Standard Team Tournament',1,1,0,36746,1,'elev',17,'2025-04-14 17:42:01','2026-01-30 12:04:12',NULL,5,40.705246,-73.924378,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,'2025.07.20.',36746,'2025-07-21 12:08:11',0,'America/New_York',124,'Having trouble waking up in the morning? Well you can enjoy your morning coffee in this One Of A Kind Ceramic Coffee Cup trophy! ![Image of a trophy that consists of a ceramic version of a classic NYC diner coffee cup](https://i.imgur.com/T6qHAHg.jpeg) (Artist rendition, actual trophy base may differ slightly in appearance, cup is not one of a kind but the trophy base is).\r\nAll you gotta do is … win NYC Megacity! \r\n\r\nDon’t worry though, for everyone else we have these beautiful Cezve Alt Arts by The Tag Mill, with an exclusive NYC Megacity Stamp, and you get one just for signing up for an event! ![Cezve Alt Art with the cups replaced with NY Diner Style Coffee Cups](https://i.imgur.com/SN9AFxS.jpeg)\r\n\r\nBut if what gets you out of bed in the morning is COMMERCE and CAPITAL, then you’ll have to WORK for it! Top half of swiss gets this stunning Alt Art Plutus by local artist and NSG regular Cat Shen! ![Plutus Alt Art with the Wall Street Bull as the central figure](https://i.imgur.com/0vlQAtc.png)\r\n\r\nBREAKING NEWS! Did you hear that NYC was awarded a Megacity???\r\n![It\'s News to Me! Image of a Slowpoke based alt art for Spin Doctor](https://i.imgur.com/yF36db6.jpeg)\r\nNow on to some actual news: Signing up for Hand and Brain gets you one of these (casual only) alt art Spin Doctors, with special NYC edits made by Atomikrin!','12:30',35,0),(4889,'Rain City May \'25 Cube Draft','2025.05.24.','12:00','Canada','','alphaalec@gmail.com','Vancouver','Rain City Games','88 W Pender St Unit 1069, Vancouver, BC V6B 6N9, Canada','ChIJ6SNusXtxhlQRfnCOSXUtcUA',8,NULL,'Format: Cube\r\nEntry: $15 (pay to Rain City Games at their register)\r\nRounds: Draft Corp cards, draft Runner cards, then 3 or 4 rounds of Double Sided Swiss\r\nWe\'ll finish by 9, there\'ll be a short dinner break\r\nNo top cut\r\n\r\n**IMPORTANT NOTE:** this is limited to 8 people, and spots will be tracked by me personally, not by the \"Going\" button on this page. If you want to participate, please reach out to me on Discord, and I will let you know if there\'s currently a slot.\r\n\r\nJoin the [Vancouver Discord Server](https://discord.gg/3G4A73u), and message me; my username is Sindarin.',1,0,0,17150,1,'elev',1,'2025-04-23 21:28:13','2025-12-03 18:43:05',NULL,4,49.280524,-123.107088,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,17150,'2025-06-19 21:39:10',0,'America/Vancouver',118,'','12:00',35,0),(4936,'[Invitational] 🌎 🌍 2025 Ultimate Showdown! 🏆 🎉','2025.11.15.','07:00','','','maninthem00n - on discord or mitm.netrunner@gmail.com','','','','',24,8,'![Ultimate Showdown 2025](https://imgur.com/U1qXh2H.png)\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\n#### This is a **24 player invitational event** to cap off the 2025 competitive season. \r\n\r\n#### [Stream will be on the Metropole Grid](https://www.youtube.com/@MetropoleGrid)\r\n\r\nI have always been a big fan of the intercontinental championship event and when I heard it was canceled this year I thought it would be worth running a similar event in it\'s honer! \r\n\r\nThis event is specifically set up to support the Showdowns I run and Online organized play. There are a few ways you can qualify for the event. \r\n\r\n1) **The top 6 players** from each 2025 Online Showdown\r\n2) **The 2025 CBI Champion**\r\n3) **The three 2025 Online Continental Champions**\r\n4) **The 2025 Worlds Champion**\r\n5) **The top player ranked on the season 3 [Beanstalk](https://netrunner-beanstalk.net/?season=3&formatCode=standard)** on Nov 1st. \r\n\r\nThere will be no hand down invitations. If anyone qualifies twice or can not attend all remaining slots will be filled from the beanstalk based on season 3 Nov 1st rankings. \r\n\r\nQualified players so far: \r\n**ant1** 1st New Year\'s Showdown\r\n**OF15-15** 2nd New Year\'s Showdown\r\n**not_yeti** 3rd New Year\'s Showdown\r\n**CobraBubbles** 4th New Year\'s Showdown\r\n**Ollie** 5th New Year\'s Showdown\r\n**AnOddRadish** 6th New Year\'s Showdown\r\n**Kikai** 1st CBI 2025\r\n**DeeR** 1st Summer Showdown \r\n**not_yeti** 2nd Summer Showdown (Double Qualify)\r\n**passive_mult** 3rd Summer Showdown \r\n**davz131** 4th Summer Showdown \r\n**Smolgrump** 5th Summer Showdown \r\n**MotionBlur** 6th Summer Showdown\r\n**TheKing** 1st at APAC Continental Championship Online\r\n**tbu3k** 1st at EMEA Continental Championship Online\r\n**AugustusCaesar** 1st at American Continental Championship Online\r\n**RotomAppliance** 1st Worlds Showdown \r\n**wowarlok** 2nd Worlds Showdown\r\n**eden_online** 3rd Worlds Showdown \r\n**jan tuno** 4th Worlds Showdown \r\n**Sl33p3r** 5th Worlds Showdown \r\n**xiaat** 6th Worlds Showdown\r\n**ZomZraft** 1st at NSG Worlds 2025\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\n#### Ultimate Showdown Event Structure:\r\n\r\nThe format will be standard with **open lists during the whole event.** For a hopefully fun and dramatic event we will be using a modified version of the SSS + cut. The event will be triple elimination. Once you lose 3 games, you will be eliminated under most circumstances.   \r\n\r\nThe first 6 rounds of the event will be paired using SSS. Players with four wins after the 6 rounds will move on to a “top 8 cut”. During the cut rounds players will still be eliminated based on their initial 3 lives, but changing way rounds are paired towards the end of the event will hopefully lead to a more dramatic finish. From the simulations I ran, this should run fairly smoothly, but there are some outliers which I will try and cover here for those who like to know what’s going to be happening with edge cases.  \r\n\r\n----\r\n#### Edge Cases I have planned for:\r\n\r\nThere will be no ties. Every player in the event will have a seed that will be used to break ties in the event that the game would usually result in a tie.  \r\n\r\nDuring the first 6 rounds, players will always be eliminated in even numbers. If an odd number of players would be eliminated, the highest ranked player with 3 losses is “saved”.  \r\n\r\nAfter the 6 rounds of SSS are complete, there is a chance that less than 8 players have all three lives remaining. In that case, all players 3/3 will still have a slim chance of winning, and I will explain how that works if we end up in that situation. If after the 6 rounds of SSS, there are more than 8 players with all 3 lives remaining, we will play a tiebreaker round to determine the final 8\r\n\r\nIf you can think of any edge cases I haven\'t covered feel free to reach out and I\'ll make sure there is a plan before the event starts.',1,1,0,37550,1,'elev',14,'2025-05-17 02:02:53','2025-11-15 23:01:07',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,37550,'2025-11-15 23:01:07',0,NULL,NULL,'**1st place** - **Champ Card** commissioned alt art featuring your likeness that will be used as one of the prizes during the 2026 showdown series. You will get 100 copies and a playmate of your alt art (as soon as it\'s finished).\r\n\r\n**Top 8** fancy laser cut ID with your handle and placement. (Second place player will help decide on the ID and design).\r\n\r\n**Top half** Foil Descent (in addition to non-foil)\r\n\r\n**Participation** Descent Alt Art and two IDs of your choice in foil from the 2025 Showdown commissions.\r\n\r\n**Beans** based on placement.','07:00',35,1),(4940,'[Online] 🌎 🌍 Frozen Showdown ❄️❄️','2027.06.26.','17:00','','','maninthem00n - on discord or mitm.netrunner@gmail.com','','','','',NULL,NULL,'Was trying to schedule this for 2025, but there are no good weekends RIP. Just saving here incase my schedule changes. \r\n\r\n![Showdown2025](https://imgur.com/gIuwoT9.png)\r\n## ➡️ *Tickets go on sale soon*\r\n\r\n➡️ **Check my timezone**  [Player meeting at 15:00 UTC , 11:00am Eastern USA, 8:00 am PDT \r\nRound 1 starts 30 minutes later](https://www.worldtimebuddy.com/?qm=1&lid=20,5786882,5128581&h=20&date=2025-5-18&sln=8-17&hf=1)\r\n\r\n\r\nI expect this to be a smaller event similar to the frozen showdown I ran last year. This is not one of my 3 main showdown events as most of the prizes will be repeats from the [Online Summer Showdown](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/4674/-summer-showdown-2025-). I have always loved playing in the APAC region events, and I hope this will help support organized play for the APAC region. \r\n\r\nI expect to run 6-7 rounds of SSS and a single elimination cut to top 4-8 depending on players. \r\n\r\nLast year this ended up being a pretty chill event and I even got to play ❤️ Ideally it will be wrapped up in 8 hours or less so I can get to bed 🙃\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\nAll CTKs are fairly casual events and I make a special effort to make these events approachable and inviting for newer players. This is a great place to start **if you\'ve never played in an online or any tournament before.** There is even a bonus prize if you have never played in an online Showdown before! The online Showdowns are a great way to make connections with netrunner players all around the globe! 😃 I expect this will be another epic netrunner tournament bringing together new and old players of all skill levels for a wonderful day of connecting with friends and hacking servers 🥳\r\n\r\nGames will be played on Jinteki.net. I will be coordinating the event through the Null Signal online events hub Discord server. You can join the server [here.](https://discord.gg/ymmy6fJnEZ)\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\n**What happens if I buy a ticket and can\'t make it?** You have two choices. First, I can refund your ticket. The earlier you can register the better it is for me and I don\'t want that to cost you if your plans change. The second option is to keep your ticket and I will ship you the participation prizes and any early registration bonuses. Playing is required to receive the *first Showdown tournament bonus*. \r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\n**Affordability** My main goal for running the Showdown tournaments is to increase access to competitive netrunner. I make an effort to keep the ticket price affordable, but I want to make sure the cost isn\'t a barrier for anyone who would like to play and receive prizes. If you are hesitant to play because of the cost you have a couple of options.  \r\n\r\nFirst of all **anyone can play completely free without a ticket** (tickets are only required to receive physical prizes). If you would like to play without receiving prizes all you need to do is register on Aesop’s Tabes and show up in the Discord events hub at the start of the event. Without a ticket you can still win a CBI invite and [Beans.](https://netrunner-beanstalk.net/?season=2&formatCode=standard)\r\n\r\nIf you want to play and receive prizes, but paying for a ticket would prevent you, use the discount code **NETRUNNER4EVERYONE** for 100% off the ticket price. This discount code does not have unlimited uses. **Please use one if it would help** but only if you plan to fully participate in the event. If the free tickets happen to run out you can check again later as quite a few players donate to support more free tickets. ❤️\r\n\r\nAlternatively, if paying the whole ticket price would be a burden, you\'re welcome to take $6 off with the code **18$TICKET**. I really want to avoid the ticket price being a financial barrier, and I\'m hoping to make sure anyone who wants to play can participate. ❤️\r\n\r\nIf you\'re in a comfortable financial position, there is an opportunity during check out to chip in an extra **1/4+ ticket** to help me offer additional free tickets. You can also support the events on [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/maninthemoon) with extra goodies!',0,1,0,37550,1,'elev',11,'2025-05-18 02:15:11','2025-12-14 14:13:43',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,108,'**Players who have never played in an Online Showdown event before** will get a playset of **End of the Line by [Brindelmold](https://www.makeplayingcards.com/sell/brindelmold-cards)!** If you\'ve been thinking about trying online competitive netrunner but haven\'t yet taken the plunge this is a great opportunity. ❤️\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\nAs is tradition with the Showdowns most of the best prizes are just for showing up! Everyone gets to pick two participation prize playsets of their choice from the list below:\r\n\r\n#### **Participation alt art choices**\r\n**[Strike Fund](https://imgur.com/UD81JEs)** by [Matheus Calza](https://www.artstation.com/matheuscalza)\r\n**[Bladderwort](https://imgur.com/MCqIOZn)** by Martin J Heade and ManintheMoon\r\n**[Arruaceiras Crew](https://imgur.com/jUW0zLb)** by [Lenney.xyz](https://lenney.xyz/)\r\nAdding at least one additional participation option. TBD\r\n\r\nGNK options getting updated\r\n**Regolith Mining License** full art by NSG GNK\r\n**Ablative Barrier** full art by NSG GNK\r\n**Your Digital Life** full art by NSG GNK\r\n***Only available for the first 48 hours!!**\r\n\r\n#### **Optional Participation Prize** \r\n**[Laser-cut acrylic Arissana ID](https://netrunnercards.net/products/arissana-rocha-nahu-bundle)** Illustration by [Cat Shen](https://www.makeplayingcards.com/sell/kysra)\r\n\r\n#### **Placement Prizes**\r\n\r\n**Early Registration** (first 48 hours only)\r\n[Epiphany Analytica, alt art by Aleksandra Simonović!](https://imgur.com/7bs0Sav)\r\n\r\n**3 wins (9+ points)**\r\nSable by [Brindelmold](https://www.makeplayingcards.com/sell/brindelmold-cards)\r\n\r\n**Top 16**\r\n**Foil** [Finality](https://netrunnercards.net/products/finality-by-cat-shen) by [Cat Shen](https://www.makeplayingcards.com/sell/kysra)\r\n\r\n**1st - 8th**\r\nUnique Jnet Cardbacks\r\n\r\n**2nd - 4th**\r\nAluminum Built to Last (laser engraved) produced by ManintheMoon.\r\n\r\n**First place**\r\n[Slate Built to Last](https://imgur.com/ncKOa7h) (laser engraved) produced by ManintheMoon\r\n\r\n**Top 5%** \r\nCBI invite handed down if needed (top cut only). \r\n\r\nOfficial casual Tournament Kit prizes as displayed.\r\n\r\nAll prizes potentially subject to change.\r\n\r\n![Summer Showdown prizes](https://imgur.com/Jvts2ZE.png)\r\n![Summer Showdown Additional prizes](https://imgur.com/TA1seTC.png)','17:00',39,1),(4953,'Zeebag\'s Suburban Wasteland Volume 4','2025.07.12.','11:00','Canada','','zeeman.chris@gmail.com','Mississauga','','7324 Joliette Crescent, Mississauga, ON L5N 1Z3, Canada','ChIJ6XiOOFpqK4gRCRn6fpuZRAo',22,4,'![Image](https://media2.giphy.com/media/v1.Y2lkPTc5MGI3NjExZ21kMzQ1b3libTNudm9rcjhyNWs2MHNwcnRjMGhhZndxbG04dXVqayZlcD12MV9pbnRlcm5hbF9naWZfYnlfaWQmY3Q9Zw/nvyL0iuIgCEBZvpQxB/giphy.gif)\r\n\r\nOh Hi! Come play Netrunner at my home (7324 Joliette Cres) on July 12. The GIF here is a lego kit I got for my birthday and it is very cool so you should DEFINITELY come look at it.\r\n\r\nAs always homebrew is on tap and all are welcome! We will be ordering a bunch Pizza for dinner and have other tasty treats for people to munch on throughout the day. Guests are also welcome to bring whatever they like to share!\r\n\r\nRegistration will be FREE this year, although food will be $10/person. On top of the gnk I have listed as prize support, I will have many other pieces of cardboard and play mats to give away!',1,0,0,25380,1,'elev',1,'2025-05-25 20:14:01','2026-01-25 14:10:37',NULL,4,43.593573,-79.771739,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,25380,'2025-07-13 13:04:56',0,'America/Toronto',123,'','10:00',35,0),(4963,'Coventry Weekly Netrunner Meet-up',NULL,'18:00','United Kingdom','','All-One-Name on Discord','Coventry','Golden Cross','8 Hay Ln, Coventry CV1 5RF, UK','ChIJzSaXsrtLd0gRrD_j9ddGAp0',NULL,NULL,'Casual Netrunner meet-up every Wednesday at The Golden Cross from 6pm until 9pm, organised in the cov-meetups channel of the [Midlands Netrunner Grid Discord](https://discord.gg/nPsFSqUCkh).',0,0,0,46826,1,'unknown',8,'2025-05-29 03:47:16','2026-02-01 17:32:26',NULL,0,52.407785,-1.508705,3,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'Europe/London',NULL,'','',35,0),(4964,'EMEA25 Team Event','2025.08.01.','12:00','Germany','','netrunner@of15-15.de / OF15-15 on discord','Köln','','','EiNTdG9sbHdlcmNraG9mLCA1MDY3OCBLw7ZsbiwgR2VybWFueSIuKiwKFAoSCV8ytfJJJL9HEecbN3OPyqNzEhQKEgnlL6tpkSW_RxHwdypK_GAnBA',24,0,'# [Discord](https://discord.gg/SfuuASdhmm) [Tickets](https://form.jotform.com/251067349970060)\r\n\r\n![Continentals banner](https://imgur.com/u1rpQm2.png)\r\n# EMEA Team Tournament\r\nQuick info:\r\n- Teams of 3\r\n- player meeting starts 12:00 local time (UTC +2)\r\n- lots of cool prizes including new laser IDs\r\n- [Format doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1XD_JjL6jdV2I-Z5RlK1hIUUDMwzo6GVw5n72nakTu8M/edit?usp=sharing)',1,1,0,34833,1,'elev',6,'2025-05-30 08:58:39','2026-01-30 10:48:48',NULL,4,50.924368,6.965036,NULL,0,0,'',0,6,NULL,34833,'2025-08-04 09:06:37',0,'Europe/Berlin',NULL,'tba','11:30',35,0),(4974,'Meet Up CTK 🏆 🎉','2025.06.12.','17:30','United States','WA','maninthem00n - on discord or mitm.netrunner@gmail.com','Seattle','Chuck\'s Hop Shop Greenwood','656 NW 85th St, Seattle, WA 98117, USA','ChIJYTPqYycUkFQRUIA3GZD6ykc',13,NULL,'This will be the same meet-up format we have been running the last few months 5 rounds SSS no top cut. Bonus door prizes as first come first serve. Drop in/out welcome. \r\n\r\nStandard format.\r\nDecklists not required.\r\n\r\n[Invite link to Seattle Discord ECG](https://discord.gg/8VfeD4qx84) \r\n\r\n$10 donation to help restock bagel boxes appreciated, but not required. Please come **don\'t pay if it would be a hardship** ❤️',1,0,0,37550,1,'elev',11,'2025-06-06 15:22:59','2025-12-04 17:17:04',NULL,5,47.690896,-122.365785,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,37550,'2025-06-13 14:34:12',0,'America/Los_Angeles',108,'I will have some fancy tokens, Acrylic ID and other items that can be drafted based on placement.','17:00',35,0),(4976,'Torneo EE33','2025.07.25.','16:30','Spain','','netrunner.bilbao@gmail.com','Baracaldo','','Bilbao Exhibition Centre, C. Rda. de Azkue, 1, 48903 Baracaldo, Vizcaya, Spain','ChIJaayxsp1QTg0RekC451UAUV8',12,NULL,'Torneo Euskal Encounter 33, organizado con la colaboración de la Guarida.\r\n\r\nSe jugara en la Opengune de la Euskal Encounter. En el Bilbao Exhibition Center\r\n\r\nTorneo con rondas a determinar dependiendo de la inscripción, con un mínimo de 3 rondas\r\n\r\nRondas de dos partidas a 70 minutos, con partida de Corp y Runner\r\n\r\nFormato Estandar con Ban List 25.04',1,1,0,42048,1,'elev',1,'2025-06-07 05:17:03','2025-12-07 20:10:43',NULL,4,43.290553,-2.989542,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,42048,'2025-07-25 17:18:21',0,'Europe/Madrid',118,'Top 8 tokens de click\r\nTop2 juego completo de tokens\r\nTop1 trofeo de La Guarida','16:00',35,0),(5002,'2025 Asia-Pacific Continental Championship','2025.08.16.','09:00 AWST','','','op@nullsignal.games','','','','',45,8,'Continental Championships are the next step up from the Megacities in the competitive season. They are competitive events so all players are welcome, but are expected to have a fair baseline understanding of the rules and the structure of an event. Deck lists will be required to enter.\r\n\r\nTickets are available on Eventbrite for those seeking prizes - however anyone may choose to participate without purchasing a ticket - they will just be ineligible for prizing. Purchase tickets here: [Eventbrite link](https://www.eventbrite.com/e/2025-continental-championships-tickets-1556852019299)\r\nTicket Sales close 15 minutes prior to the start of the event.\r\n\r\nPlayers can play in any number of Online Continentals and they are not in any way restricted by a player\'s location. The regions listed on are an indicator of the most suitable time zone for the events.\r\n\r\nThis event, the APAC Conts will begin at 9 am AWST. The number of rounds and the size of the Top Cut will be determined by the number of players, according to Organized Play Policies.\r\n\r\nThe event will be run through the [NSG Online Event Hub Discord](https://discord.gg/3EWpuTRNpk) . Details for decklist registration will be provided before the start of the event in the relevant announcement channel.',1,0,0,33530,1,'elev',9,'2025-07-02 04:02:43','2026-01-13 23:40:29',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,'2025.08.17.',33530,'2025-08-17 03:28:07',0,NULL,125,'','',35,1),(5004,'2025 Americas Continental Championship','2025.09.06.','10:00','','','op@nullsignal.games','','','','',91,16,'Continental Championships are the next step up from the Megacities in the competitive season. They are competitive events so all players are welcome, but are expected to have a fair baseline understanding of the rules and the structure of an event. Deck lists will be required to enter.\r\n\r\nTickets are available on Eventbrite for those seeking prizes - however anyone may choose to participate without purchasing a ticket - they will just be ineligible for prizing. Purchase tickets here: [Eventbrite link](https://www.eventbrite.com/e/2025-continental-championships-tickets-1556852019299)\r\nTicket Sales close 15 minutes prior to the start of the event.\r\n\r\nPlayers can play in any number of Online Continentals and they are not in any way restricted by a player\'s location. The regions listed on are an indicator of the most suitable time zone for the events.\r\n\r\nThis event, the Americas Conts will begin at 11 am CST. The number of rounds and the size of the Top Cut will be determined by the number of players, according to Organized Play Policies.\r\n\r\nThe event will be run through the [NSG Online Event Hub Discord](https://discord.gg/3EWpuTRNpk) . Details for decklist registration will be provided before the start of the event in the relevant announcement channel.',1,0,0,33530,1,'elev',9,'2025-07-02 04:06:51','2025-11-01 01:37:42',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,'2025.09.07.',33530,'2025-09-10 14:51:23',0,NULL,125,'','09:00',35,1),(5012,'Classic Metagames Premier League','2025.10.31.','','','','julia.larrea.montoya@protonmail.com or @larrea on discord','','','','',24,0,'## TL;DR: TEAM TOURNAMENT, HISTORIC METAGAMES, WEEKLY\r\n[INFO](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1aYF4kR_-XJRzc4bFYK0aXyjpu72N5tTf8yDVVhpvZCI/)\r\nThe CMPL is a tournament where teams of 3 players will play 4 weeks of double sided swiss divided among 3 historic formats. \r\nOne player will play Worlds 2025, one player will play Worlds 2019*, and one player will play Worlds 2015. One of the players is also the \"manager\" position, who is really just the point-of-contact for the team. Each team may have a substitute player if they think they will need one, however it is not mandatory \r\n### Sign up here\r\nWe\'re running the tournament with a limited size of 16 teams, so sign up as early as you can!\r\n[As a team]( https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1NrpSzpf2CvUv-CTedUIb6zFA6EQhXF21GED8hG9jWqM)\r\n[As a free agent](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1AJrGcSJ2tgxnJpWqEwKJS_83MhZk89WOWX7y4Fgc8F0/)\r\n#### If you played in the Elevation Online Swiss League you might know these two:\r\nPlayers are not locked into decks for the tournament. You may swap identities and decklists for any reason\r\nPlayers must submit replays of their played games.\r\n\r\n#### Activity Rules\r\nTODO activity rules will come eventually\r\n\r\nMore information coming eventually. Ask @ larrea on discord or slack for more information\r\n### It\'s my first time playing an asynch or a team tournament.\r\nRead the section on the [INFO document](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1aYF4kR_-XJRzc4bFYK0aXyjpu72N5tTf8yDVVhpvZCI) \r\n\r\n## FAQ: \r\nQ:\"What do you mean 4-ish\".		\r\nA:\"We\'ll have a tiebreaker round if necessary, instead of using SoS\"		\r\nQ:\"Do we need to do the Team Tournament thing of splitting factions between players?\r\nA:\"Absolutely no need to do that, plus it would get very hard to coordinate with the deck-swapping every round\"\r\nQ:\"What about prizes?\"\r\nA:\"I\'ll take care of that later.\"\r\nQ:\"Why is there an asterisk(*) in Worlds 2019?\r\nA: \"Liza Talking Thunder is banned\"\r\nQ:\"What will the top cut be like?\"\r\nA:\"During the top cut, each match will be three single-sided games, and the team with two or more wins takes it. Sides will be chosen randomly.',1,0,0,36566,1,'elev',12,'2025-07-11 12:43:08','2025-12-21 10:06:27',NULL,3,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,'2025.12.19.',36566,'2025-12-21 10:05:18',1,NULL,126,'TBD','',99999,1),(5019,'Sunday Startup: Weekly Netrunner @ The Haven Games',NULL,'14:00','United States','FL','business@thehaventabletop.com or 4079515822','Casselberry','','3385 S US Hwy 17 92 suite 269, Casselberry, FL 32707, USA','EjkzMzg1IFMgVVMgSHd5IDE3IDkyIHN1aXRlIDI2OSwgQ2Fzc2VsYmVycnksIEZMIDMyNzA3LCBVU0EiJRojChYKFAoSCblUGH7-beeIEfJF6lERDjFrEglzdWl0ZSAyNjk',NULL,NULL,'We host one of the only Netrunner events in Central Florida! Come join us and run casually! Entry is $5, gets you a snack and drink. Winner gets store credit, everyone gets promos!\r\n\r\nWe\'ll be running Startup for the time being, and work our way up into standard. \r\n\r\nWe are carrying product up to Elevation, and have pre-orders in for Vantage Point!',0,0,0,53466,1,'unknown',8,'2025-07-15 18:48:57','2026-01-18 18:19:58',NULL,0,28.678541,-81.334300,7,0,0,'',0,11,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'America/New_York',126,'','13:30',99999,0),(5029,'Let\'s see how dwarves run! -2024 CO H2-','2025.09.13.','11:00','Germany','','','Esslingen am Neckar','WürfelZwerg','Landolinsgasse 10, 73728 Esslingen am Neckar, Germany','ChIJRw5PQDLBmUcR93djfBJ-feY',11,0,'(Please see the english version below)\r\n>[ANMELDUNG](https://forms.gle/y7D4NNU6GX6pPhD86)\r\n\r\nLiebe Runner,\r\nich freue mich zu verkünden, dass der [WürfelZwerg](http://www.wuerfelzwerg.de/) am 13. September 2025 erneut seine Türen für ein famoses Netrunnertunier öffnen wird.\r\n\r\n![The Hobbit Dwarf running](https://78.media.tumblr.com/411d137ad9a87dee6da0bb9a6f37eb10/tumblr_nit9d02rF11qgzdhjo2_r1_500.gif)\r\n\r\nAufgrund der Räumlichkeiten sind wir leider auf 24 Personen beschränkt. Eine Anmeldung über diese Fomular ist daher Pflicht, sodass im Zweifel niemand umsonst anreist.\r\n>[ANMELDUNG](https://forms.gle/y7D4NNU6GX6pPhD86)\r\nBitte denkt daher auch daran, euch Abzumelden, solltet ihr nach eurer Anmeldung doch nicht kommen können.\r\n___\r\n!Startup-Tunier wird versuch zu einem späteren Zeitpunkt standalone auszurichten.!  \r\n_Aus der Stuttgarter Community kam zusätzlich der Wunsch nach einem Startup-Sidetunier. Sofern hier ausreichend Interesse besteht, findet das mit einem kleine Preispool ebenfalls statt. Bitte im Formular angeben. (sofern ich genügend Rückmeldungen erhalte, erstelle ich ein weitere Tunier hier auf ABR.)_\r\n___\r\n\r\nDie Anreise erfolgt via Zug über den Esslinger Bahnhof (RE oder S1 von Stuttgart) und einem 10min Fußmarsch in die Altstadt. Mit dem Auto am besten über die A8 oder A81/B10 von Norden kommend. Parken kann man im Parkhaus Neckarforum.\r\n\r\n> Adresse:\r\n>WürfelZwerg\r\n>Landolinsgasse 10\r\n>73728 Esslingen\r\n\r\nDie Anmeldegebühr beträgt für Standard je nach Teilnehmeranzahl 10-15€. Startup wird auf Spenden laufen. Geld über die Kosten des Preis-Kits hinaus gehen an die Location.\r\nDecklisten werden sehr gern auch via Mail entgegen genommen.\r\n\r\n>Angedachter Zeitplan (Startup je nach Zeitplan mit weniger Runden):\r\n>\r\n>10:30 - 11:00 letzter Aufbau/Anmeldung\r\n>11:00 - 11:45 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 1\r\n>11:50 - 12:35 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 2\r\n>12:40 - 13:25 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 3\r\n>13:25 - 14:15 Mittag\r\n>14:15 - 15:00 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 4\r\n>15:05 - 15:50 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 5\r\n>15:55 - 16:40 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 6\r\n>16:50 - XX:XX Top Cut\r\n\r\nPascal - Virulentz\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nDear Runners,\r\n\r\nI am pleased to announce that the [WürfelZwerg (\'DiceDwarve\')](http://www.wuerfelzwerg.de/) will open its doors for an exciting Netrunner tournament again at the 13th September 2025.\r\n\r\nDue to location restricitons we are limited to 24 persons. Therefor it is mandatory to give notice via the google form to claim your spot and to prevent people traveling without a seat available.\r\n>[ANMELDUNG](https://forms.gle/y7D4NNU6GX6pPhD86)\r\nAdditionally I would like you to inform me, if you are no longer able to come to free the spot.\r\n\r\n___\r\n!We will plan a seperate startup tournament somewhere in the future.!  \r\n_Out of the Stuttgart Community, there was also the request to have a small Startup side tournament for newer players. If you are interested, please let me know in the form and I will arange it with a small price pool. (If it happens, I will create a seperate tournament on ABR)_\r\n___\r\n\r\nArrival via train is possible with the RE or the S1 to Esslingen Station and a short 10min walk through the city. Arrival by car can be done via the A8 or A81/B10 from the north. Parking is possible at the NeckarForum parking garage.\r\n\r\n>Address:\r\n>WürfelZwerg\r\n>Landolinsgasse 10\r\n>73728 Esslingen\r\n\r\nFeel free to send your decklist via mail.\r\nEntry fee for Standard will be dependent on participation 10-15€. Startup on a donation basis. Money beyond the price kit costs will go to the location.\r\n\r\n>Schedule (for Startup we may have less that 6 rounds):\r\n\r\n>\r\n>10:30 - 11:00 letzter Aufbau/Anmeldung\r\n>11:00 - 11:45 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 1\r\n>11:50 - 12:35 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 2\r\n>12:40 - 13:25 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 3\r\n>13:25 - 14:15 Lunch\r\n>14:15 - 15:00 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 4\r\n>15:05 - 15:50 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 5\r\n>15:55 - 16:40 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 6\r\n>16:50 - XX:XX Top Cut\r\n\r\nPascal - Virulentz',1,1,0,13592,1,'elev',11,'2025-07-20 11:17:52','2026-01-30 10:48:37',NULL,4,48.742059,9.310677,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,13592,'2025-09-14 15:10:02',0,'Europe/Berlin',108,'Former GNK cards','10:30',35,0),(5031,'Central Coast Netrunners Invitational','2025.11.02.','10:00','Australia','','ivan.kent00@gmail.com','Gosford','','','ChIJcQ2a1GbMcmsRoNkyFmh9AQU',8,0,'![Image][1]\r\n\r\nCentral Coast Netrunners Invitational 2025\r\n\r\nPrizes to be based on CTK H2 2025\r\n\r\nRegister at Cobra - [Register Here][2]\r\n\r\nEntry Ticket: $15 PayID: 0418 417749\r\n\r\nEntry also gives you 2 day pass to Coast Con 2025 at same venue, so you can game all day Saturday with a wide range of board games, followed by a dish of Netrunner on Sunday - come for the weekend.\r\n\r\nFurther, [Coast Con 2025][3] is a three day event, if you want to attend on Friday as well, contact me on discord (i am the gull) to confirm ticket price to include Friday.\r\n\r\nPrizes to be based on CTK H2 2025\r\n\r\n[1]: https://kentlawgroup.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/58c0a823-bada-46d2-b394-dd904104f9f2.jpg\r\n[2]: https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/pl7i\r\n[3]: https://www.lovecentralcoast.com/events/coastcon-2025',1,1,0,50345,1,'elev',11,'2025-07-21 00:37:26','2025-11-02 08:03:08',NULL,4,-33.426667,151.341667,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,50345,'2025-11-02 08:03:08',0,'Australia/Sydney',NULL,'','09:00',37,0),(5038,'Atomic Empire August 2025 League','2025.08.06.','','United States','NC','','Durham','Atomic Empire','3400 Westgate Dr #14b, Durham, NC 27707, USA','ChIJqTY1YFfmrIkRPRh89ogVgvY',NULL,NULL,'https://www.atomicempire.com/Store/Event/7113',0,0,0,39569,1,'elev',12,'2025-07-22 13:49:38','2025-12-29 19:35:33','2025-12-29 19:35:33',0,35.965814,-78.962901,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'America/New_York',126,'','',35,0),(5047,'Netrunner gaming at Koblenz','2025.12.06.','17:00','Germany','','weinschwaermer@web.de','Koblenz','Restaurant OM','Bechelstraße 23, 56073 Koblenz, Germany','ChIJtaZ6M01jvkcRdRJLQSNCLng',NULL,NULL,'On Saturday December 6th, starting at 17, we will play some Netrunner at Restaurant OM in Koblenz.\r\nWe are currently three players, a fourth player is highly welcome.\r\nSanta Claus will bring a promo card for every player: Seamless Launch, Peace in our Time, Popup-Window or Dreamnet.',0,0,0,19089,1,'elev',8,'2025-07-28 18:30:55','2025-12-02 21:09:40',NULL,0,50.361477,7.581464,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'Europe/Berlin',NULL,'','17:00',37,0),(5052,'Bristol September GNK (evening)','2025.09.09.','18:00','United Kingdom','','nicky3.0 on discord','Bristol','Sparks Bristol','78 Broadmead, Bristol BS1 3DS, UK','ChIJA6t8y6-PcUgRiCU-D6bdM9M',13,NULL,'Tuesday evening casual tournament at Sparks Bristol! \r\n\r\nAiming to start Round 1 at 6pm, to fit in 5 rounds of Single Sided Swiss, with no top cut. Finish approx 10pm. Numbers are limited to 16 maximum.\r\n\r\nBanlist will be the current standard banlist on the day of the event (abr won\'t let me choose that one since it\'s new). Decklists are not mandatory. This tournament is *casual level*.\r\n\r\nSparks isn\'t open to the public on Tuesdays, so instead of the shop entrances you\'ll need to use the *Artist Entrance* on Broadmead (very near big bao noodle stall, opposite shipley\'s bingo). Someone will be by the entrance to direct you in and there will be signs saying \"netrunner!\" No parking at the venue, but it\'s very near the Galleries Car Park in central Bristol. Also very accessible by bus, or 20 minutes walk from Temple Meads Station.\r\n\r\nPlease be in touch if you have access needs e.g. elevator, or if you\'ll need extra time in rounds.\r\n\r\nPrizes will be from the 2025 Q3 Game Night Kit, plus bonus participation dips into the prize vault... First place prize will be a set of 4 Borealis Cycle Corp IDs by Dimik and Emilio Rodríguez - (Pictured on full-art no-text side: Pravdivost, Ob, Issuaq, Thule) first released as prize support for 2024 worlds. \r\n\r\nCost of entry will be... £1!  Numbers are limited to 16 - Tickets here: [Link](https://www.tickettailor.com/events/nicky/1811429)\r\n\r\n ![Image](https://nicjanaway.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/corpborealis.jpg)',1,0,0,8492,1,'elev',11,'2025-08-02 14:05:54','2025-11-10 12:17:50',NULL,4,51.458085,-2.590739,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,8492,'2025-09-09 20:50:18',0,'Europe/London',112,'First place prize will be a set of 4 Borealis Cycle Corp IDs (by Dimik and Emilio Rodríguez)! (Ob, Pravdivost, Issuaq, Thule)','17:30',35,0),(5053,'Bristol October GNK','2025.10.05.','11:30','United Kingdom','','nicky3.0 on discord','Bristol','Excelsior Games','51-53 Merchant St, Broadmead, Bristol BS1 3EE, UK','ChIJUQkIUU-PcUgRqm33VOi9gI8',9,NULL,'Fancy a bit of last-minute practise before worlds? Or just want to play some netrunner?\r\nCome to this Sunday casual tournament at Excelsior games! \r\n\r\nAiming to start Round 1 at 11:30am, 6 rounds of Single Sided Swiss only. Maximum capacity 24 players. Expected to finish around 5pm\r\n\r\nBanlist will be the current standard banlist on the day of the event which will probably be the upcoming pre-worlds banlist (expected to drop ~ Sep 17th) Decklists are not mandatory. This tournament is casual level.\r\n\r\nMain entrance of Excelsior is opposite tk maxx, we will be playing in the upstairs space. No parking at the venue, but it\'s very near the Galleries Car Park in central Bristol. Also very accessible by bus, or 20 minutes walk from Temple Meads Station.\r\n\r\nPrizes will be from the 2024 Q3 Game Night Kit, plus extras TBC. First prize will be a full set of gorgeous stained-glass System Gateway IDs, by Kalypso (double sided, with text and full art)\r\n\r\nCost of entry will be... £1! Tickets here: [Link](https://buytickets.at/nicky/1811431)\r\n\r\n![Image](https://nicjanaway.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/stained-glass.jpg)\r\n![Image](https://nullsignal.games/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/25q3gnk.png)',1,0,0,8492,1,'elev',11,'2025-08-02 14:13:47','2025-11-10 12:17:39',NULL,4,51.458278,-2.589720,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,8492,'2025-10-05 14:14:52',0,'Europe/London',126,'','11:00',35,0),(5084,'2025 World Championship','2025.10.17.','09:00','United Kingdom','','op@nullsignal.games','Edinburgh','Dovecot Studios','10 Infirmary St, Edinburgh EH1 1LT, UK','ChIJSTMazoXHh0gRVQEMYCEQ46w',361,16,'# **2025 Null Signal Games World Championship**\r\n## **WEEKEND SCHEDULE**\r\n**Friday, 17th of October:** Crown of Servers Team Tournament and the Cosplay Contest\r\n**Saturday, 18th of October:** Standard World Tournament Day 1\r\n**Sunday, 19th of October:** Standard World Tournament Day 2, Top Cut, Eternal side event and Startup side event.\r\n**All weekend long:** Community organized Side events\r\n\r\n## [Ticket Purchase Link](https://www.eventbrite.com/e/2025-netrunner-worlds-tickets-1257515475639)\r\n\r\nMore details on schedule & prizing over the next few weeks.\r\n\r\nWelcome to the 2025 Netrunner Worlds in Edinburgh! Get ready to immerse yourself in the thrilling world of Netrunner at this in-person event located at the beatiful Dovecot Studios. Join players from around the globe for intense matches, exciting tournaments, and the chance to showcase your skills. Whether you\'re a pro or new to the game, this event is welcome to all Netrunners.\r\n\r\n**Links**\r\n---------\r\n[**Eventbrite Ticket Purchasing Page**](https://www.eventbrite.com/e/2025-netrunner-worlds-tickets-1257515475639)\r\n[Worlds 2025 Discord Server](https://discord.gg/JmpUAsgwPW)\r\n[NSG Code of Conduct](https://nullsignal.games/about/code-of-conduct/)\r\n[NSG OP Policies & Floor Rules](https://nullsignal.games/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/NSG_Organized_Play_Policies.pdf)\r\n[NSG Standard Format](https://nullsignal.games/players/supported-formats/#standard)',1,0,0,33530,1,'elev',5,'2025-08-27 04:07:41','2025-11-03 11:42:18',NULL,4,55.948266,-3.184884,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,'2025.10.19.',33530,'2025-10-20 08:39:31',0,'Europe/London',NULL,'','08:00',35,0),(5085,'2025S4深网积分赛','2025.09.26.','','','','+8618815601325','','','','',60,16,'报名截止时间：2025年9月23日（周二）24时\r\n\r\n比赛开始时间：9月26日开始\r\n\r\n赛制：标准（Standard）\r\n\r\n禁卡表：25.10禁卡表（暂未公布）\r\n\r\n比赛地点：国服战网（play.sneakdoorbeta.net）\r\n\r\n比赛形式：双边瑞士轮+双败淘汰赛\r\n\r\n参赛费用：免费（不会获得积分）或20元（可获得深网积分），报名截止后统一二维码收款。\r\n\r\n深网积分：\r\n\r\n缴费参赛的玩家会根据最终名次获得深网积分（保底1分，即使中途退赛也会获得），积分根据参赛人数确定：\r\n\r\n16—24人：淘汰赛冠军计6分、2-4名\r\n\r\n计\r\n\r\n3分，瑞士轮5-8名\r\n\r\n计\r\n\r\n2分、9+名\r\n\r\n计\r\n\r\n1分；\r\n\r\n25—32人：淘汰赛冠军\r\n\r\n计\r\n\r\n9分、2-4名\r\n\r\n计\r\n\r\n6分、5-8名\r\n\r\n计\r\n\r\n3分，瑞士轮9-16名\r\n\r\n计\r\n\r\n2分、17+名获得1分；\r\n\r\n33—56人：淘汰赛冠军\r\n\r\n计\r\n\r\n12分、2-4名\r\n\r\n计\r\n\r\n6分、5-8名\r\n\r\n计\r\n\r\n3分，瑞士轮9-16名\r\n\r\n计\r\n\r\n2分、17+名\r\n\r\n计\r\n\r\n1分；\r\n\r\n57人以上：淘汰赛冠军\r\n\r\n计\r\n\r\n12分、2-4名\r\n\r\n计\r\n\r\n9分、5-8名\r\n\r\n计\r\n\r\n6分、9-16名\r\n\r\n计\r\n\r\n3分，瑞士轮17-32名\r\n\r\n计\r\n\r\n2分、33+名\r\n\r\n计\r\n\r\n1分。\r\n\r\n深网积分将会在每赛季后记录在深网补给池文档中，大家可随时查看自己的积分，积分赛季间不清空，累计达12分后可选择兑换实体深网异画，1分=1套。深网积分可以自由转赠他人。\r\n\r\n其他：\r\n\r\n1.若一周内无法参赛，则该轮自动判负（0-6），若2人均无法参赛，则按约和计算（3-3）。\r\n\r\n2.选手可中途自由退赛，和主办方说明即可，退赛不会影响瑞士轮轮数及深网积分。\r\n\r\n3.选手可中途参赛，但之前的分数为0，中途参赛不会影响瑞士轮轮数及深网积分。\r\n\r\n4.每轮打完后，选手可自行在cobra上填写成绩，也可以告知主办方后由主办方填写。\r\n\r\n5.欢迎热心玩家进行线上直播解说。',1,0,0,2412,1,'elev',12,'2025-08-27 08:09:22','2026-01-24 11:37:43',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,'2025.11.20.',2412,'2026-01-12 07:53:59',0,NULL,NULL,'深网异画，可用积分兑换。','',35,1),(5087,'Italian Crown of Servers 2025','2025.11.23.','10:00','Italy','','','Milano','La Casa dei Giochi','Via Sant\'Uguzzone, 8, 20126 Milano MI, Italy','ChIJ1-4BBWjHhkcRvEJbo4-4s3Y',8,NULL,'Seconda edizione dell\' Italian Crown of Servers!\r\nQuesta volta a Milano presso la casa dei giochi\r\nDomenica 23 novembre 2025\r\n\r\nATTENZIONE: Dal momento che la **nuova banlist** sarà rilasciata lunedì 17 novembre, giocheremo il CoS con la NUOVA banlist già attiva (dato che si tratta di un torneo non competitivo).\r\n\r\nLe squadre devono essere formate da 3 player, ogni squadra dovrà giocare tutte fazioni diverse, a scelta fra le 4 corp, i 3 runner principali e per i veri eroi sono valide anche le ID neutrali da ambo i lati. Si giocheranno 5 turni di svizzera double sided, senza top, e durante ogni incontro, ogni giocatore affronterà un singolo componente del team avversario: si giocheranno pertanto 3 partite in contemporanea, per un totale di 6 game a turno. I membri di ogni team possono consultarsi ed aiutarsi fra di loro durante le partite.\r\nOgni singolo game vale 3 punti in caso di vittoria (anche in caso di vittoria a tempo), 1 punto in caso di pareggio a tempo e alla fine del torneo il team con più punti sarà il vincitore e alzerà al cielo la coppa dell’Italian CoS!\r\nIl formato sarà quello standard e i mazzi dovranno essere legali secondo l\'ultima banlist in vigore.\r\nPremi per tutt*, ogni squadra riceverà qualcosa e la scelta verrà fatta in ordine di classifica finale.\r\nIscrizione: 10€ a persona\r\n\r\nOrari di massima:\r\nOre 9.30-10.00 iscrizione\r\nOre 10.00-12.30 primi 2 turni di svizzera\r\nOre 12.30-14.00 pranzo\r\nDalle 14.00 in poi ultimi turni di svizzera\r\nA seguire cena tutti insieme per chi volesse',1,0,0,34885,1,'elev',10,'2025-09-02 04:06:16','2025-11-24 13:14:23',NULL,4,45.520997,9.226088,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,34885,'2025-11-24 09:12:33',1,'Europe/Rome',NULL,'**PREMI DEL TORNEO**\r\n\r\nTutti i partecipanti otterranno una **Magdalene Keino-Chemutai** Alt Art by Claudia Pintore (esclusivo per questo evento)\r\n\r\nA fine torneo le squadre in ordine di piazzamento sceglieranno un set di premi tra i seguenti:\r\n- 9x **Sting!** by Scott Uminga (premio esclusivo del torneo continentale americano 2025)\r\n- 9x **Bravado** “Neon Static” by Adam S. Doyle\r\n- 9x **Self Modifying Code** by Cat Shen (Canadian Nationals 2023)\r\n- 9x **Scatter Field** by Watzlav (Brno Megacity 2025)\r\n- 9x **Akhet** (Swiss Nationals 2023)\r\n- Set misto *Montreal* composto da 3x **Petty Cash** by Laurent Duhamel (premio esclusivo del torneo continentale americano 2025) + 3x **Transfer of Wealth** by Adam S. Doyle (premio esclusivo del torneo continentale americano 2025) + 3x **Finality** FOIL Alt Art\r\n- Set misto *Edimburgo1* composto da 3x **Byte** FOIL full art by Cat Shen (Torneo Mondiale 2025) + 1x **Nebula** LENTICOLARE FOIL by PiCat + 3x **Clean Gateway** \"S.C.R.U.B.S.\" by Brindelmold\r\n- Set misto *Edimburgo2* composto da 3x **Daniela Jorge Inácio** by Amora Bettany + 3x **Arruaceiras Crew** by lenney.xyz + 1x **Thule Subsea** by EllesarEllie\r\n\r\nInfine il giocatore con il miglior punteggio di ogni fazione otterrà un **megnete personalizzato** con una grafica ad hoc per questo evento (max 1 magnete a giocatore)','09:30',0,0),(5094,'Run the Rhine (Beginner friendly)','2025.11.09.','11:00','Germany','','contact me on Discord for any questions (Nick: Petersilio)','Düsseldorf','','Eulerstraße 50, 40477 Düsseldorf, Germany','ChIJsfZyq47JuEcRkv8aMlTtuk0',22,0,'✨ Join Us for a Casual & Welcoming Netrunner Tournament! ✨ (German Version below)\r\n\r\nWhether it’s your very first tournament or you’re coming back to Netrunner after a long break, this event is for you! We’re keeping things fun and friendly. Everyone is welcome!\r\n\r\nREGISTER ON COBRA (with you netrunnerdb account): https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/vqpn\r\nWe will use Cobra as a tournament web app to pair matches and where you can see your standings.\r\n\r\n💡 No cards? No problem!\r\nDon’t worry if you don’t own a Netrunner collection. You can simply print out a corp and a runner deck from NetrunnerDB.com\r\n (for example, this deck:\r\n https://netrunnerdb.com/en/decklist/5f8b734a-904b-4e1e-9f9c-dc02200fe3fe/a-damn-good-deal-1st-7th-10th-46th-and-50th-emea\r\n). Just click “Print and Play”, cut out the cards, and slip them into sleeves with any kind of playing card behind them that you have laying around. Quick, easy, and you are ready to run!\r\n\r\nBring some tokens/chips/bottle caps/stones or what ever you have lying around to use as tokens during a game or share with fellow players that brought enough!\r\n\r\nWe highly recommend to get acquainted with the general rules and mechanics of the game at your own speed before the tournament, an easy and free way is to practice with the learning AI that comes with a tutorial : https://chiriboga.sifnt.net.au/    \r\n\r\n🎲 More than Netrunner!\r\nWe’ll be joining the awesome folks at IIK during their weekly board game meetup, which means that in between rounds (or during the lunch break), you’ll have a chance to try out other board games as well.\r\n\r\n💰 Tickets: 10 € (cash or PayPal). Please consider PayPal if possible, as change will be limited.\r\n\r\n🕑 Tournament Details:\r\n\r\nLocation:  IIK Deutschland // Eulerstr. 50 Düsseldorf // Room F3\r\n\r\nFormat: Standard (using the Banlist releasing on 17.09.2025)\r\n\r\nRounds: 6 Single-Sided Swiss\r\n\r\nSchedule: Register Before 11:00 --> First round begins at 11:00 → lunch break after two rounds at around 13:00 until 14:00 → 4 rounds --> Ending Ceremony at 18:00\r\n\r\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\n✨ Sei dabei beim Casual & Welcoming Netrunner Turnier! ✨\r\n\r\nEgal, ob es dein allererstes Turnier ist oder du nach einer längeren Pause wieder in Netrunner einsteigen möchtest – dieses Event ist genau das Richtige für dich! Wir halten es locker, spaßig und freundlich. Alle sind willkommen!\r\n\r\nREGISTRIERE DICH AUF COBRA (mit deinem NetrunnerDB-Konto): https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/vqpn\r\n\r\nWir verwenden Cobra als Turnier-Web-App, um die Tunierspiel-Paarungen zu erstellen und damit du deine Platzierungen einsehen kannst.\r\n\r\n💡 Keine Karten? Kein Problem!\r\nMach dir keine Sorgen, wenn du keine eigene Netrunner-Sammlung hast. Du kannst dir einfach ein Corp- und ein Runner-Deck von NetrunnerDB.com\r\n ausdrucken (zum Beispiel dieses Deck  https://netrunnerdb.com/en/decklist/5f8b734a-904b-4e1e-9f9c-dc02200fe3fe/a-damn-good-deal-1st-7th-10th-46th-and-50th-emea\r\n). Klicke einfach auf „Print and Play“, schneide die Karten aus und stecke sie in Hüllen mit beliebigen Spielkarten als Rückseite. Schnell gemacht und schon bist du startklar!\r\n\r\nBringt bitte ein paar Spielsteine, Chips, Kronkorken, Steine oder sonstige Kleinigkeiten mit, die ihr gerade da habt, um sie während des Spiels als Marker zu verwenden oder teilt mit Mitspielern, die ausreichend Material dabeihaben!\r\n\r\nWir empfehlen euch außerdem, euch schon vor dem Turnier in Ruhe mit den allgemeinen Regeln und Spielmechaniken vertraut zu machen. Eine einfache und kostenlose Möglichkeit ist das Üben mit der Lern-KI +Tutorial: https://chiriboga.sifnt.net.au/\r\n\r\n🎲 Mehr als nur Netrunner!\r\nWir schließen uns den großartigen Leuten vom IIK bei ihrem wöchentlichen Brettspieltreffen an. Das bedeutet: Zwischen den Runden (oder in der Mittagspause) hast du die Möglichkeit, einige andere Brettspiele auszuprobieren.\r\n\r\n💰 Tickets: 10 € (bar oder per PayPal). Bitte nach Möglichkeit PayPal nutzen, da Wechselgeld nur begrenzt vorhanden ist.\r\n\r\n🕑 Turnier-Details:\r\n\r\nOrt:  IIK Deutschland // Eulerstr. 50 Düsseldorf // Raum F3\r\n\r\nFormat: Standard (mit der am 17.09.2025 erscheinenden Banlist)\r\n\r\nRunden: 6 Single-Sided Swiss\r\n\r\nAnmeldung vor 11:00 Uhr --> Erste Runde beginnt um 11:00 Uhr → Mittagspause nach zwei Runden von ca. 13:00 bis 14:00 Uhr → 4 Runden --> Abschlusszeremonie um 18:00 Uhr',1,0,0,50189,1,'elev',1,'2025-09-11 11:40:45','2025-11-30 11:52:04',NULL,4,51.239992,6.787083,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,50189,'2025-11-09 17:26:31',0,'Europe/Berlin',126,'2x Precision Design by Manuel R.\r\n2x AU Co. by Manuel R.\r\n2x Magdalene by Manuel R.\r\n2x Esâ Afontov by Manuel R.\r\n2x Synapse Global by ElessarEllie\r\n2x René \"Loup\" Arcemont by ElessarEllie\r\n6x Rising Tide by ElessarEllie\r\n6x Flyswatter by Lunari\r\n6x Azimat by Lunari\r\n6x Regolith Mining License by monde\r\n6x Swift by monde\r\n6x Window of Opportunity by HelabellaArt\r\n6x Botulus by Cat Shen (NSG), edit by Wentagon\r\n6x Audrey v2 by Júlio Roca (NSG), edit by Wentagon\r\n6x Spin Doctor by David Lei (NSG)\r\n6x Steelskin Scarring by Elliott Birt (NSG)','10:30',35,0),(5097,'Barcelona\'s Elevator (Q3 2025 GNK)','2025.10.04.','10:30','Spain','','netrunnerbcn@proton.me','Barcelona','inGenio BCN Games','Pg. de St. Joan, 16, L\'Eixample, 08010 Barcelona, Spain','ChIJs4AmnOSipBIRDhSJNlGVYWc',9,0,'Haremos un torneo casual en inGenio Barcelona Games, el 04/10/2025, a las 10:30. El precio son 2,5€ y haremos 3 o 4 partidas según el tiempo, una partida por ronda. Hay que traer dos mazos, uno de runner y uno de corp, y registrarse aquí: https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/tournaments/4168/info\r\nPara cualquier duda contactad a netrunnerbcn@proton.me\r\nUsaremos la ban list más reciente que saldrá en septiembre, si no la anterior. El formato será de Standard, y se intentará que todo el mundo reciba cartas del kit.\r\n\r\nResumen:\r\n\r\n# Torneo Netrunner Casual Q3 2025 “Barcelona’s Elevator” – inGenio Barcelona\r\n\r\n**Fecha: 04/10/2025**\r\n\r\n\r\n**Lugar: Tienda inGenio Barcelona**\r\n\r\n**Coste de inscripción: 2,5€**\r\n\r\n**Hora de entrada: 10:30**\r\n\r\n**Hora de final: entre 13:30 y 14:30**\r\n\r\n**Enlace de registro: [Enlace](https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/ojfy)**\r\n\r\nCartas permitidas: Todas las del formato Standard, con la banlist más reciente (Si ha\r\nsalido la que se ha anunciado para el 17 de Septiembre, se usará esa, si no, usaremos la\r\nanterior).\r\n\r\nEstructura del torneo:\r\nSe jugarán 3 partidas, en rondas de 45 minutos, en cada una se decidirá de forma\r\naleatoria si se juega del bando de Corp o de Runner. Se intentará que lo decida la\r\naplicación Cobra. Si no funciona, se lanzará una moneda para elegir bando.\r\nRecepción: 10:30\r\nComienzo 1ª ronda: 10:50\r\nComienzo 2ª ronda: 11:35\r\nComienzo 3ª ronda: 12:20\r\nDespués de la 3ª ronda, se hará la entrega de premios y se podrá jugar una ronda más,\r\nque no contará para los premios, entre los jugadores que quieran.\r\nAl finalizar cada ronda es importante subir el resultado a Cobra.\r\nTodas las partidas usarán las reglas más actualizadas de Null Signal Games, que se\r\npueden consultar en su web https://nullsignal.games/rules/comp-rules/\r\nSe pueden usar proxies, y todos los mazos deben ir enfundados en fundas opacas que no\r\npermitan distinguir el dorso de la carta.\r\nCualquier detalle no especificado en este documento lo resolverá el organizador.\r\n\r\nPremios:\r\nSi el número de jugadores no es mayor al esperado, todos los asistentes al torneo\r\nrecibirán 3 copias de la carta Charlotte Caçador (Ilustrada por Marion Luiz) en su versión\r\npromocional del Q3 2025 Game Night Kit.\r\nEn función del número de jugadores, se repartirán copias de la carta Alarm Clock\r\n(Ilustrada por Elizaveta Sokolova) en su versión promocional del Q3 2025 Game Night Kit\r\nlo más equitativamente posible. En caso de que no todos los jugadores puedan recibir 3\r\ncopias, las sobrantes se repartirán a criterio del organizador, teniendo en cuenta que los\r\njugadores mejor clasificados tendrán más posibilidades de recibir más copias, y se\r\nintentará que al menos una vaya a sorteo para que todos tengan posibilidades de recibir\r\ncartas.\r\n\r\nNormas del local:\r\nNo se pueden entrar consumiciones de fuera a no ser que sea agua\r\n\r\nEl organizador recibe un playset de cada carta del GNK.',1,0,0,54170,1,'elev',1,'2025-09-12 06:16:11','2026-01-24 11:37:54',NULL,4,41.392339,2.179333,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,54170,'2025-10-04 12:44:11',0,'Europe/Madrid',126,'','10:30',35,0),(5103,'WORLDS-ish // Perth, Western Australia','2025.10.18.','11:00','Australia','','@DC.Abstracted or @SlobberMcGee on Discord','Cannington','Good Games Cannington','21 Liege St, Cannington WA 6107, Australia','ChIJfUL8MdO9MioROkg5k6D0roU',12,0,'WORLDS-ish // A Netrunner Worlds 2025 Companion Event.\r\n\r\nWhile the best players in the world battle it out in Edinburgh, join us for WORLDS-ish, a Netrunner Worlds 2025 Companion event in Perth, Western Australia on Saturday October 18th. \r\n\r\nThis event will be Start Up format (https://nullsignal.games/players/supported-formats/#startup) and run as Double Sided Swiss. (You\'ll play both your Runner and Corp decks in 65-70 Minutes).\r\n\r\nThis event is open to everyone who would like to come down and play, From Newbies to Seasoned players. \r\n\r\nGot questions? Hit up @DC.Abstracted or @SlobberMcGee on Discord or join the Netrunner ANZ Discord and talk to us in #Perth.',1,0,0,36526,1,'elev',6,'2025-09-15 06:48:10','2025-11-07 08:02:29',NULL,0,-32.023611,115.938889,NULL,0,0,'',0,11,NULL,41847,'2025-11-07 08:02:29',0,'Australia/Perth',108,'','10:30',35,0),(5108,'NANPC Philadelphia - You Last World Prep Chance!','2025.10.04.','11:00','United States','PA','sebastiano.debona@gmail.com','Philadelphia','Redcap\'s Corner','3850 Lancaster Ave, Philadelphia, PA 19104, USA','ChIJt_84DvfGxokR2PTzGnW5FlI',12,3,'![NANPClogo](https://nanpc.games/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/nanpc-logo.png)\r\n\r\nPrepping for [Worlds](https://nullsignal.games/blog/2025-world-championship-prizing-side-events/)? Then this is your chance! Just looking for a good time? This is the place.\r\n\r\n**[Link to Cobra for tournament registration and Pairings](https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/tournaments/4229)**\r\n\r\nJoin us for the penultimate stop of the [North American Netrunner Player Circuit](https://nanpc.games/) to claim your spot on the beanstalk, get you reps in for Worlds, or just enjoy some Netrunner games among friends.\r\n\r\nThe tournament will be played using the Standard format, and the [**latest 25.10 banlist**](https://nullsignal.games/blog/standard-ban-list-25-10/).\r\n\r\nThis is a **one day** event, played as a single-sided Swiss, with a 45\' round timer. Registration starts at 10AM, 1st round starts at 11AM.\r\n\r\n**Entry fee: 15USD**\r\nPre-register [using this link](https://redcapscorner.com/products/netrunner-north-american-netrunner-player-circuit-ticket?ticket=netrunner-north-american-netrunner-player-circuit-ticket).\r\n\r\nWhile the top cut is on the way, we\'ll have a cube going for folks who haven\'t had enough Netrunner for the day.\r\n\r\nThe event is hosted by Mutually Assured Construction.',1,0,0,38273,1,'elev',15,'2025-09-18 10:00:23','2025-11-22 13:50:58',NULL,4,39.961333,-75.199209,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,38273,'2025-11-17 12:45:02',0,'America/New_York',NULL,'NANPC prizes (NANPC dice, Charlotte Caçador) + Philly special commissioned art!\r\n\r\nThe winner will take home a **custom playmat** to celebrate the victory. A second custom playmat will be given out to the first player to achieve a certain goal...we\'ll reveal it on the day!\r\n\r\nIn addition, our very own Elliott/monkeypanls has stepped up production of some slick tokens (design by [Luuke Lute](https://www.printables.com/model/1304255-netrunner-token-set)). A lot of older prize support (alt arts, cardboard deck boxes, tokens) will be available as well!\r\n\r\n![dice](https://i.imgur.com/OseH5cI.png)\r\n![charlotte](https://i.imgur.com/INt9wfF.png)\r\n![reaper](https://imgur.com/Ko1bAcb.png)\r\n![tokens](https://imgur.com/uHfJqQM.jpg)','10:00',35,0),(5113,'Freaky Friday','2025.11.01.','10:30','Australia','','@sohum','Victoria','','','ChIJ90260rVG1moRkM2MIXVWBAQ',5,0,'halloween was yesterday and it was FREAKY FRIDAY: every corp has woken up as a runner and every runner has woken up with a suit, a tie, and a golden parachute tied to their failing upwards. \r\n\r\n* All identities have been assigned new rules text and factions on the opposing side, as seen in [this google doc](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1dNbzQQjGeDeyKBmbHBQ-Yz4jejvqNA_8QlyOCKxPpeI/edit?usp=sharing)\r\n* Deck size and influence numbers stay the same; all runner identities have 0 link and 4 base MU\r\n* Standard card pool with the 25.10 Standard ban list.\r\n* Entry price: $10; prizing tbd 👻',1,0,0,12109,1,'elev',6,'2025-09-21 11:29:35','2025-11-07 20:40:17',NULL,4,-37.813628,144.963058,NULL,0,0,'',0,6,NULL,12109,'2025-11-07 20:37:22',0,'Australia/Melbourne',NULL,'','10:00',37,0),(5117,'[Online] 🌍 🌎 - Summer Showdown 2026 🌞 🦋','2026.05.23.','08:30','','','maninthem00n - on discord or mitm.netrunner@gmail.com','','','','',NULL,NULL,'Mark those calendars, hopefully you know the drill.',0,1,0,37550,1,'elev',1,'2025-09-26 02:46:32','2025-12-10 08:09:48',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'?','08:00',35,1),(5121,'Toulouse Casual Tournament H1 2025','2026.01.25.','10:30','France','','cebonamy@gmail.com / raphael.langella@gmail.com / @Yidaho and @ galehar on GLC and District99','Toulouse','','80 Chem. du Chapitre, 31100 Toulouse, France','ChIJD82Elc-7rhIRhrvcKP9G0oQ',11,0,'**Bienvenu à Toulouse pour notre premier Casual Tournament de l\'année !**\r\n\r\n**La salle** : Salle Gironis, 80 chemin du Chapitre, 31100 Toulouse\r\nLa salle est dans un park, vous pouvez trouver l\'entrée du park ici : [Maps link](https://maps.app.goo.gl/6QcFXnXiAWxc9JCX6) \r\nLa salle : [Maps link](https://maps.app.goo.gl/AYoJKdXMLPJduWaWA) \r\n\r\n**Date et horaires** : Le tournoi aura lieu le dimanche 25 janvier, on ouvrira la salle à partir de 9h45\r\n\r\n**Début des inscriptions** : 10:00\r\n**Fin des inscriptions** : 11:15\r\n**Début tour 1** : 10:30\r\n\r\n**Format**\r\nIl y aura 6 rondes de SSS (Single Sided Swiss), ou 7 s\'il y a vraiment beaucoup de joueurs, sans top cut.\r\n\r\nL\'event se tiendra en Standard et on utilisera la banlist la plus recente (à condition qu\'elle date de plus de 2 semaines avant la date du tournoi)\r\n\r\n**Prizing**\r\nOn aura un 2025 H1 Casual Tournament kit.\r\nOn aura aussi des alt art Orbital Superiority spécial Toulouse, designed by the wonderful Brindelmold. VF d\'un coté et texte en anglais de l\'autre. Ils seront distribués en prix de participation pour les personnes qui ne les ont pas encore eu\r\n\r\n**Prix d\'entrée**\r\n6€\r\n\r\n**Information d\'accès**\r\nIl est possible de venir à la salle en transport en commun, accessible depuis la L4 au départ de Basso Cambo à l\'arrêt \"Place des Glières\".\r\nOn peut aussi organiser du covoiturage\r\n\r\nLien discord de la communauté française netrunner : https://discord.gg/YumtxJcXWq',1,0,0,23926,1,'elev',11,'2025-09-28 17:37:09','2026-01-25 21:40:23',NULL,4,43.562981,1.413324,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,23926,'2026-01-25 16:58:38',0,'Europe/Paris',119,'','10:00',37,0),(5125,'NANPC Boston','2025.11.01.','11:00','United States','MA','kevinth on discord (@pockydude)','Cambridge','Pandemonium Books & Games','4 Pleasant St, Cambridge, MA 02139, USA','ChIJDSxvI1F344kRaexDR_nRPhI',16,4,'Join us for the final stop in the North American Netrunner Players Circuit!\r\n\r\nWe will be holding a Netrunner tournament at Pandemonium Books and Games on Saturday, November 1st. This will be a tournament in the Standard format, using the 25.10 (Worlds) banlist, and will consist of 6 or 7 rounds of single-sided Swiss games, followed by a cut to top 4.\r\n\r\nRegistration starts at 10AM, and round 1 will start at 11:00AM sharp.\r\n\r\nDecklists are not required. Proxies are legal and will be available on site (messaging the TO with proxy requests in advance will make this easier but is not absolutely required)\r\n\r\nOnline registration via the Pandemonium Events page is required ($5). Purchase those here: https://pandemoniumbooks.com/products/netrunner-tournament-nanpc-boston. An additional $10 to the TO will help defray costs of some of the cool prize support (to be announced).',1,0,0,14364,1,'elev',11,'2025-10-01 10:32:36','2025-12-22 02:13:16',NULL,4,42.366081,-71.105610,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,14364,'2025-11-02 02:06:46',0,'America/New_York',NULL,'','10:00',37,0),(5126,'Birkenhead Winter Casual Tournament','2025.11.08.','11:00','United Kingdom','','Sauc3 in discord','Birkenhead','Indigo','136 Bedford Rd, Birkenhead CH42 2AS, UK','ChIJkc3K-dcne0gRkTzlkkwmn6w',10,0,'**End of season? End of shmeason!**\r\n\r\nAs far as I’m concerned, Worlds is just the starting gun firing for all the CO kits that everyone bought and then never ran because they were too busy with districts/megas…\r\n\r\nTo that end, come on down to your friendly neighbourhood cafe and play with all the secret deck tech that’s been revealed in Edinburgh! And fight for that last minute CBI invite…\r\n\r\nWe will be playing an appropriate number of Double Sided Swiss rounds, the correct format for a small casual event… IDs and 241s will be accepted but sneered at! 😅\r\n\r\n**Venue Information & Accessibility**\r\nIndigo is a neighbourhood cafe and events venue in Birkenhead. We are quickly and easily accessible from the centre of Liverpool, with trains running from Lime St and other central stations every 15 mins, arriving at Rock Ferry station just 3 mins up the road. For drivers, there is a free car park at the back of the venue (accessible from New Chester Road).\r\n\r\nIndigo\'s food offering will be available beforehand and during the lunch break, including all day breakfast, sandwiches, soups and more (with veggie and vegan options available) and we have a range of soft drinks as well as a fully licensed bar. We also have a well stocked board game cupboard, should you wish to hang out either before or after the event!\r\nMore info: https://g.co/kgs/VH1xm4x\r\n\r\nUnfortunately due to the venue space being located above the cafe, we will not be able to offer step-free access. There will be fixed seating available on request. All bathrooms are gender neutral.\r\n\r\nI may be able to host one or two people travelling from further afield, please get in touch if you\'d need a place to stay.',1,0,0,36390,1,'elev',11,'2025-10-03 11:53:33','2025-11-08 17:35:34',NULL,4,53.372886,-3.007949,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,36390,'2025-11-08 17:35:34',0,'Europe/London',108,'Lots of additional GNK and other goodies will be on offer, you will not go away empty handed, or just with stuff you already got from the Liverpool tournament!','10:30',37,0),(5132,'🔥 FireRL\'s Throwback Party 2025','2025.12.06.','11:00','United States','WA','colinrs90 | FireRL (on Discord)','Seattle','','','ChIJVTPokywQkFQRmtVEaUZlJRA',7,0,'# 🔥 ECG Throwback 💥\r\n\r\n*I.*\r\n*LOVE.*\r\n*THROWBACK.*\r\n\r\n# ❓ **WHAT IS THROWBACK (format)?**\r\n**Throwback = exactly the Standard Format, *plus* each of your decks may include 1 rotated card that was not banned when it rotated (this includes IDs).**\r\n\r\n# **Prizes:**\r\n- Raffling - Dragon IDs\r\n- Participation - Stoneship Chartroom\r\n- Placement - *TBA*\r\n\r\n# **The usual tournament details, etc:**\r\n- Location: Mox Boarding House *(Ballard)*\r\n- Participation is $10 *(for prizing)*\r\n- Tournament will be organized and ran through tournaments.nullsignal.games\r\n - Single-Sided Swiss\r\n - Lunch break after R3 estimated to be 1:15-2pm\r\n - Number of rounds is dependent on attendance, but planning on 6 plus top-4 cut\r\n\r\n__________\r\n\r\n\r\n# This event will be using the following banlist:\r\n\r\n**1) SBL 25.12 (for all current-Standard cards)**\r\n**2) A few added bans/restrictions (notated with \'❗️\'/\'‼️\')**\r\n**3) All rotated cards that were banned at the time they rotated (including all \'Currents\')...**\r\n\r\n**CORP:**\r\n - \"Clones are not People\"\r\n - 24/7 News Cycle\r\n - **❗️Accelerated Diagnostics**\r\n - **‼️ Astroscript Pilot Program (may include, but it\'s \'Limit 1 per deck)**\r\n - Brain Rewiring\r\n - Breached Dome\r\n - **❗️Breaking News**\r\n - Bryan Stinson\r\n - Cebebral Imaging\r\n - Clone Suffrage Movement\r\n - Death and Taxes\r\n - Defective Brainchips\r\n - Door to Door\r\n - Enforced Curfew\r\n - Estelle Moon\r\n - Formicary\r\n - Friends in High Places\r\n - Game Changer\r\n - Government Takeover\r\n - High-Profile Target\r\n - Hired Help\r\n - Housekeeping\r\n - Hunter Seeker\r\n - Jinteki: Potential Unleashed\r\n - Kakugo\r\n - Kill Switch\r\n - Mass Commercialization\r\n - Media Blitz\r\n - Mother Goddess\r\n - Mti Mwekundu\r\n - Mumbad City Hall\r\n - Museum of History\r\n - NAPD Contract\r\n - Obokata Protocol\r\n - Predictive Algorithm\r\n - Preemptive Action\r\n - Reconstruction Contract\r\n - Rolling Brownout\r\n - Scarcity of Resources\r\n - Sensie Actors Union\r\n - Service Outage\r\n - Shipment from Tennin\r\n - Skorpios\r\n - Slot Machine\r\n - SSL Endorsement\r\n - Surveillance Sweep\r\n - Titan Transnational\r\n - Tithonium\r\n - Violet Level Clearance\r\n - Whampoa Reclamation\r\n - Zealous Judge\r\n\r\n**RUNNNER:**\r\n - \"Freedom Through Equality\"\r\n - Aaron Marrón\r\n - **❗️ Aghora**\r\n - Another Day, Another Paycheck\r\n - Au Revoir\r\n - Blackmail\r\n - Bloo Moose\r\n - Clan Vengeance\r\n - Corporate \"Grant\"\r\n - Corporate Scandal\r\n - Crowdfunding\r\n - DDoS\r\n - Dorm Computer\r\n - Employee Strike\r\n - Film Critic\r\n - Gang Sign\r\n - Government Investigations\r\n - GPI Net Tap\r\n - Hacktivist Meeting\r\n - Interdiction\r\n - Itinerant Protesters\r\n - Kabonesa Wu\r\n - Knobkierie\r\n - Levy AR Lab Access\r\n - Liza Talking Thunder\r\n - Mars for Martians\r\n - PAD Tap\r\n - Power Tap\r\n - Rumor Mill\r\n - **❗️ Sadyojata**\r\n - Salvaged Vanadis Armory\r\n - Şifr\r\n - System Outage\r\n - System Seizure\r\n - Temüjin Contract\r\n - Traffic Jam\r\n - **❗️ Vamadeva**\r\n - Watch the World Burn\r\n - **‼️  Wireless Net Pavilion (may include, but it\'s \'Unique\')**',1,1,0,4990,1,'elev',6,'2025-10-08 03:03:21','2025-12-07 01:25:22',NULL,4,47.606139,-122.332848,NULL,0,0,'',0,6,NULL,4990,'2025-12-07 01:25:22',0,'America/Los_Angeles',NULL,'lots of prizes: raffle, participation, and placement prizing from yours truly!','10:00',37,0),(5134,'Causal Tournament beim Wilden Würfel-Wagnis','2025.12.06.','','Germany','','netrunner@of15-15.de oderr OF15-15 auf Discord','Aachen','','','ChIJHRmKsHyZwEcRT0QOC64Oo2M',5,0,'Im Rahmen der [W3: das Wilde Würfel-Wagnis der Oecher Meeples](https://www.oecher-meeples.org/w3-das-wilde-wuerfel-wagnis/) werde ich erst eine Erklärrunde und anschließend ein Turnier veranstalten. Ich werde versuchen, für neue Leute Decks zur Verfügung zu stellen, über Unterstützung dabei würde ich mich sehr freuen (gerne einfach melden). Ich plane aktuell mit 6 Runden SSS und genug Zeit pro Runde, werde mich aber am Tag selbst ggf an die Wünsche der Teilnehmenden anpassen. \r\n\r\nvorläufiger Zeitplan:\r\n`10:00`: Start Learn2Play\r\n`11:30`: Registrierung\r\n`12:00`: Turnierstart\r\n`13:30`: Mittagspause\r\n`14:00`: Runde 3\r\n`18:00`: Ende & Preisverteilung\r\n\r\nEs wird Spielmatten, Karten und noch mehr zu gewinnen geben.',1,0,0,34833,1,'elev',11,'2025-10-10 10:47:31','2025-12-20 12:04:46',NULL,4,50.775346,6.083887,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,34833,'2025-12-20 12:04:46',0,'Europe/Berlin',NULL,'','',37,0),(5136,'Startup CTK @ JWW\'s','2025.11.22.','12:00','United States','ND','','Fargo','JWW Sports Cards & Gaming','3902 13th Ave S #100, Fargo, ND 58103, USA','ChIJh8Vh7HvLyFIR-9z3YDfzZyI',9,0,'$15 dollar entry\r\nStartup Format\r\n6 rounds of Single Sided Swiss\r\n40 mins rounds\r\n\r\n\r\ntop 2: Trick Shot (illustrated by Ed Mattinian) playmat\r\ntop 4: Fermenter (illustrated by Toby Woodman) alternate art card\r\ntop 8: Angelique Garza Correa (illustrated by Olie Boldador) extended alt card\r\n\r\nTO Discretion:  Predictive Planogram (illustrated by Wyn Lacabra)',1,1,0,49460,1,'elev',11,'2025-10-12 00:44:08','2025-11-23 05:22:38',NULL,4,46.858429,-96.847709,NULL,0,0,'',0,11,NULL,49460,'2025-11-23 05:22:38',0,'America/Chicago',119,'There will be additional prizing for top three players and additional handouts for random players who did not place in the top 3!\r\n\r\nChoice of an Acrylic token, Esty Credit Set, or old GNK Playsets from available leftovers!','11:00',34,0),(5137,'Cornu-CODE-pia 🦃🤖 - NJ \"Casual Tournament\"','2025.11.16.','12:00','United States','NJ','@classicapple on Discord','Franklin Township','Gilded Raven Games','120 Cedar Grove Ln, Somerset, NJ 08873, USA','ChIJ5_71GWHBw4kRwXhQgLUnBrg',8,NULL,'Join us in Somerset NJ on the eve of the post-worlds banlist.\r\n\r\nThis is a casual tournament, but not a CT. Does that make sense? \r\n\r\n$5 entry payable to the store the day of the event, and every entrant is guaranteed a pull from our prize pool of alt arts.\r\n\r\nWe will play 5-6 rounds of Single-Sided Swiss with no top cut.\r\n\r\nCobra link: https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/tournaments/4315\r\n\r\nUpdate:\r\nSince this event isn\'t a \"real\" CT we\'re going to play with the format just a bit and try out an alternative mulligan rule.\r\n\r\n## The \"Gold\" Mulligan\r\n1. Both players draw 5 cards\r\n2. Corp mulligan:\r\n a. Corp chooses 0, 1, or 5\r\n b. Corp shuffles the chosen number of cards from their hand back into their deck\r\n c. Corp draws the chosen number of cards\r\n3. Runner mulligan:\r\n a. Runner chooses 0, 1, or 5\r\n b. Runner shuffles the chosen number of cards from their hand back into their deck\r\n c. Runner draws the chosen number of cards\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions please reach out to @classicapple on discord',1,0,0,16434,1,'elev',1,'2025-10-16 22:46:12','2025-11-17 02:21:06',NULL,4,40.521738,-74.520893,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,16434,'2025-11-17 01:37:53',0,'America/New_York',NULL,'','11:00',37,0),(5138,'SanSan South Eternal Jank','2025.11.08.','11:00','United States','CA','','Spring Valley','','','ChIJk0buB4NQ2YAR2nagpuMrlQ4',10,0,'Come on down and play some Eternal Jank! SanSanSouth discord:  [Link](https://discord.gg/E4p2bCd9g6) \r\n\r\nEvent will be hosted at my (chih) place. Contact me via discord for the address, everyone is welcome!\r\n\r\nWhat is Eternal Jank?\r\n\r\nWe\'ve got a bot in the SanSan South discord that will randomly assigned you an ID and three out-of-faction cards. You must play full playsets of those cards and, instead of your ID\'s given influence, you get 6 influence (you do not spend influence for your 3 randomly selected cards). All corps get spin doctor for free. Use !jank to get a selection of 3 random corp and 3 random runner rolls to choose from.\r\n\r\nDecks can use the eternal card pool except for the following bans: Top 25%  on [trash or busto](https://trash-or-busto.herokuapp.com/ranking). Anything that is currently banned in standard or eternal. Also, anything that is pointed in eternal is banned. We\'re going full jank here, folks. Anyone playing good decks will be ridiculed thoroughly.',1,0,0,1633,1,'elev',1,'2025-10-20 04:38:15','2025-11-09 19:50:06',NULL,0,32.744774,-116.998916,NULL,0,0,'',0,6,NULL,1633,'2025-11-09 19:50:06',0,'America/Los_Angeles',NULL,'','10:30',37,0),(5142,'Montreal Community \"GNK\"','2025.11.11.','18:00','Canada','','cscullen4640@gmail.com','Montréal','L\'Expédition','6571 Rue St-Hubert, Montréal, QC H2S 2M5, Canada','ChIJKxYya2kZyUwRmTCjKijcUrs',NULL,NULL,'**Subject to banlist change if a post-worlds banlist comes out in time to adapt to it**\r\n\r\n$5 entry fee. Let me know if entry fee will be a barrier for you. \r\n\r\n5 rounds SSS\r\n\r\nThis is a special version of our normal Netrunner GNK. Rather than a normal NSG kit, prizing will consist of an alt-art Steelskin Scarring illustrated by Montreal local artist Caj Wehrstedt, as well as a limited amount of custom faction symbol deckboxes.\r\n\r\nAs always, this is the most casual level of tournament. Bring your jank! Bring your friends! Everyone is welcome.\r\n\r\n![Image](https://i.etsystatic.com/55088468/r/il/01664d/7262830170/il_794xN.7262830170_ngkm.jpg)	\r\n\r\nThe Steelskin art will be given to all entrants.\r\nTop 4 will have a choice of their desired faction deckbox (to be delivered at some time after the even depending on on-hand quantity)',0,0,0,26646,1,'elev',1,'2025-10-21 17:09:16','2025-11-08 23:17:09','2025-11-08 23:17:09',0,45.536761,-73.604181,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'America/Toronto',NULL,'','17:00',37,0),(5145,'The post Worlds come down at Knightly Gaming','2025.11.22.','11:00','United Kingdom','','','Bathgate','Knightly Gaming','2-6 Hopetoun St, Bathgate EH48 4EU, UK','ChIJO13Vd_QOiEgRvALJ83sTnjI',16,0,'Update 18/11 - we will be using banlist as of 17/11, no false leads or dolls for you! \r\n\r\nFeeling the need to run some nets following Worlds? Come on down!\r\n\r\nWe\'ll be playing at Knightly Gaming in Bathgate, the venue has step-free access, gender neutral toilets and offers food (with vegetarian and vegan options). Fixed seating will be provided on request. \r\n\r\nThis will be a five-six round SSS tournament depending on numbers, no cut. NSG COC etc. in play. Prizing is a collection of goodies including the lovely Jakuza Orca mat, aubit tokens, Worlds 2025 Day 2 alts and more! Double dips for any first time players.\r\n\r\nPlayers can pay their store charge (£7.5 including table, meal and drink), no charge for the tournament.',1,0,0,9326,1,'elev',6,'2025-10-22 09:43:54','2025-12-02 09:22:01',NULL,4,55.902664,-3.641822,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,9326,'2025-12-02 09:22:01',0,'Europe/London',NULL,'','10:30',37,0),(5146,'Ligue asynchrone Toulouse Q4 2025','2025.11.01.','','France','','cebonamy@gmail.com / raphael.langella@gmail.com / @Yidaho and @ galehar on GLC and District99','Toulouse','','','ChIJ9eIpr3-8rhIRdLXdS_P05rU',8,0,'Ligue asynchrone IRL de Toulouse : Q4 2025\r\n\r\nL\'idée c\'est de faire les parties de la ligue les mercredis soirs lors des meet-ups, 1 round tous les 2 semaines.\r\n\r\nPossibilité de drop in / drop out selon les disponibilités. \r\n\r\n4 rounds en DSS (Double Sided Swiss) pour clôturer la ligue fin 2025 et en relancer une début 2026. Possibilité de changer ses decks entre les rounds.\r\n\r\nParticipation de 4€\r\nLien discord de la communauté française netrunner : https://discord.gg/YumtxJcXWq',1,0,0,23926,1,'elev',12,'2025-10-22 21:33:55','2026-02-02 08:22:29',NULL,4,43.587615,1.445885,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,23926,'2025-12-18 11:28:26',0,NULL,126,'','',37,0),(5148,'Whimsy Game Cafe November GNK','2025.11.08.','14:00','Philippines','','','Mandaluyong City','Whimsy Game Cafe','The Portal, Unit 14&15 Mayflower St, Greenfield District, Mandaluyong City, Metro Manila, Philippines','ChIJCxAKWQDJlzMR11GcpPenFHg',10,0,'Monthly GNK tourney at Whimsy Game Cafe',1,0,0,8431,1,'elev',1,'2025-10-23 13:15:05','2025-11-08 13:37:59',NULL,4,14.578823,121.053968,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,8431,'2025-11-08 13:37:59',0,NULL,118,'','13:00',37,0),(5150,'Standard AMT - November 9th (Americas)','2025.11.09.','','','','op@nullsignal.games','','','','',22,4,'![Accelerated Meta Test](https://alwaysberunning.net/photo/2677.png)\r\n\r\nThis is an Accelerated Meta Test in the **Standard** Format using **Single-Sided Swiss**, and is open to anyone who wants to play. Prizing for this event will be an Invite to the Circuit Breaker Invitational for the top finisher (or top 2 if we exceed 20 entrants).\r\n\r\nEvent is starting on 9am PST (UTC-8) November 9th  https://timee.io/20251109T1700?tl=Americas%20AMT\r\n\r\nWith registration closing and player meeting beginning *15 minutes beforehand*. \r\n\r\nThe event will be run through the [NSG Online Event Hub Discord](https://discord.gg/s9tWsq3sQP). Registration will open on Cobra at least an hour before event start. We anticipate this event being six rounds with a top 4 cut. \r\n\r\nThe event will be run on Jinteki.net.',1,0,0,33530,1,'elev',11,'2025-10-24 04:54:34','2025-11-11 00:51:36',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,33530,'2025-11-11 00:51:36',0,NULL,NULL,'','',37,1),(5151,'Standard AMT - November 22th (APAC)','2025.11.22.','','','','op@nullsignal.games','','','','',13,3,'![Accelerated Meta Test](https://alwaysberunning.net/photo/2677.png)\r\n\r\nThis is an Accelerated Meta Test in the **Standard** Format using **Single-Sided Swiss**, and is open to anyone who wants to play. Prizing for this event will be an Invite to the Circuit Breaker Invitational for the top finisher (or top 2 if we exceed 20 entrants).\r\n\r\nEvent is starting on 9am AWST (UTC+8) November 22th  https://timee.io/20251110T0100?tl=APAC%20AMT\r\n\r\nWith registration closing and player meeting beginning *15 minutes beforehand*. \r\n\r\nThe event will be run through the [NSG Online Event Hub Discord](https://discord.gg/s9tWsq3sQP). Registration will open on Cobra at least an hour before event start. We anticipate this event being six rounds with a top 4 cut. \r\n\r\nThe event will be run on Jinteki.net.',1,0,0,33530,1,'elev',11,'2025-10-24 04:56:31','2025-11-22 05:36:57',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,39105,'2025-11-22 05:36:57',0,NULL,NULL,'','',37,1),(5153,'Victoria Post-Worlds Showdown (Nov. 17 Banlist)','2025.11.22.','12:00','Canada','','Ghost Meat on Discord','Victoria','Interactivity Board Game Cafe','723 Yates St, Victoria, BC V8W 1L6, Canada','ChIJR0dqpZp0j1QRnRFrC1Kcg74',16,4,'Come celebrate the new Nov. 17th banlist with a Victoria tournament at Interactivity Board Game Cafe using the new SBL update (I will update this in the left column when it becomes available). \r\n\r\n*Note: False Lead and Matryoshka are BANNED for this tournament, as per the 25.12 SBL update.\r\n\r\nWe will do six rounds of Single-Sided Swiss, followed by a Top 4 Single-elimination cut (closed decklists), taking us until about 6:30-7 o’clock. There will be no scheduled lunch break during this time, but people can eat/snack/drink on the fly. \r\n\r\nThe top 6 players will each get a set of Alarm Clocks, and those placing in spots 1-5 will each get to choose a set of side event alt-arts from Worlds 2025, in descending order (1st place player gets first choice, and so on). All participants will get a MuslihaT alt-art from The Man in the Moon’s Worlds Showdown tournament, and the top 12 will get a set of Charlotte C’s. \r\n\r\nBrennan has an additional T-shirt bonus prize to add to the pot as well.\r\n\r\nEntry fee to cover prizes is $5 (to Dave), and the cafe charges a $7 stay and play fee on top of that. \r\n\r\nI’ve made a large dinner reservation for 7:30 at Cafe Malabar, which is super close to Pinhalla. Menu here: https://cafemalabar.ca/pdf/cm-menu.pdf',1,0,0,14280,1,'elev',1,'2025-10-26 21:38:32','2025-12-02 02:58:00',NULL,4,48.426053,-123.363865,NULL,0,0,'https://www.facebook.com/events/1713009219392656/?acontext=%7B%22event_action_history%22%3A[%7B%22extra_data%22%3A%22%22%2C%22mechanism%22%3A%22unknown%22%2C%22surface%22%3A%22group%22%7D%2C%7B%22extra_data%22%3A%22%22%2C%22mechanism%22%3A%22attachment%22',0,1,NULL,14280,'2025-11-23 19:21:41',0,NULL,126,'','11:45',0,0),(5154,'Netrunner at Spellenspektakel','2025.11.09.','13:00','Netherlands','','david_nys@msn.com','Utrecht','Kinepolis Jaarbeurs Utrecht','Jaarbeursboulevard 300, 3521 BC Utrecht, Netherlands','ChIJzWO_LWFvxkcR1Y7Gy5x3uIc',NULL,NULL,'Some of the Dutch Netrunner community will meet at Spellenspektakel, one of the biggest boardgame conventions in Europe. We\'ll play some Netrunner, have some fun and maybe even get some new folks into the game?\r\n\r\nThe location says online, but this is due to a bug in ABR. For exact location and time, contact cpt_nice via email or on Discord.',0,0,0,25691,1,'elev',8,'2025-10-27 11:11:51','2025-11-08 10:05:31',NULL,0,52.086218,5.104521,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'','13:00',37,0),(5155,'GNK @ Craving For A Game','2025.11.01.','10:00','','','sokkaanr@gmail.com','','','','',6,0,'**This is an event in Surrey BC. It is NOT online. The event is at Craving For A Game. Address is 10153 King George Blvd #2293, Surrey, BC V3T 2W1\r\n\r\nThe event will be from 10am to 2pm. We will play 4 or 5 rounds of single-sided swiss depending on whether we start on time. Note that there is no lunch break. We will likely go as a group for a late lunch at the food court after the event (optional).\r\n\r\nThis event has a player limit of 8. Please RSVP at the following link and await a confirmation message before attending.\r\n\r\nhttps://forms.gle/J9H24t5PQyiB2EpNA\r\n\r\nCost will be $10 per person, which includes store credit for the top 3 ($25, $10, $5). This may be adjusted according to turnout.\r\n\r\nDecklists are not required.',1,0,0,18976,1,'elev',1,'2025-10-28 05:05:53','2025-11-03 01:47:04',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,18976,'2025-11-03 01:46:42',1,NULL,110,'','10:00',37,1),(5156,'🎄Boat City: Christmas Extravaganza','2025.12.06.','11:30','Poland','','marcelina.m.witkowska@gmail.com','Łódź','Pub Goblin - Planszówki z Pubem','Wschodnia 74, 90-266 Łódź, Poland','ChIJj14H5xTLG0cRRBAZ1A34buk',24,4,'## 🎄 Boat City: Christmas Extravaganza🎄\r\nczyli łódzkie świąteczne granie w Netrunnera!\r\n\r\n![](https://i.ibb.co/M59HvvRw/e6984f3d-f649-4b2e-9831-ffdd27d874ff-1.jpg)\r\n\r\n***\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nGdy dni robią się krótsze, a śnieg zaczyna sypać, zapraszamy Was do Boat City — miejsca, gdzie Runnerzy grzeją się przy herbacie, dzielą pierniczkami i próbują _przy okazji_ zdobyć ostatnią w Polsce zaproszkę na CBI.\r\n\r\n*Zagramy*: 7 rund SSS. \r\n*Gdzie*: **Pub Goblin, ul. Wschodnia 74, Łódź** \r\n*Wpisowe*: 40 zł gotówką lub blikiem.\r\n\r\n**Banlista: 25.12**\r\n\r\nTen turniej to jednak coś więcej niż tylko standardowe granie:\r\n\r\nOprócz tradycyjnych nagród pojawią się też prezenty — wyjątkowe upominki od samego Mikołaja:)\r\n\r\n\r\n## 🎁  od Mikołaja\r\n\r\n\r\nNa pamiątkę kosmicznego wyczynu  Vetiego, Mikołaj przywiózł specjalne nagrody prosto z Jinteki:\r\n\r\n[ Cloud Eater **foil** alt art](https://netrunnercards.net/cdn/shop/files/Cloud_Eater_v3_for_web.png?v=1753649507&width=990) dla pierwszego, piątego i dziewiątego miejsca.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nA do tego – Vetiego czeka jeszcze jedno wyzwanie.\r\nTurniej rozpocznie z symboliczną koroną.\r\nOd tej pory obowiązuje zasada:\r\n\r\nJeśli pokonasz Króla,  przejmujesz koronę.\r\nZostaniesz pokonany = korona idzie dalej.\r\nGracz który zostanie z koroną na koniec turnieju dostanie prezent. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### NOWOŚĆ ✨TYLKO W BOAT CITY   \r\n\r\n\r\nKategoria: Netrunner Home DecorTM\r\n\r\nczyli… [**śfieczki**](https://i.ibb.co/JjwBkmYF/download.jpg) jako nagroda turniejowa. Tak właśnie.\r\n\r\n>  *Delikatny aromat grzanego wina z cynamonem, z nutą pomarańczy i goździka*\r\n\r\nCoś, co mogłoby  robić nastrój podczas kolacji wigilijnej u babci. \r\n\r\nZ wierzchu – elegancki słoik. W środku – ciepło i świąteczny nastrój.\r\nAle wystarczy przeczytać etykietę, żeby wszystko wróciło na swoje miejsce.\r\n\r\nTo eksperymentalna nagroda, która nie miała prawa przejść.\r\nA jednak Zombiak wiedział o tym pomyśle i mnie nie powstrzymał.\r\nWięc teraz... zostaje tylko pytanie, kto wróci do domu ze świeczką. Każda z nich będzie przypisana do unikalnej kategorii którą ujawnimy w dniu turnieju.',1,0,0,44022,1,'elev',11,'2025-10-28 09:31:34','2025-12-06 16:53:21',NULL,4,51.771389,19.458767,NULL,0,0,'https://www.facebook.com/groups/netrunner.polska/',0,1,NULL,44022,'2025-12-06 16:53:20',0,NULL,119,'***\r\n\r\n\r\n*Participation prize*: Każdy gracz wybierze dwa playsety promek z łódzkiego skarbca. \r\n\r\n\r\n***\r\n\r\n**Każdy gracz który nigdy wcześniej nie brał udziału w turnieju** otrzyma: [full art Offworld Office](https://i.ibb.co/W4kYyDp8/offoff.png) lub [alt art Spin Doctor](https://netrunnercards.net/cdn/shop/files/SpinDocfornet.png?v=1735500486&width=990). Przy 5+ nowych osób rozlosujemy jedno z [pudełek żetonów od Atien](https://i.ibb.co/fzMKLk2Q/IMG20251023150758.jpg).\r\n\r\n\r\n***\r\nCzy to wszystko? Będą też pierniczki. Ale nie wiadomo czy udane:)\r\n\r\nSee you in Boat City!','11:00',37,0),(5157,'DC Grid Winter Local','2025.11.01.','11:00','','','Safer','','','','',9,3,'NOT AN ONLINE EVENT - ABR JUST BROKEN\r\n\r\nVictory Comics Falls Church\r\n586 S Washington St, Falls Church, VA 22046',1,0,0,16086,1,'elev',6,'2025-10-28 11:31:00','2025-12-14 11:09:24',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,16086,'2025-12-14 11:09:24',0,NULL,NULL,'Foil Transfer of Wealth Alt Art from Montrael Continentals\r\nFoil Petty Cash Alt Art from Montrael Continentals\r\nChoice of ElessarEllie\'s Zodiac IDs','10:30',37,1),(5158,'Bay Area Janksgiving Charity Tournament','2025.11.22.','11:00','','','','','','','',7,0,'Join us on **Saturday, November 22**, at Victory Point Cafe in Berkeley for a Janksgiving charity Netrunner tournament! Janksgiving is a charity tournament format aimed at raising money to help fight housing and food insecurity. *The tournament is in person - ABR is having issues and so it\'s listed as online, but it\'s not!*\r\n\r\n**How does it work?**\r\nYou will first generate a set of Jank rolls using the handy dandy Jankpplication, The Janksgiver (very kindly made by @solemn_storm) which can be found here: [Janksgiver](https://jankgiver.solemn.website/). **Copy and post these rolls in the [Bay Area Netrunner Discord](https://discord.gg/4MUnqN5Wxt).** You will then choose one full set of those rolls for each side, Corp & Runner, and build decks with them using the deckbuilding rules below. If you really don\'t like any of your initial rolls on one side, you can take one free mulligan. You may only do this for ONE SIDE, and you must use your Mulliganed roll, even if you think it\'s worse than the first 3. Sometimes the jank gods are not smiling on us. There are currently no other known reasons to get a mulligan, but weird stuff happens all the time, so if you think you deserve one, message me (tzeentchling) on Discord and I\'ll take a look. I don\'t really have a way of policing these rolls, but it\'s a casual level charity tournament, so don\'t be a dick.\r\n\r\nWe\'ll play **3-4 rounds, depending on attendance, of double sided swiss** to determine the Jankschampion!\r\n\r\n**Deckbuilding Rules**\r\nThis is a casual level event. Decklists are not required unless you want to show off your wombo combo. Use your weirdest alt arts. Your opponents will be looking at the top card of R&D with confusion already anyway.\r\n\r\n* You must use 1 whole set of rolls from the 3 Janksgiver gives you for each side. You may not take the ID from one of the three rolls and use the cards from another, for example.\r\n* Your deck must include 3 copies of every card included in the roll you choose for each side.\r\nCards in your jank rolls are all out of faction for the rolled ID and DO NOT count towards your influence limit.\r\n* EVERY ID regardless of side or faction has an influence value of 6 INSTEAD of its printed influence value. Remember, your rolled cards don\'t cost influence. This influence is to spend on cards to tie your rolls together into a combo.\r\n* All corps, regardless of faction, get a full set of 3 Spin Doctors with no additional influence cost. Spend your influence on something fun.\r\n* All other Standard Format deckbuilding rules apply. Standard card pool and ban list is in effect.\r\n* Every ID uses its printed minimum deck size and Corp decks must maintain a standard agenda density for their size.\r\n\r\n**Entry fee is a minimum $10 donation, with no maximum.** Go with your heart, but don\'t go broke.  Because this is a charity tournament, the cafe has graciously waved their usual entry fee for using the space, so take advantage of that! The winner of Janksgiving will get the most coveted prize: **to be allowed to choose the charity to which all of the donations are sent**, so long as they address food or housing insecurity.\r\n\r\nEveryone will receive an alt-art ID prize for participating, picked in finish order from a prize pool I\'ve assembled with pictures below. We\'ll have 12 playsets of a special alt-art Gour(d)mand from local artist Jinksey to give out as well.  And the last-place player (who finished all their games) will get a special prize, because the jankiest of the jank should also be rewarded. More prizes may become available as the date gets nearer, but it will definitely be worth turning out for!',1,0,0,8707,1,'elev',6,'2025-10-28 17:03:12','2026-01-12 21:10:02',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,6,NULL,8707,'2026-01-03 18:22:59',0,NULL,NULL,'![Gourdmand](https://i.imgur.com/DmyVcVE.png)\r\n![Arcs IDs](https://i.imgur.com/fzlFY6y.jpeg)\r\n![stained glass IDs](https://i.imgur.com/lpThcrj.jpeg)\r\n![acrylic IDs](https://i.imgur.com/YWy26eV.jpeg)\r\n![crim IDs](https://i.imgur.com/BV62ste.jpeg)\r\n![simple IDs](https://i.imgur.com/D85PfJV.jpeg)','10:30',37,1),(5159,'Victory Point Cafe - Thanksgiving Weekend CTK','2025.11.30.','11:00','United States','CA','@bdorf (discord)','Berkeley','Victory Point Cafe','1797 Shattuck Ave. Ste A, Berkeley, CA 94709, USA','ChIJc4U-eZ9-hYAR5ih4d-bZpBI',10,NULL,'Casual standard-legal tournament using the H1 CTK kit. Come to one of your last chances in the bay area to get a CBI invite for 2026!\r\n\r\nThis tournament is planned to be 6 rounds of single sided swiss, 40 mins per round,  with a break for lunch after the second round.\r\n\r\nWe will be using the 25.12 standard banlist (not listed correctly in ABR they dont have this field updated yet)\r\nhttps://nullsignal.games/blog/standard-balance-update-25-12/',1,0,0,3455,1,'elev',11,'2025-10-28 20:32:04','2025-12-01 00:14:16',NULL,4,37.875174,-122.268461,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,3455,'2025-12-01 00:12:33',0,NULL,119,'Other random alt arts from previous NSG kits may be handed out as well depending on availability and turnout.','10:30',37,0),(5162,'RowRow\'s (Not RoRo\'s) GNKBBQ','2025.12.14.','13:30','United Kingdom','','','Dundee','','','ChIJ05xjq0RBhkgRKuVLOB475JQ',NULL,NULL,'A very casual afternoon/evening playing Netrunner at RowRow\'s. \r\n\r\nDepending on turn out may run as a small tournament or just casual games. People welcome to turn up from 13:00 and happy to have people over until late.\r\n\r\nWill likely do a BBQ for dinner, intention at present is just a load of chicken. Happy to cook anything else that is brought along. \r\n\r\nI have a Q3 GNK which will likely be handed out if you tell me you\'ve won a load of games, or brought something nice to have on or with the BBQ.\r\n\r\nI\'m RowRow MkII on the Dundee or Scottish Netrunner Discord, if you\'re interested in coming ping me and I can let you know where I live. \r\n\r\nI\'ll need an accurate estimate of how many people I\'m expecting as I may need to borrow another table and more chairs, so please sign up here so I know to expect you.',0,0,0,17269,1,'elev',1,'2025-10-29 18:57:06','2025-11-08 12:12:48',NULL,0,56.462018,-2.970721,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,126,'','13:00',37,0),(5163,'Hack O\' Lantern VI: Back 2 Tha Root','2025.11.08.','11:00','United States','TX','','Austin','Austin Beerworks - Sprinkle Valley','10300 Springdale Rd, Austin, TX 78754, USA','ChIJ3x7Sv8XJRIYR_kiwoJdR2F0',10,0,'![Image](https://imgur.com/IZmBWlF.png)\r\n\r\nWe may be a tad late for the spooky season but Hack O\' Lantern will always come back with it\'s signature **Costume Party** format.\r\n\r\nTo don a sweet costume and jam silly games for this event, follow these steps:\r\n1) For each of your decks, choose any* ID from the game\'s history\r\n	 * *Minus Discontinued Costumes and identities banned in Standard.\r\n2) Build your deck as if the chosen ID is in a different main faction on its side (Anarch, Criminal, Shaper, HB, Jinteki, NBN, Weyland).\r\n3) Use the Standard cardpool and Standard Ban List 25.10.\r\n\r\nSpecial deckbuilding rules for minifaction costumes:\r\n* You have access to all cards from your costume\'s minifaction, even rotated ones (but you spend influence to import them as usual).\r\n* Adam has to spend influence for his 3 starting directives. Think of it like they have 16 influence\r\n\r\nDiscontinued and Banned Costumes:\r\nRunner: Leela, Liza\r\nCorp: IG, PU, Skorpios, Mti, R+\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nLocation: \r\nAustin Beerworks - Sprinkle Valley\r\n10300 Springdale Rd, Austin, TX 78754\r\n\r\nThere will be 6 rounds of Single-Sided Swiss, 40 minutes each.\r\n - Registration starts at 10:30\r\n - Round 1 Starts at 11:00',1,0,0,9546,1,'elev',1,'2025-10-29 21:28:15','2025-11-08 22:16:41',NULL,4,30.344437,-97.647131,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,9546,'2025-11-08 22:16:41',0,NULL,NULL,'At the conclusion of the event, we will run the traditional prize draft and award a special playmat to the winner, but the real show is...\r\n\r\nThe Costume Contest!\r\nEach player will be given a vote slip with space to write down who brought the most creative, amusing, or downright horrifying Runner and Corp to the event. (You may vote for the same player for both sides if that\'s how you feel. Voting for yourself is cringe).','10:30',37,0),(5164,'Calgary 2025 Q3 GNK','2025.11.22.','12:30','Canada','','hereticdave@outlook.com','Calgary','Stonyslope Brewing Company','9620 Elbow Dr SW #20, Calgary, AB T2V 1M2, Canada','ChIJ_T5WWylxcVMRv5S0fljXfeY',11,0,'This will be a **STANDARD format event**\r\n\r\n**Entry:** $5\r\n\r\n**Location:** Stony Slope Brewery\r\n\r\n**What you need to bring!**\r\n\r\n* Yourself\r\n* Both a legal Corp and Runner deck, constructed from any cards in the Core sets, System Gateway and Elevation along with any Cycle: Ashes, Borealis, Liberation\r\n* Each deck should be uniformly sleeved in opaque backed sleeves\r\n* Counters, dice and tokens to track effects, credits etc\r\n\r\n**What you need to know!**\r\n\r\n* Single sided swiss format [you will play an opponent with only one deck]\r\n* Duration: Noon until 4-5pm\r\n* Each match time will be 40 minutes, there will be a visible count down, time will be called at 5 minutes and again when complete\r\n* When time is called the active player finishes their turn and their opponent gets a final turn\r\n* Matches are won via Runner Flatline, 7 Agenda points or in the case of time being called, most Agenda points',1,0,0,41926,1,'elev',1,'2025-10-30 18:40:48','2025-11-23 01:52:13',NULL,4,50.969012,-114.084118,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,41926,'2025-11-23 01:52:13',0,NULL,126,'The Regenesis playmat has been generously donated by Jack to be distributed to the top ranked new player who participates in the event :)','12:00',37,0),(5165,'GNK pour les fêtes','2025.12.06.','11:30','France','','','Paris','Playin Bar à Jeux BNF','131 Av. de France, 75013 Paris, France','ChIJg0BegJdz5kcRppVsoflcc3A',14,3,'Bonjour tout le monde !\r\nHistoire de faire quelques parties et distribuer quelques jolies cartes promos, on organise ce petit événement avec les prix du GNK Q2 2025 (Behold/Audrey), GNK Q3 2025 (Charlotte/Alarm Clock) en fonction de vos préférences, à Playin BNF (l\'événement n\'est pas en ligne, mais c\'est le seul champ qu\'il était possible de renseigner).\r\nÀ très vite!',1,0,0,37519,1,'elev',1,'2025-10-30 18:48:54','2026-01-05 09:00:07',NULL,4,48.831247,2.375707,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,37519,'2025-12-07 19:01:29',0,NULL,123,'','11:00',37,0),(5166,'Pittsburgh Casual Tournament','2025.12.06.','11:00','United States','PA','danmyth@gmail.com','Pittsburgh','Game Masters','398 Perry Hwy, Pittsburgh, PA 15229, USA','ChIJtw6agUaLNIgR3cogD65fg0w',10,3,'**Calling all Pittsburgh Netrunners!**\r\n\r\nWe will be holding an in-person Netrunner tournament at [Game Masters](https://gamemasterspgh.com/) on Saturday, December 6th. This will be a tournament in the Standard format using the most recent banlist, and will consist of 5 or 6 rounds of single-sided Swiss games, with a possible top cut depending on attendance. Last chance to win an invite to the Circuit Breaker Invitational!\r\n\r\n* Registration starts at 10:30AM, and round 1 will start at 11:00AM sharp. [Click Here to Register.](https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/mh1z)\r\n\r\n* There will be a $5 cover paid to the store at registration. \r\n\r\n* Game Masters address:  398 Perry Highway. Pittsburgh, PA 15229\r\n\r\nDecklists are not required. Proxies are legal. If you need any assistance with decks, proxies, or cost to attend, please join the [Steel City Grid Discord](https://discord.gg/KVyBtyrstX) and reach out!',1,0,0,41168,1,'elev',11,'2025-10-31 02:17:01','2025-12-07 00:28:40',NULL,4,40.517800,-80.030408,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,41168,'2025-12-07 00:28:26',0,NULL,119,'','10:30',37,0),(5167,'Muenster CT UpGr8 [CANCELLED due to COVID]','2025.11.29.','11:00','Germany','','bauzaun@posteo.de','Münster','','Elisabeth-Hürten-Weg 3, 48163 Münster, Germany','ChIJyUiEoV-luUcRRoSE4i5gYWs',NULL,NULL,'Dear Runners, \r\n\r\nit breaks my heart but unfortunately I have to cancel the tournament. I got infected with a bad case of COVID and it would be a) a safety hazard to host this tournament and b) it is beyond my capabilities at the moment. \r\n\r\nI am moved by the number of returning and first time attendees from outside Münster that wanted to make their way to us. \r\n\r\nThis won\'t be the last time. Keep your eyes out for a new tournament announcement here and on the german discord server.',0,0,0,33017,1,'elev',11,'2025-10-31 07:43:06','2025-11-26 20:40:32',NULL,0,51.928397,7.581304,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,119,'','10:30',37,0),(5168,'GNK 2025 Q3 - Utrecht','2025.11.15.','13:30','Netherlands','','veronicavanvoorst@gmail.com','Utrecht','','Beyaertdreef 5, 3562 LG Utrecht, Netherlands','ChIJ-V4JlRdvxkcR18DGly2lRlE',6,0,'Practicalities:\r\n\r\n- **There has been a change in venue!** Location is Beyaertdreef 5, 3562 LG Utrecht, Netherlands. The Venue is called **Biercafe Oproer**. \r\n\r\n- Registration starts at 13.00, round 1 starts at 13:30 Please be on time.\r\n\r\n- The format will be Standard. It will use the rules and most recent banlist found [here](https://nullsignal.games/players/supported-formats/). Please make sure your decklist is legal for the current Standard format. If you\'re unsure, please send your decklist to the TO ahead of the event to check.\r\n\r\n- There will be 3 rounds of double-sided swiss, each taking 65 minutes. There will be no top cut.\r\n\r\n- Entry fee is €5. If at all possible, pay beforehand and wire the money to NL10 ASNB 8832 5716 92, attn Veronica van Voorst. Don\'t forget to mention your name. A tikkie on the day also works.\r\n\r\n- Proxies are allowed, as long as it is clear which card it is. Written notes in a sleeve will not be accepted. If you are missing cards for a deck, please get in contact with the TO beforehand, as she may be able to provide proxies for you.\r\n\r\n- Outside drinks and food aren\'t allowed. The venue sells various drinks and food.\r\n\r\n- Veronica van Voorst will be your TO. If you have any questions, feel free to email veronicavanvoorst@gmail.com. Alternatively, you can reach out through the [Netrunner NL Discord Server](https://discord.gg/TZbTfC3kM3).\r\n\r\n- The venue is **not** within walking distance of the train station. It will be about 15 to 20 minutes using public transport.\r\n\r\nHave fun! We\'re aiming for this to be a more casual style event, with an opportunity for new players to enjoy a tournament without high stakes. If this is your first tournament, you can let the TO know, and please feel welcome to join us; we\'re happy to have you.',1,0,0,28686,1,'elev',1,'2025-10-31 16:22:13','2025-11-18 10:49:48',NULL,4,52.111267,5.111576,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,28686,'2025-11-15 16:01:13',0,NULL,126,'If there are at least 6 players, I\'ll be adding a Gamedragon Pro token to the prize pool as well, and additional promo\'s may be added to the prize pool on day of. \r\nOther people are free to contribute to the prize pool if they so desire.','13:00',37,0),(5169,'ETERNAL  COMMUNITY TOURNAMENT','2025.11.30.','11:00','','','based_breadwoman on Discord','','','','',10,0,'![Image](https://i.imgur.com/4TxFx1t.png)\r\n\r\nGET SOME PRACTICE IN TO THIS REALLY FUN FORMAT BEFORE OFF META MONTH BEGINS!!!!\r\n\r\nEVERY SET is available!!!! Come play with some of your favourite high powered cards like Mti and Account Siphon!\r\n\r\nPlayer meet up is going to be at 10h45 UTC+0 . Tournament will start at 11h00 UTC+0 30th NOVEMBER\r\n\r\nWe will be playing Single Sided Swiss in eternal format using the 25.07 banlist.\r\n\r\nThere will be 5-6 rounds , with an optional top cut, and there won\'t be any prizing for this event.\r\n\r\n\r\nCome join at https://discord.gg/9jeju9v8RE\r\n and introduce yourself\r\n\r\n\r\nIF YOUVE  NEVER PLAYED ETERNAL, FEEL FREE TO MESSAGE ME AT based_breadwoman ON DISCORD. ALSO, HERES THE BEGINNERS GUIDE TO GET YOU STARTED!!!!!\r\n\r\nhttps://docs.google.com/document/d/1SmmqHqkaESGLeeg0ulsckZyly-jQkFuH_2YfYKSPLOc/edit?tab=t.0',1,0,0,38377,1,'elev',6,'2025-11-01 10:00:48','2025-11-30 14:11:27',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,7,NULL,38377,'2025-11-30 14:11:27',0,NULL,NULL,'','09:00',99999,1),(5170,'Linköping Winter GNK 2025','2025.12.14.','10:30','Sweden','','nilsaxeljohannes@gmail.com','Linköping','','Södra Oskarsgatan 3, 582 73 Linköping, Sweden','ChIJtcvoRy5vWUYR0_pulTGDTL0',9,0,'Let\'s end the year by beginning the year with the 2025 Q1 GNK!\r\n\r\nJoin us in Linköping for a chill(y), casual tournament this December!\r\n\r\nLocation: Our usual digs at Skylten, right beside the train station. The address is Södra Oskarsgatan 3.\r\n\r\nFormat: 5 rounds of single-sided Swiss.',1,0,0,12582,1,'elev',1,'2025-11-01 19:18:59','2025-12-14 20:31:18',NULL,4,58.417878,15.625280,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,12582,'2025-12-14 14:10:16',0,NULL,118,'','10:00',28,0),(5171,'A Nottingham Janksgiving','2025.11.22.','10:30','United Kingdom','','Cobalt on discord','Nottingham','Games Haven','92 Lower Parliament St, Nottingham NG1 1EH, UK','ChIJS1F9X_HDeUgRJVS6Fsjk8TQ',6,0,'We\'ll be running the Janksgiving (https://jankgiver.solemn.website/) format, for fun! In short: you will be given a choice of 3 (for each side) combinations of ID and three cards. If you don\'t like any of them, you can reroll for a final option that **must** be chosen. \r\n\r\nYou\'ll play the ID you selected, and each of the three other cards played as full, influence-free playsets, with 3 influence-free Spin Doctors available and 6 influence to spend freely instead of the ID\'s printed influence. \r\n\r\n**Important:** Message me on Discord if you\'re intending to attend, and I\'ll give you your rolls to choose from.\r\n\r\nEntry will be a £5 (or greater) donation to Framework (https://www.frameworkha.org/), Nottingham\'s local homelessness charity. Top 3 placements will have a choice of prizing from the items I\'ve brought from the prizing stash on the day.',1,0,0,41523,1,'elev',1,'2025-11-04 09:21:09','2025-11-22 21:49:48',NULL,4,52.954464,-1.141330,NULL,0,0,'',0,6,NULL,41523,'2025-11-22 21:49:47',0,NULL,NULL,'','10:00',37,0),(5172,'Barcelona monthly tournament November','2025.11.15.','10:45','','','bcnetop@gmail.com','','','','',10,0,'Monthly tournament in Ingenio, Barcelona. \r\nSingle sided swiss, 4 rounds.\r\n15/11 10:30\r\nTournament is not online, maps wasn\'t loading',1,1,0,40364,1,'elev',6,'2025-11-04 17:24:24','2026-01-24 11:36:18',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,40364,'2025-11-15 14:29:39',0,NULL,NULL,'Store checks','10:30',37,1),(5173,'Barcelona monthly tournament December','2025.12.20.','16:45','Spain','','bcnetop@gmail.com','Barcelona','inGenio BCN Games','Pg. de St. Joan, 16, L\'Eixample, 08010 Barcelona, Spain','ChIJs4AmnOSipBIRDhSJNlGVYWc',8,0,'Monthly tournament Barcelona \r\n20/12 16:30\r\nSingle sided swiss 4 rounds\r\nIngenio, Barcelona\r\nTournament is not online, maps wasn\'t loading.',1,0,0,40364,1,'elev',6,'2025-11-04 17:27:05','2025-12-20 20:33:10',NULL,4,41.392339,2.179333,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,40364,'2025-12-20 20:33:10',0,NULL,NULL,'Store checks','16:30',37,0),(5174,'November Draft SSS GNK ($3)','2025.11.05.','18:00','United States','MI','tvaduva@yahoo.com','Ann Arbor','Michigan Union','530 S State St, Ann Arbor, MI 48109, USA','ChIJm6MvgkeuPIgRijKnzq9YR_w',8,NULL,'Let\'s take our drafted decks out for a spin and play some games.\r\n\r\nLocation: Michigan Union in Ann Arbor at our regular location (not online, just have to set it that way because the Google Maps widget isn\'t working)\r\nCost: $3\r\n\r\nThere will be 5 rounds of Single-Sided Swiss lasting 40 minutes to determine the winner.\r\n\r\nJoin our Discord to keep up with the local group: https://discord.gg/sxfueMvdbR',1,0,0,1752,1,'elev',1,'2025-11-04 20:28:48','2025-11-14 21:37:27',NULL,4,42.275049,-83.741665,NULL,0,0,'',0,4,NULL,1752,'2025-11-14 21:30:58',0,NULL,76,'I\'m contributing additional alt arts.','18:00',37,0),(5175,'Sheffield Net Gaming','2025.11.29.','10:30','United Kingdom','','lif3line on discord (find me on GLC or UK Netrunner Servers)','Sheffield','Patriot Games','97 Mary St, Sheffield City Centre, Sheffield S1 4RT, UK','ChIJpTJ-4Hl4eUgRn6irVwbFkhU',14,0,'Ever feel the need to run some nets? We got you!\r\n\r\nWe\'ll be at Patriot Games in Sheffield: [https://www.patriotgames.uk/](https://www.patriotgames.uk/). The venue has step-free access, gender neutral toilets and offers food. Fixed seating can be organised on the day or if you contact me in advance.\r\n\r\nThe tournament will be run at casual level with ~5-6 rounds of single sided swiss depending on numbers, no cut, NSG Code of Conduct and the most recent ban list (25.12). Prizing will be current competitive season prizing or a dip into my vault of goodies depending on what I can source.\r\n\r\nCost will be £5 at the door.',1,0,0,34662,1,'elev',1,'2025-11-05 16:05:53','2025-12-15 11:00:35',NULL,4,53.373974,-1.469443,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,34662,'2025-12-04 08:32:11',0,NULL,NULL,'','10:00',99999,0),(5176,'Adelaide Standard Tournament [Good Games Adelaide]','2025.11.15.','12:00','','','spaceicenr on Discord','','','','',9,0,'Note: This event is not online, and will be at Good Games Adelaide, 88 Grenfell St, Adelaide SA 5000.\r\n\r\nCasual Netrunner tournament for new, experienced, and returning players.\r\n\r\nThe prize pool will be a spread of recent GNK kits and other alt arts. Everybody will come away with at least 1-2 prizes!\r\n\r\nWe\'ll play a 3 round tournament, and in each round you play a game as Corp and a game as Runner. The round time limit is 65 minutes, with an extra turn each if games go to time.\r\n\r\nThe standard cardpool will be in place, including the current Standard Banlist (see https://nullsignal.games/players/supported-formats/ under Standard for the most up-to-date list). There is no need for decklists.\r\n\r\nProxies of any card are welcome. Feel free to reach out if you need any help getting cards.\r\n\r\nEntry is $6.',1,0,0,24590,1,'elev',1,'2025-11-07 03:22:39','2025-11-16 11:14:46',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,24590,'2025-11-16 11:13:59',0,NULL,NULL,'','12:00',37,1),(5177,'Shoreham-by-Sea (Brighton) causal meet up','2025.11.30.','10:30','United Kingdom','','willybn1@yahoo.com','Shoreham-by-Sea','KD Games','32a High St, Shoreham-by-Sea BN43 5DA, UK','ChIJeypGAh2adUgR5C60nMQdtpw',NULL,NULL,'Now the dust has settled on Edinburgh lets get back to playing casual NetRunner !\r\n\r\nShoreham is a great place to play the game ... great train connection to London, East and West coastline (subject to engineering works) ... good parking, food and seagulls. \r\n\r\nSunday 30th November\r\nStandard, DSS, 10am registration for a 10.30 start.\r\nVenue: KD Games. 32a High St, Shoreham-by-Sea BN43 5DA.\r\nAccess 5 mins walk from Shoreham-by-Sea station - great train links to London and west - Southampton, Portsmouth etc.\r\nRegistration: 10:00\r\nRound 1 start: 10:30\r\nTicket cost: £7.50\r\nPrizes:\r\nFor winner (or top two if more than six players). Choice of playmat from our prize pool for winner, plus 1 playset from the  2025 run together kit.\r\nParticipation: Echelon Alt Art (Brighton District 2025) + 1 playset from the  2025 run together kit + 1 playset of other alt art from recent kits. There may be some tokens available.\r\n\r\nhttps://nullsignal.games/blog/run-together-2025-pack-1-now-available/',0,0,0,18172,1,'elev',11,'2025-11-07 18:28:40','2025-12-01 18:48:20','2025-12-01 18:48:20',0,50.831923,-0.275950,NULL,0,0,'https://www.facebook.com/groups/1448578338750249',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'https://nullsignal.games/blog/run-together-2025-pack-1-now-available/','10:00',37,0),(5179,'Lord of the BOOMers! - Retrieval Run','2025.12.06.','10:30','','','finnbroman@hotmail.com or bridgeman7773 on Discord :)','','','','',4,0,'Time to dust off the old collection or get acquainted with the old cards you never got the chance to play!\r\n\r\nFor this tournament we are playing my self made experimental FFG only format: Retrieval Run!\r\nIt is simply all the FFG cards minus a banlist I made to make it a new experience :D\r\nOfc this also means there are combinations of cards that were never possible in standard, as Kitara and Reign and Reverie and Magnum Opus will be present with the cards hit by the first rotation.\r\n\r\nDetails can be found in this [doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1277UtRMMVyJhDGFBMDn5TvYQ9GRCrt68bpXw8sWTaQI/edit?tab=t.0).\r\n[Here](https://cataloguer.web.app/?search=is%3Affg+-%28Desperado%29+-%28Aaron+Marron%29+-%28Temujin+Contract%29+-%28Tapwrm%29+-%28Tech+Trader%29+-%28Gang+Sign%29+-%28Pad+Tap%29+-%28Crowdfunding%29+-%28Liza+Talking+Thunder%3A+Prominent+Legislator%29+-%28Miss+Bones%29+-%28Account+Siphon%29+-%28Aumakua%29+-%28Snitch%29+-%28Noise%3A+Hacker+Extraordinaire%29+-%28Whizzard%3A+Master+Gamer%29+-%28Deja+Vu%29+-%28I%27ve+Had+Worse%29+-%28Stimhack%29+-%28Vamp%29+-%28Archives+Interface%29+-%28Sifr%29+-%28Turntable%29+-%28Yog.0%29+-%28Faust%29+-%28Paperclip%29+-%28Keyhole%29+-%28Parasite%29+-%28Eater%29+-%28Medium%29+-%28Clot%29+-%28DDoS%29+-%28Data+Leak+Reversal%29+-%28Salsette+Slums%29+-%28Mars+for+Martians%29+-%28Clan+vengeance%29+-%28Salvaged+Vanadis+Armory%29+-%28Surfer%29+-%28Jarogniew+Mercs%29+-%28Indexing%29+-%28Astrolabe%29+-%28Magnum+Opus%29+-%28Misdirection%29+-%28Fan+Site%29+-%28Beth+Kilrain%29+-%28Film+Critic%29+-%28Kabonesa+Wu%3A+Netspace+Thrillseeker%29+-%28Blackmail%29+-%28Bloo+Moose%29+-%28Councilman%29+-%28Plascrete+Carapace%29+-%28Same+Old+Thing%29+-%28Citadel+Sanctuary%29+-%28The+Turning+Wheel%29+-%28Kati+Jones%29+-%28New+Angeles+City+Hall%29+-%28Watch+The+World+Burn%29+-%28Mad+Dash%29+-%28Rebirth%29+-%28DJ+Fenris%29+-%28Accelerated+Beta+Test%29+-%28Brain+Rewiring%29+-%28Clone+Suffrage+Movement%29+-%28Estelle+Moon%29+-%28Encryption+Protocol%29+-%28Lakshmi+Smartfabrics%29+-%28IT+Department%29+-%28Accelerated+Diagnostics%29+-%28Ark+Lockdown%29+-%28Ultraviolet+Clearance%29+-%28Violet+Level+Clearance%29+-%28Friends+In+High+Places%29+-%28Game+changer%29+-%28Team+sponsorship%29+-%28Jinteki%3A+Potential+Unleashed%29+-%28Philotic+Entanglement%29+-%28Bio-Ethics+Association%29+-%28Shi.Kyu%29+-%28Caprice+Nisei%29+-%28Marcus+Batty%29+-%28Breached+Dome%29+-%28Gene+Splicer%29+-%28Mti+Mwekundu%3A+Life+Improved%29+-%28Mwanza+City+Grid%29+-%28Shipment+from+Tennin%29+-%28Hangeki%29+-%28Skorpios+Defense+Systems%3A+Persuasive+Power%29+-%28Commercial+Bankers+Group%29+-%28Zealous+Judge%29+-%28Tour+Guide%29+-%28Hunter+Seeker%29+-%28Power+Shutdown%29+-%28Bryan+Stinson%29+-%28Titan+Transnational%3A+Investing+in+your+future%29+-%28Government+Takeover%29+-%28Reconstruction+Contract%29+-%28Economic+warfare%29+-%28NBN%3A+Controlling+The+Message%29+-%28Breaking+News%29+-%28AstroScript+Pilot+Program%29+-%28Blacklist%29+-%28Jackson+Howard%29+-%28News+Team%29+-%28Sensie+Actors+Union%29+-%2824%2F7+News+cycle%29+-%28Exchange+Of+Information%29+-%28Midseason+Replacements%29+-%28Echo+Chamber%29+-%28SIU%29+-%28Universal+Connectivity+Fee%29+-%28Chronos+Project%29+-%28Mumba+Temple%29+-%28Museum+of+history%29+-%28Sandburg%29+-%28Excalibur%29+-%28Macrophage%29+-%28Mother+Goddess%29+-%28Vanity+Project%29+-%28Hired+Help%29+-s%3Acurrent&order=faction) is a visual representation of the legal cards.(Except Bio-Ethics Association, TD Campaign Cards and draft IDs. Plz double check for other errors :))\r\n\r\nThe format is 40 minute single-sided swiss with a number of rounds and potential top cut based on the number of participants using the \"Casual\" chart found [here](https://access.nullsignal.games/OPPolicies/Organized%20Play%20Policies%202024.09%20-%20Standard.pdf) after page 36. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nRegistration starts 10:00 Swedish time. \r\nI put required decklists to add more material for me as a commentator :) If there is a top cut decklists will be open.\r\n\r\nThis one is a casual event for the culture, we are simply having fun with some old cards 🙂\r\nSo there is no entry fee, and no prizes beyond honor, except the winner gets a very nice Jakuza Laser ATeia that I won at a team event for worlds 2023.\r\n\r\nI will be streaming the event over [here](https://www.youtube.com/live/j_2E_fm9ddU), jumping into the games and providing commentary: \r\nIf you dont wanna be on stream that is ok, just let me know :)\r\n\r\nThe event will be run on [this](https://discord.gg/yuy9BxvF4R) discord. Feel free to use this to find practice games and discussing the format as well :)\r\nI\'ve posted some decklists doodles there as well to just share some ideas :)\r\n\r\nIf you need inspiration for decks I have posted a bunch of lists [here](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/decklists/find?faction=&sort=popularity&rotation_id=&author=RetrievalRun&title=&is_legal=&mwl_code=&packs%5B%5D=elev&cycle_28=liberation&packs%5B%5D=rwr&packs%5B%5D=tai&cycle_26=borealis&packs%5B%5D=ph&packs%5B%5D=ms&packs%5B%5D=msbp&packs%5B%5D=su21&packs%5B%5D=sg&packs%5B%5D=sm&packs%5B%5D=mor&cycle_21=ashes&packs%5B%5D=ur&packs%5B%5D=urbp&packs%5B%5D=df&packs%5B%5D=sc19&packs%5B%5D=napd&packs%5B%5D=mo&packs%5B%5D=rar&cycle_16=kitara&packs%5B%5D=ka&packs%5B%5D=win&packs%5B%5D=tdatd&packs%5B%5D=cotc&packs%5B%5D=dtwn&packs%5B%5D=ss&packs%5B%5D=core2&cycle_14=terminal-directive&packs%5B%5D=tdc&packs%5B%5D=td&cycle_13=red-sand&packs%5B%5D=cd&packs%5B%5D=fm&packs%5B%5D=baw&packs%5B%5D=eas&packs%5B%5D=so&packs%5B%5D=dc&cycle_12=flashpoint&packs%5B%5D=qu&packs%5B%5D=ml&packs%5B%5D=in&packs%5B%5D=es&packs%5B%5D=bm&packs%5B%5D=23s&cycle_11=mumbad&packs%5B%5D=ftm&packs%5B%5D=tlm&packs%5B%5D=si&packs%5B%5D=dag&packs%5B%5D=bf&packs%5B%5D=kg&packs%5B%5D=dad&cycle_9=sansan&packs%5B%5D=uot&packs%5B%5D=oh&packs%5B%5D=uw&packs%5B%5D=cc&packs%5B%5D=bb&packs%5B%5D=val&packs%5B%5D=oac&cycle_7=lunar&packs%5B%5D=ts&packs%5B%5D=atr&packs%5B%5D=uao&packs%5B%5D=fc&packs%5B%5D=tsb&packs%5B%5D=up&packs%5B%5D=hap&cycle_4=spin&packs%5B%5D=dt&packs%5B%5D=fal&packs%5B%5D=tc&packs%5B%5D=mt&packs%5B%5D=st&packs%5B%5D=om&packs%5B%5D=cac&cycle_2=genesis&packs%5B%5D=fp&packs%5B%5D=hs&packs%5B%5D=asis&packs%5B%5D=ce&packs%5B%5D=ta&packs%5B%5D=wla&packs%5B%5D=core) on netrunner DB under the username RetrievalRun to get some ideas flowing :) \r\nNote that these dont necessarily follow the latest banlist in the format so double check them before playing.\r\n\r\n[Cobr Event](https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/gxy5) - You can self register here and report results once the event is live.\r\n\r\nIf you know you are going please register here too, h\r\nIt helps me prepare for the event :)\r\n\r\nExcited to see what everyone will brew!',1,1,0,23764,1,'mo',1,'2025-11-09 12:45:32','2025-12-06 11:48:49',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,23764,'2025-12-06 11:48:49',0,NULL,NULL,'So there is no entry fee, and no prizes beyond honor, except the winner gets a very nice Jakuza Laser ATeia that I won at a team event for worlds 2023.','10:00',37,1),(5180,'German Discord Liga IV: Christkindl Open Market','2025.11.11.','00:02','','','dainestevens@gmail.com','','','','',22,0,'[English below]\r\n\r\nLiebe Community,\r\n\r\nwir starten Runde 4 der Online-Liga des Discord-Servers Netrunner Deutschland, die von unserem TorpedoTyrus ins Leben gerufen wurde. Die Spiele werden online auf jinteki.net ausgetragen oder, wenn ihr es bevorzugt, persönlich, wenn ihr mit jemandem aus eurem Meta gepaart wurdet. Die Paarungen werden in der deutschen Netrunner-Discord-Community organisiert, die ihr hier findet:\r\n\r\nhttps://discord.gg/tbZYuUTV\r\n\r\nDie Teilnahme ist kostenlos. Es gibt eine begrenzte Anzahl von Preisen aus meiner Sammlung, die nach dem Zufallsprinzip verteilt werden, auch an den Spieler, der das Turnier als Letzter beendet.\r\n\r\nDas Turnier wird nach den folgenden Regeln ausgetragen:\r\n-Es sind keine Decklisten erforderlich und die Decks können auf Wunsch jede Woche geändert werden.\r\n-Die Decks müssen gemäß der Bannliste 12.25 standardkonform sein.\r\n-Je nach Teilnehmerzahl dauert die Liga zwischen 6 und 8 Wochen.\r\n-Spiele sind DSS \r\n\r\nDear comminity,\r\n\r\nWe are starting round 4 of the online league of the German netrunner discord in the continuing tradition started by our own TorpedoTyrus. Games will be played online at jinteki.net or face-to-face if you have been paired with someone in your meta, if preferred. Pairings will be organized in the German netrunner discord found here: https://discord.gg/tbZYuUTV\r\n\r\nThere is no fee for participating. Limited prizing from my collection will be available, distributed randomly, and also to the last-place player who completes the tournament.\r\n\r\nThe tournament will be run according to the following rules:\r\n-No decklists are required and decks may be changed every week, if desired.\r\n-Decks must be standard legal according to the banlist 12.25.\r\n-Depending on turnout the league will run between 6 and 8 weeks.\r\n-Matches are double-sided swiss',1,0,0,750,1,'elev',12,'2025-11-10 08:40:06','2026-01-29 15:31:19',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,'2026.01.18.',750,'2026-01-18 11:17:37',0,NULL,NULL,'','00:01',37,1),(5181,'Standard Casual Tournament Antwerpen','2025.11.15.','13:00','Belgium','','thomas.vdcruysse@gmail.com','Antwerpen','Outpost Gamecenter','Beggaardenstraat 6, 2000 Antwerpen, Belgium','ChIJdbD50_n2w0cRLJ7oie0-DiU',7,0,'7 rounds of single-sided swiss\r\nentry fee €5',1,0,0,19819,1,'elev',11,'2025-11-10 19:07:06','2025-11-15 15:52:56',NULL,4,51.219474,4.404645,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,19819,'2025-11-15 15:52:56',0,NULL,104,'','12:30',37,0),(5182,'Curtin Card Games Club Startup Tournament','2025.12.08.','18:00','Australia','','curtincardgamers@gmail.com','Bentley','Curtin University Building 400','400, Curtin University, Kent St, Bentley WA 6102, Australia','ChIJG2NKLI-8MioR-h8-1KYBKeQ',NULL,NULL,'# Curtin Card Games Club Netrunner Startup Tournament\r\n*Get ready to break some ice as you run into R&D, or resolve some operations to advance and score out your agendas*\r\n\r\n[Curtin Card Games Club](https://linktr.ee/curtincardgamesclub) is a student run club at Curtin University focussing on trading card games. They run Monday nights weekly, hosting mostly Magic: the Gathering, but also support other TCGs.\r\n\r\nFree Entry Event is open to all, including those wishing to **learn to play**.\r\n- There will be decks to borrow if you don\'t have. Please let us know if you plan to borrow.\r\n- Otherwise bring 1x Corp and 1x Runner Startup legal decks, proxies permitted.\r\n## Details\r\n**Format**: [Startup](https://nullsignal.games/players/supported-formats/#startup), including the [25.11 Balance Update](https://nullsignal.games/blog/startup-balance-update-25-11/).\r\n**Structure**: Double-Sided Swiss (Play both Runner and Corp)\r\n**Specific Room Location**: [Health Pop Building 400.249](https://use.mazemap.com/#v=1&config=curtinuniversity&campusid=296&sharepoitype=poi&sharepoi=807521) Best to access from North end of Building East Facing Door, Map is/will be posted to discords.\r\n\r\nContact us in Discord in [Netrunner ANZ - #Perth](https://discord.gg/vEW7vb7D), or [Curtin Card Games](https://discord.gg/nyzA64P) if you want to chat or have any questions.',0,0,0,50964,1,'elev',6,'2025-11-11 13:40:59','2025-11-15 04:03:49',NULL,0,-32.002990,115.893272,NULL,0,0,'',0,11,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'Alters by Alter Vixit, to all participant, you\'ll have to wait until the day to see them!','17:00',0,0),(5183,'On the Lam and Lie(ing) Low in the Capital','2025.12.14.','10:30','Australia','','sutto','Phillip','Libraries ACT - Woden','Corner of Furzer Street &, Corinna St, Phillip ACT 2606, Australia','ChIJ5-V-cAC1F2sRCwk0ZcbIwfA',8,0,'*\"Psst. Hey buddy. Yeah you. You look like you want some of that Netrunner. I got the OP Police breathing down my neck, so I need to move this 2025 H1 kit fast\"*\r\n\r\nCome down to the Woden library in Canberra for a very casual day of Netrunner.  Throw some cards, catch up with Discord mates in meatspace, and watch my flailing impression of a TO as I try to shake tags to throw off the OP Police.  I\'m serious, they keep getting closer and closer.  Will probably just be Swiss until we get kicked out, but we\'ll see what happens with the numbers we get.',1,0,0,47553,1,'elev',11,'2025-11-12 05:49:23','2025-12-14 06:31:09',NULL,4,-35.344718,149.084241,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,47553,'2025-12-14 06:31:09',0,NULL,119,'There will be some extra things from random GNK\'s I have laying about. There will be stuff for everyone.','10:00',37,0),(5184,'Janksmas 2025 Vienna','2025.12.16.','18:00','Austria','','ischariot47@gmx-topmail.de','Wien','JO&JOE Wien','Europaplatz 1/6, 1150 Wien, Austria','ChIJGz1uScAHbUcRBmMbRxNaKBQ',8,0,'Hej fellow Netrunners,\r\nWe got inspired (a.k.a. stole) the idea of Janksgiving and transfered it to the Christmas time because Thanksgiving isn\'t a thing in Austria.\r\nIn the spirit of Janksgiving this will also be a charity event. There is no participation fee but donations are welcome and the winner will be able to choose the charity for the collected donation. Every participant will get a t least a janky alt art playset of scrounge (in the unlikely case that there are not enough, another alt art playset of my choice will be used). There will be additional prices, details are given at the tournament.\r\n\r\nWe will play probably 3 rounds of double sided swiss.\r\n\r\nFollowing an adapted description from shiiuga who organised the side event at worlds:\r\n\r\n**How does it work?**\r\nWhat do Netrunner players love doing more than anything else? That\'s right! ~~Rage quitting on JNet.~~ Playing bad jank. Well, boy do I have the format for you!\r\n\r\nYou will first generate a set of Jank rolls using our brand new handy dandy Jankpplication, The Janksgiver (very kindly made by @solemn_storm) which can be found here: https://jankgiver.solemn.website/. You will then choose one full set of those rolls for each side, Corp & Runner, and build decks with them using the deckbuilding rules below.\r\n\r\nThen, you bring your decks to the tournament and face off against everyone else\'s jank until we crown the ultimate jank champion (jankion?), all while raising some money for a good cause.\r\n\r\n**Mulligan Rules**\r\nIf you really don\'t like any of your initial rolls on one side, you can take one free mulligan. You may only do this for **ONE SIDE**, and you must use your Mulliganed roll, even if you think it\'s worse than the first 3. Sometimes the jank gods are not smiling on us. There are currently no other known reasons to get a mulligan, but weird stuff happens all the time, so if you think you deserve one, contact me.\r\n\r\n**Deckbuilding Rules**\r\nThis has been simplified this year because Ben is a genius and built an app that removes all the edge cases that needed extra rerolls. This is a casual level event. Decklists are not required unless you want to show off your wombo combo. Use your weirdest alt arts. Your opponents will be looking at the top card of R&D with confusion already anyway.\r\n\r\nDeckbuilding rules are as follows:\r\n\r\n1. You must use 1 whole set of rolls from the 3 Janksgiver gives you for each side. You may not take the ID from one of the three rolls and use the cards from another, for example.\r\n2. Your deck must include 3 copies of every card included in the roll you choose for each side.\r\n3. Cards in your jank rolls are all out of faction for the rolled ID and **DO NOT** count towards your influence limit.\r\n4. EVERY ID regardless of side or faction has an influence value of 6 **INSTEAD** of its printed influence value. Remember, your rolled cards don\'t cost influence. This influence is to spend on cards to tie your rolls together into a combo.\r\n5. All corps, regardless of faction, get a full set of 3 Spin Doctors with no additional influence cost. Spend your influence on something fun.\r\n6. All other Standard Format deckbuilding rules apply. Standard card pool and ban list is in effect. Every ID uses its printed minimum deck size and Corp decks must maintain a standard agenda density for their size.\r\n\r\nFor the rolls we use an honour system, and I trust everybody will use what the jank goods gave them. Also you need to screenshot the result and post it on the discord server or send me an email.\r\n\r\nHope to see you at the event and happy Janksmas.',1,0,0,48544,1,'elev',1,'2025-11-12 20:19:51','2025-12-22 12:29:48',NULL,4,48.195979,16.337826,NULL,0,0,'',0,6,NULL,48544,'2025-12-22 12:29:48',0,NULL,NULL,'','17:30',99999,0),(5185,'Abaco Running Wild GNK','2025.11.30.','10:30','Spain','','netrunner.bilbao@gmail.com','Bilbao','Abaco Asociación Lúdica','Aita Larramendi Kalea, 3, Errekalde, 48012 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain','ChIJxym2vixQTg0RcElYFi253T4',10,0,'Torneo Abaco Running Wild GNK, organizado con la colaboración de Abaco Bilbao\r\n\r\nSe jugara en las instalaciones de Abaco Bilbao en Aita Larramendi Kalea, 3, 2º izq\r\n\r\nInscripción para sufragar los gastos de los premios entre los participantes.\r\n\r\nTorneo con rondas a determinar dependiendo de la inscripción, con un mínimo de 3 rondas\r\n\r\nRondas de dos partidas a 70 minutos, con partida de Corp y Runner\r\n\r\nFormato Estandar con Ban List 25.10\r\n\r\nCartas prohibidas\r\nRunner\r\nBukhgalter\r\nCleaver\r\nDaily Casts\r\nDeep Dive	\r\nDreamNet	\r\nEndurance	\r\nInfo Bounty	\r\nK2CP Turbine	\r\nMoshing	\r\nRezeki	\r\nTrick Shot	\r\nTsakhia “Bankhar” Gantulga	\r\nWorld Tree	\r\n\r\nCorp\r\nBellona\r\nCayambe Grid\r\nCyberdex Sandbox\r\nCybersand Harvester\r\nDr. Vientiane Keeling\r\nDrago Ivanov\r\nEngram Flush\r\nGold Farmer\r\nNanisivik Grid\r\nNBN: Reality Plus\r\nProject Vacheron\r\nSting!\r\nTouch-ups\r\nTributary\r\n\r\nAdemás hay un máximo de 3 cartas de plan de 3 puntos de plan en el mazo de Corp',1,0,0,42048,1,'elev',1,'2025-11-13 19:49:34','2025-11-30 12:46:47',NULL,4,43.254009,-2.943564,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,42048,'2025-11-30 12:46:47',0,NULL,126,'','10:00',37,0),(5186,'Rain City November Tournament','2025.11.27.','17:30','Canada','','','Vancouver','Rain City Games','88 W Pender St Unit 1069, Vancouver, BC V6B 6N9, Canada','ChIJ6SNusXtxhlQRfnCOSXUtcUA',NULL,NULL,'WILL USE NEW BANLIST (doesn\'t appear yet when creating events)\r\n\r\nFormat: Standard\r\nEntry: $10 \r\nRounds: 4 or 5 rounds of Single Sided Swiss (however many we can fit in 3.5 hours)\r\n\r\nWe only have the space from 17:30, the registration starts time is so y\'all can message me/register online.\r\n\r\nA casual tournament. If Q4 GNKs become available, I\'ll supplement those. Otherwise prizes from my prize box\r\n\r\nA single playset of one of my Worlds \'25 Carmen and Offworld Office will be available as a prize (only available for those who didn\'t go to Worlds)\r\n\r\nFor more information, join the [Vancouver Discord Server](https://discord.gg/3G4A73u), and message me; my username is Sindarin.',0,0,0,17150,1,'elev',1,'2025-11-15 23:53:08','2025-12-02 19:05:52','2025-12-02 19:05:52',0,49.280524,-123.107088,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','17:00',37,0),(5187,'Rain City December Tournament','2025.12.11.','17:30','Canada','','','Vancouver','Rain City Games','88 W Pender St Unit 1069, Vancouver, BC V6B 6N9, Canada','ChIJ6SNusXtxhlQRfnCOSXUtcUA',5,0,'WILL USE NEW BANLIST (doesn\'t appear yet when creating events)\r\n\r\nFormat: Standard\r\nEntry: $10 \r\nRounds: 4 or 5 rounds of Single Sided Swiss (however many we can fit in 3.5 hours)\r\n\r\nWe only have the space from 17:30, the registration starts time is so y\'all can message me/register online.\r\n\r\nA casual tournament. If Q4 GNKs become available, I\'ll supplement those. Otherwise prizes from my prize box\r\n\r\nA single playset of one of my Worlds \'25 Carmen and Offworld Office will be available as a prize (only available for those who didn\'t go to Worlds)\r\n\r\nFor more information, join the [Vancouver Discord Server](https://discord.gg/3G4A73u), and message me; my username is Sindarin.',1,0,0,17150,1,'elev',1,'2025-11-15 23:55:17','2025-12-12 18:07:15',NULL,4,49.280524,-123.107088,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,17150,'2025-12-12 18:07:15',0,NULL,NULL,'','17:00',38,0),(5188,'Rain City Christmas Tournament','2025.12.20.','11:30','Canada','','','New Westminster','Rain City Games','810 Quayside Dr Unit 106, New Westminster, BC V3M 6B9, Canada','ChIJR-DYPafZhVQRkulHtcuxyA0',14,0,'WILL USE NEW BANLIST (doesn\'t appear yet when creating events)\r\n\r\nNOTE THIS IS THE NEW WESTMINSTER LOCATION\r\n\r\nFormat: Standard\r\nEntry: $20 \r\nRounds: ~6 rounds of Single Sided Swiss (however many we can fit in 6 hours)\r\n\r\nLimit 12 attendees. [Reserve your spot here](https://forms.gle/kZJonq5EtHiKytkq9). I will reach out to you to confirm your spot.\r\n\r\nWe only have the space from 11:30, the registration starts time is so y\'all can message me/register online.\r\n\r\nA casual tournament. If Q4 GNKs or the H2 CTK become available, I\'ll supplement those. Otherwise prizes from my prize box\r\n\r\nFor more information, join the [Vancouver Discord Server](https://discord.gg/3G4A73u), and message me; my username is Sindarin.',1,0,0,17150,1,'elev',1,'2025-11-15 23:57:43','2025-12-21 14:02:14',NULL,4,49.200015,-122.911731,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,17150,'2025-12-21 14:02:13',0,NULL,NULL,'','11:00',37,0),(5189,'Eastern Melbourne Sprawl GNK','2025.12.12.','18:30','Australia','','@swankyjimjams on Discord','Mitcham','Games Portal','1-5 Station St, Mitcham VIC 3132, Australia','ChIJoYb9U9I71moRBN_ent5Sv-o',17,0,'*As the supersonic liner broke through the low cloud on its landing approach, Baz took in the view of Melbourne through the window: endless streets of single-family homes, suburbia as far as the eye could see, a far cry from the density of Kota Kali. He was back in* The Sprawl.\r\n\r\nCome on out to the Eastern Suburbs for our first tournament at Games Portal in Mitcham! This is a super casual event where players of all experience levels are welcome. Want to try out a faction or archetype you\'ve not played before? Got some jank you\'ve been brewing and want to put to the test? This is the event for it!\r\n\r\n**Date:** Friday 12 December\r\n**Venue:** Games Portal, Mitcham. The store is a one minute walk from Mitcham Station.\r\n**Tickets:** $10 from the [Games Portal website](https://gamesportal.com.au/collections/events/products/friday-night-netrunner-tournament-ticket-fri-12-dec-2025?ticket=friday-night-netrunner-tournament-ticket-fri-12-dec-2025)\r\n**Format:** [Standard](https://nullsignal.games/players/supported-formats/#standard), using the 25.12 Banlist\r\n\r\nIf the ticket cost is difficult for you please get in touch with me and we\'ll sort something out.\r\n\r\nThe tournament will be four 40-minute rounds of Single-Sided Swiss, finishing up around 9:30pm.\r\nYou\'re welcome to use proxies for any card, just ensure that they are clearly legible for the sake of your opponents. As this is a casual event you are also free to use any alt-arts in your decks but as with the proxies, please avoid using any that will be hard for your opponent to read.\r\n\r\n**Prizing**\r\nEveryone who attends will get a prize in the form of a full playset of an alt-art card, and the top 3 players will win an alt art ID. We will also have a door prize in the form of a [playmat with art by Adam S Doyle](https://www.inkedgaming.com/products/athena-of-the-void-playmat?variant=4657976385), kindly provided by Games Portal.\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions, hop on over to the events channel on the Melbourne Netrunner server on Discord, or send a DM on Discord to @swankyjimjams.',1,0,0,32403,1,'elev',1,'2025-11-16 00:15:36','2025-12-12 10:32:04',NULL,4,-37.817342,145.192702,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,32403,'2025-12-12 10:32:04',0,NULL,126,'**Top 3**\r\nAn alt art ID of MuslihaT, Restoring Humanity, Sable, or Epiphany. Choice of card will be in order of standings.\r\n\r\n**General Prize Pool**\r\n- A 2025 Q2 Game Night Kit featuring full-art versions of Behold! and Audrey v2\r\n- One of each card from the [Send It!](https://www.etsy.com/au/listing/4311915811/send-it-collection-runner-staples-mega?ref=shop_home_feat_3&sts=1&logging_key=b5cfc313766c9fc254aec492cab9cf4591872968%3A4311915811) collection by the Tag Mill (prize provided by Bluestar)\r\n- A range of other alt arts from past events\r\n\r\n**Door Prizes**\r\n- A felt frog (provided by Cr4ter), perfect as the most obvious trojan indicator you could ever have.\r\n- A [playmat with art by Adam S Doyle](https://www.inkedgaming.com/products/athena-of-the-void-playmat?variant=4657976385) (provided by Games Portal)','18:00',39,0),(5190,'Off Meta Month 2026: Restart','2025.12.06.','18:30','','','llblumire on discord','','','','',10,0,'![Restart Format](https://nullsignal.games/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Restart.png)\r\n\r\n**Start times are in GMT**\r\n\r\nInspired by 1.1.1.1, restart will take you back to a previous Startup Format, real or imagined! The format consists of System Gateway, Elevation, and your choice of any single NSG Cycle and NSG Set.\r\n\r\n# [Format Primer and Custom Banlist](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1wEVjFhOVw33UJParSrQj_d6di-8X7GzBgU8viKCIWdY/edit?usp=sharing)\r\n\r\n**Changes from last year**:\r\n- Your Corp deck and Runner deck **MUST** use the same cardpool.\r\n- The [Custom Banlist](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1wEVjFhOVw33UJParSrQj_d6di-8X7GzBgU8viKCIWdY/edit?usp=sharing)\r\n- Prizing available from the Reading Prize Vault **if** you purchase an [optional ticket](https://buy.stripe.com/7sYbJ23mK5e84Eb5BM6oo05). Details on available prizing can be found in the [Format Primer](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1wEVjFhOVw33UJParSrQj_d6di-8X7GzBgU8viKCIWdY/edit?usp=sharing).\r\n- System Update 2021 has been removed in favour of Elevation.\r\n\r\nWhen you deckbuild on NRDB, choose your Identity, check casual to remove all banlists (beneath the deck name), and in the Collection tab choose the sets you are going to build with. If you change sets, or wish to quickly verify your deck is legal, after building your deck you can go to the Setting tab in deck building and choose “Sort by Set” to quickly verify you are under the 5 set restriction. You will need to manually check your deck against the custom banlist.\r\n\r\nThe event will be run on the [Netrunner Event Hub Discord](https://discord.gg/F4dDG5AK3r) with games played on JNET.',1,0,0,43515,1,'elev',6,'2025-11-16 13:21:53','2025-12-06 22:25:40',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,6,NULL,43515,'2025-12-06 22:25:40',0,NULL,NULL,'Prizing will be taken from the Reading Prize Vault **if** you purchase an [optional ticket](https://buy.stripe.com/7sYbJ23mK5e84Eb5BM6oo05). Details on available prizing can be found in the [Format Primer](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1wEVjFhOVw33UJParSrQj_d6di-8X7GzBgU8viKCIWdY/edit?usp=sharing)','18:00',99999,1),(5191,'GNK Post-Worlds SPb','2025.10.22.','19:00','Russia','','amarumacies@gmail.com','Sankt-Peterburg','Pair of Dice','Bronnitskaya Ulitsa, 26, Sankt-Peterburg, Russia, 190013','ChIJG0JqhasxlkYR8_qknN2PA1E',9,0,'',1,0,0,39503,1,'elev',1,'2025-11-16 15:22:59','2025-11-16 20:12:17',NULL,4,59.913677,30.323665,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,39503,'2025-11-16 15:23:11',0,NULL,117,'','18:30',37,0),(5192,'Off Meta Month: Eternal','2025.12.14.','17:00','','','@ wowarlok on discord','','','','',10,0,'![banner](https://i.imgur.com/bCspotW.png)\r\n\r\nCome play with your favorite cards ever in the most powerful of formats!\r\n\r\nWe\'ll be running a 5-6 SSS bracket, depending on attendance, then possibly cut to top 4 single elimination, using the 25.07 points list update. \r\n\r\nThe event starts at 16:00 UTC, there\'ll be a quick player meeting about 10 minutes before the start. \r\nTo keep up with any related information join the discord server: https://discord.gg/sxT7CXsf\r\n\r\nTo make things interesting the top 4 players will win an invite to the second season of the Eternal Super League, rolling down in case the winner isn\'t interested in playing or is already in the league.',1,0,0,7624,1,'elev',6,'2025-11-16 18:26:27','2025-12-15 08:05:30',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,7,NULL,7624,'2025-12-15 08:05:30',0,NULL,NULL,'','16:59',37,1),(5193,'Consumer-Grade 2: Jank at Chucks','2025.12.11.','17:30','United States','WA','@cablooshe on discord','Seattle','Chuck\'s Hop Shop Greenwood','656 NW 85th St, Seattle, WA 98117, USA','ChIJYTPqYycUkFQRUIA3GZD6ykc',12,0,'![ROUND 2](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/cablooshe/imagehosting/refs/heads/main/consumergrade/consumergrade2small.png)\r\n\r\n## WE ARE BACK.\r\n\r\n**Consumer-Grade** makes its return to Seattle! Build with the standard cardpool + current banlist, with one important exception:\r\n\r\n*You are allowed to have up to 6 copies of each card in your deck.*\r\n\r\n6 Humanoid? 6 Oppo Research? 6 Transfer of Wealth? 6 Simulchip? Do it all!\r\n\r\nSome minor restrictions... We are adding a **restrict list** and **Additions to the banlist**, as an update from last year\'s rules. \r\n\r\nThe **Restrict List** limits the amount of copies of a card to its normal amount (usually 3 per list, sometimes limit 1 per deck), and consists of:\r\n\r\n- All Agendas\r\n- Petty Cash\r\n- Nightmare Archive\r\n- Jeitinho\r\n- The Wizards Chest\r\n\r\nThe **Ban list** is the same as standard but with one addition for this format:\r\n\r\n- Au Co\r\n\r\nSorry Jinteki enjoyers, just do 6 Phat 6 bladderwort 6 Anemone in PT instead.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Some minor notes:\r\n\r\n- All the normal rules otherwise still apply, so keep in mind that 6 Transfer of Wealth will be 24 inf and not possible in non-crim. Ampere and Nova players in shambles.\r\n- You can have 6 copies of as many cards as you want, not just one. Feel free to start corp deckbuilding with 6 hedge fund 6 Spin Doctor 6 Measured Response and work your way up from there.\r\n- 12 copies of Matryoshka would have been allowed, but as we will be using the up to date banlist unfortunately you will not be able to do that :( \r\n- Single-sided swiss, I\'m guessing probably 5 rounds based on time. No top cut.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n-----\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions, message me on discord. I\'m on Emerald City Grid and the GLC servers as cablooshe.\r\n\r\nI\'m going to recommend a $10 entry fee to help cover my commission costs but tbh don\'t worry about it if you can\'t pay. Just come play some weird jank! I\'ll start the first round at 5:30pm, but feel free to join in later.\r\n\r\n## Deckbuilding assistance:\r\n\r\nNetrunnerdb allows for making decks with up to 9 copies of a card for draft format. If you want to deckbuild with it, open the decklist you want to edit, and go to Settings->Card Limits->Maximum 9\r\n\r\n![image to the setting](https://i.imgur.com/DRj9BEc.png)\r\n\r\nYou can save the deck using the ID that you\'re planning on using, but I think for publishing it\'ll be weird. You might be able to publish using ABR\'s auto publish feature once I put up the tournament results but if not change your ID to The Masque or The Shadow and it should allow for publishing.\r\n\r\n## Proxy printing\r\n\r\nI no longer have easy access to a printer so I can\'t do requests for proxies, but I\'m going to be pretty lenient on proxy rules for this tournament. If you want to shorthand proxies you can I will ask you to have a more detailed list of proxied cards you can give to your opponent to read though (mainly for corp side). Just make sure you keep Cost, Name, Trash Costs, and if possible some of the card text. I understand not wanting to write out all of Open Market\'s text. I\'ll be especially lenient runner-side since we don\'t need to worry about rnd accesses. \r\n\r\nAlso if you\'re local and don\'t have a library card King County lets you print off like 30 black and white pages for free per week so I\'d recommend doing that. You can get your needed proxies organized into sheets using the new \"Print and Play\" feature on netrunnerdb. I will have some scissors at the event if you need to cut them out when you get there.',1,0,0,31678,1,'elev',6,'2025-11-16 18:47:03','2025-12-12 05:25:13',NULL,4,47.690896,-122.365785,NULL,0,0,'',0,6,NULL,31678,'2025-12-12 05:25:13',0,NULL,NULL,'I\'ve got more alt-arts from my friend S.C. Schmidt, on top of some of what was made last year too!\r\n\r\n**Bold** = new cards\r\n\r\n- 3 variations of Spark of Inspiration (Lobi, Orca, Mass Driver)\r\n- Simulchip\r\n- Spin Doctor\r\n- **Side Hustle**\r\n- **Direct Access**\r\n- **Working Prototype**\r\n- **Wake Implant**\r\n- **Double-sided Spark of Inspiration** (old Lobi+Orca art)\r\n\r\n![Consumer-grade prizes](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/cablooshe/imagehosting/refs/heads/main/consumergrade/cgart.webp)\r\n\r\n\r\nI may also have some additional secret stuff in the works... We\'ll see if I get it done in time lol.','16:30',37,0),(5194,'Off Meta Month: Rebirth','2025.12.13.','18:00','','','@cablooshe on discord','','','','',5,0,'![Rebirth](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/cablooshe/imagehosting/refs/heads/main/rebirth/Rebirth_3.webp)\r\n\r\n**Start time in UTC**\r\n\r\nCome play some standard, but with some identities from the past! I\'ve curated a list of IDs that didn\'t get too much of the limelight and might have some interesting synergies with the new cardpool. Build decks with just these IDs (normal standard IDs are illegal in this format), and see what combos you can put together!\r\n\r\n## Legal IDs\r\n\r\nFor Corp:\r\n\r\n- [Harmony MedTech](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/05001) \r\n- [Jinteki Biotech](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/08012)\r\n- [Harpsichord Studios](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/08092) \r\n- [Harishchandra Ent.](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/10107) \r\n- [GRNDL](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/04097) \r\n- [Titan Transnational](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/07003) \r\n- [Seidr Laboratories](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/25067) \r\n- [The Foundry](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/06021)\r\n\r\nFor Runner:\r\n\r\n- [Silhouette](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/05030)\r\n- [Iain Stirling](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/05028)\r\n- [Khan](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/11027)\r\n- [The Professor](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/03029)\r\n- [Exile](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/03030)\r\n- [Nasir Meidan](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/06017)\r\n- [Edward Kim](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/07028)\r\n- [Alice Merchant](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/12061) (Note, there was a slight error on the NSG page that has this as Omar)\r\n- [Quetzal](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/31001) \r\n\r\nThe event will be run on the [Netrunner Event Hub Discord](https://discord.gg/EfDp7nGxPV) with games played on [JNET](https://www.jinteki.net).',1,0,0,31678,1,'elev',6,'2025-11-16 19:06:56','2025-12-13 18:37:31',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,6,NULL,31678,'2025-12-13 18:37:31',0,NULL,NULL,'','',37,1),(5195,'Off-Meta Month: No Bans Standard','2025.12.06.','10:00 AEDT (UTC+11)','','','','','','','',4,0,'![Banner](https://i.imgur.com/GA1E2an.png[/img)\r\n\r\nBan lists are always the subject of many discussions involving how great it would be if a card was unbanned (or how ridiculous). Between possible turn 1 kill combos involving Drago Ivanov and Touch-ups and controlling gameplans with Nanisivik Grid and Dr. Vientiane Keeling on the Corp side and seemingly unstoppable runner rigs using DreamNet, Endurance, Turbine and World Tree on the Runner side, this will be a high powered format for sure!\r\n\r\nEven if you don\'t find the time to brew a deck using these cards yourself, feel free to come along and bring any regular standard deck you want against these boosted ones and see how far you can go!\r\n\r\nThe event will be run in the Netrunner Event Hub on Discord and registrations will open on tournaments.nullsignal.games at 08:00 AEDT (UTC+11) 2 hours before the start time at 10:00 AEDT (UTC+11) on the 6th of December (it may still be the 5th of December for some of you in Europe, Africa or the Americas). \r\n\r\nDepending on attendance it will be a 5-6 Single Sided Swiss rounds event with a cut to top 4 single elimination.\r\n\r\nThere is no entry cost but also no prizes to win.\r\n\r\nFor a refresher on all of the cards usable at this event that are currently on the standard ban list:\r\n\r\n**CORP**\r\nBellona\r\nCayambe Grid\r\nCyberdex Sandbox\r\nCybersand Harvester\r\nDr. Vientiane Keeling\r\nDrago Ivanov\r\nEngram Flush\r\nFalse Lead\r\nGold Farmer\r\nNanisivik Grid\r\nNBN: RealityPlus\r\nProject Vacheron\r\nSting!\r\nTouch-ups\r\nTributary\r\n\r\n**RUNNER**\r\nBukhgalter\r\nCleaver\r\nDaily Casts\r\nDeep Dive\r\nDreamNet\r\n*Endurance*\r\nInfo Bounty\r\nK2CP Turbine\r\nMatryoshka\r\nMoshing\r\nRezeki\r\nTrick Shot\r\nTsakhia \"Bankhar\" Gantulga\r\nWorld Tree',1,0,0,41571,1,'elev',6,'2025-11-16 21:31:49','2025-12-13 10:08:00',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,6,NULL,41571,'2025-12-06 01:07:06',0,NULL,NULL,'','08:00 AEDT (UTC+11)',37,1),(5196,'Off Meta Month: Getting The Job Done 2025','2025.12.28.','08:00','','','Bemidiot on Discord','','','','',4,0,'![Off Meta Month Banner](https://alwaysberunning.net/photo/3830.png)\r\nShe was the strongest Corp card in history... then rotation took her away from us. It\'s time to bring her back and get the job done. And then some.\r\n\r\nThis tournament is a new format with **[Rashida Jaheem](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/21080) legal**. It follows the current standard ban list with **[Humanoid Resources](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/35039) banned**.\r\n\r\nThe event will be run on the [Netrunner Event Hub](https://discord.gg/3b3cxWFKjc) on Discord. Registrations will open on [t.nullsignal.games](https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/) at 06:00AEST/20:00GMT and the tournament will start at 08:00AEST/22:00GMT.\r\n\r\nThere will be rounds of Single Sided Swiss subject to attendance, then a cut to top 4 single elimination. \r\n\r\nThis tournament is free to enter!\r\n\r\nFor prizing there\'s an awesome [Rashida Themed Jnet Card Back](https://i.imgur.com/MXRY1eK.png) created by Nin for the winner (or top two if we get enough players)\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions feel free to reach out to me on discord, this tournament should be pretty casual so come along and fire some Rashidas.',1,0,0,42305,1,'elev',1,'2025-11-16 23:52:35','2025-12-28 02:25:43',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,6,NULL,42305,'2025-12-28 02:25:43',0,NULL,NULL,'','06:00',37,1),(5197,'Off-Meta Month: Vintage','2025.12.01.','','','','icecreamcollegechris on Discord','','','','',15,0,'![Image](https://i.imgur.com/pgOGrzZ.png)\r\n\r\nCome and play in a decade-old meta as we turn the clocks back to 2015 and experience some memorable matchups such as Prepaid VoicePAD Kate vs Biotic Astro NEH and Faust Whizzard vs Foodcoats EtF. This is an asynchronous event running throughout December, which will be run in the [Netrunner Event Hub](https://discord.gg/4XBpvgNm) on Discord. Players will [register on Cobra](https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/tournaments/4324) and games will be played on jinteki.net\r\n\r\nPlayers will construct decks utilizing the card pool from the 2012 Core Set up to Data and Destiny. There will be no bans, Wireless Net Pavilion will be unique, up to 3x copies of AstroScript Pilot Program can be played, and the modern “NCIGS” rules will be used (Ie. If Street Peddler is hosting 3 events, you can trash it without installing anything). Here are some [example decks](https://www.acoo.net/anr-tournament/802/worlds-championship-2015/) that players can use to guide their deckbuilding process.\r\n\r\nThere will be 4 rounds of closed-decklist DSS with each round being posted weekly starting on the 1st of December. Players will be responsible for scheduling and completing their assigned games in a timely manner, and replays must be shared to confirm results.\r\n\r\nPlayers are free to change their decks and IDs in between rounds! I want to take full advantage of the asynchronous format and give people the freedom to play with a variety of decks.\r\n\r\nThere is no fee to play! However, there will still be prizing in the form of Lilypad jnet card backs for the winner of the event! If more than 8 people play all 4 rounds, then the top 2 players will receive the card backs.',1,0,0,16789,1,'dad',12,'2025-11-17 01:20:18','2025-12-29 16:49:49',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,6,'2025.12.29.',16789,'2025-12-29 16:16:48',1,NULL,NULL,'','',99999,1),(5198,'Off Meta Month: Pawnshop 3','2025.12.21.','10:30','','','Cobalt on discord','','','','',10,0,'![Image](https://nro-public.s3.nl-ams.scw.cloud/voluntary/public-assets/community/cobalt/Pawnshop_3.webp)\r\n\r\nIt\'s Eternal...from a certain point of view.\r\n\r\nAll cards are allowed, save one condition: they must be in the bottom half of [Trash or Busto](https://trash-or-busto.herokuapp.com/ranking). Welcome to the arena of Because We Built It, Jesminder Sareen, Architects of Tomorrow and Reina Roja!\r\n\r\nOur dedicated channel in GLC is [#green-heart](https://discord.com/channels/425105101451952128/824714468898373632), so feel free to join in.\r\n\r\nThe event will be 5-6 40 minute single-sided swiss rounds - player count depending - played on Jinteki.net. If we get more than 15 players, we\'ll do a top 4 cut, otherwise it\'ll just be Swiss. We will be using the [Online Events 2](https://discord.com/channels/372121348300079106/789791168622755840) channel in the Netrunner Events Hub to organise and run the event. You can join the server [here](https://discord.gg/YhFjTpzX) if you have not used it before. The tournament will be managed using Cobra, which can be viewed here: [https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/tournaments/4404](https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/tournaments/4404).\r\n\r\nThe 1st and 2nd place prizing will be a playset of the **Worlds 2025 Carmen or Gourmand** - 1st place will receive their choice, and 2nd place will receive the unclaimed set. If we have a particularly large player count I\'ll put up a 3rd possible prize also. I might ask for a minor contribution towards postage if this would be prohibitively expensive to ship from the UK.\r\n\r\nThe deckbuilding cutoff has passed! The legal identities and cards for this event are:\r\n\r\n**Runner** \r\n[Full card pool](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/deck/view/011bba79-7799-44e3-9ac2-3bb256bf195f) | [Anarch](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/deck/view/81e247a6-38ac-483d-8495-6599537f1e42) | [Criminal](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/deck/view/b9cef4a9-5979-4492-ac10-a0fcc4265037) | [Shaper](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/deck/view/94020a38-d7a2-431c-9778-636f82f5c09f) | [Neutral & Minifaction](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/deck/view/69f49cdc-5ffc-4c47-8281-20d585a0a79a)\r\n* Apex: Invasive Predator\r\n* Ayla \"Bios\" Rahim: Simulant Specialist\r\n* Az McCaffrey: Mechanical Prodigy\r\n* Captain Padma Isbister: Intrepid Explorer\r\n* Dewi Subrotoputri: Pedagogical Dhalang\r\n* Exile: Streethawk\r\n* Iain Stirling: Retired Spook\r\n* Jesminder Sareen: Girl Behind the Curtain\r\n* Khan: Savvy Skiptracer\r\n* Laramy Fisk: Savvy Investor\r\n* Los: Data Hijacker\r\n* Nasir Meidan: Cyber Explorer\r\n* Nathaniel \"Gnat\" Hall: One-of-a-Kind\r\n* Nero Severn: Information Broker\r\n* Nova Initiumia: Catalyst & Impetus\r\n* Null: Whistleblower\r\n* Reina Roja: Freedom Fighter\r\n* Ryō \"Phoenix\" Ōno: Out of the Ashes\r\n* Silhouette: Stealth Operative\r\n* Sunny Lebeau: Security Specialist\r\n* The Professor: Keeper of Knowledge\r\n* Topan: Ormas Leader\r\n\r\n**Corp**\r\n[Full card pool](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/deck/view/af09e352-5287-470a-a0fc-d154d457f387) | [Haas-Bioroid](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/deck/view/77c5f0a6-5dd7-4c71-8ab7-a3711427f0be) | [Jinteki](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/deck/view/1d0ca995-c277-472b-aeb2-1cc1ba2d2d86) | [NBN](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/deck/view/e279ee58-43fc-46a4-a044-dd39a13e303c) | [Weyland](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/deck/view/7a298b99-2ebb-4465-9270-75e0aac69b77) | [Neutral](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/deck/view/5a9455ab-b001-4d57-b960-64ac2d925cba)\r\n* Ampère: Cybernetics For Anyone\r\n* BANGUN: When Disaster Strikes\r\n* Custom Biotics: Engineered for Success\r\n* Cybernetics Division: Humanity Upgraded\r\n* GameNET: Where Dreams are Real\r\n* Haas-Bioroid: Architects of Tomorrow\r\n* Haas-Bioroid: Stronger Together\r\n* Harishchandra Ent.: Where You\'re the Star\r\n* Harmony Medtech: Biomedical Pioneer\r\n* Hyoubu Institute: Absolute Clarity\r\n* Issuaq Adaptics: Sustaining Diversity\r\n* NBN: Making News\r\n* NBN: The World is Yours*\r\n* NEXT Design: Guarding the Net\r\n* New Angeles Sol: Your News\r\n* Nisei Division: The Next Generation\r\n* PT Untaian: Life\'s Building Blocks\r\n* SSO Industries: Fueling Innovation\r\n* Saraswati Mnemonics: Endless Exploration\r\n* Seidr Laboratories: Destiny Defined\r\n* Synapse Global: Faster than Thought\r\n* The Foundry: Refining the Process\r\n* Thunderbolt Armaments: Peace Through Power\r\n* Weyland Consortium: Because We Built It\r\n* Weyland Consortium: Building a Better World\r\n\r\n![Image](https://nro-public.s3.nl-ams.scw.cloud/voluntary/public-assets/community/cobalt/pawnshop3.webp)',1,0,0,41523,1,'elev',6,'2025-11-17 08:28:24','2026-01-04 19:21:34',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,6,NULL,41523,'2025-12-21 13:47:55',0,NULL,NULL,'','10:00',99999,1),(5199,'Montreal Community \"GNK\"','2025.11.18.','18:00','Canada','','','Montréal','L\'Expédition','6571 Rue St-Hubert, Montréal, QC H2S 2M5, Canada','ChIJKxYya2kZyUwRmTCjKijcUrs',13,NULL,'This is NOT using the new 25.10 banlist\r\n\r\n$5 entry fee. Let me know if entry fee will be a barrier for you.\r\n\r\n5 rounds SSS\r\n\r\nThis is a special version of our normal Netrunner GNK. Rather than a normal NSG kit, prizing will consist of an alt-art Steelskin Scarring illustrated by Montreal local artist Caj Wehrstedt, as well as a limited amount of custom faction symbol deckboxes.\r\n\r\n![Image](https://i.etsystatic.com/55088468/r/il/01664d/7262830170/il_794xN.7262830170_ngkm.jpg)	\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nAs always, this is the most casual level of tournament. Bring your jank! Bring your friends! Everyone is welcome.\r\n\r\nThe Steelskin art will be given to all entrants.\r\nTop 4 will have a choice of their desired faction deckbox (to be delivered at some time after the even depending on on-hand quantity)',1,0,0,26646,1,'elev',1,'2025-11-17 14:14:14','2025-11-24 14:02:57',NULL,4,45.536761,-73.604181,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,26646,'2025-11-24 14:02:31',0,NULL,NULL,'','17:30',36,0),(5200,'London Casual Tournament H225 (DATE CHANGE)','2025.12.07.','12:30','United Kingdom','','nickwilson521@gmail.com (@feathermark on Discord) 07796474799','London','Spellbound Games','Arch 4 Angel Ln, London SE17 3FE, UK','ChIJQ5dV6F7aIAIRr1oELzxci5U',8,0,'**NOTE THAT DATE HAS CHANGED TO SUNDAY 7TH DECEMBER**\r\nCome along in the first weekend of December for a **Casual Netrunner Event** with unique prizes brought to you by Phật Gioan Baotixita himself! \r\n_(Yes, that\'s right...! To celebrate the current meta and the banning of False Lead, **(almost) all our prizes are AU Co.-themed!!**)_\r\n\r\n**Ticket Link** is available via [Spellbound Games.](https://spellboundgames.co.uk/products/netrunner-london-casual-tournament-h225-non-ctk-prizing-07-12) The event is **capped at 18 Players** so please reserve your ticket early to avoid disappointment!\r\n\r\n**Registration** at 12pm for a 12.30 start. \r\n\r\n**Rounds** will be dependent on attendance but at least 4 rounds, no Cut. \r\n\r\n**Entry** will be £8\r\n\r\n**Prizing** will be a custom Prize Kit courtesy of ManInTheMoon: \r\n\r\n**1st/2nd Place:** Choice of \"See How They Run\" 2024 CO Playmat OR AU Co. Acrylic Laser-Cut ID\r\n**3rd Place:** Playset Foil Bladderworts\r\n**Top 6**:  Choice of Promos from the LONDON PRIZE VAULT\r\n**Top 12**: ManintheMoon Anemone Promo\r\n**Participation Prizes:**\r\nManintheMoon Stained Glass AU Co. Promo \r\n\r\n...And of course, it wouldn\'t be a London Meta event without The Man himself.\r\n**Ricky Promos** awarded via public vote to:\r\n- Most Creative Deck\r\n- Most Impressive Play\r\n- Best Dressed Netrunner\r\n\r\n**Format** will be standard with 25.12 Banlist Update. (Matryoshka and False Lead Banned) \r\nhttps://nullsignal.games/players/supported-formats/#standard\r\n\r\n**Venue** is Spellbound Games in Elephant & Castle\r\n\r\n**Nearest Stations** are Kennington on the Northern Line or Elephant & Castle on the Northern & Bakerloo Lines.\r\n\r\n**Food** is available 5mins walk from the venue at a selection of High Street Shops & Restaurants! We recommend KOI Ramen Bar 10mins away! :)',1,0,0,21954,1,'elev',1,'2025-11-18 19:09:44','2025-12-17 23:18:00',NULL,4,51.488642,-0.097405,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,21954,'2025-12-17 23:18:00',0,NULL,NULL,'','12:00',37,0),(5201,'TORONTO THROWBACK CTK','2025.12.07.','10:30','Canada','','','Toronto','','123 Queen St W, Toronto, ON M5H 3M9, Canada','ChIJoZ8Hus00K4gRfgPGjqVFR5w',13,0,'This time we\'re playing THROWBACK. It\'s Standard but you get to use either one ID or a playset of one card that wasn\'t banned when it rotated (in each of your decks).¹ ² If you have any questions about the format, just [ask in the discord](https://discord.gg/j3NB8vu)!\r\n\r\nI\'ll have some prizes and I\'ll even have a new custom promo that you haven\'t seen yet. Registration is $10 because it also comes with the aforementioned custom promo. (Please note that if you cannot afford the registration fee, you will not be turned away. Just discuss this with the TO directly [Joshua in the Torsaug Discord].) \r\n\r\nIf you have any questions about the location, the event, or if you wish to borrow decks, please [contact us in our discord](https://discord.gg/j3NB8vu).\r\n\r\nDirections to the event space can be found [here](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1mft8nPUDRx4yedQLRCxUCi-2DQ_BeB-A5uiTcsayO7w/edit?usp=sharing). Start at the [Sheraton Centre Toronto Hotel](https://maps.app.goo.gl/b2EZYoKevVponMaa8) (123 Queen St. W) and then follow our handy guide.\r\n\r\n\r\n¹ If you choose Adam as your ID, you also have access to whichever directives you want. \r\n\r\n² You can play Gang Sign, it should never have been banned. Same with Wu, who cares. Note that this is in addition to the standard 25.12 ban list. Here\'s the full (non-standard) ban list:\r\n\r\nBANNED:\r\nArchived Memories, Kakugo, Clan Vengance, System Seizure, Obokata Protocol, Shipment from Tennin, Whampoa Reclamation, Mass Commercialization, Mars for Martians, Bloo Moose, Tithonium, Salvaged Vanadis Armory, Breached Dome, Rolling Brownout, Reconstruction Contract, SSL Endorsement, Corporate \"Grant\", Death and Taxes, Knobkierie, Kill Switch, PAD Tap, MTI Mwekundu, High-Profile Target, Liza Talking Thunder, Game Changer, Crowdfunding, Slot Machine, Watch the World Burn, Hired Help, Another Day, Another Paycheck, Door to Door, Employee Strike, Enforced Curfew, Government Investigations, Interdiction, Media Blitz, Rumor Mill, Scarcity of Resources, Service Outage, Surveillance Sweep, System Outage, Violet Level Clearance, Friends in High Places, 24/7 News Cycle, Door to Door, Jinteki: Potential Unleashed, Bryan Stinson, Preemptive Action, Arron Marrón, Temüjin Contract, GPI Net Tap, Şifr, Mumbad City Hall, \"Clones are not people\", Museum of History, Clone Suffrage Movement, Government Takeover, Titan Transnational: Investing In Your Future, Housekeeping, Zealous Judge, Sensie Actors Union, Defective Brainchips, Predictive Algorithm, DDoS, Hacktivist Meeting, Dorm Computer, Traffic Jam, Film Critic, Cerebral Imaging: Infinite Frontiers, Estelle Moon\r\n\r\n\r\nUNBANNED:\r\nKabonesa Wu\r\nGang Sign',1,0,0,8982,1,'elev',1,'2025-11-18 23:16:23','2025-12-08 18:51:52',NULL,4,43.651164,-79.384172,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,8982,'2025-12-08 18:51:52',0,NULL,119,'','10:00',37,0),(5202,'Post Turkey DAY CTK 🦃','2025.11.29.','12:20','United States','OR','maninthem00n - on discord or mitm.netrunner@gmail.com','Portland','Players\' Union Games / Experience Point','1702 NE 42nd Ave, Portland, OR 97213, USA','ChIJxT-g4NmglVQRTEJbhNrUPMU',9,0,'I\'m going to be in Portland and have been wanting to run an event there for a while now! I\'ll bring a bunch of cool stuff and make sure you all get some of it. \r\n\r\nStandard Format, Decklists not Required. \r\nNew SBL, No Dolls or False Lead. (Sorry Lia)\r\n\r\nSliding scale entry fee $0-$15. \r\n\r\nStore opens at 12pm, we can start asap and play 6 rounds SSS. If there are more then 14 players we might do a quick single elim cut, but I want to be back to hang out with my hosts and wife before too late in the evening.',1,0,0,37550,1,'elev',11,'2025-11-19 02:15:45','2025-12-04 17:26:15',NULL,4,45.535258,-122.619770,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,37550,'2025-12-04 17:26:15',0,NULL,108,'Some stuff','12:00',37,0),(5203,'Off Meta Month: Costume Party!','2025.12.07.','10:00 AM PST','','','junipertheory2@gmail.com','','','','',13,0,'![costume party image](https://nullsignal.games/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Costume-party.png)\r\n\r\nWelcome to the first online edition of COSTUME PARTY, a custom format brewed up by the witches in the Austin Texas Netrunner community that has been played on Halloween for six years straight. Now, for the first time, being held online!\r\n\r\nThe format is simple:\r\n\r\n* Choose ANY IDENTITY from the history of netrunner, from [Andromeda](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/02083) to [Baz](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/35012) (minus a short banlist, see below)\r\n* Switch that identity\'s faction! Make criminals into anarchs, make HB into NBN, make apex into a shaper, your choice. The influence, decksize, and text remain the same, all that changes is the color.\r\n* Build the rest of your deck with the current standard cardpool and banlist. \r\n\r\nThat\'s all it takes! It\'s a great way to try new deck ideas, and really break netrunner wide open. Want to see what happens when you play a green [egg](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/35046)? Want to bring back [Omar](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/11043), but as a criminal this time? Want to give [the Professor](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/03029) a full [set of knives](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/34079)? Now\'s your opportunity! Also, as a fun bonus: anyone playing a minifaction (apex, adam, sunny) will get access to all of that minifaction\'s cards as if they were in the standard cardpool! ...but since you can\'t BE that minifaction, you\'ll have to spend some of your 25 influence on them. See below for more details.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, not only will we be giving out a prize to the winner of the tournament, but I\'ll be giving out an extra prize to whichever corp/runner decks are, in my very subjective opinion, the coolest idea. So if you\'ve got a great deck idea but don\'t know if it\'s viable, build it anyways!\r\n\r\nThe event will be held in the [Netrunner Event Hub Discord](https://discord.gg/EfDp7nGxPV) and the games will be played on jnet. Do note that none of your decks will be legal, so all decks must be played in the \"casual\" format. Hope to see you there in costume!\r\n\r\n**Banlist:**\r\nRunner:\r\n* [Leela](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/25021)\r\n* [Liza](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/22008)\r\n\r\nCorp:\r\n* [Industrial Genomics](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/06105)\r\n* [Potential Unleashed](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/11054)\r\n* [Skorpios](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/13041)\r\n* [MTI](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/21114)\r\n* [Reality+](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/30051)\r\n\r\n**All standard cardpool bans also apply.**\r\n\r\nAdditionally, if the runner is **Apex**, **Sunny**, or **Adam**, all cards from that faction are added to the standard cardpool for deckbuilding purposes. However, since you *must* shift factions, you would then need to pay for those cards with influence. For example, if you played as criminal sunny, you could include [Security Nexus](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/09047) in your deck, but you\'d have to pay 3 of your 25 inf for each copy. And yes, this means every Adam deck must pay for three starting directives, and thus every Adam deck is down 9 influence to begin with. If you have any further questions, please message me on discord @junipertheory.',1,1,0,34254,1,'elev',6,'2025-11-19 08:48:59','2026-01-22 13:41:54',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,6,NULL,34254,'2025-12-07 22:24:35',0,NULL,NULL,'A number of copies of alt arts from the [Hacking Pixel Art Set](https://www.makeplayingcards.com/sell/marketplace/cardgame-hacking-an-autumn-set.html) that my partner made, will be giving them out to the winners of the tournament and the best costume, along with some other possible prizes.','09:45 AM PST',37,1),(5204,'Off Meta Month - Chimera 🚀 🚀 🚀','2025.12.27.','09:00','','','maninthem00n - on discord or mitm.netrunner@gmail.com','','','','',27,0,'![Chimera 2025](https://imgur.com/dvwpjbe.png)\r\n\r\nChimera! Just the most fun way to play netrunner, honestly! tldr: New randomly generated decks each round neither player knows what\'s in their deck. Drop in and drop out welcome. \r\n\r\nEvent details will be announced during the player meeting in the [Null Signal Games Event Hub.](https://discord.gg/7H9JCMep)\r\n\r\nWe will be using the [omm-announcements](https://discord.com/channels/372121348300079106/1308629603400683575) channel for organization. Pick up the [@Chimera role](https://discord.com/channels/372121348300079106/712997555432325141/1308626011935608912) to get pings about this and future chimera events. \r\n\r\nIf you don\'t know what Chimera is check out [this stream Sokka234 hosted from a previous Chimera event.](https://www.youtube.com/live/Lx40mXhRTck?si=hyi379Dp8knEOpNv)\r\n\r\n\r\n**Start time: 9:00 PST, 12:00 EST, 17:00 UTC**',1,0,0,37550,1,'elev',6,'2025-11-20 02:12:17','2026-01-30 12:03:53',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,6,NULL,37550,'2025-12-27 23:15:45',0,NULL,NULL,'Everyone gets physical prizes just for showing up and playing. \r\n\r\nPaying me, is not required, but it is appreciated as I already sent NBkelly all the money I anticipated the event might bring in :D. If you want to send NBkelly money directly (it\'s great you should if you can you can [do so here.](https://ko-fi.com/nbkelly)','09:00',37,1),(5205,'Adelaide Cube Draft','2025.12.13.','11:30','Australia','','spaceicenr on Discord','Adelaide','Good Games Adelaide','88 Grenfell St, Adelaide SA 5000, Australia','ChIJSUEmI-kWNQARahybrMcUWyk',NULL,NULL,'A casual Netrunner cube draft tournament for 6-10 players. No need to bring your own cards, but please bring tokens, and you do need a basic understanding of how to play already.\r\n\r\n-- What\'s a Cube Draft? --\r\nIf you haven\'t played a cube draft before, it\'s basically the best thing ever! Here are the basics:\r\n\r\n      1.   The cube is a pool of Netrunner cards we\'ll all be building our decks from on the day\r\n      2.   Drafting is the process by which we pick our cards. You start with a hand of 14 cards, pick 1 and pass the rest left, then receive cards from your right and repeat. Then repeat until you have 42 cards each for corp and runner.\r\n      3.   Build decks from those cards, ignoring the normal rules for influence, factions or 3-per-deck limit. Deck sizes are 30 card minimums.\r\n      4.   Play a 3 swiss round tournament with the decks we have created. Games are to 6 points.\r\n\r\nThe cube only has cards for 10 people so be sure to reserve your place (and please let us know ASAP if you need to cancel). Reserve your place by marking yourself as \'Going\' here, or by letting me know in person or on Discord.\r\n\r\nEntry is $6 per person.\r\n\r\n-- Card list --\r\nThis is a singleton cube draft using cards from every era of Netrunner.\r\n\r\nThe list of cards included in the cube can be found here: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/130u3FxkhX0gmFkqC46kMXkd9m7IY3X6hUwZGQXr1_bo/edit?usp=sharing',0,0,0,24590,1,'elev',1,'2025-11-21 05:17:25','2025-11-24 09:12:55',NULL,0,-34.924030,138.603083,NULL,0,0,'',0,5,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'A selection of official and fan alt-art cards from the beefy Adelaide prize pool! prizes for everyone!','11:30',99999,0),(5206,'Eternal Comes to Seattle 🥹 👍','2026.01.08.','1730','United States','WA','','Seattle','','656 NW 85th St, Seattle, WA 98117, USA','ChIJ30pwYScUkFQRmVxWwKdrbn8',10,0,'This event will be an Eternal tournament at the time of the weekly Chuck\'s Hop Shop Thursday meetup. Usually we have enough time to play 5 rounds of single-sided Swiss if we get started at 5:30pm.\r\n\r\nThe Eternal legal cards as well as the Eternal point list deck-building restriction can be found here:  https://nullsignal.games/players/supported-formats/\r\n\r\nPlayers that are new to the format might find this neat document helpful for getting started: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1SmmqHqkaESGLeeg0ulsckZyly-jQkFuH_2YfYKSPLOc/edit?tab=t.0#heading=h.6bpkxxgwdaz1\r\n\r\nFurther help getting into the format can be found for those who ask in the #eternal channel of the ECG discord.',1,0,0,31051,1,'elev',6,'2025-11-21 06:17:45','2026-01-09 17:46:55',NULL,4,47.690900,-122.365767,NULL,0,0,'',0,7,NULL,31051,'2026-01-09 17:46:55',0,NULL,NULL,'Thanks to ManintheMoon for providing some sweet Eternal themed alt art prizing for this event!','1730',37,0),(5207,'TLV Startup','2025.11.20.','','Israel','','','Tel Aviv-Yafo','Freak - A Legendary Place','Dizengoff St 50, Tel Aviv-Yafo, Israel','ChIJj3ZsFJFLHRURBgYkzRZHAAw',6,NULL,'',1,0,0,36041,1,'elev',11,'2025-11-21 17:22:43','2025-11-24 09:12:12',NULL,4,32.075699,34.775459,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,36041,'2025-11-21 17:22:43',0,NULL,NULL,'','',37,0),(5208,'Off-Meta Month: 3-point Eternal!','2025.12.01.','13:00','','','@manveruppd (Discord or Stimslack)','','','','',18,4,'![Image](https://ibb.co/pBZ0xrPR)\r\n\r\nIt\'s Eternal, but 3 Points Only!\r\n=======================\r\n\r\n**Cobra link: https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/tournaments/4347\r\nSelf-registration will be live on Sunday!**\r\n\r\nWe love Eternal, but, with so many powerful cards on offer, it can be hard to find slots for some old beloved staples. Limiting deckbuilding to only use 3 rather than 7 points from the [Eternal Points List](https://nullsignal.games/players/supported-formats/#eternal) will hopefully open up deckbuilding and allow some less commonly-played cards to sneak back in. It may also lower the power level of the format just a smidge so that early mistakes are not quite as harshly punished, making it more welcoming for newer players.\r\n\r\n3 points still allows you to take a full playset of one of the most powerful cards ever printed or a combination of 1- or 2-point cards. This means you still get to play with some of the most powerful cards ever printed, which is one of the big draws of the format!\r\n\r\nFormat\r\n======\r\nThis tournament will use the [Eternal Points List 25.07](https://nullsignal.games/players/supported-formats/#eternal), but with the following changes:\r\n1. You may only pick cards up to a total value of 3 points (instead of 7) from each of the Corp and Runner lists. This means [Rumor Mill](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/11022) is functionally banned. You may include up to a full playset of each pointed card you select.\r\n2. [Jackson Howard](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/04015) goes from 2 to **1 point**.\r\n3. [Spin Doctor](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/card/30053) goes from 1 to **0 points**.\r\nCards listed as \"Banned\" are banned for this event as well. We recommend you use the [jinteki.net](jinteki.net) deckbuilder, setting the deck type to \"Eternal\", to build 3-point Eternal decks.\r\n\r\nThe Spin Doctor and Jackson Howard point changes were suggested by Eternal Format Curation lead wowarlok in order to ensure that Corps always have access to a baseline effect. Please note that this change is not reflected in the Jinteki.net deckbuilder, so you will have to build your Corp decks to 4 points (or 5 if you are including both cards). Please note that those changes apply only for 3-point Eternal. \r\n\r\nEvent Structure\r\n=============\r\nThis event will be run \"league-style\". Each week (paired on Mondays starting on December 1) you will play a Double-Sided Swiss round against your opponent, at a time that you will arrange together via the [NSG Events Discord](https://discord.gg/EfDp7nGxPV). We will run it out of one of the Asynchronous channels, if you\'re not sure which one we\'re in ask in #omm-general.\r\nYou will be able to drop in/drop out freely between rounds. Please let me know if you intend to drop out (or join) before I pair the next round each Monday.\r\nWe will aim for 5 rounds. However, based on people\'s availability over Christmas and New Year, we may decide to take 2 weeks to do round 4, in which case it\'ll be just 4 rounds.\r\nIf there are enough participants to justify it, and people want to, we\'ll run a top-4 cut in early January, at a date that\'ll suit all participants and won\'t clash with Showdown or CBI.\r\n\r\n**YOU CAN CHANGE YOUR DECKS BETWEEN ROUNDS!**  You don\'t have to stick with the same decklist throughout the tournament.\r\n\r\nAnyone planning on livestreaming their 3PE decks, please let me know and I\'ll share the link and time!',1,0,1,9511,1,'elev',12,'2025-11-21 21:10:19','2026-01-30 17:31:12',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,6,NULL,9511,'2026-01-30 10:45:48',0,NULL,NULL,'','11:00',37,1),(5209,'Off-Meta Month: Time Branch','2025.12.28.','10:00','','','aksu on discord','','','','',3,0,'![Time Traveller](https://imgur.com/a/1yt4j69)\r\n\r\nRan on the event hub server: https://discord.gg/kACvDq2Wpf \r\n\r\nStart time: https://timee.io/20251228T1000?tl=Off%20Meta%20Month%20-%20Time%20Branch \r\n\r\nWhat if a time traveller stepped on a branch sometime in the past and the butterfly effect somehow caused Elevation’s release to only rotate System Update 2021 and Red Sand Cycle?\r\n\r\nLegal sets/cycles:\r\n- Elevation\r\n- Liberation\r\n- Borealis\r\n- System Gateway\r\n- Magnum Opus\r\n- Ashes\r\n- Reign and Reverie\r\n- Kitara\r\n\r\nEvent will be the normal standard banlist with the following changes:\r\n\r\nUnbanned:\r\n\r\nCorp:\r\n- Sting!\r\n- Touch-ups\r\n\r\nRunner:\r\n- cleaver\r\n- Daily Casts\r\n- Moshing\r\n- Info Bounty\r\n\r\nAll rotated cards are legal based on their legality on the last banlist they where on.\r\n\r\n(goal for this banlist is just to unban some cards that got hit in the econ wipe of elevation release.)',1,0,0,40206,1,'elev',6,'2025-11-22 14:00:04','2025-12-29 15:34:55',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,6,NULL,40206,'2025-12-29 15:34:55',0,NULL,NULL,'','10:00',37,1),(5210,'OKORINA 7 (Off-Meta Month)','2025.12.20.','','','','testrunning on discord','','','','',7,0,'![Image](https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/1437774562598191125/1437774861907923008/Okorina_3.png?ex=692449af&is=6922f82f&hm=f292d12afc23920119009b13846c745852d1ab56a5c7f7def21af2b1829a3014&=&format=webp&quality=lossless)\r\n\r\n# OKORINA 7\r\n\r\n_“You aren’t the Only Kind Of Runner In New Angeles.”_\r\n\r\n – Kati Jones\r\n\r\nWhat if Ms. Jones was wrong? In the Only Kind Of Runner In New Angeles (OKORINA) format, we imagine what Netrunner would be like if you could take on a new Netrunner friend as your identity.\r\n\r\nWelcome to the 7th edition of this wonderful format. The format was invented by @sanjay. \r\n\r\n## Format Details\r\n\r\nInstead of choosing a standard identity, you pick a non-neutral, unique connection resource, and start the game with that as your identity after triggering any “when installed” abilities as if you had installed it.\r\n\r\nOn the corp side, instead of picking a standard identity, you pick a non-neutral agenda, and start the game with that as your identity after triggering any “when scored” abilities as if you had scored it.\r\n\r\nEach legal resource and agenda has received a minimum decksize and a maximum influence size (as well as starting link and subtypes).\r\n\r\nThe full list of legal IDs is [here](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1v9lb18mvjbpQVqA83WDMg7sdjGlq6J_MuP88Lmbb19k/edit?usp=sharing).\r\n\r\n\r\n## Tournament Details\r\n\r\n\r\nThe Tournament will be held online via the NSG [Event Hub Discord](https://discord.gg/rNNYKrGc). Registrations is now open [here](https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/ig5t)\r\n\r\nTournament will start 16:00 UTC and we will play SSS for probably 6-8 Rounds depending on Number of Players, followed by a top 3 single elimination cut. Update: Due to probably fewer player, we will probably play fewer rounds and no cut.\r\n\r\nBe in the Discord 15:45 UTC so that we can start on time.\r\n\r\n## Prizes\r\n\r\nThis is a community event for fun. However Winner has the traditional prize of designing a new ID for the OKORINA (from eg neutral cards). Also Fame and Glory.',1,0,0,15130,1,'elev',6,'2025-11-23 15:24:12','2026-01-22 13:41:45',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,6,NULL,15130,'2025-12-21 09:07:06',0,NULL,NULL,'','',37,1),(5211,'Prairie Grid Asynch CTK - 25H1','2025.11.23.','','United States','NE','@GameOfDroids','Omaha','Spielbound Board Game Cafe','3229 Harney St, Omaha, NE 68131, USA','ChIJ20BnT12Ok4cRzSX_v7vXdP8',15,NULL,'',1,0,0,14429,1,'elev',11,'2025-11-23 18:13:14','2025-11-24 09:12:24',NULL,4,41.256458,-95.961230,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,14429,'2025-11-23 18:13:14',0,NULL,119,'','',37,0),(5212,'Community Vault Holiday CTK @ L\'Expedition','2025.12.13.','10:30','Canada','','Odonuvo (Discord)','Montréal','L\'Expédition','6571 Rue St-Hubert, Montréal, QC H2S 2M5, Canada','ChIJKxYya2kZyUwRmTCjKijcUrs',9,0,'![image](https://i.ibb.co/rKTDYwsd/PXL-20251121-130317266.jpg)\r\n\r\nIt\'s the holidays which means it\'s the season of giving. I\'m back from worlds with goodies from the artist colony and I\'ve dug deep into the vault and pulled out some rare stuff from the past to make our own casual tournament kit.\r\n\r\n$10 entry fee. 6 single sided swiss rounds (you play one side per round)\r\n\r\nThis is a casual tournament. Bring your jank! Bring your friends! Everyone is welcome.',1,0,0,32798,1,'elev',6,'2025-11-24 14:41:39','2025-12-13 20:13:40',NULL,4,45.536761,-73.604181,NULL,0,0,'https://www.facebook.com/events/809109218608473',0,1,NULL,32798,'2025-12-13 20:13:40',0,NULL,NULL,'Winner: 1 playset of any Worlds 2025 card\r\nTop 2: choice of playmat (World Tree from Worlds 2023 & Worlds 2021 False Lead)\r\nTop 4: choice of ID (PCB ari/Lenticular nebula )\r\nParticipation: End of the Line  + any 1 playset from the community prize pool\r\n\r\nRaffled: 1 choice of worlds 25 prizing drafted after the winner (I only have 1 spare of each)','10:00',39,0),(5213,'Ligue asynchrone Toulouse Q1 2026','2026.01.07.','','France','','@Yidaho and @ galehar on GLC and District99','Toulouse','','95 Gd Rue Saint-Michel, 31400 Toulouse, France','ChIJdyFryn-8rhIRuIC5Qo2CzlE',NULL,NULL,'Ligue asynchrone IRL de Toulouse : Q1 2026.\r\n\r\nDate de la première round : Mercredi 7 Janvier\r\nFin : au plus tard fin Mars\r\n\r\nL\'idée c\'est de faire les parties de la ligue les mercredis soirs lors des meet-ups, 1 round tous les 2 semaines, mais ça peut être 1 round par semaine si toutes les parties ont été jouées\r\n\r\nPossibilité de drop in / drop out selon les disponibilités\r\n\r\nEntre 6 et 8 rounds en DSS (Double Sided Swiss). Possibilité de changer ses decks entre les rounds\r\n\r\nParticipation de 4€\r\nLien discord de la communauté française netrunner : https://discord.gg/YumtxJcXWq',0,0,0,23926,1,'elev',12,'2025-11-25 11:58:30','2025-12-18 20:54:33',NULL,0,43.588885,1.445662,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,128,'','',39,0),(5214,'Torneo Minas Tirith','2025.12.07.','16:00','Spain','','philspectrum13@gmail.com','Santander','Palacio de Exposiciones y Congresos de Santander','C/ Real Racing Club, 3, 39005 Santander, Cantabria, Spain','ChIJS7LRw6JLSQ0R37tB66yk8jo',6,0,'# Torneo Netrunner durante las jornadas Minas Tirith en Santander.\r\n\r\nSe jugarán cuatro rondas single de 40 minutos en formato Startup con el [Startup Balance Update 25.11](https://nullsignal.games/blog/startup-balance-update-25-11/)  que incluye las siguientes restricciones:\r\n\r\n## Set legales\r\n\r\n* System Gateway\r\n* Elevation\r\n* Liberation Cycle (The Automata Initiative y Rebellion Without Rehearsal)\r\n\r\n\r\n## Construcción de mazos\r\n\r\nEn el formato Startup, además de los banlist, una baraja de Corp solo puedo contener un máximo de **cuatro cartas** de agenda con valor de agenda de **tres** o mayor\r\n\r\n\r\n## Banlist\r\n\r\nCORP:\r\n* NBN: Reality Plus\r\n* Pharos\r\n* Tributary\r\n\r\nRUNNER:\r\n* Cleaver\r\n* Coalescence\r\n* S-Dobrado',1,1,0,53595,1,'elev',6,'2025-11-26 08:44:33','2025-12-08 07:39:12',NULL,4,43.475234,-3.791738,NULL,0,0,'',0,11,NULL,53595,'2025-12-07 21:41:22',0,NULL,NULL,'','11:00',0,0),(5215,'Hijacked Münster: Ersatzturnier in Köln!','2025.11.29.','13:00','Germany','','Tyrus auf Discord','Köln','Station - Bar, Cafe & Restaurant','Marzellenstraße 50 - 56, 50668 Köln, Germany','ChIJmw5W46Qlv0cRyRLXsmhIfgM',10,0,'Als spontaner Turnierersatz für das leider ausfallende Turnier in Münster möchten wir am Samstag den 29.11 ein Turnier in der Station Bar, Köln! \r\nIch plane aktuell mit 6 Runden SSS und 40 Minuten pro Runde! \r\n\r\nVorläufiger Zeitplan:\r\n 12:30: Registrierung 13:00: Turnierstart 14:30: Mittagspause 15:15: Runde 3 18:30 Ende & Preisverteilung\r\n\r\nEs gibt einen Preispool aus alten Kits und Karten und eine potentielle Option auf ein CTK Kit je nach Interesse und Anzahl der Leute. Wir veranschlagen 8 Euro als Basis (ggf. weniger je nachdem wie viele Leute kommen) und würden geben falls wenn es jeder möchte einen kleinen Aufpreis nehmen um das CTK Kit zu spielen wenn alle Lust haben und wir über 8 Leute sind. Der Grundpreis deckt dir Kosten und ein neues Kit fürs neue Jahr! Hier schon mal vielen danke an Colandril und Tradon',1,1,1,31154,1,'elev',1,'2025-11-27 17:58:37','2026-02-25 16:06:24',NULL,4,50.944075,6.956088,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,31154,'2025-11-30 11:33:02',0,'Europe/Berlin',95,'','12:30',37,0),(5216,'Sapporo 2026 H1 Tournament (2026/02)','2026.02.07.','13:20','Japan','','ramus42 (Discord)','Sapporo','boardgame shop friends','Japan, 〒060-0051 Hokkaido, Sapporo, Chuo Ward, Minami 1 Jōhigashi, 2-chōme−１−３ 和興ビル2階、〒060-0051','ChIJ__-zn4IpC18RLwdgueAmNew',NULL,NULL,'We\'re hosting a Netrunner tournament in Sapporo.\r\n\r\nTime: February 7, 2026, 13:00-19:00 (first round at 13:20, please arrive at 13:00)\r\nLocation: boardgame shop friends (https://maps.app.goo.gl/yNXbzxgVc8W3StgD7)\r\nEntry Fee: 2000 JPY\r\nFormat: Standard\r\nTournament Format: Single-sided Swiss, 7 rounds\r\n\r\nPrizing is a mix of prizes from older CO/CTK/Championship kits.',0,0,0,4153,1,'elev',1,'2025-11-29 10:52:43','2025-12-14 08:34:59',NULL,0,43.060043,141.358798,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,99,'','13:00',39,0),(5217,'Orange County - CTK H1','2025.12.06.','12:00','United States','CA','Discord: JoeLetsG0#5649','Orange','Dice House Games','940 E Lincoln Ave, Orange, CA 92865, USA','ChIJ9daj29DV3IARVuWfnR1IMnw',4,0,'Come join us at Dice House Games for another fun tournament.\r\n\r\nAll players welcomed. Let\'s jam some Netrunner, have a great time, and score some prizes!\r\n\r\n$7 entry fee. Registration at 11:45 AM. First round at 12:00 PM.\r\n\r\nStandard format.\r\nDouble Sided Swiss.\r\nPrinted proxy cards are legal.\r\n\r\nFOLLOWING Standard Banlist 25.12',1,0,0,2975,1,'elev',11,'2025-11-29 16:52:00','2025-12-07 03:54:58',NULL,4,33.836436,-117.843404,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,2975,'2025-12-07 03:54:58',0,NULL,119,'Additional prizing from the 2025 Q3 Game Night Kit and earlier kits.','11:45',37,0),(5218,'NANPC - 2026 Off The Grid Midwest Championship','2026.06.06.','10:30','United States','MN','anroffthegrid@gmail.com','Roseville','Gamezenter','1975 County Road B2 W, Roseville, MN 55113, USA','ChIJZaw8WvYrs1IReYlva_ezoBU',NULL,NULL,'All details TBD. Keep an eye on this spot.',0,1,0,8349,1,'unknown',15,'2025-11-29 17:53:25','2025-11-30 11:44:59',NULL,0,45.015212,-93.184092,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','10:00',0,0),(5219,'Winter GNK','2015.02.14.','','United States','NC','','Durham','Atomic Empire','3400 Westgate Dr #14b, Durham, NC 27707, USA','ChIJqTY1YFfmrIkRPRh89ogVgvY',16,NULL,'[Event info](https://www.atomicempire.com/Store/Event/444)',1,0,0,6484,1,'oac',1,'2025-11-29 18:40:19','2025-11-30 11:41:37',NULL,3,35.965814,-78.962901,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,6484,'2025-11-29 18:40:19',0,NULL,33,'','',0,0),(5220,'Atomic Empire 2015 Store Championship','2015.03.07.','','United States','NC','','Durham','Atomic Empire','3400 Westgate Dr #14b, Durham, NC 27707, USA','ChIJqTY1YFfmrIkRPRh89ogVgvY',25,8,'[Event info](https://www.atomicempire.com/Store/Event/436)\r\n\r\nNote: There is only a record of final standings, not top 8 order after Swiss. There is only a record of player faction, not identity.',1,0,0,6484,1,'oac',2,'2025-11-29 18:51:02','2025-11-30 11:41:55',NULL,3,35.965814,-78.962901,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,6484,'2025-11-29 18:51:02',0,NULL,34,'','',0,0),(5221,'Mutually Assured Construction - Merry Janksmas!','2025.12.13.','11:30','United States','PA','jameskbarnhart@gmail.com','Philadelphia','Redcap\'s Corner','3850 Lancaster Ave, Philadelphia, PA 19104, USA','ChIJt_84DvfGxokR2PTzGnW5FlI',4,0,'Merry Janksmas netrunners!\r\n\r\nOn Saturday December 13th at 11AM there will be a Charity Netrunner tournament at Redcap\'s Corner, organised by Mutually Assured Construction!\r\n\r\nWhat on earth is Janksmas?\r\n\r\nJanksmas is a charity tournament format aimed at raising money to help fight houselessness and food insecurity. Inspired by Janksgiving ,started in NYC by shiiuga in 2019. \r\n\r\nHow does it work?\r\n\r\nWhat do Netrunner players love doing more than anything else? That’s right! Rage quitting on JNet. Playing bad jank. Well, boy do I have the format for you! \r\n\r\nAfter you register for the event, you will contact the SkoolKnight4 (the TO) on the Neo Philly discord to receive your first set of Jank rolls using the handy dandy Janksgiver (very kindly made by @solemn_storm) which can be found here: https://jankgiver.solemn.website/. You will then choose one full set of those rolls for each side, Corp & Runner, and build decks with them using the deckbuilding rules below. Then, you bring your decks to the tournament and face off against everyone else’s jank until we crown the ultimate jank champion (jankion?), all while raising some money for a good cause.\r\n\r\nWhere: Redcap\'s Corner\r\n\r\nWhen: Please arrive by 11AM EST\r\n\r\nFormat: Standard (with a twist) 3+ Rounds Double Sided Swiss, 90 min rounds.\r\n\r\nDonation/Buy In: Entry will be a minimum donation of $15, with no maximum donation. Go with your heart, but don’t go broke. The first $5 will contribute to a store credit prize pool (paid to top players, the second $5 will go the MAC Event Organizing Fund (to facilitate future events), and all other donated funds will go to the approved charity of the winner\'s choice.\r\n\r\nEveryone who donates will receive a playset of MAC Reaper Function Promos as a door prize. The winner will get to take home the coveted Janksmas trophy that I’ve definitely already purchased and am not leaving until the last minute. Most importantly will get to choose the charity that will receive the balance of the group donation. There will be other prizes in the form of Promos, Tokens, etc.\r\n\r\nMulligan Rules\r\n\r\nIf you really don’t like any of your initial rolls on one side, you can take one free mulligan. You may only do this for ONE SIDE, and you must use your Mulliganed roll, even if you think it’s worse than the first 3. Sometimes the jank gods are not smiling on us. There are currently no other known reasons to get a mulligan, but weird stuff happens all the time, so if you think you deserve one, ping me and I’ll take a look. To activate a reroll, the TO in the Neo Philly Netrunner Discord and tell me which side you are choosing to reroll. I will do the roll for you on the bot.\r\n\r\nDeckbuilding Rules\r\n\r\nDeckbuilding rules are as follows: You must use 1 whole set of rolls from the 3 Janksgiver gives you for each side. You may not take the ID from one of the three rolls and use the cards from another, for example. Your deck must include 3 copies of every card included in the roll you choose for each side. Cards in your jank rolls are all out of faction for the rolled ID and DO NOT count towards your influence limit. EVERY ID regardless of side or faction has an influence value of 6 IN PLACE of its printed influence value. Remember, your rolled cards don’t cost influence. This influence is to spend on cards to tie your rolls together into a combo. All corps, regardless of faction, get a full set of 3 Spin Doctors with no additional influence cost. Spend your influence on something fun. All other Standard Format deckbuilding rules apply. Standard card pool and ban list is in effect. Every ID uses its printed minimum deck size and Corp decks must maintain a standard agenda density for their size.\r\n\r\nJankgiver note: Rolls will be made using Standard Only. We are not using rotated cards at this event.',1,0,0,44167,1,'elev',1,'2025-12-01 13:00:21','2025-12-17 18:41:26',NULL,0,39.961333,-75.199209,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,44167,'2025-12-17 18:41:26',0,NULL,NULL,'- MAC Reaper Function Promos\r\n- 3D Printed Tokens\r\n- Older Promos\r\n- More Goodies like a goofy trophy!','10:30',37,0),(5222,'Netrunner gaming at OM',NULL,'17:00','Germany','','weinschwaermer@web.de','Koblenz','Restaurant OM','Bechelstraße 23, 56073 Koblenz, Germany','ChIJtaZ6M01jvkcRdRJLQSNCLng',NULL,NULL,'Dear Runners and Corps,\r\n\r\non Saturday, December 6th we will meet up in Restaurant Om at Koblenz, Bechelstraße 23 for some rounds of Android Netrunner gaming in Standard format.\r\nSanta Claus will bring one promo card for each participant: Seamless Launch, Popup-Window, Peace in our time, Dreamnet.\r\nSo far, three players signed up, a fourth player would be great.',0,0,0,19089,1,'elev',8,'2025-12-01 16:33:48','2025-12-06 09:16:30',NULL,0,50.361477,7.581464,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'','17:00',37,0),(5223,'GNK @ Craving For A Game','2025.12.13.','13:00','Canada','','sokkaanr@gmail.com','Surrey','Craving For A Game','10153 King George Blvd #2293, Surrey, BC V3T 2W1, Canada','ChIJo6aWiNPZhVQRPGAkKfDy_X8',7,0,'The event will be from 1pm to 5pm. We will play 6 rounds of single-sided swiss. \r\n\r\nThis event has a player limit of 8. Please RSVP at the following link and await a confirmation message before attending.\r\n\r\n[https://forms.gle/J9H24t5PQyiB2EpNA](https://forms.gle/J9H24t5PQyiB2EpNA)\r\n\r\nIf we get 8 players, cost will be $10 per person, which includes store credit for the top 3 ($25, $10, $5). If we get less than 8 players, the cost may be adjusted and store credit removed. \r\n\r\nDecklists are not required.',1,0,0,18976,1,'elev',1,'2025-12-02 05:33:00','2025-12-15 01:15:04',NULL,4,49.186084,-122.849663,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,18976,'2025-12-15 01:15:04',0,NULL,112,'','12:45',37,0),(5225,'St. Hackersburg Showdown: Netrunner Online Cube Draft Derby v2.0','2025.11.09.','','Russia','','','Saint Petersburg','','','ChIJnW9Kx4w3lkYR5MklR1rKR_o',8,NULL,'',1,0,0,16188,1,'elev',6,'2025-12-02 08:42:23','2025-12-06 16:42:59',NULL,4,59.934260,30.335094,NULL,0,0,'',0,5,NULL,16188,'2025-12-02 08:42:23',0,NULL,NULL,'','',37,0),(5226,'X-mass GNK @Black Oil, Brno','2025.12.18.','16:30','Czechia','','krasty23 (at) gmail.com or just Krasty everywhere else (Discord, Slack, etc.)','Jihomoravský kraj','BLACK OIL – Gaming & Social Hub','Kotlářská 51a, 602 00 Brno-střed, Czechia','ChIJnQu_9WmUEkcRtVnjhqAs4u0',9,0,'Malé vánoční posezení u nejlepší  hry na této a daších planetách. Budeme hrát buď 3 kola double side swissu nebo 5 kol single side swissu.   \r\nRegistrace: 16:00   \r\nStart: 16:30   \r\nPříspěvek (alespoň): 200,- Kč (10 euro)',1,0,0,15340,1,'elev',1,'2025-12-02 18:18:25','2025-12-20 10:04:33',NULL,4,49.208263,16.602794,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,15340,'2025-12-18 21:50:06',0,NULL,123,'Pokud stihnou dorazit, tak budou nejake specialni proma s vanocni tematikou!!!   \r\n...a dalsich  spousty ruznych krasnych karet...','16:00',39,0),(5227,'ECG Meet up CTK!','2025.12.05.','5:30','United States','WA','','Seattle','Chuck\'s Hop Shop Greenwood','656 NW 85th St, Seattle, WA 98117, USA','ChIJYTPqYycUkFQRUIA3GZD6ykc',8,NULL,'This will be the same meet-up format we have been running the last few months 5 rounds SSS no top cut. Bonus door prizes as first come first serve. Drop in/out welcome. \r\n\r\nStandard format.\r\nDecklists not required.\r\n\r\n[Invite link to Seattle Discord ECG](https://discord.gg/8VfeD4qx84) \r\n\r\n$10 donation to help restock bagel boxes appreciated, but not required. Please come **don\'t pay if it would be a hardship** ❤️',1,0,0,37550,1,'elev',11,'2025-12-04 17:18:43','2025-12-25 03:03:50',NULL,3,47.690896,-122.365785,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,119,'8 players FireRL wins CBI invite with 2nd place. Event not conclude-able from ABR bugs!','5:00',39,0),(5228,'Dallas December Dustup','2025.12.13.','11:30','United States','TX','lukegschlenker@gmail.com','Dallas','Common Ground Games','1314 Inwood Rd, Dallas, TX 75247, USA','ChIJn-TRwwucToYRLQVUliOhUic',12,0,'Come down and compete at the Dallas December Dustup!  Well be competing for glory and clairerio11 alt arts and a tbd top prize (probably something from common ground itself)!\r\n\r\nEntry will be $5 at the front.  We will do SSS with doors opening at 11:00 and round one starting at 11:30, with 40 minute rounds and a 45 minute lunch break in the middle.',1,0,0,40916,1,'elev',1,'2025-12-05 14:37:02','2025-12-14 00:21:30',NULL,4,32.805327,-96.851893,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,40916,'2025-12-14 00:21:30',0,NULL,118,'clairerio11 Alt Arts','11:00',37,0),(5229,'Calgary 2025 Xmas Special','2025.12.27.','11:30','Canada','','hereticdave@outlook.com','Calgary','Good Cheer Brewing','1220 20 Ave SE, Calgary, AB T2G 1M8, Canada','ChIJZUzZJgB7cVMRAQJdWTd4mrY',14,0,'This will be a **STANDARD format event**\r\n\r\n**Cobra:** [https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/z1cp](https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/z1cp)\r\n\r\n**Entry:** $5\r\n\r\n**Location:** Good Cheer Brewery\r\n\r\n**What you need to bring!**\r\n\r\n* Yourself\r\n* Both a legal Corp and Runner deck, constructed from any cards in the Core sets, System Gateway and Elevation along with any Cycle: Ashes, Borealis, Liberation\r\n* Each deck should be uniformly sleeved in opaque backed sleeves\r\n* Counters, dice and tokens to track effects, credits etc\r\n\r\n**What you need to know!**\r\n\r\n* Single sided swiss format [you will play an opponent with only one deck]\r\n* Duration: Noon until 4-5pm\r\n* Each match time will be 40 minutes, there will be a visible count down, time will be called at 5 minutes and again when complete\r\n* When time is called the active player finishes their turn and their opponent gets a final turn\r\n* Matches are won via Runner Flatline, 7 Agenda points or in the case of time being called, most Agenda points',1,0,0,41926,1,'elev',1,'2025-12-05 22:32:31','2025-12-28 03:24:06',NULL,4,51.036031,-114.035881,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,41926,'2025-12-28 03:24:06',0,NULL,126,'As the Q4 kits aren\'t out yet this will use a Q3 kit, here\'s your chance to get that Alarm Clock you missed last time :D\r\n\r\nAs it is Christmas there will be additional supplemental prizes and if they arrive in time door prizes :D','11:00',37,0),(5230,'Oops! All Id\'s','2025.12.21.','11:30','United States','CO','infinity_lake on discord (zhae in servers)','Boulder','Grandmaster Games - Boulder, CO','4800 Baseline Rd Suite C103, Boulder, CO 80303, USA','ChIJq0Bh-Ljta4cRu1CgV2_5coo',9,0,'The rules are simple. Standard Ban List 25.12 applies, standard cardpool, but all* ID\'s are legal!\r\n*The following Id\'s are not legal\r\nCorp\r\n - NBN: Reality+\r\n - Mti Mwekundu: Life Improved\r\n - Jinteki: Potential Unleashed \r\n - Jinteki: Replicating Perfection (winner of last event)\r\n\r\nRunner\r\n - Noise: Hacker Extraordinaire \r\n - Kabonesa Wu: Netspace Thrillseeker \r\n - Leela Patel: Trained Pragmatist  (winner of last event)',1,0,0,49633,1,'elev',6,'2025-12-06 00:07:04','2025-12-23 19:14:44',NULL,4,39.997959,-105.233857,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,49633,'2025-12-23 19:14:44',0,NULL,NULL,'','11:00',39,0),(5231,'[Invitational] 🌎 🌍 2026 Ultimate Showdown 🏆 🎉','2026.11.14.','08:30','','','maninthem00n - on discord or mitm.netrunner@gmail.com','','','','',NULL,NULL,'24 player invitational event - date placeholder\r\n\r\nHow to qualify? \r\nFirst at the 2025 Ultimate Showdown\r\n1st - 4th at any of the 5 showdown events scheduled for 2026. \r\ntop ranked player on [the Beanstalk](https://netrunner-beanstalk.net/) on Nov 1st\r\n2 invites are still TBD\r\n\r\nQualified players so far: \r\n**AugustusCaesar** 1st at Ultimate Showdown 2025',0,1,0,37550,1,'unknown',14,'2025-12-06 20:28:28','2025-12-10 08:15:36',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'**1st place** - Champ Card\r\nRest TBD','08:00',39,1),(5232,'[NANPC] Seattle 2026 Districts','2026.03.14.','10:30','United States','WA','danvgf@gmail.com','Bellevue','Mox Boarding House','13310 NE Bel Red Rd, Bellevue, WA 98005, USA','ChIJo8wNCFZskFQRrlQ9Fdyv2eE',NULL,NULL,'# Buy tickets [here](https://www.eventcreate.com/e/seattle-2026-district).\r\n\r\n![Image](https://nullsignal.games/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/2026districtsfan.png)\r\n\r\nThe District event for the Seattle area in 2026! It will also be the first NANPC event of the year, as well as making use of the new set Vantage Point! Come join in and kick the new meta off with a bang!\r\n\r\nThis event is capped at 35 players, and tickets cost $18. Use the link at the top of the description to purchase a ticket (or [here](https://www.eventcreate.com/e/seattle-2026-district) if you don\'t want to scroll back up).\r\n\r\nCan\'t afford full price? It\'s important that Netrunner is accessible, and for those that need it, feel free to use SAVE50 as a discount code to get 50 percent off. If you need more financial assistance, you can reach out to me at danvgf@gmail.com to talk about a cheaper ticket.\r\n\r\nDecklists will be required! A cobra link will be updated here the night before to allow people to upload decklists digitally.\r\n\r\n# PRIZING: \r\n\r\nParticipation: Scatter Field NANPC Alt by V4Lvi_ \r\nParticipation: Recurring Credit NANPC token by KenSeventy\r\nTop 24: Fully Operational Alt by Amirul Hhf\r\nTop 8: Raindrops Cut Stone Alt by Amirul Hhf\r\nTop 4: Scrounge Playmat by Amirul Hhf\r\nWinner: Muse Alt by Hela_Bela (This prize will be available for top prizing at other events in the area throughout the year, although only the winner of this event will have full-art-no-text back faces!)\r\nWinner: Bye for any 2026 Megacity Championship \r\n\r\n# EVENT TIMING:\r\n\r\nWe will have a player meeting at 10:30 am when registration closes. Rounds will be 40 minutes long, with a small buffer of 10 minutes between rounds. We will (if the event is full) be running 7 rounds of swiss with a cut to either Double Elim Top 4 or Single Elim Top 8 (Will update once this is locked). So the event will look something like this (exact times may change)\r\n\r\n10:00 Mox Opens\r\n10:30 Registration Closes / Player Meet\r\n10:40 Round 1\r\n11:30 Round 2\r\n12:20 Lunch\r\n13:20 Round 3\r\n14:10 Round 4\r\n15:00 Round 5\r\n15:50 Round 6\r\n16:40 Round 7\r\n17:30 Swiss Ends!\r\n\r\n18:15 Minor Side Event (TBD)\r\n18:15 Cut Round 1\r\n19:00 Cut Round 2\r\n19:45 Cut Round 3\r\n20:30 Cut Round 4 (if needed)\r\n\r\nLess Swiss rounds will happen if we have less people, naturally.',0,1,0,23888,1,'elev',16,'2025-12-08 03:28:32','2026-01-21 07:37:35',NULL,0,47.622735,-122.162591,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,129,'Participation - NANPC Recurring Credit Tokens','10:00',37,0),(5233,'Montreal January GNK @ L\'Expedition','2026.01.13.','18:00','Canada','','Odonuvo (Discord)','Montréal','L\'Expédition','6571 Rue St-Hubert, Montréal, QC H2S 2M5, Canada','ChIJKxYya2kZyUwRmTCjKijcUrs',12,0,'$5 entry fee.\r\n\r\nJoin us for a special edition of our weekly Netrunner gatherings that includes prize support!\r\n\r\nThis is the most casual level of tournament. Bring your jank! Bring your friends! Everyone is welcome.\r\n\r\nIf we are more than the prize kit can support, additional prizes will be provided.',1,0,0,32798,1,'elev',1,'2025-12-08 11:44:32','2026-01-14 01:58:01',NULL,4,45.536761,-73.604181,NULL,0,0,'https://www.facebook.com/events/1396785558564585',0,1,NULL,32798,'2026-01-14 01:58:01',0,NULL,127,'','17:30',39,0),(5234,'Torino December Saturday GNK','2025.12.13.','10:30','Italy','','@ wowarlok on discord','Torino','','Corso Dante, 50, 10126 Torino TO, Italy','ChIJkWFil0ltiEcRdtCi4udEobM',5,0,'Iscrizione 5€\r\nFormato: Standard\r\nNumero di round da definire in funzione degli iscritti\r\nPremi per tutti più premi extra per i giocatori più nuovi!\r\nPer chi ha partecipato ad altri eventi a Torino: occhio che siamo alla sede di corso Dante',1,0,0,7624,1,'elev',1,'2025-12-08 15:24:43','2025-12-15 08:04:02',NULL,4,45.047478,7.672042,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,7624,'2025-12-15 08:04:02',0,NULL,112,'Pick from the prize vault','10:00',39,0),(5235,'[Online] 🌏 🌎 2026 APAC Showdown! 🏆 🎉','2026.03.21.','09:30','','','maninthem00n - on discord or mitm.netrunner@gmail.com','','','','',NULL,NULL,'Everything you\'ve come to love about the showdown series with a APAC focused start time. American region players should still be able to attend with a Friday evening (on the 20th) start.\r\n\r\nDate placeholder',0,1,0,37550,1,'elev',11,'2025-12-08 17:34:06','2025-12-10 10:36:55',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'Full showdown prizes, All new alt arts.','09:00',39,1),(5236,'[Online] 🌍 🌏 2026 EMEA Showdown! 🏆 🎉','2026.07.11.','08:30','','','maninthem00n or OF15-15 - on discord or mitm.netrunner@gmail.com','','','','',NULL,NULL,'Everything you\'ve come to love about the showdown series with a EMEA focused start time. APAC region players should still be able to attend with an evening start time.\r\n\r\nDate placeholder',0,1,0,37550,1,'elev',11,'2025-12-08 17:38:10','2025-12-14 14:15:28',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'Full showdown prizes, All new alt arts.','08:00',39,1),(5237,'Boulder District Championship 2026','2026.04.12.','11:00','United States','CO','infinity_lake on discord (zhae in servers)','Boulder','Grandmaster Games - Boulder, CO','4800 Baseline Rd Suite C103, Boulder, CO 80303, USA','ChIJq0Bh-Ljta4cRu1CgV2_5coo',NULL,NULL,'The District Championship for Colorado, happening at Grandmaster Games for the second year in the row!\r\nDate is highly likely, but tentative (might reschedule for Vantage Point release, might be forced to reschedule if a Magic prerelease event claims our store)\r\nTournament will use whatever the most recent banlist is, and if Vantage Point has released it will be legal as well. Event starts at 11am but please show up early to submit your decklist , rounds will depend on attendance but will likely be 6 with a lunch round after round 2. A top cut will be put in place if attendance is 14 or more players.\r\nWatch this space for update information on dates, format, and prizing!\r\nFeel free to join the Colorado Netrunner Discord as well: https://discord.gg/Z4Asj6jRgY',0,1,0,49633,1,'elev',16,'2025-12-08 18:52:12','2025-12-10 10:37:13',NULL,0,39.997959,-105.233857,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','10:15',39,0),(5238,'Reading Monthly GNK (2026-Jan)','2026.01.10.','11:00','United Kingdom','','LLBlumire on Discord','Reading','RISC World Shop and Global Refills','35-39 London St, Reading RG1 4PS, UK','ChIJLw5ADD6bdkgRl7EUUAMWaVg',10,0,'![banner](https://nro-public.s3.nl-ams.scw.cloud/voluntary/public-assets/2026-gnk/gnk_banner.webp)\r\n\r\n**Location:** RISC Meeting Rooms, 35-39 London Street, RG1 4PS, (Down the Alley)\r\n**Format:** Standard\r\n**Structure:** 7 Rounds, Single Sided Swiss\r\n**Start Time:** 11:00 AM\r\n**Ticket Price:** Pay what you want (even free!)\r\n**DATES:** [January 10th][jan], [February 14th][feb], [March 14th][mar], [May 9th][may]\r\n\r\nPlayers of all experience level are welcome! If you\'re a completely new player, come along to a [Reading Indie Gamers][rig] weekly meetup at the Biscuit Factory from 6pm on a Tuesday, and we can teach you the game and help you get set up with competitive decks!\r\n\r\nEvents in H1 will be held on the second Saturday of every month, except for April and June for reasons that will be announced at a later date.\r\n\r\n## [Donation Link][dono]\r\n\r\n**Schedule**\r\n    11:00    Round 1\r\n    11:45    Round 2\r\n    12:30    Round 3\r\n    13:15    Lunch\r\n    14:00    Round 4\r\n    14:45    Round 5\r\n    15:30    Round 6\r\n    16:15    Round 7\r\n    16:55    Prizes\r\n\r\n[rig]: https://readingindie.co.uk\r\n[dono]: https://donate.stripe.com/7sI7uGdKl1ry3o4288\r\n[jan]: https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5238/reading-in-person-monthly-gnk-2026-jan\r\n[feb]: https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5239/reading-in-person-monthly-gnk-2026-feb\r\n[mar]: https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5240/reading-in-person-monthly-gnk-2026-mar\r\n[may]: https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5241/reading-in-person