Donation Link][dono]\r\n\r\n**Schedule**\r\n    11:00    Round 1\r\n    11:45    Round 2\r\n    12:30    Round 3\r\n    13:15    Lunch\r\n    14:00    Round 4\r\n    14:45    Round 5\r\n    15:30    Round 6\r\n    16:15    Round 7\r\n    16:55    Prizes\r\n\r\n[rig]: https://readingindie.co.uk\r\n[dono]: https://donate.stripe.com/7sI7uGdKl1ry3o4288\r\n[jan]: https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5238/reading-in-person-monthly-gnk-2026-jan\r\n[feb]: https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5239/reading-in-person-monthly-gnk-2026-feb\r\n[mar]: https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5240/reading-in-person-monthly-gnk-2026-mar\r\n[may]: https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5241/reading-in-person-monthly-gnk-2026-may',0,0,0,43515,1,'elev',1,'2025-12-09 21:51:52','2025-12-31 13:51:28',NULL,0,51.452814,-0.968153,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'This event will use the [ReadCoin™ Prize Redemption Scheme][redcoin], awarding playsets from the Reading Prize Vault for participating and for doing well!\r\n\r\n[redcoin]: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1TxCTOBnonbw_h89d_8h45b_iKTP7cqsEn-9rTjtWZV0','10:30',39,0),(5242,'Milano 2026 District Championship','2026.03.15.','10:30','Italy','','','Milano','La Casa dei Giochi','Via Sant\'Uguzzone, 8, 20126 Milano MI, Italy','ChIJ1-4BBWjHhkcRvEJbo4-4s3Y',NULL,NULL,'Join us in Milano for the second italian 2026 Netrunner District Championship tournament! The winner will receive a bye at one 2026 Megacity Championship and an invitation to the 2027 Circuit Breaker Invitational (CBI).\r\n\r\nBEWARE: For this tournament **Vantage Point** and the **new ban list** will be used\r\n\r\nThe tournament will be followed by a community dinner, if you would like to join **please fill** the following form (form still to be issues, stay tuned)\r\n\r\nTournament structure will be six rounds of single sided Swiss followed by a top4 single elimination cut.\r\n\r\nRegistration starts at 10:00, and the tournament starts at 10:30\r\n\r\nEntry fee 10€\r\n\r\nPrizing will consist of the 2026 District Championship kit\r\n\r\nThe format for the event will be the NSG Standard format. Decklists will be required (digital decklist only).\r\n\r\nFor any additional information please reach out to the tournament organizer.\r\n\r\nHope to see you there, and Always Be Running!',0,1,0,34885,1,'elev',16,'2025-12-10 11:53:01','2026-01-05 21:18:24',NULL,0,45.520997,9.226088,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','10:00',0,0),(5243,'Milano 2026 MegaCity championship','2026.05.16.','10:30','Italy','','','Milano','La Casa dei Giochi','Via Sant\'Uguzzone, 8, 20126 Milano MI, Italy','ChIJ1-4BBWjHhkcRvEJbo4-4s3Y',NULL,NULL,'# Welcome to Italian Megacity 2026\r\n\r\nJoin us in Milano for the 2026 italian Netrunner Megacity Championship tournament! The winner will receive a bye at one 2026 Continental Championship and an invitation to the 2027 Circuit Breaker Invitational (CBI).\r\n\r\nSaturday evening there will be the classic community dinner all together for everybody who is willing to join (a specific form will be issued in order to book the restaurant)\r\n\r\nTournament structure will be single sided Swiss followed (number of rounds still to be defined) on saturday and a double elimination top cut on sunday (top cut size to be defined).\r\nFor the ones not playing in the top cut we will have multiple draft cubes and several boardgames.\r\n\r\nRegistration starts at 10:00, and the tournament starts at 10:30\r\n\r\nEntry fee: TBD\r\n\r\nPrizing will consist of the 2026 Megacity Championship kit + special alt art for everybody provided by the TO\r\n\r\nThe format for the event will be the NSG Standard format. Decklists will be required (digital decklist only).\r\n\r\nFor any additional information please reach out to the tournament organizer.\r\n\r\nHope to see you there, and Always Be Running!',0,1,0,34885,1,'elev',17,'2025-12-10 11:56:48','2026-01-05 21:21:04',NULL,0,45.520997,9.226088,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,'2026.05.17.',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'More information to come','10:00',0,0),(5244,'Milano CTK Asynchronous 2025','2025.12.11.','21:00','Italy','','','Milano','La Casa dei Giochi','Via Sant\'Uguzzone, 8, 20126 Milano MI, Italy','ChIJ1-4BBWjHhkcRvEJbo4-4s3Y',8,NULL,'Asynchronous tournament in the Milan community',1,0,0,34885,1,'elev',11,'2025-12-11 22:27:18','2026-01-07 10:56:39',NULL,4,45.520997,9.226088,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,34885,'2025-12-12 06:43:46',0,NULL,119,'','20:30',39,0),(5245,'North Carolina District Championship','2026.03.28.','11:00','United States','NC','exiledox or odsywrenn on discord','Durham','Atomic Empire','3400 Westgate Dr #14b, Durham, NC 27707, USA','ChIJqTY1YFfmrIkRPRh89ogVgvY',NULL,NULL,'A wise fictional character once said \"to go north, you must journey south. To reach the west, you must go east.\" What does this mean? It means you must travel to the North Carolina District Championship in the southeast United States! \r\n\r\nSchedule: \r\n10 am: Doors open\r\n10:45 am: Player meeting \r\n11 am: Round 1 begins\r\nAfter round 3: Lunch break\r\n\r\nThere will likely be six rounds of single-sided swiss (although this depends on attendance), followed by a cut to top 4 if we reach 16 people. \r\n\r\nThe format is standard. Vantage Point and the newest banlist will be legal!\r\n\r\nDecklists will be required; I will provide sheets to fill these out on, however we plan to start promptly at 11 am so either arrive with enough time to write lists, print them out beforehand, or submit them beforehand on [Cobra](https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/tournaments/4428). \r\n\r\nPrizing:\r\n***Winner:*** Bye for any 2026 Megacity Championship, invitation to the 2027 Circuit Breaker Invitational Championship, and a very cool prize that will be announced when ready\r\n***Top 4:*** Scrounge playmat \r\n***Top 8:*** Raindrops Cut Stone alt art\r\n***Top 24:*** Fully Operational alt art \r\n6 playsets of a Mavirus alt art will be raffled off to players after the Swiss rounds are finished\r\nAll participants will receive an additional alt art specific to this event that will be announced along with the extra prize for the winner in the coming months\r\n\r\n**Cost of a ticket is $15 before March 22nd, and $20 thereafter- register at [Atomic Empire](https://www.atomicempire.com/Store/Event/7606#evnt9339).**\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions, feel free to message exiledox or odsywrenn (the co-organizer of this event) on discord. Also, feel free to join the [Atomic Empire discord server](https://discord.gg/442bQjYMqk), select the Netrunner role in the card games options, and hangout in the nsg-netrunner channel to get to know folks.',0,1,0,29629,1,'elev',16,'2025-12-12 00:07:23','2026-01-10 00:20:03',NULL,0,35.965814,-78.962901,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','10:00',39,0),(5246,'Düsseldorf District Championship 2026','2026.04.18.','11:00','Germany','','Discord contact me @ Petersilio','Düsseldorf','IIK Deutschland','Eulerstraße 50, 40477 Düsseldorf, Germany','ChIJAQAQq47JuEcR4XVR5VdoBs4',NULL,NULL,'![Image](https://nullsignal.games/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/2026districtsfan.png)\r\n\r\nThe event will be held in the IIK Düsseldorf Language School Building in the second floor in:\r\nEulerstraße 50, 40477 Düsseldorf\r\n\r\nThe tournament will run in the **Standard Format (including Vantage Point)** with the most up-to-date banlist.\r\n\r\nThe tournament will run 6 rounds of single sided swiss (40mins each). Preliminary timeline is:\r\n\r\n10:30 Registration Starts & Pay your Tickets (You are highly encouraged to register in advance on COBRA and pay your ticket via PayPal/Revolut/bank transfer)\r\n\r\n11:00 Start Round 1 \r\n11:45 Start Round 2 \r\n12:30 Start Round 3\r\n13:15 Start Lunch Break\r\n14:15 Start Round 4 \r\n15:00 Start Round 5 \r\n15:45 Start Round 6 \r\n16:30 Celebration of Swiss Results & Prizes\r\n\r\nBased on the Player count there will *potentially be a top 4 cut single elimination* afterwards, during which other players not in the top cut are invited to stay for some board games!\r\n\r\n**Link to COBRA Tournament Page for Registration:** *Cobra Page will become available 7 days before the tournament*',0,0,0,50189,1,'elev',16,'2025-12-12 08:42:04','2026-01-31 10:05:49',NULL,0,51.239911,6.787072,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,129,'**Participation: Exclusive regional alt art** *(which will be revealed closer to the date)*\r\n\r\n**Additional prizing will be available so all players, regardless of placement, will come home with at least 3 alt art prizes.**','10:30',39,0),(5247,'Birmingham and Dudley District Championships','2026.02.07.','10.45','United Kingdom','','ebillink@gmail.com','Stourbridge','St Thomas\' Church, Stourbridge','Market St, Stourbridge DY8 1AG, UK','ChIJuQrburuRcEgR381p3tToPlE',NULL,NULL,'![Birmingham District Championship](https://nro-public.s3.nl-ams.scw.cloud/voluntary/public-assets/2026-districts/districts-banner-birmingham.webp)\r\n\r\nVenue: St Thomas\' Church\r\nRegistration: 10am\r\nRound 1 start: 10.45am\r\nTicket cost: £17.00\r\nMax tickets available: 48\r\n\r\n## [Buy Tickets](https://BirminghamandDudleyDistrictChampionship2026.eventbrite.com)\r\n\r\n\r\n**What Are District Championships?**\r\n\r\nDistrict Championships replace the UKs old Regional Circuit and form the introductory level of competitive play! They are run throughout the UK by local TOs and Judges, and are a fantastic opportunity for any Netrunner player to get involved in organised play!\r\n\r\nBirmingham District has been announced early due to it\'s start date, but you can expect there to be 8 Districts total this year, and details of them will follow soon.\r\n\r\n\r\n**Prizing**\r\n\r\nThis year, each District is organising it\'s own prizing. All will include 2026 District Championship Prize Kit by NSG, but additional prizes may vary by location.\r\n\r\nAt Birmingham, we are pleased to offer the following additional prizes: Raindrops Cut Stone by Bocky\r\n\r\n**Format** \r\n\r\nThanks to a change in the OP structure for districts this event will be run without a top cut and with extra rounds of swiss to make up for this. This means the event will be 8 rounds of swiss under the standard ban list that is in effect on the 7th of February\r\n\r\nRound 1 will start at 10.45 folling the player meeting at 10.30 with lunch at 2.15 and the last round ending around 6.30ish with prizing afterwards\r\n\r\n**Venue Information & Accessibility**\r\nSt Johns is a fully-accessible and inclusive venue. Travel info is available in this google document - there\'s lots of nearby parking, and bus and train stations in walking distance! There\'s also lots of local nearby options for food and drink.  More information can be found in this [Travel Document](https://docs.google.com/document/d/14iIBnHAqbJn8jXR0rIZwhpQcHE62O1QxdMM4PPYAhCw/edit?usp=sharing)\r\n\r\n**Ticket Price & Maximum Capacity**\r\n\r\nThe price for this event will be £17. Tickets are available [here](https://BirminghamandDudleyDistrictChampionship2026.eventbrite.com). If you are in hardship please get in touch with us and we can help you out! This event is cap at 48 players due to venue size.\r\n\r\n**Contact**\r\nIf there\'s anything we haven\'t covered, or you\'d like to find out more, get in touch! The main contact for Midlands Regional is @Ish on Discord or ebillink@gmail.com.\r\n\r\n**Uk Districts**\r\n[Brighton on the 14th of February](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5287/south-coast-brighton-district-championship)\r\n- [Bathgate on the 14th of March](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5259/bathgate-district-championship)\r\n- [Ipswich on the 14th of March](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5309/east-anglian-district-championships-ipswich)\r\n- [London on a TBD date in March](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5310/london-district-championship-2026)\r\n- [Reading on the 4th of April](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5255/reading-district-championship)\r\n- [Birkenhead on the 11th of April](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5311/birkenhead-north-west-uk-district-championships)\r\n- [Bristol on the 25th of April](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5257/bristol-south-west-district-championship)',0,1,0,47126,1,'elev',16,'2025-12-13 08:59:10','2026-01-15 14:51:36',NULL,0,52.455825,-2.148147,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'2026 District Kit by NSG \r\n\r\nKatirga Breakout by Bocky','10.00',39,0),(5248,'25th Birthday CO Gent','2026.01.18.','13:15','Belgium','','alexander.piters01@gmail.com','Gent','','Ottergemsesteenweg 13, 9000 Gent, Belgium','ChIJL7e4xFdxw0cR9Wa_sWQgfPQ',7,0,'There\'s no better way of celebrating my 25th birthday than playing some Netrunner. It\'s a casual standard tournament. Free entry; the kit is on me. Bring some fun decks. ;)\r\n\r\nWe play in outpost Gent: Ottergemsesteenweg 13, 9000 Gent\r\nStart at 13:00\r\n\r\nYou can eat in the venue, but don\'t bring your own drinks; you will need to buy a drink there.\r\n\r\nFor any questions, PM me on Discord, AlPi.',1,0,0,39502,1,'elev',11,'2025-12-13 09:58:49','2026-01-20 17:31:55',NULL,4,51.037245,3.727036,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,39502,'2026-01-20 17:31:55',0,NULL,119,'','13:00',39,0),(5249,'Megacity Hasselt (Belgium)','2026.07.04.','','Belgium','','alexander.piters01@gmail.com','Hasselt','','Kruisherenlaan 29, 3500 Hasselt, Belgium','ChIJxx_vbSYiwUcRqdtLUTLdjQs',NULL,NULL,'Dates for Megacity Hasselt (Belgium): 2026.07.04. - 2026.07.05.\r\n\r\nlocation: Kruisherenlaan 29, 3500 Hasselt\r\n\r\nThe standard tournament is on the 4th of July. Top cut + startup side event on the 5th of July.\r\n\r\nThis event was in 2025 a big success, we will run it back with BBQ and camping space in 2026! More info soon!',0,1,0,39502,1,'elev',17,'2025-12-13 10:19:30','2025-12-17 17:23:41',NULL,0,50.920778,5.326307,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','',39,0),(5250,'Off Meta Month - Random Access Memories','2025.12.21.','07:20 PM UTC','','','coldlava on discord','','','','',14,4,'![RAM Banner](https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1437774562598191125/1437774916782002256/RAM_3.png?ex=693ff93c&is=693ea7bc&hm=72bed3e701b68c7d88833db5073db2c643d4c1aa16cc89dad8e718647bbc0ab7&)\r\n\r\nRAM is a format where the cardpool is unknown until 2 hours before the event. at 5PM UTC a cardpool consisting of 12 datapacks/sets and 2 big-boxes/core sets from the entire modern history of Netrunner will be randomized and players will be given 2 hours to build their decks. After the building period a SSS tournament (likely 6 rounds depending on size) with a cut to single elimination top 4 will commence.\r\n\r\nFor new players or anyone not familiar with older cards: We will be attempting to do an on stream deck building session and posting what we build. Use it to get ideas or just play the decks we build card for card! This is a great format and I hope this will make it more accessible to all players!\r\n\r\nIf you\'d like to play please join the Netrunner events hub discord and communication on the day will be done in the OMM channels.',1,1,0,39034,1,'elev',7,'2025-12-14 13:56:30','2025-12-26 17:27:16',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,12,NULL,39034,'2025-12-26 17:27:16',0,NULL,NULL,'','05:00 PM UTC',99999,1),(5251,'Utrecht Pubrunner tournament','2026.01.24.','13:30','Netherlands','','david_nys@msn.com','Utrecht','Oproer Biercafé','Beyaertdreef 5, 3562 GL Utrecht, Netherlands','ChIJM7wL0HRvxkcRPw4lb0j0cbw',6,0,'Starting of the year with a new tournament..\r\n\r\n**Practicalities:**\r\n\r\n* The tournament will take place at Cafe Oproer. The address is Beyaertdreef 5, 3562 GL Utrecht. The bar is easy to reach from Utrecht Centraal via bus or bike.\r\n\r\n* Registration starts at 13.00, round 1 starts at 13.30 sharp.\r\n\r\n* There will be 3 to 5 rounds of singlesided swiss, depending on the number of players.\r\n\r\n* Entree fee is € 5 if you pay before the event, € 7 on the day itself (cash or via bank app). If you want to pay beforehand, wire the money to NL57 INGB 0689 9171 20, attn David Nys. Don\'t forget to mention your name.\r\n\r\n* We\'ll play Standard format. All decks have to comply to the most recent banlist. The most recent legal set will be Elevation.\r\n\r\n* Proxies are allowed, as long as it is immediately clear which card it is. Black and white printed proxies are fine.\r\n\r\n* Outside drinks and food aren\'t allowed. The venue sells various drinks and food.\r\n\r\n* David Nys will be your TO. If you have any questions, feel free to email david_nys@msn.com.\r\n\r\nPrize support:\r\n\r\nChoose one playset from the prize pool. An additional playset will be provided to the winner',1,0,0,25691,1,'elev',11,'2025-12-15 13:57:29','2026-01-24 16:38:33',NULL,4,52.111179,5.111592,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,25691,'2026-01-24 16:37:32',0,NULL,NULL,'','13:00',39,0),(5252,'Running the Core (System Gateway + Elevation)','2026.01.10.','','United States','OR','','Portland','','','ChIJJ3SpfQsLlVQRkYXR9ua5Nhw',10,0,'![ ](http://complicatedreality.b-cdn.net/misc/Prizing_Flyer.webp)\r\nWe got a handful of new players in Portland, and I hear Salem did, too. I\'ve wanted to explore matchups in the Core format for a while now, and what better way than with a tournament? Come play with those cards you just got for Christmas! Come play R+ again! Come snag some cool alt-arts! Maybe Phoenix is actually playable in Core!\r\n\r\nHuge thanks to Complicated Reality and ManintheMoon for donating, like, half the prizing! There\'s lots of stuff and lots of ways to get it, from first place to last place  and everything in between. Plus a set of Sure Gambles and Hedge Funds just for showing up!\r\n\r\nSystem Gateway + Elevation\r\nNo banlist\r\n6 rounds Single-Sided Swiss\r\n$0-20 sliding scale entry. ($15 suggested, no one turned away for lack of credits)\r\nJan 10, 2026, 12pm\r\nCapes & Crepes open play area.\r\n4990 SE Division St, Portland, OR 97206',1,0,0,46092,1,'elev',6,'2025-12-16 00:55:15','2026-01-11 10:10:38',NULL,4,45.515232,-122.678385,NULL,0,0,'',0,6,NULL,46092,'2026-01-11 10:10:38',0,NULL,NULL,'Top Placement:\r\n- [Night Network playmat](https://imgur.com/gt3jc9H) - Illus. and Prod. [Complicated Reality](https://www.complicatedreality.com)\r\n- 3x [Foil Mahkota Langit Grid - Illus. Henry A. Papprill & John W. Hill, Prod. ManintheMoon](https://imgur.com/c7cwtpT)\r\n\r\n2nd place:\r\nChoose one dual-sided ID from [NSG\'s 2021 Startup Prize Kit](https://nullsignal.games/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/marketing-startup-kit-751x1024.png)\r\n- Zahya Sadeghi/Tāo Salonga - Illus. Benjamin Giletti \r\n- Precision Design/Built to Last - Illus. Emilio Rodríguez\r\nas well as whichever acrylic ID 3rd place didn\'t take.\r\n\r\n3rd Place:\r\nChoose one acrylic ID from ManintheMoon\r\n- [AU Co. - Illus. Aleksandra Simonović](https://i.imgur.com/UpHLjWG.jpeg)\r\n- [Built to Last - Illus. Emilio Rodríguez](https://i.imgur.com/m9PXVgY.jpeg)\r\nas well as whichever double-sided ID 2nd place didn\'t take.\r\n\r\nTop 5:\r\n- 3x Biawak - Illus. Anthony Hutchings ([NSG 2025 Q4 GNK](https://nullsignal.games/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/2025_Q4_GNK_Card_Fan.png))\r\n\r\nBottom 5:\r\n- 3x Jailbreak - Illus. David Lei ([NSG 2021 Startup Prize Kit](https://nullsignal.games/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/marketing-startup-kit-751x1024.png))\r\n- 3x Send a Message - Illus. David Lei ([NSG 2021 Startup Prize Kit](https://nullsignal.games/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/marketing-startup-kit-751x1024.png))\r\n\r\n(If there\'s fewer than 10 people, those who are in both the top and bottom 5 will get their choice of one prize or the other, not both.)\r\n\r\nLast place:\r\n- Any single playset or ID from [netrunnercards.net](https://netrunnercards.net/collections/netrunner-cards). (I obviously won\'t be able to have it ready for you at the end of the tournament, but I\'ll order it for you before we leave the venue.)\r\n\r\nWin at least one game*:\r\n- 3x Azimat - Illus. Elwin \"Jakuza\" Rumplmair ([NSG 2025 Q4 GNK](https://nullsignal.games/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/2025_Q4_GNK_Card_Fan.png))\r\n\r\nFirst 5 people to pre-\"register\" here on Always Be Running (and actually come to the tournament):\r\n- 3x [Spin Doctors - Lucius Felimus](https://www.makeplayingcards.com/design/dn_product_share.aspx?type=11F48D428FF36AB59BE22C9B145D0EC9&id=43721682F5FE86D601AD580A8EF4AB62D6750C28127798208B526A4174ED2DD3ADDD96B76040E688&w=320&ws=1&f=&sign=&c=1)\r\n\r\nEverybody*:\r\n- 3x [Sure Gamble - Illus. Zoe Hope, Prod. The Tag Mill](https://www.makeplayingcards.com/design/dn_product_share.aspx?type=11F48D428FF36AB59BE22C9B145D0EC9&id=DC69974920DAA9CE3696A352512D5CC001B90477C318559FD0E9E78D7BA0E6E0030B10D64CAE9E38&w=320&ws=1&f=&sign=&c=1)**\r\n- 3x [Hedge Stonks - Illus. Lucius Felimus](https://www.makeplayingcards.com/design/dn_product_share.aspx?type=11F48D428FF36AB59BE22C9B145D0EC9&id=7A1A1887511EDFE192D6501F62898B4EB336928A6CCB6A7F08EEAA93768E32216152876C9BEC6F36&w=320&ws=1&f=&sign=&c=1)\r\n\r\nAlso choose one from the [Netrunnercards.net Community Art Pack (ManintheMoon)](https://netrunnercards.net/products/community-art-pack)**:\r\n- 1x [Precision Design - Illus. Manuel R.](https://netrunnercards.net/cdn/shop/files/PDforweb.png?v=1754956521&width=1346)\r\n- 1x [AU Co - Illus. Manuel R.](https://netrunnercards.net/cdn/shop/files/AUCo.forweb.png?v=1754956521&width=1346)\r\n- 1x [Magdalene - Illus. Manuel R.](https://netrunnercards.net/cdn/shop/files/Magdaleneforweb.png?v=1754956521&width=1346)\r\n- 1x [Synapse Global - Illus. ElessarEllie](https://netrunnercards.net/cdn/shop/files/Synapseforweb.png?v=1754956521&width=1346)\r\n- 1x [René \"Loup\" Arcemont - Illus. ElessarEllie](https://netrunnercards.net/cdn/shop/files/Loupforweb.png?v=1754956521&width=1346)\r\n- 3x [Rising Tide - Illus. ElessarEllie](https://netrunnercards.net/cdn/shop/files/RisingTideforweb.png?v=1754956521&width=1346)\r\n- 3x [Flyswatter - Illus. Lunari](https://netrunnercards.net/cdn/shop/files/Flyswatterforweb.png?v=1754956521&width=1346)\r\n- 3x [Azimat - Illus. Lunari](https://netrunnercards.net/cdn/shop/files/Azimatforweb.png?v=1754956521&width=1346)\r\n- 3x [Regolith Mining License - Illus. monde](https://netrunnercards.net/cdn/shop/files/Regolithforweb.png?v=1754956521&width=1346)\r\n- 3x [Botulus - Illus. Cat Shen, Ed. Wentagon](https://netrunnercards.net/cdn/shop/files/CorruptBotulusforweb.png?v=1754956521&width=1346)\r\n- 3x [Spin Doctor - Illus. David Lei, Ed. Phill the Canadian](https://netrunnercards.net/cdn/shop/files/SpinDrforweb.png?v=1754956521&width=1346)\r\n- Any leftovers from the other prizing\r\n\r\n*If we somehow run out, I\'ll issue IOUs and order more ASAP.\r\n**Drafted by player ranking, while supplies last','',99999,0),(5253,'Taiwan January Meetup - Startup','2026.01.04.','13:00','Taiwan','','0979226799','Taipei City','Cacacity Gongguan','106, Taiwan, Taipei City, Da’an District, Section 3, Roosevelt Rd, 281號 4號樓之1','ChIJg7MS_4upQjQR8k8AIWoafek',8,0,'[起始賽制]矩陣潛襲一月交流賽\r\n\r\n活動日期: 2026/01/04 (日)\r\n\r\n報到時間: 中午12點至下午一點\r\n\r\n比賽開始時間: 下午一點\r\n\r\n需提供牌組清單(自行列印或現場填寫空白表格)\r\n\r\n牌池: 系統入門、向上攀升、解放循環(自動人形提案、未經排演的革命)\r\n\r\n費用：僅場地費用\r\n\r\n參加獎：表岩屑採礦許可24張參加者平分\r\n\r\n前三名獎品：Maw異畫卡(已退循)\r\n\r\n使用起始賽制平衡更新25.11\r\n公司禁牌：\r\n　。網際傳媒：身歷其境\r\n　。大燈塔\r\n　。支流\r\n(公司牌組特殊規定：最多只能放四張三分議案)\r\n\r\n潛襲者禁牌：\r\n　。剁肉刀\r\n　。卡波耶拉－Ｓ型猴翻\r\n　。凝聚',1,1,0,9343,1,'elev',1,'2025-12-17 07:51:01','2026-01-04 09:40:59',NULL,4,25.018002,121.531381,NULL,0,0,'https://www.facebook.com/events/886296634085583',0,11,NULL,9343,'2026-01-04 09:40:59',0,NULL,106,'','12:00',38,0),(5254,'Taiwan January Meetup - Standard','2026.01.18.','13:00','Taiwan','','0979226799','Hsinchu City','謎寶空間','300, Taiwan, Hsinchu City, North District, Section 3, Zhonghua Rd, 9號5樓之1','ChIJfyGgsjw1aDQRI5-KhWO6y4M',8,0,'[標準賽制]矩陣潛襲一月交流賽\r\n\r\n活動日期: 2026/01/18 (日)\r\n\r\n報到時間: 中午12點至下午一點\r\n\r\n比賽開始時間: 下午一點\r\n\r\n需提供牌組清單(自行列印或現場填寫空白表格)\r\n\r\n牌池: \r\n。系統入門\r\n。向上攀升\r\n。解放循環(自動人形提案、未經排演的革命)\r\n。極光循環(午夜太陽、幻日奇景)\r\n。餘燼循環(淪陷、重生)\r\