he 14th of February](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5287/south-coast-brighton-district-championship)\r\n- [Bathgate on the 14th of March](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5259/bathgate-district-championship)\r\n- [Ipswich on the 14th of March](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5309/east-anglian-district-championships-ipswich)\r\n- [London on the 28th of March](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5310/london-district-championship-2026)\r\n- [Reading on the 4th of April](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5255/reading-district-championship)\r\n- [Birkenhead on the 11th of April](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5311/birkenhead-north-west-uk-district-championships)\r\n- [Bristol on the 25th of April](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5257/bristol-south-west-district-championship)\r\n\r\n**Prizing**\r\n\r\nThis year, each District is organising it\'s own prizing. All will include 2026 District Championship Prize Kit by NSG, but additional prizes may vary by location.\r\n\r\nAt Reading, we will be providing additional prizing which will be announced closer to the events date.\r\n\r\n**Format**\r\n\r\nThis event will be run as 9 rounds of Single Sided Swiss without a Top Cut. \r\n\r\nRound 1 will begin at 11:00, Lunch will be after round 2 and end at 13:20, dinner will be after round 6 and will end at 17:40. The final round is expected to end and prizing to be handed out by 20:45.\r\n\r\n**Venue Information & Accessibility**\r\n\r\nThe RISC meeting rooms has step free access, but it is up a fairly steep incline. The entrance to the venue can be found up an alley way down the right hand side of the World Shop and Global Refills store.\r\n\r\n**Ticket Price & Maximum Capacity**\r\n\r\nThe price for this event will be £17. Tickets are available [here](https://buy.stripe.com/28EbJ22iG8qkeeL8NY6oo06). If you are in hardship please get in touch with us and we can help you out! We can host up to 50 players at this event.\r\n\r\n**Contact**\r\n\r\nLLBlumire on Discord',0,1,0,43515,1,'elev',16,'2025-12-17 18:50:58','2026-01-28 14:54:00',NULL,0,51.452814,-0.968153,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,129,'','10:00',39,0),(5256,'Bristol - South West District Championship','2026.04.25.','10:45','','','nicky3.0 on discord - nishadham@gmail.com','','','','',NULL,NULL,'![Bristol District Championship](https://nro-public.s3.nl-ams.scw.cloud/voluntary/public-assets/2026-districts/districts-banner-bristol.webp)\r\n\r\n![{Location District Championship}]({link})\r\n\r\nVenue: Sparks Bristol, 78 Broadmead BS1 3DS\r\n\r\nRegistration: 10am\r\n\r\nRound 1 start: 10:45am\r\n\r\nTicket cost: tbc, £15-£20. Tickets available soon!\r\n\r\nMax tickets available: 50\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n**What Are District Championships?**\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nDistrict Championships replace the UKs old Regional Circuit and form the introductory level of competitive play! They are run throughout the UK by local TOs and Judges, and are a fantastic opportunity for any Netrunner player to get involved in organised play!\r\n\r\nThis year, there will be 8 total districts across the UK:\r\n\r\n![distrits-map](https://nro-public.s3.nl-ams.scw.cloud/voluntary/public-assets/2026-districts/districts-map.webp)\r\n\r\n\r\n- [Birmingham on the 7th of February](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5247/uk-regionals-birmingham-and-dudley-district-champ)\r\n\r\n- Bathgate on the 21st of February\r\n\r\n- South Coast on a TBD day in February\r\n\r\n- [Reading on the 4th of April](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5255/reading-district-championship)\r\n\r\n- Birkenhead on the 11th of April\r\n\r\n- Bristol on the 25th of April\r\n\r\n- London, and Ipswich dates TBD.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n**Prizing**\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThis year, each District is organising it\'s own prizing. All will include 2026 District Championship Prize Kit by NSG, but additional prizes may vary by location. In Bristol, we will have exclusive prizes, to be announced shortly!\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n**Format**\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThis event will be run as single sided swiss, 8 or 9 rounds.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n**Venue Information & Accessibility**\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSparks, 78 Broadmead, Bristol BS1 3DS\r\n\r\nhttps://sparksbristol.co.uk/\r\n\r\nWe will be running the tournament on the first floor event space. On arrival *the shop will be closed* so please head to the artist\'s entrance on Broadmead (the other side of the building from primark* someone will be at the entrance to let you in. For step-free access, please get in touch with Nicky (nicky3.0 on discord) there is a lift to all floors, but the way in is different - please do feel free to get in touch to ask.',0,0,0,8492,NULL,'unknown',16,'2025-12-17 23:12:50','2025-12-17 23:13:25','2025-12-17 23:13:25',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'2026 District Championship Kit - yet to be revealed - plus extra exclusive prizes to be announced.','10:00',39,1),(5257,'Bristol - South West District Championship','2026.04.25.','11:30','United Kingdom','','nicky3.0 on discord - nishadham@gmail.com','Bristol','Sparks Bristol','78 Broadmead, Bristol BS1 3DS, UK','ChIJA6t8y6-PcUgRiCU-D6bdM9M',NULL,NULL,'![Bristol District Championship](https://nro-public.s3.nl-ams.scw.cloud/voluntary/public-assets/2026-districts/districts-banner-bristol.webp)\r\n\r\nBristol - South West District Championship\r\n\r\nVenue: Sparks Bristol, 78 Broadmead BS1 3DS\r\nRegistration: 11:00 am\r\nRound 1 start: 11:30 am\r\nTickets: 15\r\nMax tickets available: 50\r\n\r\n# **[Click here for tickets](https://www.tickettailor.com/events/nicky/2035855)**\r\n\r\n**What Are District Championships?**\r\n\r\nDistrict Championships replace the UKs old Regional Circuit and form the introductory level of competitive play! They are run throughout the UK by local TOs and Judges, and are a fantastic opportunity for any Netrunner player to get involved in organised play!\r\n\r\nThis year, there will be 8 total districts across the UK:\r\n\r\n![districts-map](https://nro-public.s3.nl-ams.scw.cloud/voluntary/public-assets/2026-districts/districts-map.webp)\r\n\r\n- [Birmingham on the 7th of February](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5247/uk-regionals-birmingham-and-dudley-district-champ)\r\n- [Brighton on the 14th of February](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5287/south-coast-brighton-district-championship)\r\n- [Bathgate on the 14th of March](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5259/bathgate-district-championship)\r\n- [Ipswich on the 14th of March](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5309/east-anglian-district-championships-ipswich)\r\n- [London on the 28th of March](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5310/london-district-championship-2026)\r\n- [Reading on the 4th of April](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5255/reading-district-championship)\r\n- [Birkenhead on the 11th of April](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5311/birkenhead-north-west-uk-district-championships)\r\n- [Bristol on the 25th of April](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5257/bristol-south-west-district-championship)\r\n\r\n\r\n**Prizing**\r\n\r\nThis year, each District is organising it\'s own prizing. All will include 2026 District Championship Prize Kit by NSG, but additional prizes may vary by location. In Bristol, we will have exclusive prizes, to be announced shortly!\r\n\r\n**Format**\r\n\r\nThis event will be run as single sided swiss, 8 or 9 rounds.\r\n\r\n**Venue Information & Accessibility**\r\n\r\nSparks, 78 Broadmead, Bristol BS1 3DS\r\nhttps://sparksbristol.co.uk/\r\nWe will be running the tournament on the first floor event space. The shop entrances on ground floor will only be open from 11am, we will let you in from then. For step-free access, please get in touch with Nicky (nicky3.0 on discord) there is a lift to all floors, but the way in is different - please do feel free to get in touch to ask.',0,1,0,8492,1,'elev',16,'2025-12-18 10:49:40','2026-01-22 18:48:06',NULL,0,51.458085,-2.590739,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'2026 District Championship Kit - yet to be revealed - plus extra exclusive prizes to be announced.','11:00',39,0),(5258,'New Year Super GNK in Dundee','2026.01.17.','12:30','United Kingdom','','','Dundee','Paper Dragon','6, Queens Hotel Buildings, Nethergate, Dundee DD1 4DT, UK','ChIJ6wOqR8BdhkgRdiTlYes_Mcw',NULL,NULL,'We\'ll be playing at Paper Dragon in Dundee!\r\n\r\nThis will be a four round DSS tournament, no cut. NSG COC etc. in play. Prizing is a combined 2025 Q4 and 2026 Q1 Game Night Kit.\r\n\r\nhttps://nullsignal.games/blog/2025-gnk-q4-2026-q1-gnk-available-on-mpc/\r\n\r\n£10 fee for the tournament, due to the later start there will be no lunch break but we\'ll have a wee coffee break after round 2.',0,0,0,9326,1,'elev',1,'2025-12-19 08:53:37','2026-01-09 14:19:14','2026-01-09 14:19:14',0,56.457147,-2.976199,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,128,'','12:00',39,0),(5259,'Bathgate District Championship','2026.03.14.','10:30','United Kingdom','','ronan_mcgarry@hotmail.co.uk','Bathgate','Knightly Gaming','2-6 Hopetoun St, Bathgate EH48 4EU, UK','ChIJO13Vd_QOiEgRvALJ83sTnjI',NULL,NULL,'Bathgate District Championship\r\n\r\n**Venue:** Knightly Gaming, Bathgate\r\n**Registration:** 10:00\r\n**Round 1 start:** 10:30\r\n**Ticket cost:** £18/£24\r\n\r\n\r\n## [Buy Tickets](https://www.eventbrite.com/e/bathgate-district-championship-2026-tickets-1978614369843?aff=oddtdtcreator)\r\n\r\n**What Are District Championships?**\r\n\r\nDistrict Championships replace the UKs old Regional Circuit and form the introductory level of competitive play! They are run throughout the UK by local TOs and Judges, and are a fantastic opportunity for any Netrunner player to get involved in organised play!\r\n\r\nThis year, there will be 8 total districts across the UK:\r\n\r\n- [Birmingham on the 7th of February](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5247/uk-regionals-birmingham-and-dudley-district-champ)\r\n- Bathgate on the 14th of March\r\n- South Coast on a TBD day in February\r\n- [Reading on the 4th of April](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5255/reading-district-championship)\r\n- Birkenhead on the 11th of April\r\n- Bristol on the 25th of April\r\n- London, and Ipswich dates TBD.\r\n\r\n**Prizing**\r\n\r\nThis year, each District is organising it\'s own prizing. All will include 2026 District Championship Prize Kit by NSG, but additional prizes may vary by location.\r\n\r\nAt Bathgate, we are pleased to offer the following additional prizes: all participants will receive 3x Dr. Nuka Vrolyck alt art created by Ezbior!\r\n\r\n**Format**\r\n\r\nThis event will be run as single sided swiss, with a cut. This is expected to be 7 rounds of swiss, with a top 8 cut, but depends on numbers.\r\n\r\nExpected start time 10:30, lunch around 13:30, end of swiss around 18:30 and close of tournament 20:30.\r\n\r\n**Venue Information & Accessibility**\r\n\r\nThe venue has step-free access, gender neutral toilets and offers food (with vegetarian and vegan options). Fixed seating will be provided on request.\r\n\r\n**Ticket Price & Maximum Capacity**\r\n\r\nThe price for this event will be £18, or £24 for a ticket and lunch. Tickets are available [here](https://www.eventbrite.com/e/bathgate-district-championship-2026-tickets-1978614369843?aff=oddtdtcreator). If you are in hardship please get in touch with us and we can help you out! \r\n\r\n**Contact**\r\n\r\nronan_mcgarry@hotmail.co.uk',0,1,0,9326,1,'elev',16,'2025-12-19 13:29:57','2026-01-06 07:56:02',NULL,0,55.902664,-3.641822,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','10:00',39,0),(5260,'Madison, WI 2026 District Championship','2026.03.14.','11:00','United States','WI','andrew3820@gmail.com','Fitchburg','Noble Knight Games','2835 Commerce Park Dr, Fitchburg, WI 53719, USA','ChIJybuHU6QQBogR1fgk_Q5b2jY',NULL,NULL,'Join us at Noble Knight Games for Madison, Wisconsin\'s 2025 Netrunner District Championship tournament! The winner will receive a bye at one 2026 Megacity Championship and an invitation to the 2027 Circuit Breaker Invitational (CBI).\r\n\r\nThe format for the event will be the NSG Standard format. **Decklists will be required, no exceptions.** For information regarding card legality and ban list, please visit https://nullsignal.games/players/supported-formats/#standard.\r\n\r\nTournament structure will be six rounds of single sided Swiss (dependent on player count), followed by a top cut provided we reach at least 16 registered players.\r\n\r\nThis tournament is a Competitive-level event, and the Organized Play Policies can be found at https://nullsignal.games/organizers/organized-play-policies/.\r\n\r\nMore information regarding prizing will be announced as we approach the date of the event.\r\n\r\nRegistration starts at 10:00 AM, and the tournament starts at 11:00 AM sharp.\r\n\r\nIf there are any questions, please reach out to the tournament organizer, Andrew, by emailing andrew3820@gmail.com.\r\n\r\nHope to see you there, and Always Be Running!',0,1,0,4423,1,'elev',16,'2025-12-19 13:59:11','2025-12-19 20:13:29',NULL,0,43.008874,-89.469359,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','10:00',39,0),(5261,'Madison, WI 2026 Megacity Championship','2026.06.20.','11:00','United States','WI','andrew3820@gmail.com','Fitchburg','Noble Knight Games','2835 Commerce Park Dr, Fitchburg, WI 53719, USA','ChIJybuHU6QQBogR1fgk_Q5b2jY',NULL,NULL,'Join us at Noble Knight Games for Madison, Wisconsin\'s 2026 Netrunner Megacity Championship!\r\n\r\nThis event will be run as a two-day event, with the Swiss rounds taking place on Saturday, June 20th and the top cut taking place on Sunday, June 21st.\r\n\r\n**There is a hard cap of 60 players due to venue space limitations. Please register here on ABR so I have an idea of how many players will be attending!**\r\n\r\nMore details regarding the event to be announced as the date approaches.',0,1,0,4423,1,'elev',17,'2025-12-19 14:46:44','2025-12-29 16:46:33',NULL,0,43.008874,-89.469359,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','10:00',39,0),(5262,'Colorado Smash-Up Tournament','2026.01.25.','11:00','United States','CO','I\'m Pedantic on the CO Netrunner Discord: https://discord.gg/GPKCuvqM','Denver','The Wizard\'s Chest','451 Broadway, Denver, CO 80203, USA','ChIJpTV5qZd-bIcRqOTi0e9b8BI',NULL,NULL,'Smash-up is a semi-random casual format we\'re trying out! Players will bring \"half-decks\" from different IDs. Each round, you\'ll receive a random pairing of 2 different half-decks, shuffle them together, and play the result with both identities in effect. Final scores will be a combination of your personal record, and the record of the decks you brought.\r\n\r\n[Please sign up on here, indicating which identities you\'ll be bringing.](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1lcnykj0Z7_7T_bLh_r__j4j4RlVPEJDJbAHP7ojqn14/edit?usp=sharing)\r\nIn order to make the format work, players will need to bring unique identities, and we\'ll need to maintain a pretty even distribution of factions. The spreadsheet will only allow you to pick identities that have not yet been chosen, and please check the faction balance numbers off to the right. We\'re trying to keep them in parity when you sign up!\r\n\r\n## Half-deck Construction:\r\n**Cardpool:** Standard format with the most recent banlist.\r\n\r\n**Sleeves:** All players must select a unique sleeve color, and sleeve 1 corp and 1 runner half-deck in it. You can sleeve your cards yourself, or we\'ll provide sleeves on the day of.\r\n\r\n**Deck Size:** Your deck must be half as big as the minimum deck size for your identity as a runner, or half as big as the nearest agenda threshold to your minimum deck size for a corp, rounding down:\r\n-40 card runner -> 20 card half-deck\r\n-45 card runner -> 22 card half-deck\r\n-45 card corp (49) -> 24 card half-deck\r\n-50 card corp (54) -> 27 card half-deck\r\n\r\n**Agenda Points:** Corp half-decks must include half the number of minimum agenda points for their size (or 1 more)\r\n-24 card half-deck -> 10-11 agenda points\r\n-27 card half-deck -> 11-12 agenda points\r\n\r\n**Influence:** Half-decks receive half the influence of their identity, rounded up, **and** may only include **1 copy** of any **neutral cards**\r\n-15 influence ID -> 8 influence half-deck\r\n-17 influence ID -> 9 influence half-deck\r\n\r\n**Sure Gamble/Hedge Fund:** Bring an extra copy of Sure Gamble/Hedge Fund, you\'ll add 1 copy to your deck after combining the two half-decks.\r\n\r\n## Rules for play:\r\nDecks will have 2 different colors of sleeve, which will have a minor impact on gameplay that slightly advantages the runner. Generally, players should attempt to mitigate that where possible:\r\n\r\n**Shuffling:** Shuffling and/or cutting should be done blind, not controlling for the color that ends up on top.\r\n\r\n**HQ Access/Damage:** Rolling dice or similar randomization method should be used to pick which cards are affected.',0,0,0,2970,1,'elev',6,'2025-12-19 19:14:56','2026-01-22 17:01:26',NULL,0,39.723625,-104.987989,NULL,0,0,'',0,6,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','10:30',39,0),(5263,'End of the Year Megasota Startup Event','2025.12.21.','12:30','United States','MN','stwyde','White Bear Lake','The Battleground Cafe','2008 County Rd E E, White Bear Lake, MN 55110, USA','ChIJWXsw97TWslIR4LeNZm1RZ-Y',13,0,'STARTUP. LATEST BALANCE UPDATE. GET CARDS.\r\n\r\n$10 entry to the store.',1,0,0,44049,1,'elev',1,'2025-12-21 01:29:25','2025-12-27 17:50:07',NULL,4,45.049599,-93.015643,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,44049,'2025-12-26 19:06:57',0,NULL,128,'1 playset of Azimat or Biawak\r\n1 playset of Friendo or Otto\r\n1 playset of Spin Doctor or Mayfly\r\n1 haunted AU Co Acrylic (optional) \r\n1 playset of Coalescence\r\n1 playset of older GNK prizing\r\nTop 2: 1 playset of Measured Response\r\n\r\nYou may trade in a playset you get for a playset of Ritual or simulchip','12:00',39,0),(5264,'District Championship @ Redraft, Katowice','2026.02.07.','11:30','Poland','','dvoraque@gmail.com','Katowice','Redraft','Kamienna 7/2, 40-067 Katowice, Poland','ChIJZWZMVwDPFkcRPiADxKCPQvs',NULL,NULL,'![Image](https://nullsignal.games/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/2026districtsheader.png)\r\nENGLISH BELOW\r\n\r\nZapraszamy na pierwszy w serii turniejów District Championships w 2026! W sobotę 07 lutego ponownie ugości nas sklep Redraft, kilka minut pieszo od głównego dworca PKP.\r\n\r\nGramy w formacie Standard, zgodnie z obowiązującymi zasadami turniejowymi i wytycznymi dla turniejów competitive; w zależności od liczby graczy grane będzie 6-7 rund Single Side Swiss + TOP4.\r\n\r\nNa każdym polskim District Championshipie czekają was dodatkowe nagrody za uczestnictwo przygotowane specjalnie na każdy z tych turniejów, a także nagrody z kita zgodnie z oficjalną rozpiską:\r\n\r\n**Zwycięzca**: Bye na dowolnym Megacity Championship w 2026,, zaproszenie na 2027 Circuit Breaker Invitational Championship\r\nTop 4: mata Scrounge (by Amirul Hhf)\r\nTop 8: playset promo Raindrops Cut Stone (by Amirul Hhf)\r\nTop 24: playset promo Fully Operational (by Amirul Hhf)\r\n\r\nDo zobaczenia!\r\n\r\nWpisowe 50 PLN płatne gotówką bądź BLIKiem.\r\n\r\nTurnieje District Championship w Polsce w 2026 roku:\r\n\r\n7 lutego - Redraft, Katowice\r\n21 lutego - Time4Magic, Wrocław\r\n21 marca - Rojber Pub, Poznań\r\nŁódź\r\n\r\n==========\r\n\r\nWe\'d like to invite you to the first tournament in the series of Polish District Championships in 2026! The event will take place on Saturday, February the 7th, at our Friendly Local Game Store Redraft, just a couple of minutes away on foot from the main train station.\r\n\r\nWe\'ll be playing in the standard format, following the official tournament rules and competitive event guidelines; depending on the number of players, we will play 6-7 rounds of Single Sided Swiss and a TOP4.\r\n\r\nEach Polish District Championship will feature special participation prizes unique to each event along with the prizes in accordance with the District Tournament 2026 prize kit (see below).\r\n\r\n**Winner**: Bye for any 2026 Megacity Championship, invitation to the 2027 Circuit Breaker Invitational Championship\r\nTop 4: Scrounge playmat (illustrated by Amirul Hhf)\r\nTop 8: Raindrops Cut Stone alt art (illustrated by Amirul Hhf)\r\nTop 24: Fully Operational alt art (illustrated by Amirul Hhf)\r\n\r\nSee you there!\r\n\r\nEntry fee: 50 PLN, by cash or BLIK.\r\n\r\nDistrict Championship tournaments in Poland in 2026\r\n\r\nFebruary 7th - Redraft, Katowice\r\nFebruary 21st - Time4Magic, Wrocław\r\nMarch 21st - Rojber Pub, Poznań\r\nŁódź',0,1,0,7009,1,'elev',16,'2025-12-21 19:55:55','2026-01-23 18:32:08',NULL,0,50.257129,19.012159,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,129,'Additional participation prize: a unique promo playset designed for Katowice by Ash in the Polish nature & landscapes series ;)','11:00',39,0),(5265,'Learn to Play Netrunner - Wheeling, WV',NULL,'','United States','WV','ynalak7@icloud.com','Triadelphia','Clutch Gaming LLC','335 Wharton Cir Suite 121, Triadelphia, WV 26059, USA','ChIJCbwiZojZNYgRO6y2DqL827o',NULL,NULL,'## Come learn to play Netrunner! \r\n\r\nThis event is FREE and starter decks will be available for demo. Come learn any time between 12-3pm, and once you\'ve learned stick around to play with locals! Bring a friend!\r\n\r\nThis event is one time only, on Saturday January 31st 2026 (1/31/26).\r\n\r\n**What is Netrunner?**\r\nNetrunner is a two-player asymmetric card game set in a dystopian future where four megacorporations control almost every aspect of daily life. Legendary hackers known as “runners” aim to fight the corps’ influence by hacking into their servers and preventing them from advancing their sinister agendas.\r\n\r\nNetrunner **isn\'t** a trading card game, and proxies are legal at every level of play. Cards are sold by Null Signal Games, a registered nonprofit dedicated to providing ongoing support for the game of Netrunner. Complete sets of cards can be purchased through NSG or printed to be used as proxies.\r\n\r\n*In the case of inclement weather, the event may be rescheduled. Watch this page or the Facebook event for updates.*',0,0,0,49194,1,'elev',8,'2025-12-21 21:14:32','2026-01-23 12:11:35',NULL,0,40.053689,-80.603737,NULL,0,0,'https://www.facebook.com/events/1338112591451345/?rdid=GimmdJPprKOPEW1G&share_url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fshare%2F1DRXAwnZ7s%2F#',0,6,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'','12:00',39,0),(5266,'Mutually Assured Construction - Philly Core','2026.01.17.','12:30','United States','PA','jameskbarnhart@gmail.com','Philadelphia','Brauhaus Schmitz','718 South St, Philadelphia, PA 19147, USA','ChIJdaSbpyDGxokRte6dD4EqA_g',14,0,'Mutually Assured Construction - Philly Core is a casual beginner friendly event aimed at new and returning players. Enfranchised players welcome, use this event to foster community and help to educate and onboard new players joining the game with Elevation.\r\n\r\nFormat: Core (System Gateway + Elevation only)\r\nBanlist: Cleaver\r\nBuy In/ Registration: $10 + Brauhaus Receipt.\r\nRecord Based Prize Support for\r\n4+ Single sided rounds, Swiss pairings\r\n55 Minute round timer',1,0,0,44167,1,'elev',11,'2025-12-21 21:56:09','2026-01-18 22:49:26',NULL,4,39.942217,-75.154600,NULL,0,0,'',0,6,NULL,44167,'2026-01-18 22:49:26',0,NULL,127,'MAC Reaper Function Promos\r\n3D Print Token Set and Mark Dice\r\nAcrylic Token Set\r\nFull Art Alarm Clock\r\nDonated Box Sets\r\n2014 Store Champion Playmat','12:00',39,0),(5267,'Sansan North South Bay January Startup','2026.01.18.','10:30','United States','CA','','Santa Clara','Game Kastle (Santa Clara)','1350 Coleman Ave, Santa Clara, CA 95050, USA','ChIJVUnugrDLj4ARraVneZnSOqs',NULL,NULL,'Welcome to 2026! Let’s kick things off right with a Startup tournament. If you need some in person play after playing in or watching CBI, or if you didn’t get invited (like yours truly), or if you’re tired of Standard or just want to experience Elevation startup one more time, we’re here for you.\r\n\r\n\r\n## Format\r\n\r\nWe will be playing the Startup format using the most current banlist (Startup Balance Update 25.11 as of this writing).\r\n\r\n## Registration\r\n\r\nEntry fee is $20 paid to the organizer. Cash at the event or venmo to @jzhanson.\r\n\r\nYou can pre-register yourself at the Cobra event (https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/tournaments/4421) or this Always Be Running event. \r\n\r\n## Logistics\r\n\r\nThis is a Casual level event. Decklists not required.\r\n\r\nIf we have < 16 players, we will play 6 rounds of Single Sided Swiss. If we have > 16 players, we will play 6 rounds of Single Sided Swiss with a Top 4 cut.\r\n\r\nEach round will be 40 minutes. We will aim to wrap up Swiss around 4-5 pm. and the Top Cut by 6 pm.\r\n	\r\nRegistration opens at 10:00 am and games begin at 10:30 am. There will be a ~50 minute lunch break after round 2.\r\n\r\n## Prizing\r\nParticipation: Double-sided Knickknack alt art by Zhansonic\r\nParticipation: Ritual alt art by Zhansonic\r\nParticipation: Draft an alt art from the collection (now featuring alt arts by local artist Jinksey!)\r\n\r\n## Venue\r\n\r\nThis event will take place at the Game Kastle Santa Clara, 1350 Coleman Ave, Santa Clara, CA, 95050. There is usually enough parking before in their parking lot, but you can always park along some side streets. The venue is a 10 minute walk from the Santa Clara Caltrain station.\r\n\r\nOutside food is permitted. Game Kastle Santa Clara also sells some snacks, drinks, and instant noodles. There\'s fast food and other fast casual food within walking distance.\r\n\r\nLearn more about Bay Area Netrunner at https://sansan.cards/join/ and join the SanSan North discord at https://discord.com/invite/mvGB3hNWNE\r\n\r\n\r\n![knickknack front](https://i.imgur.com/em8OKdR.png)\r\n![knickknack back](https://i.imgur.com/FjTfhHl.png)\r\n![ritual](https://i.imgur.com/70OR9Ky.jpeg)',0,0,0,46685,1,'elev',11,'2025-12-23 01:24:00','2026-01-17 17:24:57','2026-01-17 17:24:57',0,37.357398,-121.935280,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'Participation: Double-sided Knickknack alt art by Zhansonic\r\nParticipation: Ritual alt art by Zhansonic\r\nParticipation: Draft an alt art from the collection (now featuring alt arts by local artist Jinksey!)','10:00',39,0),(5268,'Vancouver 2026 District Championship','2026.04.25.','11:30','Canada','','sindarin@nullsignal.games','Vancouver','Rain City Games','88 W Pender St Unit 1069, Vancouver, BC V6B 6N9, Canada','ChIJ6SNusXtxhlQRfnCOSXUtcUA',NULL,NULL,'Welcome back to the second Vancouver District Championship event\r\n\r\nEntry fee is $25. [Tickets may be purchased online here](https://www.raincity.games/netrunner-2026-district-championship.html)\r\nThere is a limit of 23 spots available\r\n\r\nFormat will be Single Sided Swiss. Rounds and top cut will be based on attendance, and focused on being able to finish all rounds and top cut in a single day. Ideally the top cut will be double elimination, but if need be, we will use single elimination.\r\n\r\nNote: A District Championship is a competitive tier event, and as such, decklists are required to enter, and alt arts must follow the guidelines found in [Appendix III of the OP Policies](https://access.nullsignal.games/OPPolicies/Organized%20Play%20Policies%202024.09%20-%20Standard.pdf)\r\n\r\nFor more local information and announcements, join the [Vancouver Discord Server](https://discord.gg/PF3VRabDsa), and message me; my username is Sindarin.',0,1,0,17150,1,'elev',16,'2025-12-23 21:47:59','2025-12-29 22:53:13',NULL,0,49.280524,-123.107088,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','11:00',39,0),(5269,'Dallas Late Nightrunner',NULL,'20:45','United States','TX','','Dallas','Soju 101 Karaoke, Bar & Korean Kitchen','11445 Emerald St #101, Dallas, TX 75229, USA','ChIJu8f8KvMnTIYRiHAeHsfEvVc',NULL,NULL,'',0,0,0,45738,1,'elev',8,'2025-12-23 23:12:17','2025-12-27 17:48:59',NULL,0,32.896971,-96.899618,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'Prizing will be provided.','20:30',39,0),(5271,'Netrunner Local Meetup - 12/20/25','2025.12.20.','01:00','United States','ND','','Fargo','JWW Sports Cards & Gaming','3902 13th Ave S #100, Fargo, ND 58103, USA','ChIJh8Vh7HvLyFIR-9z3YDfzZyI',6,NULL,'',1,0,0,49460,1,'elev',1,'2025-12-25 07:17:44','2025-12-27 17:49:35',NULL,4,46.858429,-96.847709,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,49460,'2025-12-25 07:17:44',0,NULL,117,'','12:30',39,0),(5272,'Every Other Week Netrunner Local Meetup',NULL,'01:00','United States','ND','','Fargo','JWW Sports Cards & Gaming','3902 13th Ave S #100, Fargo, ND 58103, USA','ChIJh8Vh7HvLyFIR-9z3YDfzZyI',NULL,NULL,'Join our Local discord for the most updated information on meet ups, as there are times that we cancel the event due to availability. \r\n\r\nhttps://discord.gg/Hr4kMfm8Ru',0,0,0,49460,1,'unknown',8,'2025-12-25 08:00:13','2025-12-27 17:49:17',NULL,0,46.858429,-96.847709,6,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'','12:30',39,0),(5273,'Torino District Champioship','2026.02.08.','10:30','Italy','','@ wowarlok on discord','Torino','Jolly Joker Game Café - San Martino','Corso S. Martino, 8G, 10122 Torino TO, Italy','ChIJSehu3attiEcR-uwcF5QpKOY',NULL,NULL,'Last year we had one of the most stacked districts, let\'s start the new competitive season with an other BANG!\r\n\r\nWe\'ll run a 6 round SSS with cut to top 4.\r\nEntry fee is 10€ and the players are required to spend at least 5€ at the venue, who kindly hosts us for free.\r\n\r\nIf you have any dietary restriction CONTACT ME ABOUD IT AHEAD OF TIME!\r\n\r\nSee you there!',0,1,0,7624,1,'elev',16,'2025-12-28 19:43:53','2026-01-07 10:25:00',NULL,0,45.074937,7.668457,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'Pick from the prize vault','10:00',39,0),(5274,'GNK des fêtes Toulouse meta','2025.12.30.','','France','','','Castelnau-d\'Estrétefonds','','','ChIJKZXwdrwCrBIRQCtBL5z2BgQ',4,NULL,'',1,0,0,23926,1,'elev',1,'2025-12-31 10:20:59','2026-01-01 21:17:31',NULL,4,43.780984,1.360316,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,23926,'2025-12-31 10:20:59',0,NULL,NULL,'','',39,0),(5275,'New Year Same Old Thing','2025.12.31.','21:00','','','','','','','',8,0,'',1,0,0,5351,1,'elev',6,'2025-12-31 11:43:44','2025-12-31 12:06:08',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,5351,'2025-12-31 12:02:22',0,NULL,NULL,'','21:00',39,1),(5277,'NRANZ Standard League - #05','2025.10.06.','','','','','','','','',23,0,'',1,0,0,8216,1,'elev',12,'2025-12-31 13:03:00','2025-12-31 13:11:51',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,8216,'2025-12-31 13:03:10',0,NULL,NULL,'','',37,1),(5278,'NRANZ Standard League - #06','2025.12.04.','','','','','','','','',14,NULL,'',1,0,0,8216,1,'elev',12,'2025-12-31 13:04:37','2025-12-31 13:12:22',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,8216,'2025-12-31 13:04:37',0,NULL,NULL,'','',39,1),(5279,'Reading Megacity Championship','2026.06.13.','11:00','United Kingdom','','LLBlumire on Discord','Reading','RISC World Shop and Global Refills','35-39 London St, Reading RG1 4PS, UK','ChIJLw5ADD6bdkgRl7EUUAMWaVg',NULL,NULL,'placeholder event description, will be filled in closer to event',0,1,0,43515,1,'elev',17,'2025-12-31 13:47:45','2026-01-30 12:10:17',NULL,0,51.452814,-0.968153,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,'2026.06.14.',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','10:00',39,0),(5280,'Reading Vantage Point Release H1 CTK*','2026.03.07.','11:00','United Kingdom','','LLBlumire on Discord','Reading','RISC World Shop and Global Refills','35-39 London St, Reading RG1 4PS, UK','ChIJLw5ADD6bdkgRl7EUUAMWaVg',NULL,NULL,'![banner](https://nro-public.s3.nl-ams.scw.cloud/voluntary/public-assets/2026-ct/h1/Reading%20H1%20CTK%20Banner.png)\r\n\r\n# Reading Vantage Point Release H1 CTK*\r\n\r\n[**BUY TICKETS £3 + PRIZE DONATION (SEE BELOW)**](https://buy.stripe.com/5kQcN6f5says7Qn1lw6oo07)\r\n\r\nVantage Point is out, so get on down to Reading!\r\n\r\nOn the 7th, in the gap in the districts season where Vantage Point is released but not yet legal, we will be ignoring that and playing with them anyway!\r\n\r\nThis could be your first opportunity to get reps in with Vantage Point cards before they start showing up at districts.\r\n\r\nThis is scheduled to be a H1 CTK, but there\'s been no announcement of those or the timeline on them from NSG yet, so if there isn\'t a kit by the event it won\'t be. Fortunately, to make sure there\'s lots of prizing going around despite that, we\'ll be running a large prize raffle!\r\n\r\n![prizes](https://nro-public.s3.nl-ams.scw.cloud/voluntary/public-assets/2026-ct/h1/Reading%20CTK%20Announcement.png)\r\n\r\nThe event will cost £3 and the donation of a playset of an alt art of any card to the raffle, and then we\'ll be randomly distributing the cards between everyone at the end of the event; so you\'re certain to walk away with a prize!\r\n\r\n[**BUY TICKETS £3 + PRIZE DONATION**](https://buy.stripe.com/5kQcN6f5says7Qn1lw6oo07)\r\n\r\nIn addition to the raffle, everyone who attends will receive a copy of the newly commissioned Spec Work by @beefpie_art!\r\n\r\nIf you are not able to donate a playset of prizing to the raffle, you can purchase a more expensive ticket that gets you off the hook (I\'ll use the extra fund to provide the prize myself).\r\n\r\n[**BUY MORE EXPENSIVE TICKETS £8**](https://buy.stripe.com/8x24gAbTggWQb2z7JU6oo08)\r\n\r\n## Schedule\r\n\r\n    10:00	Room Open\r\n    11:00	Round 1 Start\r\n    11:50	Round 2 Start\r\n    12:40	Round 3 Start\r\n    	Lunch\r\n    14:20	Round 4 Start\r\n    15:10	Round 5 Start\r\n    16:00	Round 6 Start\r\n    16:50	Round 7 Start\r\n    17:40	Round 8 Start\r\n    18:30	Prizes Raffle\r\n\r\n[**BUY TICKETS £3 + PRIZE DONATION**](https://buy.stripe.com/5kQcN6f5says7Qn1lw6oo07)\r\n[**BUY MORE EXPENSIVE TICKETS £8**](https://buy.stripe.com/8x24gAbTggWQb2z7JU6oo08)',0,0,0,43515,1,'elev',11,'2025-12-31 13:50:11','2026-01-28 14:34:54',NULL,0,51.452814,-0.968153,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'- Prize Raffle!\r\n- Spec Work by @beefpie_art','10:00',39,0),(5281,'SanSan Central Inaugural GNK','2026.01.25.','12:30','United States','CA','Ketzol#5982 on Discord','Clovis','','455 W Fir Ave, Clovis, CA 93611, USA','ChIJpTEBrrhclIARTH5IyUF8UNQ',4,0,'With all our new players & Vantage Point on the horizon, let\'s have some organized play to kick off 2026!\r\n\r\n# Logistics\r\n\r\nWe\'ll be using the main conference room at Provost & Pritchard Consulting Group -- 455 W. Fir Ave, Clovis, CA 93611. I\'d recommend parking near the main entrance of the building, and enter through the courtyard (main & rear entrances will be locked). The plan is to have some signs up to help as well.\r\n\r\nEntry is pay what you want; $5 donations welcome to cover the kits. Cash preferred. \r\n\r\nTournament will be ran via Cobra, and we\'ll cover that in the player meeting // registration\r\n\r\n# Details\r\n\r\n25.12 ban list, standard format. No decklists required. \r\n\r\nPrizing will be from the 2024 Q3 & 2024 Q4 GNKs. Prizing will be one copy of Ablative Barrier or Carpe Diem for each round played (max. three) and up to one copy of Slap Vandal or Saisentan for each round won (max. three).\r\n\r\nWe\'ll practice single-sided swiss, 40 minute rounds. I\'d expect 4-5 based on attendance.\r\n\r\nOther details & prizes TBD.',1,0,0,49256,1,'elev',1,'2026-01-02 04:50:32','2026-01-25 23:24:44',NULL,0,36.839383,-119.718734,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,49256,'2026-01-25 23:24:44',0,NULL,117,'2024 Q3 Game Night Kit also included','12:00',39,0),(5282,'👁️ Vantage Point Release Party 👁️',NULL,'10:00','United Kingdom','','ewanmilneu@gmail.com','Norwich','The Plasterer\'s Arms','43 Cowgate, Norwich NR3 1SZ, UK','ChIJvY6UqNzj2UcRJCiqhMu4E94',NULL,NULL,'Norwich\'s traditional launch day celebration will once again be taking place on Monday, 2nd March to celebrate the release of Vantage Point.\r\n\r\nCome of down for a day of scrappy games, communal deck building and plenty of debating if this one new card really breaks Detente. \r\n\r\nThe pub is opening early especially for us and will be serving tea and coffee throughout the day. We\'ll likely all get a takeaway in the evening and keep playing until Dave kicks us out.\r\n\r\nThis event is totally free, we\'ll have multiple proxied copies of VP in case your pre-order hasn\'t arrived so don\'t worry about that at all. If you want a bed to crash on the night before then shoot me a message, I can put you up!\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions I\'m **not_yeti** on discord and slack.\r\n\r\nLooking forward to seeing you!',0,0,0,39463,1,'elev',8,'2026-01-02 11:08:22','2026-01-02 18:26:37',NULL,0,52.636701,1.298255,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'','10:00',39,0),(5283,'NH Netrunners Jan 2026 DOUBLE GNK @ Midgard','2026.01.11.','10:30 AM','United States','NH','.cannister on discord','Derry','Midgard Hobbies and Games Inc.','55 Crystal Ave #21, Derry, NH 03038, USA','ChIJqR8HjahT4okR43kMVLePtfo',NULL,NULL,'We\'re hosting a DOUBLE GNK in the Standard Format at Midgard Hobbies and Games in Derry, NH!\r\n\r\nJoin the New Hampshire Netrunners discord: https://discord.gg/bGkmbTqxqM\r\nNOTE: We\'re combing the 2025 Q4 GNK and the 2026 Q1 GNK kits for a total of 4 official prizing cards!\r\n\r\nThere is an entry fee of $10 - registration begins at 10:00 am (when the store opens) and the tournament will start at 11:00 am.\r\n\r\nWe run events in the Single Sided Swiss format and the tournament will be hosted on https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/\r\n\r\nHope to see you there!\r\n\r\nWe will also have PLENTY of additional prizes including a \"Scorched Earth\" prize - which is usually something great that goes to the person who completed all rounds and came in last.\r\n\r\nEVERYONE that comes to our tournaments will be able to pick something from the prizing table.',0,0,0,20126,1,'elev',1,'2026-01-02 14:03:46','2026-01-02 18:26:54',NULL,0,42.890823,-71.323878,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,127,'2026 Q1 Game Night Kit - Otto Campaign and Friend of  Friend','10:00 AM',39,0),(5284,'🌎 🌍 2026 Worlds Showdown! 🏆 🎉','2026.09.26.','08:20','','','maninthem00n - on discord or mitm.netrunner@gmail.com','','','','',NULL,NULL,'Mark those calendars, hopefully you know the drill.\r\n\r\nDate placeholder. The event will be 3 weeks before worlds and since worlds hasn\'t been announced yet this date may end up changing.',0,1,0,37550,1,'unknown',11,'2026-01-03 16:48:51','2026-01-04 07:47:57',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'The goods','08:00',39,1),(5285,'Stockholm Winter GNK 2026','2026.02.07.','10:30','Sweden','','simon@gokstorp.se','Hägersten','AlphaBar','Instrumentvägen 4, 126 53 Hägersten, Sweden','ChIJTXWlAOV3X0YRrFDy15qA_WQ',NULL,NULL,'Join us in cold and dark Stockholm for a fun and friendly casual GNK!\r\n\r\nIf you want to attend but the start time or location is an issue for you, let me know and we\'ll see if we can sort something out.\r\n\r\nLocation: Alphabar in Hägersten, address: Instrumentvägen 4, 126 53 Hägersten, Sweden\r\n\r\nFormat: 5 rounds of single-sided Swiss.',0,0,0,14400,1,'elev',1,'2026-01-04 13:52:02','2026-01-04 19:23:09',NULL,0,59.305901,17.986196,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,127,'','10:00',39,0),(5286,'H&S GNK - Jan 2026','2026.01.11.','','Philippines','','profwacko','Makati City','Hobbies and Sheets Play Center','100 Tordesillas Street, corner H.V. Dela Costa, Makati City, Metro Manila, Philippines','ChIJrQrFKX_JlzMRJ_T0-5fI2B0',8,0,'First GNK of the year',1,0,0,8431,1,'elev',1,'2026-01-06 01:55:38','2026-01-11 13:14:32',NULL,4,14.560965,121.019847,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,8431,'2026-01-11 13:14:32',0,NULL,112,'','',39,0),(5287,'South Coast (Brighton) District Championship','2026.02.14.','10:45','United Kingdom','','willybn1@yahoo.com','Brighton and Hove','','88 London Rd, Brighton and Hove, Brighton BN1 4JF, UK','ChIJSa-NlZ2FdUgR945AhMtTJGM',NULL,NULL,'![Brighton District Championship](https://nro-public.s3.nl-ams.scw.cloud/voluntary/public-assets/2026-districts/districts-banner-brighton.webp)\r\n\r\n\r\n**Venue:** Dice Saloon, 88 London Rd, Brighton BN1 4JF\r\n**Registration:** 10:00\r\n**Round 1 start:** 10:45\r\n**Ticket cost:** £20\r\n**Max tickets available:** 24\r\n\r\n## [Buy Tickets](https://www.eventbrite.com/e/south-coast-brighton-district-championship-2026-tickets-1979846506196?aff=oddtdtcreator)\r\n\r\n**What Are District Championships?**\r\n\r\nDistrict Championships replace the UKs old Regional Circuit and form the introductory level of competitive play! They are run throughout the UK by local TOs and Judges, and are a fantastic opportunity for any Netrunner player to get involved in organised play!\r\n\r\nThis year, there will be 8 total districts across the UK:\r\n\r\n![distrits-map](https://nro-public.s3.nl-ams.scw.cloud/voluntary/public-assets/2026-districts/districts-map.webp)\r\n\r\n- [Birmingham on the 7th of February](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5247/uk-regionals-birmingham-and-dudley-district-champ)\r\n- [Brighton on the 14th of February](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5287/south-coast-brighton-district-championship)\r\n- [Bathgate on the 14th of March](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5259/bathgate-district-championship)\r\n- [Ipswich on the 14th of March](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5309/east-anglian-district-championships-ipswich)\r\n- [London on the 28th of March](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5310/london-district-championship-2026)\r\n- [Reading on the 4th of April](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5255/reading-district-championship)\r\n- [Birkenhead on the 11th of April](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5311/birkenhead-north-west-uk-district-championships)\r\n- [Bristol on the 25th of April](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5257/bristol-south-west-district-championship)\r\n\r\n**Prizing**\r\n\r\nThis year, each District is organising it\'s own prizing. All will include 2026 District Championship Prize Kit by NSG, but additional prizes may vary by location.\r\n\r\n**Format**\r\n\r\nThis event will be run as 7 rounds of Single Sided Swiss without a Top Cut. The venue has a strict 7pm close so we will need to be completed by 18:45. Exact # rounds and timing of lunch confirmed nearer the date. \r\n\r\n**Venue Information & Accessibility**\r\n\r\nDice Saloon is an 10 minute walk from Brighton station and has stepless access.,\r\n\r\nDice Saloon has a selection of hot and cold food but if you prefer to bring your own food there is a £3.50 surcharge, but there are plenty of food outlets within 5 minutes walk.\r\n\r\n**Ticket Price & Maximum Capacity**\r\n\r\nThe price for this event will be £20. Tickets are available [here]({link}). If you are in hardship please get in touch with us and we can help you out!. Max 24 players.\r\n\r\n**Contact**\r\n\r\nwillybn1 on Discord or willybn1@yahoo.com',0,0,0,18172,1,'elev',16,'2026-01-06 07:03:49','2026-01-26 19:50:37',NULL,0,50.830493,-0.135845,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','10:00',39,0),(5288,'Berlin Standard Casual Tournament Event','2026.01.31.','10:00','Germany','','alexkwoody@gmail.com','Berlin','','Reuterstraße 90, 12053 Berlin, Germany','ChIJDbkvvLtPqEcRd3edwUutURg',8,0,'Come celebrate the start of the new year and one of the last few standard events before Vantage Point is released in March. This will also be one of the first opportunities to earn a CBI invite for 2027. Whether you are a newer or an experienced player, you are welcome at this casual Netrunner tournament! \r\n\r\nThe event will take place at **10am on Saturday the 31st of January**.\r\n\r\nI am usually a tournament organiser in Australia so I look forward to meeting as many people from the German Netrunner scene as I can!\r\n\r\n**Location**\r\nWe will be playing in the Genossenschaftstreff in Reuterstraße 90 near U Boddinstraße, which has generously been to provided to us by Sebastian ([@sebki](https://alwaysberunning.net/profile/33086))!\r\n\r\nDETAILS - How to get in\r\n\r\nYou will have to ring two bells and go through two apartment buildings: At the entrance at Reuterstraße 90, there is a big button saying something akin to \"Mitgliederzentrum\". Ring that, and go through the building to enter the courtyard. There, you should see a sign pointing to the next door where you have to ring the bell again. Go through that second building to enter the second courtyard behind it. The entrance to the venue is in this second courtyard, and someone should be there welcoming you in.\r\n\r\n**Tickets**\r\nPlease send me an e-mail at alexkwoody@gmail.com to organise payment for your entry. The participation fee will be **10,- EUR**. Hopefully online transfer will work for you but if not cash payment on the day will be ok as well.\r\n\r\n**Format + Structure**\r\n* Elevation Standard\r\n* Single Sided Swiss\r\n* Up to 15 players: 6 rounds, no cut\r\n* 16-32 players: 6 rounds, top 4 cut\r\n* 40 minute rounds\r\n\r\n**Timing**\r\n* 9:30 - check-in opens\r\n* 9:55 - check-in closes\r\n* 10:00 - round 1\r\n* 10:45 - round 2\r\n* 11:30 - round 3\r\n* 12:15 - round 4\r\n* 13:00 - lunch break (45 minutes)\r\n* 13:45 - round 5\r\n* 14:30 - round 6\r\n* 15:15 - top 4 cut (if needed)\r\n\r\n**After-party**\r\nAll are welcome to gather for dinner and drinks on Saturday night.',1,0,0,41571,1,'elev',11,'2026-01-06 19:56:53','2026-01-31 16:48:08',NULL,4,52.482144,13.428775,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,41571,'2026-01-31 16:48:08',0,NULL,119,'All participants will leave with a prize from my broader prize pool!','09:30',39,0),(5289,'Inaugural Round-robin Netrunner Classic Draft Tournament (IRNCDT)','2025.12.20.','','United States','PA','brannon@brannondorsey.com','Philadelphia','','','ChIJ60u11Ni3xokRwVg-jNgU9Yk',4,NULL,'A casual in-person draft tournament using the original FFG Cyber War Draft packs.\r\n\r\nTournament format follows the original FFG tournament rules with no time restrictions. All players will play one round of double-sided swiss against each other player to produce the final ranking. A single-sided tiebreaker will be played if there is tie between the top players only.\r\n\r\n[Cobra link](https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/tournaments/4435)',1,0,0,51310,1,'elev',6,'2026-01-06 23:55:35','2026-01-08 14:48:51',NULL,4,39.952584,-75.165222,NULL,0,0,'',0,5,NULL,51310,'2026-01-06 23:55:35',0,NULL,NULL,'','',99999,0),(5290,'Megacity de Lille','2026.07.18.','11:00','France','','dzeitline@gmail.com','Lille','','4 Parv. Saint-Maurice, 59800 Lille, France','ChIJ3biGa4nVwkcRodSUh-e8DF0',NULL,NULL,'Le Mégacity de cette année aura lieu le week-end du 18/19 juillet à Lille! Plus de détails à venir\r\n\r\nSave the date, this year\'s french Megaicty will be held one the weekend of the 18th of July in Lille! More details forthcoming',0,0,0,37519,1,'unknown',17,'2026-01-07 14:06:37','2026-01-08 14:50:42',NULL,0,50.635511,3.067631,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','10:00',39,0),(5291,'Hannover City Grid Netrunner',NULL,'18:00','Germany','','Netrunner Deutschland - Hannover: https://discord.gg/UrKxTGZ','Hannover','','Glashüttenstraße 2, 30165 Hannover, Germany','ChIJP_4a0WZzsEcRLDCiWEVIOCU',NULL,NULL,'Glashüttenstrasse wieder da!\r\n\r\nDE/EN\r\n\r\nNetrunner City Grid Hannover. Jeden Donnerstag 18:00 Uhr in der Glashüttenstraße 2, 30165 Hannover bei den Hannoverschen Tabletopfreunden in Kooperation mit dem 3TH. \r\n\r\nSchaut doch kurz im Netrunner Deutschland Discord vorbei bei der Hannover Gruppe https://discord.gg/UrKxTGZ , auch verlinkt auf der Nullsignal Community Seite, oder schaut direkt vor Ort rein. Anfänger ohne eigene Karten sind ebenfalls gerne gesehen.\r\n\r\nWir freuen uns auf euch!\r\n\r\nEN\r\n\r\nNetrunner  City Grid Hanover. Every Thursday at 18 o\'clock, at Glashüttenstraße 2, 30165 Hannover, at Hannoversche Tabletopfreunde in cooperation with 3TH. \r\n\r\nVisit us at Germany\'s Netrunner Discord server https://discord.gg/UrKxTGZ, also linked from Nullsignal\'s community page oder just come over. Beginner\'s are welcome, even if you don\'t have any cards yet!\r\n\r\nSee you running!',0,0,0,54884,1,'unknown',8,'2026-01-07 15:26:49','2026-01-28 20:14:07',NULL,0,52.393961,9.725225,4,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'','',39,0),(5292,'Rīga District Championship 2026','2026.03.14.','14:30','Latvia','','maris.suipe@gmail.com','Rīga','UniCon Cafe','Aleksandra Čaka iela 58, Latgales priekšpilsēta, Rīga, LV-1011, Latvia','ChIJ96sGCzPO7kYR1DQ2coeia6Y',NULL,NULL,'![Prizing](https://nullsignal.games/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/2026districtsfan.png) \r\n\r\nFor the first time since Null Signal Games took over development of Netrunner, Rīga is once again hosting an official competitive circuit Netrunner event! We\'re even expecting guests from abroad.\r\n\r\nThe upcoming Vantage Point set will be legal for this event. If your copy hasn\'t arrived yet, remember that PROXIES ARE LEGAL in all levels of competitive play. If you are new or a returning player, message me, and I\'ll lend you a deck. Participation fee is 5€.\r\n\r\nPrize Structure\r\nWinner: Bye for any 2026 Megacity Championship, invitation to the 2027 Circuit Breaker Invitational Championship\r\nTop 4: Scrounge playmat (illustrated by Amirul Hhf)\r\nTop 8: 3x Raindrops Cut Stone alt art (illustrated by Amirul Hhf)\r\nTop 24: 3x Fully Operational alt art (illustrated by Amirul Hhf)\r\nTO’s Discretion (6 playsets): Mavirus alt art (illustrated by Cat Shen)',0,0,0,7345,1,'unknown',16,'2026-01-07 18:46:02','2026-01-17 09:20:09',NULL,0,56.954706,24.133949,NULL,0,0,'https://www.facebook.com/events/903940238700854',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','14:00',39,0),(5293,'Irish Standard League','2026.01.16.','10:00','Ireland','','Abr.subtext883@aleeas.com','Dublin','','','ChIJL6wn6oAOZ0gRoHExl6nHAAo',NULL,NULL,'This is a hybrid event to support the Irish Netrunner community, with games played online, or in-person where possible. If there is sufficient interest a final day event will be arranged!\r\n\r\nThis will be organised via the Irish Netrunners Discord community, where double-sided pairings will be issued each week. You can schedule your game with your opponent at your convenience. \r\n\r\nThe format is standard, and decks can be changed round to round. I won’t be checking, so be cool. If your opponent agrees you can play whatever you want. \r\n\r\nRounds and prizing will be dictated by number of sign-ups, but I’ve been collecting GNKs for a while now, among other things, so I will be pulling from 2024/2025/2026. \r\n\r\nIndicate interest here, via email above, or on Discord. \r\n\r\nPrice is €10 in dirty pound notes, stuffed in a brown envelope. Revolut is also acceptable.',0,0,0,39464,1,'elev',12,'2026-01-08 09:54:27','2026-01-08 15:05:55',NULL,0,53.349805,-6.260310,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,128,'','09:00',39,0),(5294,'Sydney/Gadigal District Championship','2026.03.14.','09:30','Australia','','ivan.kent00@gmail.com','Ultimo','','99 Jones St, Ultimo NSW 2007, Australia','ChIJszXoai-uEmsRBSiGU4cxfwE',NULL,NULL,'# Join us for the 2026 Sydney/Gadigal District Championship, held at Behold Games in Ultimo on Saturday 14th March !!!\r\n\r\n![Image][1]\r\n\r\n## Format\r\nThere will be 6 rounds of Single Sided Swiss, followed by a cut to Top 4 Single Elimination. We will be playing in the Standard format on the active banlist as of the day of the tournament.\r\n## Timing\r\nDoors will open for Registration at 9am, with Round 1 beginning at 9:30am. I know this is an early start, but we have a lot of Netrunner to play and we only have the space until 6pm at the latest, so will be aiming to have everything happening as per schedule. Please let @i am the gull know on discord if you are running late. There will be a lunch break around Midday, and an afternoon break at the end of Swiss.\r\n## Price\r\nEntry for this event is *$tbd*, please ensure you buy tickets on *tbd* Eventbrite. Due to timing and space restrictions, there are only 24 tickets available, so please purchase yours early to avoid missing out. If purchasing a ticket at this price is not feasible due to personal circumstances, feel free to reach out to @i am the gull on discord (if you feel comfortable doing so).\r\n## Player Expectations\r\nThis is a competitive-level event, and as such has stricter expectations on competitors. The main things to note are:\r\n•	Proxies are legal (at all levels of play), but please ensure that your proxies are legible (handwritten proxies are not allowed).\r\n•	Printed decklists are mandatory (ordered by Type and then Alphabetical). There will be printed templates available to handwrite your decklist if needed (also NetrunnerDB has a deck printout function).\r\n•	Alt Arts must adhere to Appendix III of the NSG Organised Play Policy. If you are unsure if your alt arts adhere, please check with the TO prior to the tournament (and bring the original card as a back up).\r\n\r\nFor more information on Player Expectations see https://nullsignal.games/organizers/organized-play-policies/\r\n## Venue Information\r\nBehold Games is home to Sydney Netrunner’s fortnightly Wednesday sessions. The store is very LGBTQIA+ friendly and has a wide range of Boardgames, RPGs, Card Games, Dice and other gaming accessories on offer, as well as great selection of snacks!  The store is at C17/99 Jones Street Ultimo, for more information on how to get there (including parking), please visit https://beholdgames.com.au/pages/how-to-find-us).\r\n## Prizing (see image above)\r\nWinner: Bye for any 2026 Megacity, invite to 2027 CBI\r\nTop 4: Scrounge playmat\r\nTop 8: Raindrops Cut Stone alt art\r\nTop 24: Fully Operational alt art\r\n\r\n[1]: https://kentlawgroup.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Screenshot-2026-01-12-155653.png',0,1,0,50345,1,'elev',16,'2026-01-10 22:39:21','2026-01-12 04:09:04',NULL,0,-33.879788,151.197129,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','09:00',39,0),(5295,'Metro Manila District Championships 2026','2026.03.14.','11:00','Philippines','','joaquin.almirante@gmail.com','Mandaluyong City','Whimsy Game Cafe','The Portal, Unit 14&15 Mayflower St, Greenfield District, Mandaluyong City, Metro Manila, Philippines','ChIJCxAKWQDJlzMR11GcpPenFHg',NULL,NULL,'# JOIN US FOR METRO MANILA DISTRICT DISTRICT CHAMIONSHIPS 2026\r\n\r\nStart off the competitive season with the hottest district championship in the region!\r\n\r\n![Image](https://i.ibb.co/TBvH6QKF/NETRUNNER-DISTRICT-CHAMPS-2026.png)\r\n\r\n## VENUE\r\nVenue: Whimsy Game Cafe, The Portal, Greenfield District, Mandaluyong City, Metro Manila\r\n\r\nhttps://maps.app.goo.gl/YKD6Xx9DKx9Xy5uq9\r\n\r\n\r\n## SCHEDULE\r\n11:00 AM Registration\r\n11:45 AM Round 1 Start\r\n1:45 PM BREAK\r\n2:30 PM Round 4 Start\r\n~4:30 PM END of SWISS ROUNDS\r\n\r\n+3 More rounds for Top Cut 4 Single Elimination\r\n6 PM estimated END OF TOURNAMENT\r\n\r\n6:30 PM COMMUNITY DINNER\r\n\r\n## FORMAT\r\n6 Rounds of Single Sided Swiss, with a Top 4 Single Elimination Cut\r\n\r\n## PRICE \r\n550 Registration Fee (includes free drink from the cafe + Districts participation and previous prize pool prizes + raffle!)\r\n\r\n## Player Expectations\r\n\r\nAs a Competitive-tier event, players are expected to:\r\n\r\n- Provide written/printed decklists (ordered by Type and then Alphabetical). There will be printed templates available to handwrite your decklist if needed (or you may use NetrunnerDB deck printout function)\r\n- Have their decks appropriately sleeved in Opaque Sleeves\r\n- Follow NSG\'s competitive-tier guidelines\r\n\r\nON PROXIES:\r\nProxies are legal (at all levels of play), but please ensure that your proxies are legible.\r\n\r\nAlt Arts must adhere to Appendix III of the NSG Organised Play Policy. If you are unsure if your alt arts adhere, please check with the TO prior to the tournament (and bring the original card as a back up).\r\n\r\nPlayers are responsible for replacing any cards deemed unsuitable for play. You may work with me to find suitable replacements.\r\n\r\nNo handwritten proxies will be permitted. As much as possible, please use colored paper proxy prints, B&W proxies allowed but may be subject to quality check by judges/deck checkers.\r\n\r\nFor more information on Player Expectations see https://nullsignal.games/organizers/organized-play-policies/\r\n\r\nPlease reach out to me (Discord: profwacko) if you intend to attend -- especially if you are flying in! Don\'t hesitate to reach out to me if you have questions.\r\n\r\ntraffic is notoriously bad in metro manila so i recommend staying very close to the venue',0,1,0,8431,1,'unknown',16,'2026-01-11 13:28:22','2026-01-23 04:19:13',NULL,0,14.578823,121.053968,NULL,0,0,'https://www.facebook.com/groups/NetrunnerPH',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,129,'Prize Pool Alt Arts to be given away, including prizes from previous tournaments!','10:00',39,0),(5296,'2026 Sydney Megacity Chapionships','2026.07.11.','09:30','Australia','','ivan.kent00@gmail.com','New South Wales','','','ChIJP3Sa8ziYEmsRUKgyFmh9AQM',NULL,NULL,'Details coming soon\r\n2-day event',0,1,0,50345,1,'elev',17,'2026-01-12 04:11:52','2026-01-22 13:40:58',NULL,0,-33.872741,151.205714,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','09:00',39,0),(5297,'Perth District Championship','2026.03.29.','10:30','Australia','','netrunner@majucham.com','Victoria Park','Beskar Forge Gaming','55 Washington St, Victoria Park WA 6100, Australia','ChIJ6TjNgdq7MioRIYDoaP5XUo0',NULL,NULL,'# 2026 Perth District Championsip, March 29th @ Beskar Forge Gaming\r\n\r\n![image](https://conjuringcreativity.com.au/wp-content/uploads/district-champs-v3.png)\r\n![image](https://conjuringcreativity.com.au/wp-content/uploads/district-prizes.png)\r\n\r\n**Format**\r\nThere will be 6 rounds of Single Sided Swiss, followed by a cut to Top 4 Single Elimination. We will be playing in the Standard format on the active banlist as of the day of the tournament.\r\n\r\n**Timing**\r\nDoors will open for Registration at 10am, with Round 1 beginning at 10:30am. Timing is tight so we\'ll likely have to play without a lunch break so pack something to eat.\r\n\r\n**Price**\r\n$tbd, paid on the day.\r\n\r\n**Player Expectations**\r\nThis is a competitive-level event, and as such has stricter expectations on competitors. The main things to note are:\r\n• Proxies are legal (at all levels of play), but please ensure that your proxies are legible (handwritten proxies are not allowed).\r\n• Printed decklists are mandatory (ordered by Type and then Alphabetical). There will be printed templates available to handwrite your decklist if needed (also NetrunnerDB has a deck printout function).\r\n• Alt Arts must adhere to Appendix III of the NSG Organised Play Policy. If you are unsure if your alt arts adhere, please check with the TO prior to the tournament (and bring the original card as a back up).\r\n\r\nFor more information on Player Expectations see https://nullsignal.games/organizers/organized-play-policies/\r\n\r\n**Prizing (see image above)**\r\nWinner: Bye for any 2026 Megacity, invite to 2027 CBI\r\nTop 4: Scrounge playmat\r\nTop 8: Raindrops Cut Stone alt art\r\nTop 24: Fully Operational alt art',0,1,0,41847,1,'elev',16,'2026-01-12 05:57:32','2026-01-22 13:39:49',NULL,0,-31.973683,115.888791,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','10:00',39,0),(5298,'Whimsy Game Cafe January 2026 GNK','2026.01.25.','','Philippines','','joaquin.almirante@gmail.com','Mandaluyong City','Whimsy Game Cafe','The Portal, Unit 14&15 Mayflower St, Greenfield District, Mandaluyong City, Metro Manila, Philippines','ChIJCxAKWQDJlzMR11GcpPenFHg',8,0,'',1,0,0,8431,1,'elev',1,'2026-01-12 12:51:46','2026-01-25 14:18:11',NULL,4,14.578823,121.053968,NULL,0,0,'https://www.facebook.com/groups/NetrunnerPH',0,1,NULL,8431,'2026-01-25 14:18:11',0,NULL,NULL,'','',39,0),(5299,'District Championship @ Time4Magic, Wrocław','2026.02.21.','11:30','Poland','','zadeberny.szymon@gmail.com, 518374817','Wrocław','Sklep Time4Magic - Magic: The Gathering - Pokemon - Gry Karciane','Legnicka 49/D, 54-203 Wrocław, Poland','ChIJWUwiqiXDD0cRWmUlpLbf2PM',NULL,NULL,'ENGLISH BELOW\r\n\r\nZapraszamy na drugi w serii turniejów District Championships w 2026! W sobotę 21 lutego ponownie ugości nas sklep Time4Magic. Najłatwiej dojechać do niego linią tramwaju 21 i 22, ale jest kilka innych opcji z pojedynczą przesiadką. \r\n\r\nGramy w formacie Standard, zgodnie z obowiązującymi zasadami turniejowymi i wytycznymi dla turniejów competitive; w zależności od liczby graczy grane będzie 6-7 rund Single Side Swiss + TOP4.\r\n\r\nNa każdym polskim District Championshipie czekają was dodatkowe nagrody za uczestnictwo przygotowane specjalnie na każdy z tych turniejów, a także nagrody z kita zgodnie z oficjalną rozpiską:\r\n\r\nZwycięzca: Bye na dowolnym Megacity Championship w 2026, zaproszenie na 2027 Circuit Breaker Invitational Championship\r\nTop 4: mata Scrounge (by Amirul Hhf)\r\nTop 8: playset promo Raindrops Cut Stone (by Amirul Hhf)\r\nTop 24: playset promo Fully Operational (by Amirul Hhf)\r\n\r\nDo zobaczenia!\r\n\r\nWpisowe 50 PLN płatne gotówką bądź BLIKiem.\r\n\r\nTurnieje District Championship w Polsce w 2026 roku:\r\n- 07.02  - Redraft, Katowice\r\n- 21.02  - Time4Magic, Wrocław\r\n- 21.03 Poznań\r\n- Łódź\r\n\r\n==========\r\n\r\nWe\'d like to invite you to the first tournament in the series of Polish District Championships in 2026! The event will take place on Saturday, February the 21st, at our Friendly Local Game Store Time4Magic, just a short tram ride away from the Train station. Lines 21 and 22 will take you straight from there right under the doors of the shop.\r\n\r\nWe\'ll be playing in the standard format, following the official tournament rules and competitive event guidelines; depending on the number of players, we will play 6-7 rounds of Single Sided Swiss and a TOP4.\r\n\r\nEach Polish District Championship will feature special participation prizes unique to each event along with the prizes in accordance with the District Tournament 2026 prize kit (see below).\r\n\r\nWinner: Bye for any 2026 Megacity Championship, invitation to the 2027 Circuit Breaker Invitational Championship\r\nTop 4: Scrounge playmat (illustrated by Amirul Hhf)\r\nTop 8: Raindrops Cut Stone alt art (illustrated by Amirul Hhf)\r\nTop 24: Fully Operational alt art (illustrated by Amirul Hhf)\r\n\r\nSee you there!\r\n\r\nEntry fee: 50 PLN, by cash or BLIK.\r\n\r\nDistrict Championship tournaments in Poland in 2026\r\n- 07.02 - Redraft, Katowice\r\n- 21.02 - Time4Magic, Wrocław\r\n- 21.03 Poznań\r\n- Łódź',0,1,0,38801,1,'elev',16,'2026-01-12 14:20:35','2026-01-24 08:43:48',NULL,0,51.122264,16.992928,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,129,'','11:00',39,0),(5300,'SanSan North - South Bay Districts','2026.03.15.','10:30','United States','CA','','Santa Clara','','1350 Coleman Ave, Santa Clara, CA 95050, USA','ChIJFwC3errLj4AR09D7KWKrQYA',NULL,NULL,'Placeholder event - details to come',0,0,0,46685,1,'elev',16,'2026-01-12 21:13:10','2026-01-22 13:38:49',NULL,0,37.357458,-121.935267,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','10:00',39,0),(5301,'CBI - Double Elimination Bracket','2026.01.24.','23:00 UTC+0','','','','','','','',16,16,'![Circuit Breaker Invitational](https://alwaysberunning.net/photo/3872.png)',1,0,0,33530,1,'elev',13,'2026-01-13 06:11:07','2026-01-28 16:38:17',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,33530,'2026-01-25 03:23:56',0,NULL,NULL,'','',39,1),(5302,'Circuit Breaker Invitational - APAC Pod','2026.01.17.','09:30 AWST (UTC + 8)','','','','','','','',35,0,'![Circuit Breaker Invitational](https://alwaysberunning.net/photo/3872.png)',1,0,0,33530,1,'elev',13,'2026-01-13 06:19:33','2026-01-22 15:14:13',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,33530,'2026-01-22 15:14:13',0,NULL,NULL,'','09:00 AWST (UTC + 8)',39,1),(5303,'Circuit Breaker Invitational - Americas Pod','2026.01.17.','09:30 PST (UTC - 8)','','','','','','','',54,0,'![Circuit Breaker Invitational](https://alwaysberunning.net/photo/3872.png)',1,0,0,33530,1,'elev',13,'2026-01-13 06:20:37','2026-01-22 15:14:44',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,33530,'2026-01-22 15:14:44',0,NULL,NULL,'','09:00 PST (UTC - 8)',39,1),(5304,'Circuit Breaker Invitational - EMEA Pod','2026.01.18.','09:30 GMT (UTC + 0)','','','','','','','',51,0,'![Circuit Breaker Invitational](https://alwaysberunning.net/photo/3872.png)',1,0,0,33530,1,'elev',13,'2026-01-13 06:22:00','2026-01-22 15:13:53',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,33530,'2026-01-22 15:13:53',0,NULL,NULL,'','09:00 GMT (UTC + 0)',39,1),(5305,'[NANPC] New Jersey 2026 Districts','2026.03.22.','11:30','United States','NJ','@classicapple on Discord','Franklin Township','','120 Cedar Grove Ln, Somerset, NJ 08873, USA','ChIJWcwgct3Aw4kR-xZx4lvOPz8',NULL,NULL,'# Welcome to... The Hortum State!\r\n\r\n### Purchase tickets [HERE](https://gildedravengames.com/products/netrunner-nanpc-new-jersey-2026-districts-ticket-sun-mar-22-2026?ticket=)\r\n\r\n### BONUS: anyone who attends this event gets $5 off their entry to Philly Districts the following week. (Click [HERE](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5329/nanpc-2026-philadelphia-districts) to learn more)\r\n\r\n![2026 Districts header image](https://nullsignal.games/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/2026districtsfan.png)\r\n\r\nThe District Championships and [NANPC](https://nanpc.games/#events) are returning to NJ in 2026. \r\n\r\nDETAILS:\r\nFormat will be Standard, including [Vantage Point]() and any banlist changes announced on or before March 8th.\r\nRegistration will begin when the doors open at 11a. \r\nAt 1130a there will be a brief player meeting before pairing the first round.\r\nWe will play 6-7 rounds of swiss with a 30 minute break for lunch and a top cut.\r\n$20 entry fee (if you are in need of financial assistance, please reach out to @classicapple on Discord)\r\nDecklists to be submitted via Cobra during registration on the day of the event\r\n\r\n### Register and submit decklists on Cobra HERE (this is where the link will be added as soon as it is created)\r\n\r\nPRIZING:\r\nParticipation: Scatter Field NANPC Alt by V4Lvi_\r\nTop 24: Fully Operational Alt by Amirul Hhf\r\nTop 8: Raindrops Cut Stone Alt by Amirul Hhf\r\nTop 4: Scrounge Playmat by Amirul Hhf\r\nWinner: Bye for any 2026 Megacity Championship',0,1,0,16434,1,'elev',16,'2026-01-14 01:35:06','2026-02-01 19:33:23',NULL,0,40.521101,-74.521823,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,129,'Winner: FOIL Scatter Field NANPC Alt by V4Lvi_\r\n\r\nParticipation: Scatter Field NANPC Alt by V4Lvi_, NANPC Click Tracker tokens, discounted entry for NANPC Philly on 3/28','11:00',39,0),(5306,'Adelaide Startup GNK','2026.01.31.','12:00','Australia','','jackmsellars@gmail.com','Adelaide','Good Games Adelaide','88 Grenfell St, Adelaide SA 5000, Australia','ChIJSUEmI-kWNQARahybrMcUWyk',NULL,NULL,'Maybe the last Startup event we have before rotation! Come and show off your trick shots.\r\n\r\n$6 entry.\r\n\r\nDouble-sided swiss rounds. \r\n\r\nreach out to @backtrackjack in the #adelaide channel for questions https://discord.gg/t9ZsGv37',0,0,0,53081,1,'elev',1,'2026-01-14 01:50:18','2026-01-22 13:33:07',NULL,0,-34.924030,138.603083,NULL,0,0,'',0,11,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,128,'Top 8: Otto Campaign alt playset\r\nTop 4: Friend of a Friend alt playset','11:30',39,0),(5307,'Montreal February GNK','2026.02.10.','18:00','Canada','','Odonuvo (Discord)','Montréal','L\'Expédition','6571 Rue St-Hubert, Montréal, QC H2S 2M5, Canada','ChIJKxYya2kZyUwRmTCjKijcUrs',NULL,NULL,'$5 entry fee.\r\n\r\nJoin us for a special edition of our weekly Netrunner gatherings that includes prize support!\r\n\r\nThis is the most casual level of tournament. Bring your jank! Bring your friends! Everyone is welcome.\r\n\r\nParticipation: Friend of a Friend\r\nOtto Campaigns will be raffled\r\n\r\nIf we are more than the prize kit can support, additional prizes will be provided.',0,0,0,32798,1,'elev',1,'2026-01-14 12:22:46','2026-01-22 13:36:19',NULL,0,45.536761,-73.604181,NULL,0,0,'https://www.facebook.com/events/922851403739463',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,128,'','17:30',39,0),(5308,'Bern District Championships','2026.02.15.','10:30','Switzerland','','Discord: lostgeek','Bern','DracheNäscht','Rathausgasse 52, 3011 Bern, Switzerland','ChIJIcns68M5jkcRl2X2aEsb67s',NULL,NULL,'![2026 District Championship Prizes](https://nullsignal.games/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/2026districtsfan.png)\r\n\r\nWir laden ein zum District Championship im [Drachenäscht](https://fatamorgana.ch/drachenaescht/) in Bern!\r\n\r\nGemäss Vorgaben wird das Turnier im [**Standardformat**](https://nullsignal.games/players/supported-formats/) gespielt. Geplant sind 6 Runden Single Sided Swiss + Top 2 Cut. Registrierung startet um 10:00. Turnierstart um 10:30 Uhr. Turnierende wird gegen 17 Uhr sein.\r\n\r\nKosten: 10 CHF pro Person\r\n\r\n**English:**\r\nWe welcome you to the District Championship at the [Drachenäscht](https://fatamorgana.ch/drachenaescht/) in Bern!\r\n\r\nAs per regulations, the tournament will be played in the [**Standard format**](https://nullsignal.games/players/supported-formats/). The plan is for 6 rounds of Single Sided Swiss + a Top 2 Cut. Registration starts at 10 AM. The tournament starts at 10:30 AM and is expected to end around 5 PM.\r\n\r\nCosts: 10 CHF per person.',0,1,0,24742,1,'elev',16,'2026-01-14 15:40:59','2026-01-22 13:37:09',NULL,0,46.948627,7.449351,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','10:00',39,0),(5309,'East Anglian District Championships - Ipswich','2026.03.14.','10:30','United Kingdom','','ewanmilneu@gmail.com','Ipswich','','','ChIJh9jVHoYH2UcRqUItfazD3TM',NULL,NULL,'![](https://nro-public.s3.nl-ams.scw.cloud/voluntary/public-assets/2026-districts/districts-banner-ipswich.webp)\r\n\r\nEast Anglian District Championship\r\n\r\nVenue: TBC\r\nRegistration: 10:00\r\nRound 1 start: 11:00\r\nTicket cost: TBC\r\nMax tickets available: TBC\r\n\r\n**Welcome to Vantage Point**\r\n\r\nThis will be the first competetive level event in England where the new set Vantage Point will be legal! Ipswich doesn\'t have much of a local Netrunner scene but it does have a couple of good board game shops and not_yeti knows the decent pubs and resturants!\r\n\r\n\r\n**What Are District Championships?**\r\n\r\nDistrict Championships replace the UKs old Regional Circuit and form the introductory level of competitive play! They are run throughout the UK by local TOs and Judges, and are a fantastic opportunity for any Netrunner player to get involved in organised play!\r\n\r\n![](https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/1207991839622430750/1459980576143442194/districts-map.webp?ex=696934de&is=6967e35e&hm=f7320cc028f1a4b2bdc1c36544e86f929ef9a6df0fce1be56ee45eeb82ca1a1f&=&format=webp&width=1635&height=920)\r\n\r\nThis year, there will be 8 total districts across the UK:\r\n\r\n- [Birmingham on the 7th of February](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5247/uk-regionals-birmingham-and-dudley-district-champ)\r\n- [Brighton on the 14th of February](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5287/south-coast-brighton-district-championship)\r\n- [Bathgate on the 14th of March](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5259/bathgate-district-championship)\r\n- Ipswich on the 14th of March\r\n- London on a TBD date in March\r\n- [Reading on the 4th of April](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5255/reading-district-championship)\r\n- Birkenhead on the 11th of April\r\n- [Bristol on the 25th of April](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5257/bristol-south-west-district-championship)\r\n**Prizing**\r\n\r\nThis year, each District is organising it\'s own prizing. All will include 2026 District Championship Prize Kit by NSG, but additional prizes may vary by location.\r\n\r\nExcept local artist Brindlemold\'s work to be available at the event.\r\n\r\nLast, but not least, the London & Ipswich Districts will play host to the Annual Londwich Mayoral Election, in which the highest-placing player from a Londwich District Meta (London, East Anglia, South Coast, Aldershot) by total points across both events will be named Mayor of Londwich, and receive the gold-plated Mayor of Londwich Title Badge from its current incumbent, me!\r\n\r\n**Format**\r\n\r\nThis event will be run as 8 rounds of Single Sided Swiss, with no top cut.\r\n\r\nRound 1 will begin at 10:30 with a break for lunch, I will aim to have the event wrapped up around 6pm so we can all go for a drink and a curry!\r\n\r\nVenue Information & Accessibility\r\n\r\nTBC\r\n\r\nTicket Price & Maximum Capacity\r\n\r\nTBC\r\n\r\nContact\r\n\r\nnot_yeti on Discord',0,0,0,39463,1,'elev',16,'2026-01-14 22:40:40','2026-01-22 13:38:34',NULL,0,52.059669,1.148087,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','10:00',39,0),(5310,'London District Championship 2026','2026.03.28.','11:40','United Kingdom','','Nick Wilson - Feathermark on Slack/Discord, 07796474799, nickwilson521@gmail.com','London','The Brotherhood Games Cafe','210-212 Southwark Park Rd., London SE16 3RW, UK','ChIJKcOu8h0DdkgRxztIEM88_H0',NULL,NULL,'![London District Championship](https://nro-public.s3.nl-ams.scw.cloud/voluntary/public-assets/2026-districts/districts-banner-london.webp)\r\n\r\n**London District Championship 2026**\r\n\r\n**Venue:** The Brotherhood Games Cafe, London\r\n**Registration:** 11:00\r\n**Round 1 start:** 11:30\r\n**Ticket cost:** £20.00\r\n**Max tickets available:** 44\r\n\r\n## [Tickets Available Here!](https://www.thebrotherhoodgames.co.uk/special-events) \r\nGet Yours Now and Help Us Extend Our Event Cap! \r\n\r\n\r\n**What Are District Championships?**\r\n\r\nDistrict Championships replace the UKs old Regional Circuit and form the introductory level of competitive play! They are run throughout the UK by local TOs and Judges, and are a fantastic opportunity for any Netrunner player to get involved in organised play!\r\n\r\nThis year, there will be 8 total districts across the UK:\r\n\r\n![districts-map](https://nro-public.s3.nl-ams.scw.cloud/voluntary/public-assets/2026-districts/districts-map.webp)\r\n\r\n- [Birmingham on the 7th of February](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5247/uk-regionals-birmingham-and-dudley-district-champ)\r\n- [Brighton on the 14th of February](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5287/south-coast-brighton-district-championship)\r\n- [Bathgate on the 14th of March](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5259/bathgate-district-championship)\r\n- [Ipswich on the 14th of March](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5309/east-anglian-district-championships-ipswich) \r\n- [London on the 28th of March](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5310/London-District-Championship-2026) \r\n- [Reading on the 4th of April](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5255/reading-district-championship)\r\n- [Birkenhead on the 11th of April](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5311/birkenhead-north-west-uk-district-championships)\r\n- [Bristol on the 25th of April](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5257/bristol-south-west-district-championship)\r\n\r\n**Prizing**\r\nThis year, each District is organising its own prizing. All will include 2026 District Championship Prize Kit by NSG, but additional prizes may vary by location.\r\n\r\nFor the London Event, we are pleased to offer the following additional participation prizes:\r\n**London-themed \"Illumination\" Alt-Art** *by Ams*\r\n**2026 UK District Championship Commemorative Pin** *(for any player that hasn\'t claimed a pin at a previous event)*\r\n\r\nThe winner will also receive the **London District Commemorative Trophy** \r\nto rickognise and celebrate their achievement. \r\n\r\nLast, but not least, the London & Ipswich Districts will play host to the **Annual Londwich Mayoral Election**, in which the highest-placing player from a Londwich District Meta (London, East Anglia, South Coast, Aldershot) by total points across both events will be named **Mayor of Londwich**, and receive the gold-plated **Mayor of Londwich Title Badge** from its current incumbent, not_yeti. \r\n\r\n**Format**\r\nThis event will be 8 rounds of single-sided swiss under the standard ban list that is in effect from the 7th of February. All cards from Vantage Point will be legal for play. \r\n\r\n**Provisional Timetable**\r\n\r\n**Registration Opens:** 11:00 \r\n**Player Meeting:** 11:30\r\n**R1 Start:** 11.40\r\n**Lunch:** 14.10 \r\n**Est. Finish:** by 19:00\r\n\r\nJoin us for Food & Drinks at a local pub after the event! (details to follow!) \r\n\r\n**Venue Information & Accessibility**\r\n\r\n**Nearest Stations** are Surrey Quays on the Windrush Line, Bermondsey on the Jubilee line, or South Bermondsey via Southern Rail\r\n\r\n**Food** will be available to order on site, and there is a selection of takeaway shops and cafes nearby. **No External Food is allowed in the venue.**\r\n\r\n**Ticket Price & Maximum Capacity**\r\nThe price for this event will be £20. Tickets are available [here](https://www.thebrotherhoodgames.co.uk/special-events). If you are in hardship please get in touch with us and we can help you out! \r\n\r\nThe event is currently capped at 44 Players total, but may be able to be extended in the event that we look to exceed this amount by late February. Please book your ticket(s) early to help us gauge numbers and avoid disappointment! \r\n\r\n**Contact**\r\nNick Wilson - nickwilson521@gmail.com, +44 7796 474799, @Feathermark on Discord and Stimhack Slack',0,0,0,21954,1,'elev',16,'2026-01-15 06:51:14','2026-01-24 17:59:21',NULL,0,51.492005,-0.064150,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','11:00',39,0),(5311,'Birkenhead - North West UK District Championships','2026.04.11.','10:45','United Kingdom','','@Sauc3 on discord/slack','Birkenhead','Indigo','136 Bedford Rd, Birkenhead CH42 2AS, UK','ChIJkc3K-dcne0gRkTzlkkwmn6w',NULL,NULL,'![Birkenhead District Championship](https://nro-public.s3.nl-ams.scw.cloud/voluntary/public-assets/2026-districts/districts-banner-birkenhead.webp)\r\n\r\n**Venue:** Indigo Cafe\r\n**Registration:** 10:00\r\n**Round 1 start:** 10:45\r\n**Ticket cost:** £17\r\n**Max tickets available:** 32\r\n\r\n## [Buy Tickets](https://buytickets.at/indigovenuelimited/2024624)\r\n\r\n**What Are District Championships?**\r\n\r\nDistrict Championships replace the UKs old Regional Circuit and form the introductory level of competitive play! They are run throughout the UK by local TOs and Judges, and are a fantastic opportunity for any Netrunner player to get involved in organised play!\r\n\r\nThis year, there will be 8 total districts across the UK:\r\n\r\n![distrits-map](https://nro-public.s3.nl-ams.scw.cloud/voluntary/public-assets/2026-districts/districts-map.webp)\r\n\r\n- [Birmingham on the 7th of February](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5247/uk-regionals-birmingham-and-dudley-district-champ)\r\n- [Brighton on the 14th of February](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5287/south-coast-brighton-district-championship)\r\n- [Bathgate on the 14th of March](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5259/bathgate-district-championship)\r\n- [Ipswich on the 14th of March](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5309/east-anglian-district-championships-ipswich)\r\n- [London on the 28th of March](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5310/london-district-championship-2026)\r\n- [Reading on the 4th of April](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5255/reading-district-championship)\r\n- [Birkenhead on the 11th of April](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5311/birkenhead-north-west-uk-district-championships)\r\n- [Bristol on the 25th of April](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/5257/bristol-south-west-district-championship)\r\n\r\n**Prizing**\r\n\r\nThis year, each District is organising it\'s own prizing. All will include 2026 District Championship Prize Kit by NSG, but additional prizes may vary by location.\r\n\r\nAt Birkenhead, we are pleased to offer the following additional prizes: [MuslihaT - Illus. Valentine de la Rosa](https://alwaysberunning.net/photo/3778.png) as an additional participation prize (if we have over 24 players everyone will get something, but not everyone will get both!) and a special shiny PD for the winner: [Precision Design - Illus. Aleksandra Simonović](https://alwaysberunning.net/photo/thumb_3790.png)\r\n\r\n**Format**\r\n\r\nThis event will be run as a no-cut, extra swiss round event, so that will be 8 rounds of SSS.\r\nRound 1 will start at 10.45 following a player meeting at 10.30. Lunch will be at around 2.15 and the last round will end around 6.30pm\r\n\r\n**Venue Information & Accessibility**\r\nIndigo is a neighbourhood cafe and events venue in Birkenhead. We are quickly and easily accessible from the centre of Liverpool, with trains running from Lime St and other central stations every 15 mins, arriving at Rock Ferry station just 3 mins up the road. For drivers, there is a free car park at the back of the venue (accessible from New Chester Road).\r\n\r\nIndigo\'s food offering will be available beforehand and during the lunch break, including all day breakfast, sandwiches, soups and more (with veggie and vegan options available) and we have a range of soft drinks as well as a fully licensed bar. We also have a well stocked board game cupboard, should you wish to hang out either before or after the event!\r\nMore info: https://g.co/kgs/VH1xm4x\r\n\r\nUnfortunately due to the venue space being located above the cafe, we will not be able to offer step-free access. There will however be fixed seating available, in a separate, quieter side room, so please let a TO if that will be required. All bathrooms are gender neutral.\r\n\r\nI am able to host more than a few people travelling from further afield, please get in touch if you\'d need a place to stay. I know we may be a little more in the sticks than some districts but please don\'t let the cost of accommodation be the thing that puts you off. My parents have recently moved abroad so I literally have a whole empty house down the road I can put people up in!\r\n\r\n**Ticket Price & Maximum Capacity**\r\n\r\nThe price for this event will be £17. Tickets are available [here](https://buytickets.at/indigovenuelimited/2024624). If you are in hardship please get in touch with us and we can help you out! \r\nUnfortunately due to venue size constraints we have a hard cap of 32 players, so get your tickets early!\r\n\r\n**Contact**\r\n\r\nSauc3 on discord/slack',0,0,0,36390,1,'elev',16,'2026-01-15 14:19:39','2026-01-22 13:40:18',NULL,0,53.372886,-3.007949,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','10:00',39,0),(5312,'District Championship @ Rojber, Poznań','2026.03.21.','11:00','Poland','','Bookkeeper (b00kk33per) on Discord','Poznań','','Feliksa Nowowiejskiego 8/5, 61-731 Poznań, Poland','EjJGZWxpa3NhIE5vd293aWVqc2tpZWdvIDgvNSwgNjEtNzMxIFBvem5hxYQsIFBvbGFuZCIdGhsKFgoUChIJVyv2-EdbBEcRPD_lH-Vm5fASATU',NULL,NULL,'ENGLISH BELOW\r\n\r\nZapraszamy na trzeci w serii turniejów District Championships w 2026! W sobotę 21. marca ponownie ugości nas pub Rojber, w ścisłym centrum Poznania.\r\nGramy w formacie Standard, zgodnie z obowiązującymi zasadami turniejowymi i wytycznymi dla turniejów competitive; w zależności od liczby graczy grane będzie 6-7 rund Single Side Swiss + TOP4.\r\n\r\nNa każdym polskim District Championshipie czekają was dodatkowe nagrody za uczestnictwo przygotowane specjalnie na każdy z tych turniejów, a także nagrody z kita zgodnie z oficjalną rozpiską:\r\n\r\nZwycięzca: Bye na dowolnym Megacity Championship w 2026,, zaproszenie na 2027 Circuit Breaker Invitational Championship\r\n\r\nTop 4: mata Scrounge (by Amirul Hhf)\r\nTop 8: playset promo Raindrops Cut Stone (by Amirul Hhf)\r\nTop 24: playset promo Fully Operational (by Amirul Hhf)\r\n\r\nDo zobaczenia!\r\n\r\nWpisowe 50 PLN płatne gotówką bądź BLIKiem.\r\nTurnieje District Championship w Polsce w 2026 roku:\r\n2026-02-07 - Redraft, Katowice\r\n2026-02-21 - Time4Magic, Wrocław\r\n2026-03-21 - Rojber Pub, Poznań\r\n(TBA) Łódź\r\n\r\n==========\r\n\r\nWe\'d like to invite you to the third tournament in the series of Polish District Championships in 2026! The event will take place on Saturday, March the 21st, at our Friendly Rojber Pub, in the very center of Poznań Old Town.\r\n\r\nWe\'ll be playing in the standard format, following the official tournament rules and competitive event guidelines; depending on the number of players, we will play 6-7 rounds of Single Sided Swiss and a TOP4.\r\n\r\nEach Polish District Championship will feature special participation prizes unique to each event along with the prizes in accordance with the District Tournament 2026 prize kit (see below).\r\nWinner: Bye for any 2026 Megacity Championship, invitation to the 2027 Circuit Breaker Invitational Championship\r\n\r\nTop 4: Scrounge playmat (illustrated by Amirul Hhf)\r\nTop 8: Raindrops Cut Stone alt art (illustrated by Amirul Hhf)\r\nTop 24: Fully Operational alt art (illustrated by Amirul Hhf)\r\nSee you there!\r\n\r\nEntry fee: 50 PLN, by cash or BLIK.\r\n\r\nDistrict Championship tournaments in Poland in 2026\r\n2026-02-07 - Redraft, Katowice\r\n2026-02-21 - Time4Magic, Wrocław\r\n2026-03-21 - Rojber Pub, Poznań\r\n(TBA) Łódź',0,1,0,30836,1,'elev',16,'2026-01-15 22:55:40','2026-01-23 21:43:27',NULL,0,52.409357,16.926996,NULL,0,0,'https://www.facebook.com/events/1452751543182798/',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,129,'','10:30',39,0),(5313,'Pawnshop: Now Playing In A Game Store Near You','2026.01.31.','10:30','United Kingdom','','Cobalt on discord (@plunderbird6)','Nottingham','Games Haven','92 Lower Parliament St, Nottingham NG1 1EH, UK','ChIJS1F9X_HDeUgRJVS6Fsjk8TQ',11,0,'The People\'s Garbage returns! And now in person!\r\n\r\nAll cards are allowed, save one condition\\*: they must be in the bottom half of [Trash or Busto](https://trash-or-busto.herokuapp.com/ranking). Welcome to the arena of Because We Built It, Jesminder Sareen, Architects of Tomorrow and Reina Roja!\r\n\r\nThe event will be 5-6 40 minute single-sided swiss rounds - player count depending. If we get more than 15 players, we\'ll do a top 4 cut, otherwise it\'ll just be Swiss. The tournament will be managed using Cobra.\r\n\r\nFor getting to Games Haven, it\'s within reasonable [walking distance](https://www.google.co.uk/maps/dir/Nottingham+Railway+Station,+Carrington+St.,+Nottingham+NG2+3AQ/Games+Haven,+Lower+Parliament+Street,+Nottingham/@52.9509074,-1.1445198,16.58z/data=!4m14!4m13!1m5!1m1!1s0x4879c30fa5de4cc1:0xdab4041216dcb98e!2m2!1d-1.1455799!2d52.9474425!1m5!1m1!1s0x4879c3f15f7d514b:0x34f1e4c816ba5425!2m2!1d-1.1413296!2d52.9544642!3e2) of Nottingham Railway Station, and there\'s also a robust bus network to bring you closer if arriving from outside the city. Limited, free on-site parking is available.\r\n\r\nPrices are a door fee of £7.50 for Games Haven itself, providing unlimited tea and coffee, plus £3 to me for event entry. We\'ll be using the 2025 Q4 GNK (Azimat, Biawak) as prizing!\r\n\r\n\\*We are **restricting playing LLDS Energy Regulator and Time Bomb in the same deck**, though. Nobody is here for that. Sorry! ❤\r\n\r\nThe lists of legal cards are locked in and are available below:\r\n\r\n[Runner](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/deck/view/5f948911-4a87-4113-afa9-5a37ff23a4ec)\r\n[Corp](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/deck/view/f2c35cd1-0ecd-4272-b2e8-ebfb13889520)\r\n\r\n**Sublists**\r\n[Haas-Bioroid](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/deck/view/5baa24fe-742d-4f14-8160-5508e482585a)\r\n[Jinteki](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/deck/view/7db639b9-f2e7-400d-830c-b4c2acedf296)\r\n[NBN](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/deck/view/0a35edf0-05a6-4cb4-bda2-7b771f6024d6)\r\n[Weyland](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/deck/view/881e355f-96fc-4eb4-83e0-75bd33e2fd0c)\r\n[Neutral Corp](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/deck/view/a9aa805a-1e74-42a3-99b3-30c18e4e9511)\r\n\r\n[Anarch](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/deck/view/9613a512-dbe6-4621-856e-2bfe794c66d0)\r\n[Criminal](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/deck/view/b059437b-2a53-4e52-a33f-e1511fcc3482)\r\n[Shaper](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/deck/view/591ef4e2-c8a8-4824-b452-e31b60f91217)\r\n[Neutral & Mini-faction](https://netrunnerdb.com/en/deck/view/b7667973-5b2e-4d5e-8757-6d2581c35b81)\r\n\r\nThe legal identities are:\r\n\r\n**Runner**\r\n- Apex: Invasive Predator\r\n- Ayla \"Bios\" Rahim: Simulant Specialist\r\n- Az McCaffrey: Mechanical Prodigy\r\n- Captain Padma Isbister: Intrepid Explorer\r\n- Dewi Subrotoputri: Pedagogical Dhalang\r\n- Exile: Streethawk\r\n- Iain Stirling: Retired Spook\r\n- Jesminder Sareen: Girl Behind the Curtain\r\n- Khan: Savvy Skiptracer\r\n- Laramy Fisk: Savvy Investor\r\n- Los: Data Hijacker\r\n- Nasir Meidan: Cyber Explorer\r\n- Nathaniel \"Gnat\" Hall: One-of-a-Kind\r\n- Nero Severn: Information Broker\r\n- Nova Initiumia: Catalyst & Impetus\r\n- Null: Whistleblower\r\n- Reina Roja: Freedom Fighter\r\n- Ryō \"Phoenix\" Ōno: Out of the Ashes\r\n- Silhouette: Stealth Operative\r\n- Sunny Lebeau: Security Specialist\r\n- The Professor: Keeper of Knowledge\r\n- Topan: Ormas Leader\r\n\r\n**Corp**\r\n- Ampère: Cybernetics For Anyone\r\n- BANGUN: When Disaster Strikes\r\n- Custom Biotics: Engineered for Success\r\n- Cybernetics Division: Humanity Upgraded\r\n- Earth Station: SEA Headquarters\r\n- GRNDL: Power Unleashed\r\n- GameNET: Where Dreams are Real\r\n- Haas-Bioroid: Stronger Together\r\n- Harishchandra Ent.: Where You\'re the Star\r\n- Harmony Medtech: Biomedical Pioneer\r\n- Hyoubu Institute: Absolute Clarity\r\n- Issuaq Adaptics: Sustaining Diversity\r\n- NBN: Making News\r\n- NBN: The World is Yours*\r\n- NEXT Design: Guarding the Net\r\n- New Angeles Sol: Your News\r\n- Nisei Division: The Next Generation\r\n- PT Untaian: Life\'s Building Blocks\r\n- Poétrï Luxury Brands: All the Rage\r\n- SSO Industries: Fueling Innovation\r\n- Saraswati Mnemonics: Endless Exploration\r\n- Seidr Laboratories: Destiny Defined\r\n- Synapse Global: Faster than Thought\r\n- The Foundry: Refining the Process\r\n- Thunderbolt Armaments: Peace Through Power\r\n- Weyland Consortium: Because We Built It\r\n- Weyland Consortium: Building a Better World',1,0,0,41523,1,'elev',1,'2026-01-16 09:15:39','2026-02-25 08:37:25',NULL,4,52.954464,-1.141330,NULL,0,0,'',0,6,NULL,41523,'2026-01-31 16:56:12',0,'Europe/London',127,'','10:00',39,0),(5314,'HQ Shuffle Ep.1',NULL,'','United States','CA','','Cupertino','','','ChIJq3fTG1e0j4ARtHjho-E_TTk',NULL,NULL,'Private cube draft - HQ Shuffle Ep. 1',0,0,0,51010,NULL,'unknown',8,'2026-01-17 08:07:27','2026-01-17 08:08:04','2026-01-17 08:08:04',0,37.322998,-122.032182,NULL,0,0,'',0,5,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'','',39,0),(5315,'Muenster Disctrict Championship','2026.03.29.','10:30','Germany','','bauzaun@posteo.de or discord @sciurus_vulgaris','Münster','','Am Mittelhafen 42, 48155 Münster, Germany','ChIJD94bBim7uUcR5cNQZ7Sa90A',NULL,NULL,'Liebe Runner:innen,\r\n(english version below)\r\n\r\n Wir freuen uns den Zuschlag für die District Championships erhalten zu haben. 1 Jahr nach unserem aller ersten Casual Turnier, dürfen wir nun schon ein offizielles Turnier ausrichten. Aufregend. Glücklicherweise konnten wir auch eine großartige Location für die DC finden.\r\n\r\nMehr Informationen folgen in den nächsten Wochen. \r\n\r\nHier die Hard Facts bisher:\r\n- Es werden 6 Runden Single Sided Swiss (40min. time slots) gespielt. Danach folgt ein Top Cut aus wahrscheinlich 2 Runden\r\n- Wir haben zwei Räume in der Location von 10-21 Uhr. Danach kann aber noch open End an der Bar und in den großen Räumen abgehangen werden\r\n- Neben den DC Preisen, werden wir auch noch zusätzliche Participation Prizes aushändigen können :)\r\n- Wir peilen eine 1-stündige Mittagspause an. Wenn ihr mögt, können wir Euch auf eine Bestellliste für Pizza mit aufnehmen.\r\n\r\nAufgrund der Räumlichkeiten sind wir leider auf 30 Personen beschränkt.\r\nDie Teilnahme an der Veranstaltung wird zwischen 8-13€ kosten. Es gibt eine Bar für Getränke am Veranstaltungsort. Eigene Getränke und Snacks dürfen in unseren Räumen konsumiert werden. Ein paar Snacks werden wir vorher einkaufen.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nAwareness & Code of Conduct\r\nWir möchten, dass sich alle auf unserer Veranstaltung sicher und wohl fühlen. Wenn du dich unwohl fühlst, eine unangenehme Situation erlebst oder Unterstützung brauchst, kannst du dich jederzeit vertrauensvoll an den TO (sciurus_vulgaris) wenden.\r\nVorfälle wie Belästigung, Diskriminierung, Einschüchterung oder Gewaltandrohungen nehmen wir ernst. Solche Verhaltensweisen können zur sofortigen Disqualifikation und zum Ausschluss von der Veranstaltung führen. Wenn du so etwas erlebst, wende dich bitte direkt an den TO. Unser Vorgehen richtet sich nach dem Code of Conduct von NSG.\r\n\r\nAdresse:\r\nB-Side \r\nAm Mittelhafen 42\r\n48155 Münster \r\n(Veranstaltung findet im 1. OG statt. Es gibt einen Fahrstuhl)\r\nBei Fragen schreibt mir gerne an die E-Mail oder schreibt mir eine PN über Discord (Ihr findet mich auf dem deutschen Netrunner Server).\r\nsciurus_vulgaris -- Jole\r\n\r\n--------\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nDear Runners,\r\n(deutsche Version unten)\r\n\r\n We are delighted to have been awarded the District Championships. One year after our very first casual tournament, we now have the opportunity to host an official tournament. Exciting! Fortunately, we have also found a great location for the DC.\r\n\r\nMore information will follow in the coming weeks. \r\n\r\nHere are the hard facts so far:\r\n- There will be 6 rounds of Single Sided Swiss (40-minute time slots). This will be followed by a top cut of probably 2 rounds.\r\n- We have two rooms at the location from 10 a.m. to 9 p.m. After that, you can still hang out at the bar and in the large rooms until closing time.\r\n- In addition to the DC prizes, we will also be able to hand out additional participation prizes :)\r\n- We are aiming for a 1-hour lunch break. If you like, we can add you to an order list for pizza.\r\n\r\nDue to the size of the venue, we are unfortunately limited to 30 people.\r\nParticipation in the event will cost between €8 and €13. There is a bar for drinks at the venue. You are welcome to consume your own drinks and snacks in our rooms. We will buy a few snacks beforehand.\r\n\r\n\r\nAwareness & Code of Conduct\r\nWe want everyone to feel safe and comfortable at our event. If you feel uncomfortable, experience an unpleasant situation, or need support, you can always contact the TO (sciurus_vulgaris) in confidence.\r\nWe take incidents such as harassment, discrimination, intimidation, or threats of violence seriously. Such behavior can lead to immediate disqualification and exclusion from the event. If you experience something like this, please contact the TO directly. Our approach is based on the NSG Code of Conduct.\r\n\r\nAddress:\r\nB-Side \r\nAm Mittelhafen 42\r\n48155 Münster \r\n(The event will take place on the 1st floor. There is an elevator.)\r\nIf you have any questions, feel free to email me or send me a private message on Discord (you can find me on the German Netrunner server).\r\nsciurus_vulgaris -- Jole',0,0,0,33017,1,'elev',16,'2026-01-17 21:11:29','2026-01-28 15:37:17',NULL,0,51.950609,7.644352,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,129,'','10:00',39,0),(5316,'GNK @ Craving For A Game','2026.01.31.','10:00','Canada','','sokkaanr@gmail.com','Surrey','Craving For A Game','10153 King George Blvd #2293, Surrey, BC V3T 2W1, Canada','ChIJo6aWiNPZhVQRPGAkKfDy_X8',NULL,NULL,'The event will be from 10am to 2pm. We will play 6 rounds of single-sided swiss. Note that there is no lunch break. We will likely go as a group for a late lunch at the food court after the event (optional).\r\n\r\nThis event has a player limit of 8. Please RSVP at the following link and await a confirmation message before attending.\r\n\r\n[https://forms.gle/J9H24t5PQyiB2EpNA](https://forms.gle/J9H24t5PQyiB2EpNA)\r\n\r\nIf we get 8 players, cost will be $10 per person, which includes store credit for the top 3 ($25, $10, $5). If we get less than 8 players, the cost may be adjusted and store credit removed.\r\n\r\nDecklists are not required.',0,0,0,18976,1,'elev',1,'2026-01-18 03:45:22','2026-01-22 13:33:37',NULL,0,49.186084,-122.849663,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,118,'','10:00',39,0),(5317,'German Discord Liga V: Next Big Helau','2026.01.29.','12:02','','','dainestevens@gmail.com','','','','',NULL,NULL,'[English below]\r\n\r\nLiebe Community,\r\n\r\nwir starten Runde 5 der Online-Liga der deutschen Netrunner-Discord-Community, die von unserem TorpedoTyrus ins Leben gerufen wurde. Die Spiele werden online auf jinteki.net ausgetragen oder, wenn ihr es bevorzugt, persönlich, wenn ihr mit jemandem aus eurem Meta gepaart wurdet. Die Paarungen werden in der deutschen Netrunner-Discord-Community organisiert, die ihr hier findet: https://discord.gg/tbZYuUTV\r\n\r\nDie Teilnahme ist kostenlos. Es gibt eine begrenzte Anzahl von Preisen aus meiner Sammlung, die nach dem Zufallsprinzip verteilt werden. Preise für die Teilnahme werden organisiert, ebenso wie eine Möglichkeit, auf Wunsch für diesen Fonds zu spenden.\r\n\r\nDas Turnier wird nach den folgenden Regeln durchgeführt:\r\n- Es sind keine Decklisten erforderlich und die Decks können auf Wunsch jede Woche geändert werden.\r\n-Die Decks müssen gemäß der neuesten Bannliste standardkonform sein.\r\n-Je nach Teilnehmerzahl wird die Liga über 6 Runden ausgetragen.\r\n-Spiele sind DSS\r\n\r\nDear comminity,\r\n\r\nWe are starting round 5 of the online league of the German netrunner discord in the continuing tradition started by our own TorpedoTyrus. Games will be played online at jinteki.net or face-to-face if you have been paired with someone in your meta, if preferred. Pairings will be organized in the German netrunner discord found here: https://discord.gg/tbZYuUTV\r\n\r\nThere is no fee for participating. Limited prizing from my collection will be available, distributed randomly. Prizes for participation are being organized, as well as a way to donate to that fund, if desired.\r\n\r\nThe tournament will be run according to the following rules:\r\n-No decklists are required and decks may be changed every week, if desired.\r\n-Decks must be standard legal according to the newest banlist.\r\n-Depending on turnout the league will run 6 rounds.\r\n-Matches are double-sided swiss\r\n\r\nOrganizer\r\nDaine – dainestevens@gmail.com\r\n\r\nDate & Time\r\nThursday, January 29, 2026\r\nFormat and Deckbuilding\r\nSwiss Format: Double-sided\r\nGame Format: Standard\r\nDeckbuilding Restrictions: Standard Ban List 25.12',0,0,0,750,1,'elev',12,'2026-01-18 11:13:38','2026-01-22 13:32:52',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','12:01',39,1),(5320,'NLB Throwback','2026.02.28.','13:00','United States','MD','ke.claytor@gmail.com','Baltimore','No Land Beyond','108 W North Ave, Baltimore, MD 21201, USA','ChIJF4gmsrEFyIkR9g7TettXVro',NULL,NULL,'Last stretch before Vantage Point comes out - let\'s do something interesting to get our deckbuilding juices flowing.\r\n\r\n# Enter [throwback](https://alwaysberunning.net/tournaments/4551/sansan-south-december-throwback-event)\r\n\r\ntldr; \"You get one playset of rotated cards to choose for your corporation, and one playset of rotated cards to choose for your runner, for two playsets total... the card can not have been banned at the moment it was rotated.\"\r\n\r\nDepending on players this will likely be 4-5 rounds of swiss without cut.\r\n\r\nNote: there is a $5 table fee paid to store on entry, no other entry fee.',0,0,0,10243,1,'elev',1,'2026-01-18 20:01:30','2026-01-22 13:38:03',NULL,0,39.311352,-76.618380,NULL,0,0,'',0,6,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,117,'Top 1: AuCo Laser Cut ID by KC\r\nTop 4: 3D ID (your choice from available)','12:30',39,0),(5321,'Sydney Android Union GNK','2026.02.22.','12:30','Australia','','ivan.kent00@gmail.com','Ultimo','Behold Games','17, 99 Jones Street Corner of Macarthur and Jones, Ultimo NSW 2007, Australia','ChIJJ4JSosevEmsR8ScyjS_OfQo',NULL,NULL,'',0,0,0,50345,1,'elev',1,'2026-01-19 00:39:43','2026-01-22 13:37:31',NULL,0,-33.880006,151.197556,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,127,'','12:00',39,0),(5322,'Netrunner Local Meetup - 1/17/2026','2026.01.17.','','United States','ND','','Fargo','JWW Sports Cards & Gaming','3902 13th Ave S #100, Fargo, ND 58103, USA','ChIJh8Vh7HvLyFIR-9z3YDfzZyI',6,NULL,'',1,0,0,49460,1,'elev',1,'2026-01-19 04:28:25','2026-01-22 13:31:05',NULL,4,46.858429,-96.847709,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,49460,'2026-01-19 04:28:25',0,NULL,117,'','',39,0),(5324,'Netrunning in Abaco','2026.02.08.','10:30','Spain','','netrunnet.bilbao@gmail.com','Bilbao','Abaco Asociación Lúdica','Aita Larramendi Kalea, 3, Errekalde, 48012 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain','ChIJxym2vixQTg0RcElYFi253T4',NULL,NULL,'Torneo con el GNK del Q4 de 2025, sin reglas raras para montar mazos\r\nSuizo de ida y vuelta con corp y runner a un mínimo de 3 rondas.',0,1,0,42048,1,'elev',1,'2026-01-19 13:02:30','2026-01-22 13:36:05',NULL,0,43.254009,-2.943564,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,127,'','10:00',39,0),(5325,'SanSan South February Standard Event','2026.02.01.','11:00','United States','CA','','San Diego','At Ease Games Gaming & Tournament Center','8400 Miramar Rd #250, San Diego, CA 92126, USA','ChIJOYx-5jP624AR5EuZHI5X7Jo',NULL,NULL,'[our discord](https://discord.gg/E4p2bCd9g6)\r\n\r\nCome on down to Sunny San Diego and play some Standard! :D\r\n\r\n$5 entry fee to the store.\r\n\r\nI\'ve got plenty of proxies to serve as prize support :D\r\n\r\nThis will be a single-sided swiss event of 6 rounds of 40 minutes each, with a potential runoff if deemed appropriate the day of.',0,0,0,7308,1,'elev',1,'2026-01-20 01:46:15','2026-01-29 17:07:49','2026-01-29 17:07:49',0,32.891923,-117.141539,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,128,'GNK will be the prize if it arrives in time, otherwise proxies :)','10:30',39,0),(5326,'AstroScript Delivery Service No 1 - 14/02/26','2026.02.14.','16:00','','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,'![discord.com/invite/6uNKtXEwPe](https://www.vice.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2018/10/1540226541262-port-ill-astroscript.jpeg)\r\n\r\nWelcome to the inaugural event of AstroScript Delivery Service, an Online Eernal Focused tournament series!\r\n\r\nIf you\'ve never gotten into eternal and want to give it a chance, join us over athttps://discord.gg/6uNKtXEwPe and there will be tonnes of players who will introduce you to the highest powered netrunner format there is. If you like high stakes, powerful swings, and tense games, It will be a good chance to give it a try!\r\n\r\nPlacing well in the tournament will earn you a playset of Ams\' Slot Machine alt arts, a staple for the format. \r\n\r\nThe tournament takes place on the 14th February 2026, at 1600UTC. That\'s 1100 EST and 0800 PST. We will play 5 sides of single sided swiss, with an optional top cut.\r\n\r\nIN THE TOURNAMENT SERIES THERE IS A BONUS PRIZE FOR THE FUNNIEST/MOST CREATIVE DECK. If your deck wins this prize, it will go into the hall of fame, where it will be seen for the rest of netrunner history!\r\n\r\n\r\nJoin now at https://discord.gg/6uNKtXEwPe',0,0,0,38377,1,'elev',6,'2026-01-20 15:55:24','2026-01-22 13:36:33',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,7,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','10:00',39,1),(5327,'Berlin Megacity Championship 2026 - SAVE THE DATE','2026.05.30.','','Germany','','@awildturtok on discord','Berlin','Jugendherberge Berlin Ostkreuz','Marktstraße 9-12, 10317 Berlin, Germany','ChIJ9cl27fBOqEcRHYOrTsx8-MA',NULL,NULL,'## Get in the robot shinji!\r\n\r\nWe\'re doing it again: Berlin Megacity Championship. For those that are still dreaming of German Nats, or whatever the boomers called it back when. Anyway, I\'m just domain squatting for the moment. More info in the coming future (I hope!).\r\n\r\nThis will be a two day event,\r\n* Saturday: Swiss\r\n* Sunday: Top Cut + Side Events\r\n\r\nLocation will be the [Jugendherrberge at Ostkreuz](https://www.jugendherbergeberlinostkreuz.de/): https://maps.app.goo.gl/Q8M79YnozcwYRC42A\r\nMarktstraße 9-12, 10317 Berlin\r\n\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions feel free to DM me.',0,0,0,40004,1,'unknown',17,'2026-01-20 16:26:28','2026-01-22 13:40:43',NULL,0,52.504127,13.471346,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','',39,0),(5328,'Netrunner Sealed Draft','2026.02.07.','13:15','United States','MI','7346602769','Detroit','Opal Grove Games','3546 Michigan Ave, Detroit, MI 48216, USA','ChIJ3fzf7MxObwUR_OnKEacx9jM',NULL,NULL,'Netrunner Sealed Cube Draft thrown by Metro Detroit Netrunners Discord. Can support 8 players, priority given to those who haven\'t drafted before. All cards provided. 1 hour for deckbuilding followed by 5-6 single sided Swiss rounds. Entrance fee $8.',0,0,0,23117,1,'elev',11,'2026-01-21 17:08:47','2026-02-01 00:58:15',NULL,0,42.331678,-83.093000,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'TBD','13:00',39,0),(5329,'[NANPC] 2026 Philadelphia Districts','2026.03.28.','12:00','United States','PA','jameskbarnhart@gmail.com','Pennsylvania','Alternate Universes Holmes','2129 MacDade Boulevard, Holmes, PA 19043, USA','ChIJyU9b3PXCxokRRSpX44n7Y38',NULL,NULL,'DETAILS:\r\nCard pool will include Vantage Point\r\nRegistration will begin when the doors open at 11am\r\nAt 11:30am there will be a brief player meeting before pairing the first round at noon\r\nWe will play 6-7 rounds of Single side swiss with a 30 minute meal break and a top cut.\r\n$20 entry fee ($5 discount for players who registered for and attended both Jersey and Philly Districts)\r\n45 min rounds\r\nDecklists to be submitted via Cobra upon registration',0,1,0,44167,1,'elev',16,'2026-01-22 16:39:40','2026-01-24 11:35:08',NULL,0,39.898390,-75.310960,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'2026 Districts Prize Kit:\r\nTop 24: Fully Operational Alt by Amirul Hhf\r\nTop 8: Raindrops Cut Stone Alt by Amirul Hhf and AU store credit payout.\r\nTop 4: Scrounge Playmat by Amirul Hhf\r\nWinner: Bye for any 2026 Megacity Championship','11:00',39,0),(5330,'Mutually Assured Construction - Philly Startup','2026.02.21.','12:30','United States','PA','jameskbarnhart@gmail.com','Philadelphia','','','ChIJ60u11Ni3xokRwVg-jNgU9Yk',NULL,NULL,'Mutually Assured Construction is a casual beginner friendly event aimed at new and returning players. This time we are graduating to the Startup cardpool! New and experienced players welcome, use this event to foster community and help to educate and onboard new players joining the game with Elevation.\r\n\r\nFormat: Startup (System Gateway + Elevation only + Liberation)\r\nBanlist: Cleaver, Pharos, Tributary, NBN: Reality Plus, Coalescence, S-Dobrado\r\nBuy In/ Registration: $10\r\nLocation: TBA, In or near Philly\r\nRecord Based Prize Support for 4 Single sided rounds, Swiss pairings, 50 Minute round timer',0,0,0,44167,1,'elev',1,'2026-01-22 20:17:38','2026-01-24 11:34:40',NULL,0,39.952584,-75.165222,NULL,0,0,'',0,11,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,128,'3D Printed Token Set\r\nMAC Reaper Function Alt Art Promos\r\n3D Printed Mark Dice','11:30',39,0),(5331,'Toulouse District Championship 2026','2026.04.04.','09:30','France','','raphael.langella@gmail.com','Toulouse','','20 Pl. Jean Diebold, 31300 Toulouse, France','ChIJ__8PmXG7rhIRaoSW-iUM5F4',NULL,NULL,'The Toulouse District Championship will be held on April the 4th and 5th.\r\nIt will take place at 20 Place Jean Diebold (Saint Cyprien district) and the venue has a capacity of 40 players. Entry fee will be 15€ and we\'re planning on 6 rounds of single sided swiss on the Saturday with the top cut and side events on the Sunday.',0,1,0,24472,1,'unknown',16,'2026-01-22 20:51:06','2026-01-24 11:35:24',NULL,0,43.597824,1.430128,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,129,'','09:00',39,0),(5332,'11 Ogólnopolska Liga Netrunnera : Standard','2025.11.03.','','','','','','','','ChIJAZ-GmmbMHkcR_NPqiCq-8HI',28,0,'11 Liga ogólnopolska \r\nod 03.11.2025 do 23.01.2026',1,0,0,45677,1,'elev',1,'2026-01-22 22:47:43','2026-01-24 11:34:09',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,45677,'2026-01-22 22:48:55',0,NULL,NULL,'','',38,1),(5333,'Cologne Pub Brawl #1','2026.02.07.','12:00','Germany','','Tyrus on Discord','Köln','Station - Bar, Cafe & Restaurant','Marzellenstraße 50 - 56, 50668 Köln, Germany','ChIJmw5W46Qlv0cRyRLXsmhIfgM',NULL,NULL,'### Cologne Pub Brawl #1\r\n\r\n*** English Below ***\r\n\r\nHallo Freunde! Wir haben die Ehre am 07.02. mal wieder in der Station Bar ein Turnier auszurichten! Wir werden ein letztes mal das alte Standard Meta in Köln feiern! Es gibt wie immer Alt Art Preise (genaueres gebe ich später bekannt), Matten und den süßen Geschmack des Sieges zu gewinnen! Der Preis wird je nach Teilnehmerzahl zwischen 5-8 Euro liegen, falls das jedoch ein Problem sein sollte kommt gerne trotzdem, das bekommen wir hin ohne große Mühen! Die Einstiegshürde soll niedrig sein, jetzt ist der perfekte Zeitpunkt sich nocheinmal mit dem kleinen Standard-Pool vertraut zu machen bevor die neuen Karten kommen! Falls jemand Decks benötigt (sowohl Ideen als auch physische Karten) einfach melden!\r\n\r\nGespielt werden 6 Runden Single Sided Swiss mit 40 Minuten Zeit pro Runde. \r\n\r\nAußerdem wird es ein neues turnierübergreifendes Goody in Form einer Bingo Karte geben. Erfüllt die Punkte bei Casual Tournements und ihr bekommt selbstredent einen Preis dafür! Keine Sorge, jeder wird eine Reihe finden die erfüllbar ist ungeachtet der Spielerstärke! Bei allen NRW Events (welche kleiner sind als Districts) könnt ihr die Karte mitnehmen!\r\n\r\nWir können sehr gerne nach dem Turnier dort bleiben und Brettspiele spielen! \r\n\r\nFreu mich auf euch!\r\n\r\n------\r\n\r\nHello friends! We are honoured to host another tournament at Station Bar on 7 February! We will celebrate the old Standard Meta in Cologne one last time! As always, there will be Alt Art prizes (I will announce the details later), mats and the sweet taste of victory to be won! The entry fee will be between 5€ and 8€, depending on the number of participants, but if that\'s a problem, feel free to come anyway, we\'ll work something out! The barrier to entry should be low, so now is the perfect time to familiarise yourself with the small Standard pool before the new cards arrive! If anyone needs decks (both ideas and physical cards), just let us know!\r\n\r\nWe will play 6 rounds of Single Sided Swiss with 40 minutes per round. \r\n\r\nThere will also be a new tournament-wide goody in the form of a bingo card. Earn points in casual tournaments and you will of course receive a prize! Don\'t worry, everyone will find a row that can be completed regardless of player strength! You can take the card with you to all NRW events (which are smaller than Districts)!\r\n\r\nHappy to see y\'all!',0,1,0,31154,1,'elev',1,'2026-01-23 08:32:27','2026-01-23 11:14:59',NULL,0,50.944075,6.956088,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','11:30',39,0),(5334,'Barcelona District Tournament Zacatrus!','2026.03.21.','','Spain','','David/valerian32','Barcelona','Zacatrus','Carrer de Casanova, 3, Eixample, 08011 Barcelona, Spain','ChIJgTmrmX6jpBIRgG6qr1MLU78',NULL,NULL,'Es \r\n\r\nEl torneo district se realizará en la tienda Zacatrús! en Barcelona. \r\n\r\n**Entrada gratuita** (requisito del local)\r\n\r\nSeguramente haya ya salido Vantage Point y haya una Standard Ban List actualizada.\r\n\r\nEN\r\n\r\nDisctrict Tournament will be held in Zacatrús! Barcelona during the day. Exact hours to be determined. \r\n\r\n**Free entry** (requirement from the venue)\r\n\r\nProbably there Vantage Point would have been released and there will be the \"with the set\" banlist appliable.',0,1,0,6869,1,'unknown',16,'2026-01-23 22:01:25','2026-01-24 11:34:54',NULL,0,41.382093,2.162987,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,129,'','',39,0),(5335,'Barcelona monthly tournament January','2026.01.31.','10:45','Spain','','bcnetop@gmail.com','Barcelona','inGenio BCN Games','Pg. de St. Joan, 16, Eixample, 08010 Barcelona, Spain','ChIJs4AmnOSipBIRDhSJNlGVYWc',NULL,NULL,'Just our monthly tournament in ingenio.',0,1,0,40364,1,'elev',6,'2026-01-24 10:40:47','2026-01-24 11:34:24',NULL,0,41.392339,2.179333,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','10:30',39,0),(5336,'CT in Köln am 14.03.2026','2026.03.14.','12:30','Germany','','tradonnetrunner@hotmail.com','Köln','Station - Bar, Cafe & Restaurant','Marzellenstraße 50 - 56, 50668 Köln, Germany','ChIJmw5W46Qlv0cRyRLXsmhIfgM',NULL,NULL,'Bitte meldet euch an - das hilft uns bei der Planung und andere Leute sehen, dass auch jemand kommt und sind dadurch vielleicht motivierter.\r\n\r\nWas: CT - Standard\r\nSamstag Abend nach dem Turnier können wir vor Ort noch Netrunnern, Brettspiele spielen usw. \r\nSchreibt mir gern an bei Fragen aller Art :)\r\n\r\n*Ort:* siehe Karte am Rand: Station Bar in Köln in der Nähe des HBF (Marzellenstraße 50 - 56, 50668 Köln)\r\n*Zeit:* Registrierung ab 11:30uhr - Start Runde 1 ab 12:30uhr (gebt gern direkt Bescheid wenn ihr zeitlich knapp seid - wir sind flexibel!)\r\n*Kosten:* 5-10€ pro Person (Geld wird benutzt für Kosten CT-Preiskit - je mehr Leute, desto günstiger wird es)\r\n\r\n*gespieltes Format:* NSG-Standard, aktueller Kartenpool + jeweils aktuelle MWL\r\n**inkl. Vantage Point!!!!!!**\r\nRundenanzahl, Top-Cut usw. nach Anzahl der Spieler - voraussichtlich 5-6 Runden SSS\r\n\r\nWer mag darf mir gern ne Mail schicken, dann kann ich ihn/sie/es/euch per Mail über Änderungen informieren. Ist aber komplett optional. Guckt gern auch im Netrunner-Deutschland-Discord vorbei :)\r\n\r\nFalls Fragen sind: schickt mir eine Mail\r\n\r\nIf someone needs english information or has questions - pls mail me and I will happily translate or answer everything you\'d like to know :)\r\n\r\nPat, aka Tradon\r\n\r\n- keep runnin\'',0,0,0,23078,1,'elev',11,'2026-01-24 13:31:42','2026-01-29 13:38:44',NULL,0,50.944075,6.956088,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,119,'','11:30',39,0),(5337,'[NANPC] Toronto Districts 2026','2026.03.28.','11:00','Canada','','zeeman.chris@gmail.com','Toronto','Sheraton Centre Toronto Hotel','123 Queen St W, Toronto, ON M5H 2M9, Canada','ChIJxVYPt800K4gRFtI3GZJCKx4',NULL,NULL,'Hello Netrunners! With the new set, Vantage Point, releasing on March 2nd it\'s time to get hyped for the upcoming competitive season! This event will be both a stop on the NANPC tour along with being a District Championship. All participants will receive a custom NANPC alt of Scatterfield!\r\n\r\nLocation: The [PATH](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1mft8nPUDRx4yedQLRCxUCi-2DQ_BeB-A5uiTcsayO7w/edit) (Under the Sheraton Hotel)\r\n\r\nPrice: $10\r\nLunch Pizza Party (not mandatory): $10\r\n\r\nRegistration time: 10:00am\r\nTournament Start: 11:00am\r\n\r\nThis will be 6-7 rounds of Single Sided Swiss with a lunch break of 45 minutes after the first 3 or 4 rounds.\r\n\r\nDecklists must be provided and can be entered during registration [HERE](https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/tournaments/4477)  .\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions you can contact me via the provided email, my discord under the handle zeebag , or you can join the Torsaug community [discord](https://discord.gg/UBDMBKus9g) .',0,1,0,25380,1,'elev',16,'2026-01-24 14:39:44','2026-01-29 13:39:00',NULL,0,43.651195,-79.384257,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,129,'![Image](https://alwaysberunning.net/photo/3865.png)','10:00',39,0),(5338,'Pittsburgh Vantage Point Release Party!','2026.03.07.','11:00','United States','PA','danmyth@gmail.com','Pittsburgh','Mimic\'s Market','4707 Liberty Ave, Pittsburgh, PA 15224, USA','ChIJo8fumr7zNIgRP_R5cdxo4uo',NULL,NULL,'## Vantage Point Release Party!\r\n\r\n![Image](https://nullsignal.games/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/OWL_C9_Illustration.png)\r\n\r\nJoin us at Mimic\'s Market on Saturday, March 7th to celebrate the release of Vantage Point, the new set for Netrunner!\r\n\r\nYou can buy your copy of Vantage Point at the store, sleeve up a few decks, and play casual games to win prizes. In addition to participation prizing, there will be an achievements list/bingo card. Be the first to win with a new ID, take an 8 click turn, or flatline a Runner, and you\'ll get your pick off the Alt Art table. \r\n\r\nPlayers of all experience levels are welcome. Come learn to play Netrunner!\r\n\r\nIf you\'d like a copy of Vantage Point from the store, please fill out this **interest form (TBD).**\r\n\r\nJoin the [Steel City Grid Discord](https://discord.gg/s9NNDeFs)  for any questions and future events.',0,0,0,41168,1,'elev',8,'2026-01-24 19:44:13','2026-01-29 13:37:31',NULL,0,40.462188,-79.949496,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,127,'','',39,0),(5339,'Brno District Championship 2026','2026.04.11.','13:00','Czechia','','krasty23 (at) gmail.com or just Krasty everywhere else (Discord, Slack, etc.)','Jihomoravský kraj','BLACK OIL – Gaming & Social Hub','Kotlářská 51a, 602 00 Brno-střed, Czechia','ChIJnQu_9WmUEkcRtVnjhqAs4u0',NULL,NULL,'There will be 4 rounds of double sided swiss or 6 rounds of single sided swiss following with TOP 4 single elim cut, but depending on number of attendees.\r\n\r\nRounds will be 65 minutes long for double sided swiss or 40 minutes for SSS.\r\n\r\nDecklists are required, please bring written lists with you or send it by e-mail to adress of TO: krasty23 (at) gmail.com. Proxies are allowed, as long as the proxies are sleeved and readable (printed) and have about the same thickness as the official cards.\r\n\r\nIn order to avoid distributing BYE during games the TO will play only to even the number of players.\r\n\r\nDoors open: 12:00\r\nRegistration: 12:30\r\nTournament start: 13:00 (!!!)\r\nRegistration fee: 300 CZK or 15 EUR\r\n\r\nI assume Vantage Point will be legal for this tournament.\r\n\r\nDrinks and food are possible to buy in a venue!',0,1,0,15340,1,'unknown',16,'2026-01-26 13:00:38','2026-01-28 13:26:28',NULL,0,49.208263,16.602794,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,129,'..there will be more promo cards from the collection of TO!','12:00',39,0),(5340,'CTK Standard Format - Lyon - Pharmacie Ludique','2026.02.13.','18:30','France','','discord: _zanis_ / téléphone : 06 11 95 33 29','Lyon','La Pharmacie','202 Rue de Créqui, 69003 Lyon, France','ChIJd9godt3r9EcR5TkvvjcjbkE',NULL,NULL,'Tournoi au format standard à la Pharmacie Ludique, PAF indicative de 8€',0,0,0,4847,1,'elev',11,'2026-01-27 08:59:47','2026-01-29 13:32:10',NULL,0,45.757722,4.848087,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,119,'','18:00',39,0),(5341,'Münster GameNight & Learn2Play @ B-Side','2026.02.18.','17:30','Germany','','bauzaun@posteo.de','Münster','','Am Mittelhafen 42, 48155 Münster, Germany','ChIJD94bBim7uUcR5cNQZ7Sa90A',NULL,NULL,'Liebe Runner:innen,\r\n\r\nim Februar möchten wir wieder ein Learn2Play Event in der B-Side anbieten. Wir werden Starterdecks und mehrere Personen vor Ort haben, die Euch das Spiel beibringen. \r\n\r\nFür alle die wir schon im Januar in den Bann ziehen durften, bringen wir einige Decks mit, die das Spiel um neue Mechanismen erweitertern. \r\n\r\nUnd für die unter Euch, die eh schon mit dem gesamten Kartenpool spielen, bieten wir Euch je nach Bedarf bis zu 4 Runden Single-Sided-Swiss an, mit einem kleinen Preis für den:die Gewinner:in.  \r\n\r\nDie Veranstaltung findet im kleinen Gruppenraum statt. Im Hauptraum des Cafés wird es nebenbei einen Soundcheck und später auch ein Konzert geben, bringt Euch also Kopfhörer oder Ohrstöpsel mit, falls es Euch mit Musik schwerer fällt Euch zu konzentrieren. \r\n\r\nDie Teilnahme ist kostenfrei. Wer sich an den Kosten für das GameNightKit, Snacks und den PrizeSupport beteiligen kann, darf sich gerne an Jole wenden. \r\n\r\nAwareness & Code of Conduct\r\nWir möchten, dass sich alle auf unserer Veranstaltung sicher und wohl fühlen. Wenn du dich unwohl fühlst, eine unangenehme Situation erlebst oder Unterstützung brauchst, kannst du dich jederzeit vertrauensvoll an den TO (sciurus_vulgaris) wenden.\r\nVorfälle wie Belästigung, Diskriminierung, Einschüchterung oder Gewaltandrohungen nehmen wir ernst. Solche Verhaltensweisen können zur sofortigen Disqualifikation und zum Ausschluss von der Veranstaltung führen. Wenn du so etwas erlebst, wende dich bitte direkt an Jole. Unser Vorgehen richtet sich nach dem Code of Conduct von NSG.',0,0,0,33017,1,'elev',1,'2026-01-27 09:45:15','2026-01-29 13:32:45',NULL,0,51.950609,7.644352,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,126,'Partizipation Prizes for first time attendees will be handed out as well. There is a special prize for the first place in SSS.','',39,0),(5342,'Dresden Startup Turnier - Vantage Point','2026.03.07.','10:30','Germany','','humankirby@gmail.com','Dresden','Brettspielhelden Dresden e. V.','Kultur- und Nachbarschaftszentrum Striesen, Schandauer Str. 64, 01277 Dresden, Germany','ChIJnUSXLJPJCUcRZ5N1RSF0tCM',NULL,NULL,'**english below**\r\n\r\nWir laden euch herzlich zu uns nach Dresden ein. Mit dem hohen Aufkommen an neuen Spielern erwarten wir eine entspannte  Atmosphäre  (Game Night, aber mit Turnierstruktur). Ziel ist es, einen ersten Einstieg in das Ecosystem zu geben, entsprechend helfen ich und andere gerne bei Fragen zu ABR, Cobra und NetrunnerDB.\r\n\r\nGespielt wird ein Vantage Point Startup Turnier (mit entsprechender Banliste) für 6 Runden SSS. Proxies sind natürlich erlaubt, bei Fan Alt Arts bedenkt aber bitte die neuen Spieler (falls ihr euch unsicher seit, einfach eine DM an mich auf Discord oder per E-Mail).\r\n\r\nBeginn ist voraussichtlich 10 Uhr für die Registrierung, mit der ersten Runde 10:30 und einer Mittagspause nach der 3. Runde. Ab 14:30 beginnt das Familientreffen unseres Vereins, also eventuelle Kopfhörer/Ohrenstöpsel einpacken, falls diese zur Konzentration benötigt werden. Nach dem Turnier besteht die Möglichkeit weitere Spiele zu spielen oder gemeinsam durch die Stadt zu ziehen.\r\n\r\nTeilnahme ist kostenfrei und es gibt ein Playset aus dem 2025 Q4 Set für die Teilnahme. Spenden würden aber sicher den Verein oder Location freuen. ^^\r\n\r\nIch freue mich auf alle Teilnehmer. Gebt mir bitte noch per ABR, Discord oder E-Mail Bescheid, ob ihr kommt, damit wir Tische und Räumlichkeiten planen können. (Wir erwarten derzeit ~6 Teilnehmer.)\r\n\r\nZudem ist an dem Freitag davor ab 18:30 das offene Treffen unseres Brettspielvereins. Wer also schon vorher anreisen will, kann gerne daran teilnehmen. Ob Netrunner, Blood on the Clocktower oder eines der anderen Spiele aus unserem Katalog, wir würden uns freuen wenn ihr vorbeikommt (meldet euch am besten vorher bei mir, damit ich Plätze reservieren kann).\r\n\r\nAlways be running\r\n\r\nLinus/Kirby\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nWe are happy to invite everyone to Dresden. With a high number of new players, we expect a rather relaxed atmosphere (think Game Night, but with a tournament structure). The goal is to give a first impression of the surrounding ecosystem, so if you have any questions regarding ABR, Cobra and NetrunnerDB, I am happy to help.\r\n\r\nWe play Vantage Point Startup (and the respective banlist) for 6 rounds of SSS. Proxies are welcome, but please consider our new players when bringing community alt arts (if you are unsure about it, simply send me a DM on Discord or an email).\r\n\r\nThe start is currently planned for a 10am registration, with the first round starting at 10:30 and a break after the 3rd round. Around 14:30, our club\'s family meetup starts, so carry some headphones or earplugs if you are easily distracted. After the tournament you have the option to stay for other games or stroll through the city together.\r\n\r\nParticipation is free and we hand out some playsets from the 2025 Q4 GNK, simply for participating. However, donations for our club or the location are surely welcome. ^^\r\n\r\nI am excited for everyone participating. Please give me a heads-up via ABR, Discord or email so we can organize the rooms and tables. (We currently expect around ~6 participants.)\r\n\r\nOur board game club also hosts its open event just a day earlier. So if you plan a longer stay, you are invited to join. No matter if Netrunner, Blood on the Clocktower or one of the many other games in our catalogue, we would be happy for you to join us (just give me a sign so I can potentially reserve a seat).\r\n\r\nAlways be running\r\n\r\nLinus/Kirby',0,1,0,31178,1,'elev',1,'2026-01-27 13:23:49','2026-01-29 13:37:47',NULL,0,51.041077,13.800582,NULL,0,0,'',0,11,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,127,'','10:00',0,0),(5343,'Rain City February Tournament','2026.02.07.','11:15','Canada','','','Vancouver','Rain City Games','88 W Pender St Unit 1069, Vancouver, BC V6B 6N9, Canada','ChIJ6SNusXtxhlQRfnCOSXUtcUA',NULL,NULL,'Format: Standard\r\nEntry: $10\r\nRounds: 4 or 5 rounds of Single Sided Swiss (however many we can fit in 4 hours)\r\n\r\nI will be starting round 1 at 11:15am sharp. If you\'re not here at that point, you\'ll forfeit the first round. I don\'t like being so cutthroat on time, but we have a hard \"cleaned up and out the room\" by 4pm, and I want to get as much Netrunner in as possible.\r\n\r\nIf you\'re cutting it close to start time, registration will be able to be completed online\r\n\r\nFor more information, join the [Vancouver Discord Server](https://discord.gg/3G4A73u), and message me; my username is Sindarin.',0,0,0,17150,1,'elev',1,'2026-01-27 16:28:26','2026-01-29 13:31:54',NULL,0,49.280524,-123.107088,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,127,'','09:00',39,0),(5344,'The Dwarven Vantage Point Release Party','2026.03.07.','11:00','Germany','','Discrod: Virulentz // pascal.ziniel at gmail.com','Esslingen am Neckar','WürfelZwerg','Landolinsgasse 10, 73728 Esslingen am Neckar, Germany','ChIJRw5PQDLBmUcR93djfBJ-feY',NULL,NULL,'(Please see the english version below)\r\n\r\nLiebe Runner,\r\nich freue mich zu verkünden, dass der [WürfelZwerg](http://www.wuerfelzwerg.de/) am 07. März 2026 erneut seine Türen für ein famoses Netrunner Turnier öffnen wird.\r\n\r\nWir feiern die Veröffentlichung von \'Vantage Point\' mit einem einsteigerfreundlichen Turnier im Startup Format.\r\n\r\n![Zwergen Feier](https://media2.giphy.com/media/v1.Y2lkPTc5MGI3NjExcHF1NTM0bjFpb2FzeHZpY2NuNjFpY2dtaGRicDAwbWg1dzJqcnF3bSZlcD12MV9pbnRlcm5hbF9naWZfYnlfaWQmY3Q9Zw/gi6xuIOq9z5pc5GgbQ/giphy.gif)\r\n\r\nAufgrund der Räumlichkeiten sind wir leider auf 24 Personen beschränkt. Über eine kurze Rückmeldung wird daher gebenten, sodass ich abschätzen kann, ob wir ausreichend Platz haben.\r\n\r\nDie Anreise erfolgt via Zug über den Esslinger Bahnhof (RE oder S1 von Stuttgart) und einem 10min Fußmarsch in die Altstadt. Mit dem Auto am besten über die A8 oder A81/B10 von Norden kommend. Parken kann man im Parkhaus Neckarforum.\r\n\r\n> Adresse:\r\n>WürfelZwerg\r\n>Landolinsgasse 10\r\n>73728 Esslingen\r\n\r\nDie Anmeldegebühr beträgt für je nach Teilnehmeranzahl 10-15€. \r\nGeld über die Kosten des Preis-Kits hinaus gehen an die Location.\r\nDecklisten werden sehr gern auch via Mail entgegen genommen.\r\n\r\n>Angedachter Zeitplan:\r\n>\r\n>10:30 - 11:00 letzter Aufbau/Anmeldung\r\n>11:00 - 11:45 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 1\r\n>11:50 - 12:35 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 2\r\n>12:40 - 13:25 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 3\r\n>13:25 - 14:15 Mittag\r\n>14:15 - 15:00 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 4\r\n>15:05 - 15:50 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 5\r\n>15:55 - 16:40 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 6\r\n>16:50 - XX:XX Top Cut (Optional)\r\n\r\nPascal - Virulentz\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nDear Runners,\r\n\r\nI am pleased to announce that the [WürfelZwerg (\'DiceDwarve\')](http://www.wuerfelzwerg.de/) will open its doors for an exciting Netrunner tournament again at the 7th March 2026.\r\n\r\nWe are celebrating the release of \'Vantage Point\' with a beginner friendly Startup Tournament.\r\n\r\nDue to location restricitons we are limited to 24 persons. Therefor a small hint that you are comming is appreciated to have a small overview of attendances.\r\n\r\nArrival via train is possible with the RE or the S1 to Esslingen Station and a short 10min walk through the city. Arrival by car can be done via the A8 or A81/B10 from the north. Parking is possible at the NeckarForum parking garage.\r\n\r\n>Address:\r\n>WürfelZwerg\r\n>Landolinsgasse 10\r\n>73728 Esslingen\r\n\r\nFeel free to send your decklist via mail.\r\nEntry fee will be dependent on participation 10-15€. \r\nMoney beyond the price kit costs will go to the location.\r\n\r\n>Schedule:\r\n\r\n>\r\n>10:30 - 11:00 letzter Aufbau/Anmeldung\r\n>11:00 - 11:45 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 1\r\n>11:50 - 12:35 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 2\r\n>12:40 - 13:25 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 3\r\n>13:25 - 14:15 Lunch\r\n>14:15 - 15:00 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 4\r\n>15:05 - 15:50 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 5\r\n>15:55 - 16:40 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 6\r\n>16:50 - XX:XX Top Cut (Optional)\r\n\r\nPascal - Virulentz',0,0,0,13592,1,'elev',11,'2026-01-27 17:56:54','2026-01-29 13:38:13',NULL,0,48.742059,9.310677,NULL,0,0,'',0,11,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,119,'Various cards of former GNKs/ tournaments','10.30',38,0),(5345,'Dwarven District Championship 2026 Esslingen','2026.04.11.','11:00','Germany','','Discord: Virulentz // pascal.ziniel at gmail.com','Esslingen am Neckar','WürfelZwerg','Landolinsgasse 10, 73728 Esslingen am Neckar, Germany','ChIJRw5PQDLBmUcR93djfBJ-feY',NULL,NULL,'(Please see the english version below)\r\n\r\nLiebe Runner,\r\nich freue mich zu verkünden, dass der [WürfelZwerg](http://www.wuerfelzwerg.de/) am 11. April 2026 erneut seine Türen für ein famoses Netrunner Turnier öffnen wird.\r\n\r\nWir veranstalten ein Disctrict Championship, als erste Instanz der kompetitiven Netrunner Saison 2026.\r\n\r\n![Match Time](https://media1.giphy.com/media/v1.Y2lkPTc5MGI3NjExN3B0dTgyaW1ydzA3Zjdnb3BtbmVlNTllNjU1eW4xN3M3bTg1dHc5eSZlcD12MV9pbnRlcm5hbF9naWZfYnlfaWQmY3Q9Zw/xL5WGnWbeTQuA/giphy.gif)\r\n\r\nAufgrund der Räumlichkeiten sind wir leider auf 24 Personen beschränkt. Über eine kurze Rückmeldung wird daher gebenten, sodass ich abschätzen kann, ob wir ausreichend Platz haben.\r\n\r\nDie Anreise erfolgt via Zug über den Esslinger Bahnhof (RE oder S1 von Stuttgart) und einem 10min Fußmarsch in die Altstadt. Mit dem Auto am besten über die A8 oder A81/B10 von Norden kommend. Parken kann man im Parkhaus Neckarforum.\r\n\r\n> Adresse:\r\n>WürfelZwerg\r\n>Landolinsgasse 10\r\n>73728 Esslingen\r\n\r\nDie Anmeldegebühr beträgt für je nach Teilnehmeranzahl 10-15€. \r\nGeld über die Kosten des Preis-Kits hinaus gehen an die Location.\r\nDecklisten werden sehr gern auch via Mail entgegen genommen.\r\n\r\n>Angedachter Zeitplan:\r\n>\r\n>10:30 - 11:00 letzter Aufbau/Anmeldung\r\n>11:00 - 11:45 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 1\r\n>11:50 - 12:35 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 2\r\n>12:40 - 13:25 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 3\r\n>13:25 - 14:15 Mittag\r\n>14:15 - 15:00 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 4\r\n>15:05 - 15:50 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 5\r\n>15:55 - 16:40 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 6\r\n>16:50 - XX:XX Top Cut\r\n\r\nPascal - Virulentz\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nDear Runners,\r\n\r\nI am pleased to announce that the [WürfelZwerg (\'DiceDwarve\')](http://www.wuerfelzwerg.de/) will open its doors for an exciting Netrunner tournament again at the 11th April 2026.\r\n\r\nWe are organizing a District Championship as the first instance of the 2026 competitive Netrunner season.\r\n\r\nDue to location restricitons we are limited to 24 persons. Therefor a small hint that you are comming is appreciated to have a small overview of attendances.\r\n\r\nArrival via train is possible with the RE or the S1 to Esslingen Station and a short 10min walk through the city. Arrival by car can be done via the A8 or A81/B10 from the north. Parking is possible at the NeckarForum parking garage.\r\n\r\n>Address:\r\n>WürfelZwerg\r\n>Landolinsgasse 10\r\n>73728 Esslingen\r\n\r\nFeel free to send your decklist via mail.\r\nEntry fee will be dependent on participation 10-15€. \r\nMoney beyond the price kit costs will go to the location.\r\n\r\n>Schedule:\r\n\r\n>\r\n>10:30 - 11:00 letzter Aufbau/Anmeldung\r\n>11:00 - 11:45 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 1\r\n>11:50 - 12:35 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 2\r\n>12:40 - 13:25 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 3\r\n>13:25 - 14:15 Lunch\r\n>14:15 - 15:00 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 4\r\n>15:05 - 15:50 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 5\r\n>15:55 - 16:40 Single-Sided-Swiss Round 6\r\n>16:50 - XX:XX Top Cut\r\n\r\nPascal - Virulentz',0,0,0,13592,1,'elev',16,'2026-01-27 18:05:55','2026-01-29 13:39:19',NULL,0,48.742059,9.310677,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,129,'Former tournament and GNK cards','10:30',39,0),(5346,'MegaCity Brno 2026','2026.05.02.','12:00','Czechia','','krasty23 (at) gmail.com or just Krasty everywhere else (Discord, Slack, etc.)','Jihomoravský kraj','BLACK OIL – Gaming & Social Hub','Kotlářská 51a, 602 00 Brno-střed, Czechia','ChIJnQu_9WmUEkcRtVnjhqAs4u0',NULL,NULL,'...more info will come soon... just to safe the date!   \r\n***\r\n![more info comming soon](https://www.shutterstock.com/image-illustration/coming-soon-black-color-background-600nw-2659927991.jpg)',0,1,0,15340,1,'unknown',17,'2026-01-28 11:58:29','2026-01-28 13:34:07',NULL,0,49.208263,16.602794,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,'2026.05.03.',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','11:00',0,0),(5347,'Vantage Point Release & Warm-up Tournament','2026.03.07.','11:00','United States','WI','se.wisconsin.gaming@gmail.com','Milwaukee','Old Guard Games','3132 N Downer Ave, Milwaukee, WI 53211, USA','ChIJFbb0l8kZBYgR9yhiJW-i2T4',NULL,NULL,'Casual warm-up tournament for 2026 competitive Netrunner events!\r\n\r\nFull event details to come, as they are worked out with our host - [Old Guard Games!](https://www.facebook.com/OldGuardMKE/)  \r\n\r\nRounds based on attendance - single-sided Swiss, likely 5-6 rounds, with no cut.\r\n\r\nTest out those new deck ideas and celebrate the release of Vantage Point! Barring unforeseen delays, Vantage Point will be available for purchase. And proxies are always welcome!',0,0,0,45350,1,'elev',1,'2026-01-28 12:33:48','2026-01-29 13:38:28',NULL,0,43.075402,-87.877654,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,126,'','10:30',39,0),(5348,'Muenster CT UpGr8 @ B-Side','2026.03.01.','11:00','Germany','','bauzaun@posteo.de [or DM via german netrunner discord ]','Münster','','Am Mittelhafen 42, 48155 Münster, Germany','ChIJD94bBim7uUcR5cNQZ7Sa90A',NULL,NULL,'Liebe Runner:innen,\r\n(english version below)\r\n\r\nnach den ersten Erfahrungen mit der neuen Location wollen wir wir am 01. März unser erstes Casual Tournament in diesem Jahr in der B-Side veranstalten.\r\nEinen Tag vor dem Release von Vantage Point spielen wir trotzdem noch mit dem Kartenpool bis Elevation. \r\nDas Event richtig sich explizit an neuere Spieler:innen. Wenn dies also Dein erstes Event ist, fühl Dich herzlich eingeladen und schreib mir gerne deine Fragen oder Unsicherheiten bzgl. einer Teilnahme per E-Mail. \r\n\r\n\r\nEs werden 6 Runden Single Sided Swiss (40min. time slots) gespielt. \r\n\r\nAufgrund der Räumlichkeiten sind wir auf 20 Personen beschränkt. Im Laufe des Nachmittags wird es eine Tanzveranstaltung im Nebenraum geben. Wenn du geräuschempfindlich, oder leicht ablenkbar bist, nimm dir gerne Kopfhörer oder Ohrstöpsel mit. \r\n\r\nDie Teilnahme an der Veranstaltung wird zwischen 8-13€ Kosten um die Fixkosten zu decken und ggf. etwas an die Location spenden zu können. Getränke, Croissants und Kuchen gibt es den Tag über an der Bar. Eigene Getränke und Snacks dürfen konsumiert werden. Wasser gibt es gratis. Ein paar Snacks werden wir vorher einkaufen.\r\n\r\nZwischen 13:40-14:30 gibt es eine Mittagspause. Nicht zu weit entfernt gibt es eine Pizzeria und eine Brauerei. Wenn ihr mögt, könnt ihr Euch morgens mit auf die Bestellliste für eine Pizzalieferung setzen. \r\n\r\nAwareness & Code of Conduct\r\nWir möchten, dass sich alle auf unserer Veranstaltung sicher und wohl fühlen. Wenn du dich unwohl fühlst, eine unangenehme Situation erlebst oder Unterstützung brauchst, kannst du dich jederzeit vertrauensvoll an den TO (sciurus_vulgaris) wenden.\r\nVorfälle wie Belästigung, Diskriminierung, Einschüchterung oder Gewaltandrohungen nehmen wir ernst. Solche Verhaltensweisen können zur sofortigen Disqualifikation und zum Ausschluss von der Veranstaltung führen. Wenn du so etwas erlebst, wende dich bitte direkt an den TO. Unser Vorgehen richtet sich nach dem Code of Conduct von NSG.\r\n\r\nZeitplan:\r\n10:30-11:00 Registration\r\n11:00-11:10 Venue & Tournament Rules + Pizza Order\r\n11:10-11:50 SSS 1\r\n12:05-12:45 SSS 2\r\n13:00-13:40 SSS 3\r\n13:40-14:30 Lunch Break\r\n14:30-15:10 SSS 4\r\n15:25-16:05 SSS 5\r\n16:20-17:00 SSS 6\r\n17:05-17:20 Ceremony + Pay your bills\r\n17:20 + Open, Hang Out\r\n\r\nWir werden COBRA für die Durchführung des Turniers nutzen. Ihr könnt euch hier mit Eurer NetrunnerDB eintragen: https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/q8f\r\n\r\nAnreise:\r\nDie Anreise erfolgt via Zug über den Bahnhof Münster (West.). Von dort sind es entweder 18 Minuten (1,3km)  zu Fuß, oder ihr nehmt die Buslinien 5/8 bis zur Halle Münsterland und lauft von da die 7 Minuten (450m). \r\nFür Anreisende mit dem Auto gibt es direkt vor dem Gelände umfassend Parkmöglichkeiten.\r\n\r\nAdresse:\r\nB-Side\r\nAm Mittelhafen 42, 48155 Münster\r\n(Veranstaltung findet im 1.OG statt - solltest Du Unterstützung beim Zugang benötigen, melde Dich vorher gerne bei sciurus_vulgaris)\r\n\r\nBei Fragen schreibt mir gerne an die E-Mail oder schreibt mir eine PN über Discord (Ihr findet mich auf dem deutschen Netrunner Server).\r\nsciurus_vulgaris -- Jole\r\n\r\n--------\r\n\r\nDear Runners,\r\n\r\nAfter our initial positive experiences with the new location, we would like to host our first Casual Tournament of the year at B-Side on March 1.\r\n\r\nOne day before the release of Vantage Point, we will still be playing with the card pool up to Elevation. This event is aimed specifically at newer players. If this is your first event, you are very welcome to attend and feel free to send us your questions in advance by email. \r\n\r\nThere will be 6 rounds of Single Sided Swiss (40-minute time slots). \r\n\r\nDue to the size of the venue, we are limited to 20 people. There will be a dance event in the adjoining room during the afternoon. If you are sensitive to noise or easily distracted, please bring headphones or earplugs.\r\n\r\nParticipation in the event will cost between €8 - €13 to break even. Any surplus will be donated to the venue. Drinks, croissants, and cake will be available at the bar throughout the day at the event venue. You are welcome to bring your own drinks and snacks. Water will be provided free of charge. We will buy a few snacks in advance. \r\n\r\nThere will be a lunch break between 1:40 p.m. and 2:30 p.m. A pizzeria and a brewery are both in walking distance from the venue. If you like, you can add your name to the order list for pizza delivery in the morning. \r\n\r\nAwareness & Code of Conduct\r\nWe want everyone to feel safe and comfortable at our event. If you feel uncomfortable, experience an unpleasant situation or need support, you can contact the TO (sciurus_vulgaris) in confidence at any time.\r\nWe take incidents such as harassment, discrimination, intimidation or threats of violence seriously. Such behavior can lead to immediate disqualification and exclusion from the event. If you experience such behavior, please contact the TO directly. Our procedure is based on the NSG Code of Conduct.\r\n\r\n##Schedule:\r\n10:30-11:00 Registration\r\n11:00-11:10 Venue & Tournament Rules + Pizza Order\r\n11:10-11:50 SSS 1\r\n12:05-12:45 SSS 2\r\n13:00-13:40 SSS 3\r\n13:40-14:30 Lunch Break\r\n14:30-15:10 SSS 4\r\n15:25-16:05 SSS 5\r\n16:20-17:00 SSS 6\r\n17:05-17:20 Ceremony + Pay your bills\r\n17:20 + Open, Hang Out\r\n\r\nWe will use COBRA to run the tournament. You can register here with your NetrunnerDB: https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/q8f\r\n\r\n\r\nHow to get there:\r\nYou can get there by train via Münster (West) station. From there, it\'s either an 18-minute walk (1.3 km) or you can take bus lines 5/8 to Halle Münsterland and walk 7 minutes (450 m) from there. \r\nFor those arriving by car, there is ample parking directly in front of the venue.\r\n\r\nAddress:\r\nB-Side\r\nAm Mittelhafen 42, 48155 Münster\r\n(The event will take place on the 1st floor – if you need assistance with access, please contact sciurus_vulgaris in advance).\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions, please feel free to email me or send me a private message on Discord (you can find me on the German Netrunner server).\r\nsciurus_vulgaris – Jole',0,0,0,33017,1,'elev',11,'2026-01-28 15:35:45','2026-01-29 13:34:23',NULL,0,51.950609,7.644352,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,119,'Cloud Eater - Alt Art by ManintheMoon & Elihu Vedder ( https://netrunnercards.net/products/48x-cloud-eater-by-maninthemoon )','10:30',39,0),(5349,'TORONTO MEGACITY 2026','2026.05.30.','10:00','Canada','','','Toronto','','','ChIJpTvG15DL1IkRd8S0KlBVNTI',NULL,NULL,'# PLEASE AWAIT FURTHER INSTRUCTION',0,0,0,8982,1,'unknown',17,'2026-01-28 23:38:01','2026-01-29 13:39:38',NULL,0,43.654825,-79.388447,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,'2026.05.31.',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','9:00',0,0),(5350,'Standard AMT - February 7th (EMEA)','2026.02.07.','9:00','','','op@nullsignal.games','','','','',NULL,NULL,'![Accelerated Meta Test](https://alwaysberunning.net/photo/2677.png)\r\n\r\nThis is an Accelerated Meta Test in the **Standard** Format using **Single-Sided Swiss**, and is open to anyone who wants to play. Prizing for this event will be an Invite to the Circuit Breaker Invitational in January of \'27 for the top finisher (or more if we exceed 20 entrants) and a AMT unique cardback prize on Jnet\r\n\r\n**Netrunners from all levels of play are welcome and encouraged to participate in AMTs**\r\n\r\nThis event is starting on [February 7th, 09:00 UTC](https://timee.io/20260207T0900?tl=EMEA%20AMT). With registration closing and player meeting beginning *15 minutes beforehand*. \r\n\r\nThe event will be run through the [NSG Online Event Hub Discord](https://discord.gg/qUEHWSDPWa). Registration will open on [cobra](https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/) at least an hour before event start. We anticipate this event being six rounds with a top 4 cut. \r\n\r\nThe event will be run on Jinteki.net.',0,0,0,33530,1,'elev',11,'2026-01-29 05:47:42','2026-01-29 05:47:49',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','8:45',39,1),(5351,'Standard AMT - February 22th (APAC)','2026.02.22.','9:00','','','op@nullsignal.games','','','','',NULL,NULL,'![Accelerated Meta Test](https://alwaysberunning.net/photo/2677.png)\r\n\r\nThis is an Accelerated Meta Test in the **Standard** Format using **Single-Sided Swiss**, and is open to anyone who wants to play. Prizing for this event will be an Invite to the Circuit Breaker Invitational in January of \'27 for the top finisher (or more if we exceed 20 entrants) and a AMT unique cardback prize on Jnet\r\n\r\n**Netrunners from all levels of play are welcome and encouraged to participate in AMTs**\r\n\r\nThis event is starting on [February 22th,  9am AWST](https://timee.io/20260222T0100?tl=APAC%20AMT). With registration closing and player meeting beginning *15 minutes beforehand*. \r\n\r\nThe event will be run through the [NSG Online Event Hub Discord](https://discord.gg/qUEHWSDPWa). Registration will open on [cobra](https://tournaments.nullsignal.games/) at least an hour before event start. We anticipate this event being six rounds with a top 4 cut. \r\n\r\nThe event will be run on Jinteki.net.',0,0,0,33530,1,'elev',11,'2026-01-29 05:49:31','2026-01-29 13:33:47',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','8:45',39,1),(5352,'Wednesday LCG Night',NULL,'06:00','United States','AZ','legacybear. (Discord)','Chandler','Mox Boarding House','1371 N Alma School Rd, Chandler, AZ 85224, USA','ChIJ7x_wNrYHK4cRE05oZ6PcDls',NULL,NULL,'Every Wednesday 6-9 PM we run LCG Night and have a large Netrunner crowd.',0,0,0,54640,1,'unknown',8,'2026-01-29 18:08:25','2026-01-30 12:00:54',NULL,0,33.326910,-111.858272,3,0,0,'',0,11,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'','06:00',39,0),(5353,'Vienna District Championship 2026','2026.03.21.','','Austria','','','Vienna','','','ChIJn8o2UZ4HbUcRRluiUYrlwv0',NULL,NULL,'Save the date for the Vienna District Championship!\r\n\r\nLocation and further details: TBA',0,0,0,38747,1,'unknown',16,'2026-01-30 07:52:01','2026-01-30 12:01:24',NULL,0,48.208070,16.371309,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,129,'','',0,0),(5354,'Standardizing the Catalyst and Syndicate','2026.02.28.','10:30','','','manu.r@t-online.de','','','','',NULL,NULL,'Standard Card pool but the only IDs allowed are The syndicate and The catalyst.\r\nBoth are neutral IDs with infinite influence and a 30 card deck minimum.\r\nAs we are playing with the Starter IDs, we will only be going to 6 Agenda points for the win!\r\nYou can trust NetrunnerDB with everything else! (The Syndicate can use any agendas)\r\n\r\nPrize pool access costs but you can attend for free.\r\n\r\n!!!!From here infor is bound to change within the next 2 or 3 days!!!!\r\n\r\nEntry is 15€.\r\nI shall trust that everyone pays. Paypal works, but if you are at worlds cash works as well!\r\nI will Ship prizes by letter, or can hand them over in person at worlds.\r\n\r\nI plan on ~6 rounds of single sided Swiss.\r\nStart will be at 8AM UTC or 10AM German time.\r\nAnyone is welcome.\r\nIt will take place in the German Netrunner discord\r\n\r\nThere will be no official Prize kit.\r\nEvery participant will receive 3 of mine or her alt arts of your choice.\r\nThe top 3 will recieve 3 Additional sets of Alt arts.\r\n\r\nHere you can find our cards (Any card that I have a print of that was made by us is a valid prize request. Success in the event grants you priority in prize picks.)\r\n\r\nEveryone is welcome.\r\nIf the cost is an issue, please do let me know. I am a student and know what it’s like to not have much money.\r\nPlease let me know if you plan to attend, so that I can plan.\r\n\r\nHit me up via manuelderfallendefersteher on discord.',0,0,0,43283,1,'elev',1,'2026-01-30 11:10:55','2026-02-25 06:27:44',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','10:00',39,1),(5355,'Stockholm District Champoinship 2026','2026.03.28.','10:30','Sweden','','filip@gokstorp.se','Hägersten','Alphaspel','Instrumentvägen 2, 126 53 Hägersten, Sweden','ChIJR4y7FAd3X0YRQg5zreYs9HE',NULL,NULL,'Welcome to the Stockholm District Championship 2026!\r\n\r\nFormat is expected to be 5 or 6 rounds of single-sided swiss. This is a competitive-tier event, so make sure you bring only tournament-legal alts and sleeves!\r\n\r\nThere will be a fee (to be confirmed) to enter the tournament to cover the cost of the kit and venue.\r\n\r\nDecklists will be submitted through Cobra closer to the date.\r\n\r\nThe event will use the latest legal set and ban list. Vantage Point is expected to be legal for this event.',0,1,0,13624,NULL,'unknown',16,'2026-01-31 07:40:41','2026-01-31 07:40:41',NULL,0,59.305990,17.986801,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,129,'','10:00',0,0),(5356,'Jinteki.net Quick Draft GNK','2026.02.14.','17:00','','','@larrea on discord','','','','',NULL,NULL,'- Meet up on the  [NSG Tournaments discord](https://discord.com/channels/372121348300079106/688460127275319368)\r\n\r\n- Play 5 rounds Jinteki.net\'s latest mode: **Quick Draft**\r\n\r\nFirst place gets a 15€ dollar pound gift card to use on Alt Arts from MITM or The Tag Mill',0,0,0,36566,NULL,'elev',1,'2026-01-31 10:57:44','2026-01-31 11:15:46',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'','',39,1),(5357,'Test Tournament','2026.03.01.','','Hungary','','','Budapest','Metagame Kártya-, és Társasjáték Bolt','Budapest, Kádár u. 10, 1132 Hungary','ChIJIaFnNgzcQUcRnH7g2gqy2Xk',NULL,NULL,'',0,0,0,21903,1,'elev',1,'2026-02-25 16:15:14','2026-02-25 20:36:39',NULL,0,47.511688,19.054359,NULL,0,0,'',0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Europe/Budapest',NULL,'','',39,0);
